Name: Abnormality of body height
Definition: "Deviation from the norm of height with respect to that which is expected according to age and gender norms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Multicystic kidney dysplasia
Definition: "Multicystic dysplasia of the kidney is characterized by multiple cysts of varying size in the kidney and the absence of a normal pelvicaliceal system. The condition is associated with ureteral or ureteropelvic atresia, and the affected kidney is nonfunctional." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Mode of inheritance
Definition: "The pattern in which a particular genetic trait or disorder is passed from one generation to the next." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Autosomal dominant inheritance
Definition: "A mode of inheritance that is observed for traits related to a gene encoded on one of the autosomes (i.e., the human chromosomes 1-22) in which a trait manifests in heterozygotes. In the context of medical genetics, an autosomal dominant disorder is caused when a single copy of the mutant allele is present. Males and females are affected equally, and can both transmit the disorder with a risk of 50% for each child of inheriting the mutant allele." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Autosomal recessive inheritance
Definition: "A mode of inheritance that is observed for traits related to a gene encoded on one of the autosomes (i.e., the human chromosomes 1-22) in which a trait manifests in individuals with two pathogenic alleles, either homozygotes (two copies of the same mutant allele) or compound heterozygotes (whereby each copy of a gene has a distinct mutant allele)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal morphology of female internal genitalia
Definition: "An abnormality of the female internal genitalia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Functional abnormality of the bladder
Definition: "Dysfunction of the urinary bladder." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Recurrent urinary tract infections
Definition: "Repeated infections of the urinary tract." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Neurogenic bladder
Definition: "A type of bladder dysfunction caused by neurologic damage. Neurogenic bladder can be flaccid or spastic. Common manifestatios of neurogenic bladder are overflow incontinence, frequency, urgency, urge incontinence, and retention." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:18095004, PMID:22400020]

Name: Urinary urgency
Definition: "Urge incontinence is the strong, sudden need to urinate." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:12559262]

Name: Hypoplasia of the uterus
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the uterus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the bladder
Definition: "An abnormality of the urinary bladder." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bladder diverticulum
Definition: "Diverticulum (sac or pouch) in the wall of the urinary bladder." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Urinary retention
Definition: "Inability to completely empty the urinary bladder during the process of urination." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Nocturia
Definition: "Abnormally increased production of urine during the night leading to an unusually frequent need to urinate." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Urinary hesitancy
Definition: "Difficulty in beginning the process of urination." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Urinary incontinence
Definition: "Loss of the ability to control the urinary bladder leading to involuntary urination." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154, PMID:12559262]

Name: Megacystis
Definition: "Dilatation of the bladder postnatally." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal male internal genitalia morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the male internal genitalia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Inguinal hernia
Definition: "Protrusion of the contents of the abdominal cavity through the inguinal canal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Prostatitis
Definition: "The presence of inflammation of the prostate." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Functional abnormality of male internal genitalia
Male hypogonadism
Definition: "Decreased functionality of the male gonad, i.e., of the testis, with reduced spermatogenesis or testosterone synthesis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Azoospermia
Definition: "Absence of any measurable level of sperm,whereby spermatozoa cannot be observed even after centrifugation of the semen pellet." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20514278]

Name: Cryptorchidism
Definition: "Testis in inguinal canal. That is, absence of one or both testes from the scrotum owing to failure of the testis or testes to descend through the inguinal canal to the scrotum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:23650202]

Name: Testicular atrophy
Definition: "Wasting (atrophy) of the testicle (the male gonad) manifested by a decrease in size and potentially by a loss of fertility." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Testicular gonadoblastoma
Definition: "The presence of a gonadoblastoma of the testis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Epididymitis
Definition: "The presence of inflammation of the epididymis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of male external genitalia
Definition: "An abnormality of male external genitalia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ambiguous genitalia, male
Definition: "Ambiguous genitalia in an individual with XY genetic gender." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hydrocele testis
Definition: "Accumulation of clear fluid in the between the layers of membrane (tunica vaginalis) surrounding the testis." [PMID:32644551]

Name: Abnormal testis morphology
Definition: "An anomaly of the testicle (the male gonad)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal penis morphology
Definition: "Abnormality of the male external sex organ." []

Name: Male pseudohermaphroditism
Definition: "Hermaphroditism refers to a discrepancy between the morphology of the gonads and that of the external genitalia. In male pseudohermaphroditism, the genotype is male (XY) and the external genitalia are imcompletely virilized, ambiguous, or complete female. If gonads are present, they are testes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Epispadias
Definition: "Epispadias is a urogenital malformation characterized by the failure of the urethral tube to tubularize on the dorsal aspect. Unlike in hypospadias, where the meatus is on the ventral aspect, children with epispadias have a wide-open urethral plate on the dorsum. It is commonly seen as a component in the spectrum of bladder exstrophy-epispadias-complex. Isolated epispadias constitutes less than 10 percent of the total cases of epispadias." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:23650202, PMID:33085327]

Name: Long penis
Definition: "Penile length more than 2 SD above the mean for age." []

Name: Chordee
Definition: "Ventral, lateral, or ventrolateral bowing of the shaft and glans penis of more than 30 degrees." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:23650202]

Name: Absent external genitalia
Definition: "Lack of external genitalia in a male or female individual." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypogonadotropic hypogonadism
Definition: "Hypogonadotropic hypogonadism is characterized by reduced function of the gonads (testes in males or ovaries in females) and results from the absence of the gonadal stimulating pituitary hormones: follicle stimulating hormone (FSH) and luteinizing hormone (LH)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:23503957]

Name: Small scrotum
Definition: "Apparently small scrotum for age." [PMID:23650202]

Name: Hypospadias
Definition: "Abnormal position of urethral meatus on the ventral penile shaft (underside) characterized by displacement of the urethral meatus from the tip of the glans penis to the ventral surface of the penis, scrotum, or perineum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:21968448]

Name: Bifid scrotum
Definition: "Midline indentation or cleft of the scrotum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:23650202]

Name: Shawl scrotum
Definition: "Superior margin of the scrotum superior to the base of the penis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:23650202]

Name: Hypoplastic male external genitalia
Definition: "Underdevelopment of part or all of the male external reproductive organs (which include the penis, the scrotum and the urethra)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Perineal hypospadias
Definition: "Hypospadias with location of the urethral meatus in the perineal region." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:8097257]

Name: Urethral atresia, male
Definition: "Congenital anomaly characterized by closure or failure to develop an opening in the urethra in males." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Macroorchidism
Definition: "The presence of abnormally large testes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Micropenis
Definition: "Abnormally small penis. At birth, the normal penis is about 3 cm (stretched length from pubic tubercle to tip of penis) with micropenis less than 2.0-2.5 cm." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:15102623]

Name: Abnormality of female external genitalia
Definition: "An abnormality of the female external genitalia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the clitoris
Definition: "An abnormality of the clitoris." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal labia morphology
Definition: "An anomaly of the labia, the externally visible portions of the vulva." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplastic labia majora
Definition: "Undergrowth of the outer labia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Clitoral hypoplasia
Definition: "Developmental hypoplasia of the clitoris." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ambiguous genitalia, female
Definition: "Ambiguous genitalia in an individual with XX genetic gender." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ambiguous genitalia
Definition: "A genital phenotype that is not clearly assignable to a single gender. Ambiguous genitalia can be evaluated using the Prader scale: Prader 0: Normal female external genitalia. Prader 1: Female external genitalia with clitoromegaly. Prader 2: Clitoromegaly with partial labial fusion forming a funnel-shaped urogenital sinus. Prader 3: Increased phallic enlargement. Complete labioscrotal fusion forming a urogenital sinus with a single opening. Prader 4: Complete scrotal fusion with urogenital opening at the base or on the shaft of the phallus. Prader 5: Normal male external genitalia. The diagnosis of ambiguous genitalia is made for Prader 1-4." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:15102623]

Name: Fused labia minora
Definition: "Fusion of the labia minora as a result of labial adhesions resulting in vaginal obstruction." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Urethral atresia, female
Definition: "Congenital anomaly characterized by closure or failure to develop an opening in the urethra in females." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Urethral atresia
Definition: "Congenital anomaly characterized by closure or failure to develop an opening in the urethra." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the ureter
Definition: "An abnormality of the ureter. The ureter is the duct by which urine passes from the kidney to the bladder." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ureterocele
Definition: "A ureterocele is a congenital saccular dilatation of the distal segment of the ureter." [eMedicine:453993]

Name: Ureteral stenosis
Definition: "The presence of a stenotic, i.e., constricted ureter." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hydroureter
Definition: "The distention of the ureter with urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:33085364]

Name: Ureteral duplication
Definition: "A developmental anomaly characterized by the presence of two, instead of one, ureter connecting a kidney to the bladder." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ureteropelvic junction obstruction
Definition: "Blockage of urine flow from the renal pelvis to the proximal ureter." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:Eurenomics_ewuehl]

Name: Renal duplication
Definition: "A congenital anomaly of the urinary tract, in which the kidney is duplicated and is drained via two separate renal pelves and ureters." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Vesicoureteral reflux
Definition: "Abnormal (retrograde) movement of urine from the bladder into ureters or kidneys related to inadequacy of the valvular mechanism at the ureterovesicular junction or other causes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the kidney
Definition: "An abnormality of the kidney." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the genital system
Definition: "An abnormality of the genital system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the urinary system
Definition: "An abnormality of the urinary system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of reproductive system physiology
Definition: "An abnormal functionality of the genital system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Duplicated collecting system
Definition: "A duplication of the collecting system of the kidney, defined as a kidney with two (instead of, normally, one) pyelocaliceal systems. The pyelocaliceal system is comprised of the renal pelvis and calices. The duplicated renal collecting system can be associated with a single ureter or with double ureters. In the latter case, the two ureters empty separately into the bladder or fuse to form a single ureteral orifice." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Renal insufficiency
Definition: "A reduction in the level of performance of the kidneys in areas of function comprising the concentration of urine, removal of wastes, the maintenance of electrolyte balance, homeostasis of blood pressure, and calcium metabolism." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Horseshoe kidney
Definition: "A connection of the right and left kidney by an isthmus of functioning renal parenchyma or fibrous tissue that crosses the midline." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ectopic kidney
Definition: "A developmental defect in which a kidney is located in an abnormal anatomic position." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Renal hypoplasia
Definition: "Hypoplasia of the kidney." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Nephronophthisis
Definition: "Presence of cysts at the corticomedullary junction of the kidney in combination with tubulointerstitial fibrosis." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:Eurenomics_fschaefer]

Name: Abnormal renal tubule morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the renal tubules." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Renal tubular atrophy
Definition: "The presence of renal tubules with thick redundant basement membranes, or a reduction of greater than 50% in tubular diameter compared to surrounding non-atrophic tubules." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:27211375]

Name: Proteinuria
Definition: "Increased levels of protein in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal renal glomerulus morphology
Definition: "A structural anomaly of the glomerulus." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:Eurenomics_ewuehl, PMID:18184729]

Name: Glomerular sclerosis
Definition: "Accumulation of scar tissue within the glomerulus." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:Eurenomics_fschaefer]

Name: Focal segmental glomerulosclerosis
Definition: "Segmental accumulation of scar tissue in individual (but not all) glomeruli." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:Eurenomics_fschaefer, PMID:16164633]

Name: Tall stature
Definition: "A height above that which is expected according to age and gender norms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Glomerulonephritis
Definition: "Inflammation of the renal glomeruli." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Nephrotic syndrome
Definition: "Nephrotic syndrome is a collection of findings resulting from glomerular dysfunction with an increase in glomerular capillary wall permeability associated with pronounced proteinuria. Nephrotic syndrome refers to the constellation of clinical findings that result from severe renal loss of protein, with Proteinuria and hypoalbuminemia, edema, and hyperlipidemia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Polyuria
Definition: "An increased rate of urine production." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Renal agenesis
Definition: "Agenesis, that is, failure of the kidney to develop during embryogenesis and development." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Enlarged kidney
Definition: "An abnormal increase in the size of the kidney." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Renal cyst
Definition: "A fluid filled sac in the kidney." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:Eurenomics_fschaefer]

Name: Renal corticomedullary cysts
Definition: "The presence of multiple cysts at the border between the renal cortex and medulla." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Renal dysplasia
Definition: "The presence of developmental dysplasia of the kidney." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Renal juxtaglomerular cell hypertrophy/hyperplasia
Definition: "Increased number and size of the juxtaglomerular cells." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:Eurenomics_ewuehl]

Name: Nephropathy
Definition: "A nonspecific term referring to disease or damage of the kidneys." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Polycystic kidney dysplasia
Definition: "The presence of multiple cysts in both kidneys." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Proximal tubulopathy
Definition: "Dysfunction of the proximal tubule, which is the portion of the duct system of the nephron of the kidney which leads from Bowman's capsule to the loop of Henle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Renal phosphate wasting
Definition: "High urine phosphate in the presence of hypophosphatemia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Phenotypic abnormality
Definition: "A phenotypic abnormality." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the genitourinary system
Definition: "The presence of any abnormality of the genitourinary system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Nephrocalcinosis
Definition: "Nephrocalcinosis is the deposition of calcium salts in renal parenchyma." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Unilateral renal agenesis
Definition: "A unilateral form of agenesis of the kidney." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Nephritis
Definition: "The presence of inflammation affecting the kidney." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Renal tubular dysfunction
Definition: "Abnormal function of the renal tubule. The basic functional unit of the kidney, the nephron, consists of a renal corpuscle attached to a renal tubule, with roughly 0.8 to 1.5 nephrons per adult kidney. The functions of the renal tubule include reabsorption of water, electrolytes, glucose, and amino acids and secretion of substances such as uric acid." []

Name: Pelvic kidney
Definition: "A developmental defect in which a kidney is located in an abnormal anatomic position within the pelvis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hydronephrosis
Definition: "Severe distention of the kidney with dilation of the renal pelvis and calices." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Renal salt wasting
Definition: "A high concentration of one or more electrolytes in the urine in the presence of low serum concentrations of the electrolyte(s)." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:Eurenomics_fschaefer]

Name: Renal potassium wasting
Definition: "High urine potassium in the presence of hypokalemia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the uterus
Definition: "An abnormality of the uterus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Uterine leiomyoma
Definition: "The presence of a leiomyoma of the uterus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Menorrhagia
Definition: "Prolonged and excessive menses at regular intervals in excess of 80 mL or lasting longer than 7 days." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:22594864]

Name: Female hypogonadism
Definition: "Decreased functionality of the female gonads, i.e., of the ovary." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypogonadism
Definition: "A decreased functionality of the gonad." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bifid uterus
Definition: "The presence of a bifid uterus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the ovary
Definition: "An abnormality of the ovary." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ovarian cyst
Definition: "The presence of one or more cysts of the ovary." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Uterine prolapse
Definition: "The presence of prolapse of the uterus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the menstrual cycle
Definition: "An abnormality of the ovulation cycle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:23281358]

Name: Amenorrhea
Definition: "Absence of menses for an interval of time equivalent to a total of more than (or equal to) 3 previous cycles or 6 months." [PMID:22594864]

Name: Abnormal vagina morphology
Definition: "Any structural abnormality of the vagina." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Rectovaginal fistula
Definition: "The presence of a fistula between the vagina and the rectum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Vaginal atresia
Definition: "Congenital occlusion of the vagina or adhesion of the walls of the vagina causing occlusion." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ovarian gonadoblastoma
Definition: "The presence of a gonadoblastoma of the ovary." [eMedicine:986581, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Gonadoblastoma
Definition: "The presence of a gonadoblastoma, a neoplasm of a gonad that consists of aggregates of germ cells and sex cord elements." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia of the uterus
Definition: "Aplasia of the uterus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of head or neck
Definition: "An abnormality of head and neck." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the mouth
Definition: "An abnormality of the mouth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Wide mouth
Definition: "Distance between the oral commissures more than 2 SD above the mean. Alternatively, an apparently increased width of the oral aperture (subjective)." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Oral ulcer
Definition: "Erosion of the mucous mebrane of the mouth with local excavation of the surface, resulting from the sloughing of inflammatory necrotic tissue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the tongue
Definition: "Any abnormality of the tongue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Macroglossia
Definition: "Increased length and width of the tongue." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Abnormal lip morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the lip." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Narrow mouth
Definition: "Distance between the commissures of the mouth more than 2 SD below the mean. Alternatively, an apparently decreased width of the oral aperture (subjective)." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Median cleft lip
Definition: "A type of cleft lip presenting as a midline (median) gap in the upper lip." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Glossoptosis
Definition: "Posterior displacement of the tongue into the pharynx, i.e., a tongue that is mislocalised posteriorly." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125428]

Name: Abnormal oral cavity morphology
Definition: "Abnormality of the oral cavity, i.e., the opening or hollow part of the mouth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the dentition
Definition: "Any abnormality of the teeth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Severe periodontitis
Definition: "A severe form of periodontitis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the gingiva
Definition: "Any abnormality of the gingiva (also known as gums)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Gingival fibromatosis
Definition: "The presence of fibrosis of the gingiva." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Microglossia
Definition: "Decreased length and width of the tongue." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Abnormal uvula morphology
Definition: "Abnormality of the uvula, the conic projection from the posterior edge of the middle of the soft palate." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal palate morphology
Definition: "Any abnormality of the palate, i.e., of roof of the mouth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cleft palate
Definition: "Cleft palate is a developmental defect of the palate resulting from a failure of fusion of the palatine processes and manifesting as a separation of the roof of the mouth (soft and hard palate)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Submucous cleft hard palate
Definition: "Hard-palate submucous clefts are characterized by bony defects in the midline of the bony palate that are covered by the mucous membrane of the roof of the mouth. It may be possible to detect a submucous cleft hard palate upon palpation as a notch in the bony palate." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19779505]

Name: Abnormal upper lip morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the upper lip." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal lower lip morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the lower lip." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thick lower lip vermilion
Definition: "Increased thickness of the lower lip, leading to a prominent appearance of the lower lip. The height of the vermilion of the lower lip in the midline is more than 2 SD above the mean. Alternatively, an apparently increased height of the vermilion of the lower lip in the frontal view (subjective)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125428]

Name: Lobulated tongue
Definition: "Multiple indentations and/or elevations on the edge and/or surface of the tongue producing an irregular surface contour." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Cleft soft palate
Definition: "Cleft of the soft palate (also known as the velum, or muscular palate) as a result of a developmental defect occurring between the 7th and 12th week of pregnancy. Cleft soft palate can cause functional abnormalities of the Eustachian tube with resulting middle ear anomalies and hearing difficulties, as well as speech problems associated with hypernasal speech due to velopharyngeal insufficiency." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short upper lip
Definition: "Decreased width of the upper lip." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Narrow palate
Definition: "Width of the palate more than 2 SD below the mean (objective) or apparently decreased palatal width (subjective)." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Abnormal oral frenulum morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the lingual frenulum, that is of the small fold of mucous membrane that attaches the tongue to the floor of the mouth, or the presence of accessory frenula in the oral cavity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:23633765]

Name: Accessory oral frenulum
Definition: "Extra fold of tissue extending from the alveolar ridge to the inner surface of the upper or lower lip." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Bifid uvula
Definition: "Uvula separated into two parts most easily seen at the tip." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Open mouth
Definition: "A facial appearance characterized by a permanently or nearly permanently opened mouth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lower lip pit
Definition: "Depression located on the vermilion of the lower lip, usually paramedian." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154, PMID:19125428]

Name: Abnormal parotid gland morphology
Definition: "Any abnormality of the parotid glands, which are the salivary glands that are located in the subcutaneous tissues of the face overlying the mandibular ramus and anterior and inferior to the external ear." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short lingual frenulum
Definition: "The presence of an abnormally short lingual frenulum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pierre-Robin sequence
Definition: "Pierre Robin malformation is a sequence of developmental malformations characterized by micrognathia (mandibular hypoplasia), glossoptosis and cleft palate." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Orofacial cleft
Definition: "The presence of a cleft in the oral cavity, the two main types of which are cleft lip and cleft palate. In cleft lip, there is the congenital failure of the maxillary and median nasal processes to fuse, forming a groove or fissure in the lip. In cleft palate, there is a congenital failure of the palate to fuse properly, forming a grooved depression or fissure in the roof of the mouth. Clefts of the lip and palate can occur individually or together. It is preferable to code each defect separately." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:21331089]

Name: Cleft upper lip
Definition: "A gap in the upper lip. This is a congenital defect resulting from nonfusion of tissues of the lip during embryonal development." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pursed lips
Definition: "An abnormality of the appearance of the face caused by constant contraction of the lips leading to a puckered or pursed appearance." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Glossitis
Definition: "Inflammation of the tongue." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Triangular mouth
Definition: "The presence of a triangular form of the mouth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Trismus
Definition: "Limitation in the ability to open the mouth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Gingival overgrowth
Definition: "Hyperplasia of the gingiva (that is, a thickening of the soft tissue overlying the alveolar ridge. The degree of thickening ranges from involvement of the interdental papillae alone to gingival overgrowth covering the entire tooth crown." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Lip telangiectasia
Definition: "Telangiectasia (that is, the presence of small dilated superficial blood vessels) of the lips." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thick upper lip vermilion
Definition: "Height of the vermilion of the upper lip in the midline more than 2 SD above the mean. Alternatively, an apparently increased height of the vermilion of the upper lip in the frontal view (subjective)." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Xerostomia
Definition: "Dryness of the mouth due to salivary gland dysfunction." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: High palate
Definition: "Height of the palate more than 2 SD above the mean (objective) or palatal height at the level of the first permanent molar more than twice the height of the teeth (subjective)." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Thin upper lip vermilion
Definition: "Height of the vermilion of the upper lip in the midline more than 2 SD below the mean. Alternatively, an apparently reduced height of the vermilion of the upper lip in the frontal view (subjective)." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Velopharyngeal insufficiency
Definition: "Inability of velopharyngeal sphincter to sufficiently separate the nasal cavity from the oral cavity during speech." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_jhurst]

Name: Furrowed tongue
Definition: "Accentuation of the grooves on the dorsal surface of the tongue." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Gingival hyperkeratosis
Definition: "Hyperkeratosis of the gingiva." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Hypogeusia
Definition: "A decreased ability to perceive flavor." []

Name: Gingival bleeding
Definition: "Hemorrhage affecting the gingiva." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Tongue telangiectasia
Definition: "Telangiectasia (that is, the presence of small dilated superficial blood vessels) of the tongue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Oral cavity telangiectasia
Definition: "Presence of telangiectases in the oral cavity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Gingivitis
Definition: "Inflammation of the gingiva." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Everted lower lip vermilion
Definition: "An abnormal configuration of the lower lip such that it is turned outward i.e., everted, with the Inner aspect of the lower lip vermilion (normally opposing the teeth) being visible in a frontal view." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Thin vermilion border
Definition: "Height of the vermilion of the medial part of the lip more than 2 SD below the mean, or apparently reduced height of the vermilion of the lip in the frontal view. The vermilion is the red part of the lips (and confusingly, the vermilion itself is also often referred to as being equivalent the lips)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125428]

Name: Abnormality of the head
Definition: "An abnormality of the head." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the fontanelles or cranial sutures
Definition: "Any abnormality of the fontanelles (the regions covered by a thick membrane that normally ossify in the first two years of life) or the cranial sutures (the fibrous joints in which the articulating bones or cartilages of the skull are connected by sutural ligaments)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:12825844]

Name: Abnormality of the anterior fontanelle
Definition: "An abnormality of the anterior fontanelle, i.e., the cranial fontanelle that is located at the intersection of the coronal and sagittal sutures." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Small anterior fontanelle
Definition: "Abnormally decreased size of the anterior fontanelle with respect to age-dependent norms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hydrocephalus
Definition: "Hydrocephalus is an active distension of the ventricular system of the brain resulting from inadequate passage of CSF from its point of production within the cerebral ventricles to its point of absorption into the systemic circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:18211712, PMID:19410151]

Name: Large fontanelles
Definition: "In newborns, the two frontal bones, two parietal bones, and one occipital bone are joined by fibrous sutures, which form a small posterior fontanelle, and a larger, diamond-shaped anterior fontanelle. These regions allow for the skull to pass the birth canal and for later growth. The fontanelles gradually ossify, whereby the posterior fontanelle usually closes by eight weeks and the anterior fontanelle by the 9th to 16th month of age. Large fontanelles are diagnosed if the fontanelles are larger than age-dependent norms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of skull size
Definition: "Any abnormality of the size of the skull." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Parietal bossing
Definition: "Parietal bossing is a marked prominence in the parietal region." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Trigonocephaly
Definition: "Wedge-shaped, or triangular head, with the apex of the triangle at the midline of the forehead and the base of the triangle at the occiput." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Brachyturricephaly
Definition: "Abnormal vertical height of the skull and a shortening of its anterior-posterior length, frequently combined with malformations of the occipital region." [PMID:8460563]

Name: Abnormal paranasal sinus morphology
Definition: "Abnormality of the paranasal (cranial) sinuses, which are air-filled spaces that are located within the bones of the skull and face and communicate with the nasal cavity. They comprise the maxillary sinuses, the frontal sinuses, the ethmoid sinuses, and the sphenoid sinuses." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sinusitis
Definition: "Inflammation of the paranasal sinuses owing to a viral, bacterial, or fungal infection, allergy, or an autoimmune reaction." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Brachycephaly
Definition: "An abnormality of skull shape characterized by a decreased anterior-posterior diameter. That is, a cephalic index greater than 81%. Alternatively, an apparently shortened anteroposterior dimension (length) of the head compared to width." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125436]

Name: Dense calvaria
Definition: "An abnormal increase of density of the bones making up the calvaria." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Microcephaly
Definition: "Head circumference below 2 standard deviations below the mean for age and gender." [PMID:15806441, PMID:19125436, PMID:25465325, PMID:9683597]

Name: Progressive microcephaly
Definition: "Progressive microcephaly is diagnosed when the head circumference falls progressively behind age- and gender-dependent norms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Acute sinusitis
Definition: "An acute form of sinusitis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Macrocephaly
Definition: "Occipitofrontal (head) circumference greater than 97th centile compared to appropriate, age matched, sex-matched normal standards. Alternatively, a apparently increased size of the cranium." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Wide anterior fontanel
Definition: "Enlargement of the anterior fontanelle with respect to age-dependent norms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Turricephaly
Definition: "Tall head relative to width and length." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Oxycephaly
Definition: "Oxycephaly (from Greek oxus, sharp, and kephalos, head) refers to a conical or pointed shape of the skull." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal mastoid morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the mastoid process, which is the conical prominence projecting from the undersurface of the mastoid portion of the temporal bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cranial asymmetry
Definition: "Asymmetry of the bones of the skull." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Dolichocephaly
Definition: "An abnormality of skull shape characterized by a increased anterior-posterior diameter, i.e., an increased antero-posterior dimension of the skull. Cephalic index less than 76%. Alternatively, an apparently increased antero-posterior length of the head compared to width. Often due to premature closure of the sagittal suture." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125436]

Name: Prominent occiput
Definition: "Increased convexity of the occiput (posterior part of the skull)." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Delayed cranial suture closure
Definition: "Infants normally have two fontanels at birth, the diamond-shaped anterior fontanelle at the junction of the coronal and sagittal sutures, and the posterior fontanelle at the intersection of the occipital and parietal bones. The posterior fontanelle usually closes by the 8th week of life, and the anterior fontanel closes by the 18th month of life on average. This term applies if there is delay of closure of the fontanelles beyond the normal age." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the face
Definition: "An abnormality of the face." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Malar flattening
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the malar prominence of the jugal bone (zygomatic bone in mammals), appreciated in profile, frontal view, and/or by palpation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5889-4463, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125436]

Name: Small face
Definition: "A face that is short and narrow." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Narrow face
Definition: "Bizygomatic (upper face) and bigonial (lower face) width are both more than 2 standard deviations below the mean (objective); or, an apparent reduction in the width of the upper and lower face (subjective)." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Long face
Definition: "Facial height (length) is more than 2 standard deviations above the mean (objective); or, an apparent increase in the height (length) of the face (subjective)." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Abnormal mandible morphology
Definition: "Any abnormality of the mandible, the bone of the lower jaw." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Retrognathia
Definition: "An abnormality in which the mandible is mislocalised posteriorly." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Coarse facial features
Definition: "Absence of fine and sharp appearance of brows, nose, lips, mouth, and chin, usually because of rounded and heavy features or thickened skin with or without thickening of subcutaneous and bony tissues." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Broad face
Definition: "Bizygomatic (upper face) and bigonial (lower face) width greater than 2 standard deviations above the mean (objective); or an apparent increase in the width of the face (subjective)." [PMID:19125436]

Name: obsolete Abnormality of the ocular region
Epicanthus
Definition: "A fold of skin starting above the medial aspect of the upper eyelid and arching downward to cover, pass in front of and lateral to the medial canthus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased facial adipose tissue
Definition: "An increased amount of subcutaneous fat tissue in the face." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the philtrum
Definition: "An abnormality of the philtrum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Broad philtrum
Definition: "Distance between the philtral ridges, measured just above the vermilion border, more than 2 standard deviations above the mean, or alternatively, an apparently increased distance between the ridges of the philtrum." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Abnormality of the forehead
Definition: "An anomaly of the forehead." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Loss of facial adipose tissue
Definition: "Loss of normal subcutaneous fat tissue in the face." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Full cheeks
Definition: "Increased prominence or roundness of soft tissues between zygomata and mandible." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2972-5481]

Name: Low anterior hairline
Definition: "Distance between the hairline (trichion) and the glabella (the most prominent point on the frontal bone above the root of the nose), in the midline, more than two SD below the mean. Alternatively, an apparently decreased distance between the hairline and the glabella." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Doll-like facies
Definition: "A characteristic facial appearance with a round facial form, full cheeks, a short nose, and a relatively small chin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Facial hypotonia
Definition: "Reduced muscle tone of a muscle that is innervated by the facial nerve (the seventh cranial nerve)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Mask-like facies
Definition: "A lack of facial expression often with staring eyes and a slightly open mouth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Oval face
Definition: "A face with a rounded and slightly elongated outline." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of facial musculature
Definition: "An anomaly of a muscle that is innervated by the facial nerve (the seventh cranial nerve)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Mandibular prognathia
Definition: "Abnormal prominence of the chin related to increased length of the mandible." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the chin
Definition: "An abnormality of the chin, i.e., of the inferior portion of the face lying inferior to the lower lip and including the central prominence of the lower jaw." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125436]

Name: Pointed chin
Definition: "A marked tapering of the lower face to the chin." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Microretrognathia
Definition: "A form of developmental hypoplasia of the mandible in which the mandible is mislocalised posteriorly." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal midface morphology
Definition: "An anomaly of the midface, which is a region and not an anatomical term. It extends, superiorly, from the inferior orbital margin to, inferiorly, the level of nasal base. It is formed by the maxilla (upper jaw) and zygoma and cheeks and malar region. Traditionally, the nose and premaxilla are not included in the midface." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125436]

Name: Round face
Definition: "The facial appearance is more circular than usual as viewed from the front." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Hypertelorism
Definition: "Interpupillary distance more than 2 SD above the mean (alternatively, the appearance of an increased interpupillary distance or widely spaced eyes)." [PMID:19125427]

Name: Facial myokymia
Definition: "Facial myokymia is a fine fibrillary activity of one or more muscles innervated by the facial nerve (the seventh cranial nerve)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Smooth philtrum
Definition: "Flat skin surface, with no ridge formation in the central region of the upper lip between the nasal base and upper vermilion border." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Square face
Definition: "Facial contours, as viewed from the front, show a broad upper face/cranium and lower face/mandible, creating a square appearance." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Short philtrum
Definition: "Distance between nasal base and midline upper lip vermilion border more than 2 SD below the mean. Alternatively, an apparently decreased distance between nasal base and midline upper lip vermilion border." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Facial asymmetry
Definition: "An abnormal difference between the left and right sides of the face." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Triangular face
Definition: "Facial contour, as viewed from the front, triangular in shape, with breadth at the temples and tapering to a narrow chin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9602-2321, PMID:19125436]

Name: Abnormal maxilla morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the Maxilla (upper jaw bone)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplasia of the maxilla
Definition: "Abnormally small dimension of the Maxilla. Usually creating a malocclusion or malalignment between the upper and lower teeth or resulting in a deficient amount of projection of the base of the nose and lower midface region." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Facial hemangioma
Definition: "Hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, occurring in the face." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short chin
Definition: "Decreased vertical distance from the vermilion border of the lower lip to the inferior-most point of the chin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125436]

Name: Prominent supraorbital ridges
Definition: "Greater than average forward and/or lateral protrusion of the supraorbital portion of the frontal bones." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Broad forehead
Definition: "Width of the forehead or distance between the frontotemporales is more than two standard deviations above the mean (objective); or apparently increased distance between the two sides of the forehead." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Hypomimic face
Definition: "A reduced degree of motion of the muscles beneath the skin of the face, often associated with reduced facial crease formation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pugilistic facies
Definition: "Coarse facial features reminiscent of those of a boxer." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sloping forehead
Definition: "Inclination of the anterior surface of the forehead from the vertical more than two standard deviations above the mean (objective); or apparently excessive posterior sloping of the forehead in a lateral view." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Narrow forehead
Definition: "Width of the forehead or distance between the frontotemporales is more than two standard deviations below the mean (objective); or apparently narrow intertemporal region (subjective)." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Long philtrum
Definition: "Distance between nasal base and midline upper lip vermilion border more than 2 SD above the mean. Alternatively, an apparently increased distance between nasal base and midline upper lip vermilion border." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Whistling appearance
Definition: "An abnormality of facial morphology characterized by a small mouth opening and constant contraction of the lips as if the patient were whistling." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:856233]

Name: Micrognathia
Definition: "Developmental hypoplasia of the mandible." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: High forehead
Definition: "An abnormally increased height of the forehead." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Widow's peak
Definition: "Frontal hairline with bilateral arcs to a low point in the midline of the forehead." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Small forehead
Definition: "The presence of a forehead that is abnormally small." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the outer ear
Definition: "An abnormality of the external ear." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal location of ears
Definition: "Abnormal location of the ear." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Posteriorly rotated ears
Definition: "A type of abnormal location of the ears in which the position of the ears is characterized by posterior rotation (the superior part of the ears is rotated towards the back of the head, and the inferior part of the ears towards the front)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152421]

Name: Abnormality of the inner ear
Definition: "An abnormality of the inner ear." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Tinnitus
Definition: "Tinnitus is an auditory perception that can be described as the experience of sound, in the ear or in the head, in the absence of external acoustic stimulation." []

Name: Otosclerosis
Definition: "In otosclerosis, a callus of bone accumulates on the stapes creating a partial fixation. This limits the movement of the stapes bone, which results in hearing loss." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:15931303]

Name: Abnormal earlobe morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the lobule of pinna." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hearing abnormality
Definition: "An abnormality of the sensory perception of sound." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hearing impairment
Definition: "A decreased magnitude of the sensory perception of sound." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the nose
Definition: "An abnormality of the nose." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Low-set, posteriorly rotated ears
Definition: "Ears that are low-set and posteriorly rotated." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Low-set ears
Definition: "Upper insertion of the ear to the scalp below an imaginary horizontal line drawn between the inner canthi of the eye and extending posteriorly to the ear." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152421]

Name: Abnormality of the middle ear
Definition: "An abnormality of the middle ear." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Acute otitis media
Definition: "Acute otitis media is a short and generally painful infection of the middle ear." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the auditory canal
Definition: "An abnormality of the External acoustic tube (also known as the auditory canal)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal cochlea morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the cochlea." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Incomplete partition of the cochlea type II
Definition: "With incomplete partition II, the cochlea consists of 1.5 turns; the apical and middle cochlea turns are undifferentiated and form a cystic apex. The vestibule is normal while the vestibular aqueduct is always enlarged. Developmental arrest occurs at the seventh week of gestation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:21849370, PMID:34698066]

Name: Abnormal pinna morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the pinna, which is also referred to as the auricle or external ear." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cupped ear
Definition: "Laterally protruding ear that lacks antihelical folding (including absence of inferior and superior crura)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19162421, PMID:22073081]

Name: Stapes ankylosis
Definition: "Stapes ankylosis refers to congenital or acquired fixation of the stapes (the stirrup-shaped small bone or ossicle in the middle ear), which is associated with conductive hearing resulting from impairment of the sound-conduction mechanism (the external auditory canal, tympanic membrane, and/or middle-ear ossicles)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:12089654]

Name: Preauricular skin tag
Definition: "A rudimentary tag of skin often containing ear tissue including a core of cartilage and located just anterior to the auricle (outer part of the ear)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Small earlobe
Definition: "Reduced volume of the earlobe." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152421]

Name: Absent earlobe
Definition: "Absence of fleshy non-cartilaginous tissue inferior to the tragus and incisura." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152421]

Name: Otitis media
Definition: "Inflammation or infection of the middle ear." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Chronic otitis media
Definition: "Chronic otitis media refers to fluid, swelling, or infection of the middle ear that does not heal and may cause permanent damage to the ear." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thickened helices
Definition: "Increased thickness of the helix of the ear." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lop ear
Definition: "Anterior and inferior folding of the upper portion of the ear that obliterates triangular fossa and scapha." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152421]

Name: Prominent antihelix
Definition: "The presence of an abnormally prominent antihelix." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Overfolded helix
Definition: "A condition in which the helix is folded over to a greater degree than normal. That is, excessive curling of the helix edge, whereby the free edge is parallel to the plane of the ear." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152421]

Name: Prelingual sensorineural hearing impairment
Definition: "A form of sensorineural deafness with either congenital onset or infantile onset, i.e., before the acquisition of speech." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Macrotia
Definition: "Median longitudinal ear length greater than two standard deviations above the mean and median ear width greater than two standard deviations above the mean (objective); or, apparent increase in length and width of the pinna (subjective)." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Stenosis of the external auditory canal
Definition: "An abnormal narrowing of the external auditory canal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Recurrent otitis media
Definition: "Increased susceptibility to otitis media, as manifested by recurrent episodes of otitis media." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Conductive hearing impairment
Definition: "An abnormality of vibrational conductance of sound to the inner ear leading to impairment of sensory perception of sound." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sensorineural hearing impairment
Definition: "A type of hearing impairment in one or both ears related to an abnormal functionality of the cochlear nerve." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Progressive sensorineural hearing impairment
Definition: "A progressive form of sensorineural hearing impairment." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Mixed hearing impairment
Definition: "A type of hearing loss resulting from a combination of conductive hearing impairment and sensorineural hearing impairment." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Protruding ear
Definition: "Angle formed by the plane of the ear and the mastoid bone greater than the 97th centile for age (objective); or, outer edge of the helix more than 2 cm from the mastoid at the point of maximum distance (objective)." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Atresia of the external auditory canal
Definition: "Absence or failure to form of the external auditory canal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bulbous nose
Definition: "Increased volume and globular shape of the anteroinferior aspect of the nose." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Abnormality of the choanae
Definition: "Abnormality of the choanae (the posterior nasal apertures)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Narrow nasal ridge
Definition: "Decreased width of the nasal ridge." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Abnormal nasal septum morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the nasal septum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short nasal septum
Definition: "Reduced superior to inferior length of the nasal septum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Epistaxis
Definition: "Epistaxis, or nosebleed, refers to a hemorrhage localized in the nose." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal nasal bridge morphology
Definition: "Abnormality of the nasal bridge, which is the saddle-shaped area that includes the nasal root and the lateral aspects of the nose. It lies between the glabella and the inferior boundary of the nasal bone, and extends laterally to the inner canthi." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152422]

Name: Prominent nasal bridge
Definition: "Anterior positioning of the nasal root in comparison to the usual positioning for age." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Abnormal morphology of the nasal alae
Definition: "An abnormality of the Ala of nose." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152422]

Name: Underdeveloped nasal alae
Definition: "Thinned, deficient, or excessively arched ala nasi." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Wide nasal bridge
Definition: "Increased breadth of the nasal bridge (and with it, the nasal root)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152422]

Name: Nasal mucosa telangiectasia
Definition: "Telangiectasia of the nasal mucosa." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal nasal tip morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the nasal tip." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152422]

Name: Depressed nasal tip
Definition: "Decreased distance from the nasal tip to the nasal base." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Convex nasal ridge
Definition: "Nasal ridge curving anteriorly to an imaginary line that connects the nasal root and tip. The nose appears often also prominent, and the columella low." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Wide nose
Definition: "Interalar distance more than two standard deviations above the mean for age, i.e., an apparently increased width of the nasal base and alae." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Narrow nasal bridge
Definition: "Decreased width of the bony bridge of the nose." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Prominent nose
Definition: "Distance between subnasale and pronasale more than two standard deviations above the mean, or alternatively, an apparently increased anterior protrusion of the nasal tip." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Choanal stenosis
Definition: "Abnormal narrowing of the choana (the posterior nasal aperture)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Choanal atresia
Definition: "Absence or abnormal closure of the choana (the posterior nasal aperture). Most embryologists believe that posterior choanal atresia results from a failure of rupture between the 35th and 38th day of fetal life of the partition which separates the bucconasal or buccopharyngeal membranes. The resultant choanal atresia may be unilateral or bilateral, bony or membranous, complete or incomplete. In over 90 per cent of cases the obstruction is bony, while in the remainder it is membranous. The bony type of atresia is commonly located 1-2 mm. anterior to the posterior edge of the hard palate, and the osseous septum varies in thickness from 1 to 10 mm. In the membranous form of choanal atresia the obstruction usually occurs further posteriorly. In approximately one third of cases the atresia is bilateral." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5889-4463, PMID:4996574]

Name: Broad nasal tip
Definition: "Increase in width of the nasal tip." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152422]

Name: Bifid nasal tip
Definition: "A splitting of the nasal tip. Visually assessable vertical indentation, cleft, or depression of the nasal tip." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154, PMID:19152422]

Name: Depressed nasal ridge
Definition: "Lack of prominence of the nose resulting from a posteriorly-placed nasal ridge." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152422]

Name: Anosmia
Definition: "An inability to perceive odors. This is a general term describing inability to smell arising in any part of the process of smelling from absorption of odorants into the nasal mucous overlying the olfactory epithelium, diffusion to the cilia, binding to olfactory receptor sites, generation of action potentials in olfactory neurons, and perception of a smell." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Narrow nose
Definition: "Interalar distance more than 2 SD below the mean for age, or alternatively, an apparently decreased width of the nasal base and alae." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Anteverted nares
Definition: "Anteriorly-facing nostrils viewed with the head in the Frankfurt horizontal and the eyes of the observer level with the eyes of the subject. This gives the appearance of an upturned nose (upturned nasal tip)." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Abnormality of the neck
Definition: "An abnormality of the neck." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Webbed neck
Definition: "Pterygium colli is a congenital skin fold that runs along the sides of the neck down to the shoulders. It involves an ectopic fibrotic facial band superficial to the trapezius muscle. Excess hair-bearing skin is also present and extends down the cervical region well beyond the normal hairline." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:24523736]

Name: Neck muscle weakness
Definition: "Decreased strength of the neck musculature." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased adipose tissue around the neck
Definition: "An increased amount of subcutaneous fat tissue around the neck." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short neck
Definition: "Diminished length of the neck." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Gastrointestinal angiodysplasia
Definition: "Dysplasia affecting the vasculature of the gastrointestinal tract." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Long neck
Definition: "Increased inferior-superior length of the neck." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Torticollis
Definition: "Involuntary contractions of the neck musculature resulting in an abnormal posture of or abnormal movements of the head." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thickened nuchal skin fold
Definition: "A thickening of the skin thickness in the posterior aspect of the fetal neck. A nuchal fold (NF) measurement is obtained in a transverse section of the fetal head at the level of the cavum septum pellucidum and thalami, angled posteriorly to include the cerebellum. The measurement is taken from the outer edge of the occiput bone to the outer skin limit directly in the midline. An NF measurement greater than 5 mm at 14 to 17+6 weeks of gestation, or 6 mm at 18 to 28 weeks has been associated with a markedly increased risk for Down syndrome." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16100637, PMID:30431620]

Name: Broad neck
Definition: "Increased side-to-side width of the neck." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cystic hygroma
Definition: "A cystic lymphatic lesion of the neck." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the eye
Definition: "Any abnormality of the eye, including location, spacing, and intraocular abnormalities." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal retinal morphology
Definition: "A structural abnormality of the retina." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Retinal coloboma
Definition: "A notch or cleft of the retina." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal cornea morphology
Definition: "Any abnormality of the cornea, which is the transparent tissue at the front of the eye that covers the iris, pupil, and anterior chamber." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Microcornea
Definition: "A congenital abnormality of the cornea in which the cornea and the anterior segment of the eye are smaller than normal. The horizontal diameter of the cornea does not reach 10 mm even in adulthood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Astigmatism
Definition: "A type of astigmatism associated with abnormal curvatures on the anterior and/or posterior surface of the cornea." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_ncarter, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0986-4123]

Name: Hyperopic astigmatism
Definition: "A form of astigmatism in which one meridian is hyperopic while the one at a right angle to it has no refractive error." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Megalocornea
Definition: "An enlargement of the cornea with normal clarity and function. Megalocornea is diagnosed with a horizontal corneal diameter of 12 mm or more at birth or 13 mm or more after two years of age." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Strabismus
Definition: "A misalignment of the eyes so that the visual axes deviate from bifoveal fixation. The classification of strabismus may be based on a number of features including the relative position of the eyes, whether the deviation is latent or manifest, intermittent or constant, concomitant or otherwise and according to the age of onset and the relevance of any associated refractive error." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0986-4123, PMID:26319345]

Name: Retinopathy
Definition: "Any noninflammatory disease of the retina. This nonspecific term is retained here because of its wide use in the literature, but if possible new annotations should indicate the precise type of retinal abnormality." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: obsolete Abnormality of globe location or size
Deeply set eye
Definition: "An eye that is more deeply recessed into the plane of the face than is typical." [PMID:19125427]

Name: Keratitis
Definition: "Inflammation of the cornea." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal eyelid morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the eyelids." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal foveal morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the fovea centralis, the central area of the macula that mediates central, high resolution vision and contains the largest concentration of cone cells in the retina." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Downslanted palpebral fissures
Definition: "The palpebral fissure inclination is more than two standard deviations below the mean." [PMID:19125427]

Name: Recurrent corneal erosions
Definition: "The presence of recurrent corneal epithelial erosions. Although most corneal epithelial defects heal quickly, some may show recurrent ulcerations." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of eye movement
Definition: "An abnormality in voluntary or involuntary eye movements or their control." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Globe retraction and deviation on abduction
Blepharitis
Definition: "Inflammation of the eyelids." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal eyelash morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the eyelashes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Glaucoma
Definition: "Glaucoma refers loss of retinal ganglion cells in a characteristic pattern of optic neuropathy usually associated with increased intraocular pressure." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:11815354]

Name: Abnormal conjunctiva morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the conjunctiva." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Tortuosity of conjunctival vessels
Definition: "The presence of an increased number of twists and turns of the conjunctival blood vessels." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of vision
Definition: "Abnormality of eyesight (visual perception)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Visual impairment
Definition: "Visual impairment (or vision impairment) is vision loss (of a person) to such a degree as to qualify as an additional support need through a significant limitation of visual capability resulting from either disease, trauma, or congenital or degenerative conditions that cannot be corrected by conventional means, such as refractive correction, medication, or surgery." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8727-6592]

Name: Telecanthus
Definition: "Distance between the inner canthi more than two standard deviations above the mean (objective); or, apparently increased distance between the inner canthi." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ptosis
Definition: "The upper eyelid margin is positioned 3 mm or more lower than usual and covers the superior portion of the iris (objective); or, the upper lid margin obscures at least part of the pupil (subjective)." [PMID:19125427]

Name: Conjunctivitis
Definition: "Inflammation of the conjunctiva." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Rod-cone dystrophy
Definition: "An inherited retinal disease subtype in which the rod photoreceptors appear to be more severely affected than the cone photoreceptors. Typical presentation is with nyctalopia (due to rod dysfunction) followed by loss of mid-peripheral field of vision, which gradually extends and leaves many patients with a small central island of vision due to the preservation of macular cones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20212494]

Name: Vertical supranuclear gaze palsy
Definition: "A supranuclear gaze palsy is an inability to look in a vertical direction as a result of cerebral impairment. There is a loss of the voluntary aspect of eye movements, but, as the brainstem is still intact, all the reflex conjugate eye movements are normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20671861]

Name: Abnormal electroretinogram
Definition: "Any abnormality of the electrical responses of various cell types in the retina as measured by electroretinography." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Slow saccadic eye movements
Definition: "An abnormally slow velocity of the saccadic eye movements." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal lens morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the lens." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cataract
Definition: "A cataract is an opacity or clouding that develops in the crystalline lens of the eye or in its capsule." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Developmental cataract
Definition: "A cataract that occurs congenitally as the result of a developmental defect, in contrast to the majority of cataracts that occur in adulthood as the result of degenerative changes of the lens." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Proptosis
Definition: "An eye that is protruding anterior to the plane of the face to a greater extent than is typical." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154, PMID:19125427]

Name: Alacrima
Definition: "Absence of tear secretion." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Subcapsular cataract
Definition: "A cataract that affects the region of the lens directly beneath the capsule of the lens." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Conjunctival telangiectasia
Definition: "The presence of small (ca. 0.5-1.0 mm) dilated blood vessels near the surface of the mucous membranes of the conjunctiva." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality iris morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the iris, which is the pigmented muscular tissue between the cornea and the lens, that is perforated by an opening called the pupil." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aniridia
Definition: "Abnormality of the iris characterized by, typically bilateral, complete or partial iris hypoplasia. The phenotype ranges from mild defects of anterior iris stroma only to almost complete absence of the iris." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0986-4123, PMID:24138039, PMID:25313118, PMID:29850208]

Name: Long eyelashes
Definition: "Mid upper eyelash length >10 mm or increased length of the eyelashes (subjective)." [PMID:19125427, PMID:26288407]

Name: Anophthalmia
Definition: "Absence of the globe or eyeball." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_ncarter]

Name: Progressive visual loss
Definition: "A reduction of previously attained ability to see." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal chorioretinal morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the choroid and retina." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Chorioretinal atrophy
Definition: "Atrophy of the choroid and retinal layers of the fundus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20224472]

Name: Abnormal eyebrow morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the eyebrow." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Epicanthus inversus
Definition: "A fold of skin starting at or just below the medial aspect of the lower lid and arching upward to cover, extend in front of and lateral to the medial canthus." [PMID:19125427]

Name: Pseudopapilledema
Definition: "Apparent optic disc swelling in the absence of increased intracranial pressure." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of refraction
Definition: "An abnormality in the process of focusing of light by the eye in order to produce a sharp image on the retina." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypermetropia
Definition: "An abnormality of refraction characterized by the ability to see objects in the distance clearly, while objects nearby appear blurry." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Retinal detachment
Definition: "Separation of the inner layers of the retina (neural retina) from the pigment epithelium." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Impaired ocular adduction
Definition: "Reduced ability to move the eye in the direction of the nose." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Optic disc pallor
Definition: "A pale yellow discoloration of the optic disk (the area of the optic nerve head in the retina). The optic disc normally has a pinkish hue with a central yellowish depression." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: External ophthalmoplegia
Definition: "Paralysis of the external ocular muscles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Myopia
Definition: "An abnormality of refraction characterized by the ability to see objects nearby clearly, while objects in the distance appear blurry." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Retinal degeneration
Definition: "A nonspecific term denoting degeneration of the retinal pigment epithelium and/or retinal photoreceptor cells." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0986-4123]

Name: Abnormal conjugate eye movement
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal motor coordination of the eyes that allows for bilateral fixation on a single object." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Undetectable electroretinogram
Definition: "Lack of any response to stimulation upon electroretinography." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Color vision defect
Definition: "An anomaly in the ability to discriminate between or recognize colors." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Tritanomaly
Definition: "Difficulty distinguishing between yellow and blue, possible related to dysfunction of the S photopigment." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal uvea morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the uvea, the vascular layer of the eyeball." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Uveitis
Definition: "Inflammation of one or all portions of the uveal tract." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Leukocoria
Definition: "An abnormal white reflection from the pupil rather than the usual black reflection." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Retinal dystrophy
Definition: "Retinal dystrophy is an abnormality of the retina associated with a hereditary process. Retinal dystrophies are defined by their predominantly monogenic inheritance and they are frequently associated with loss or dysfunction of photoreceptor cells as a primary or secondary event." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0986-4123]

Name: Buphthalmos
Definition: "Diffusely large eye (with megalocornea) associated with glaucoma." []

Name: Rieger anomaly
Definition: "A congenital malformation of the anterior segment characterized by iridicorneal malformation, glaucoma, iris stroma hypoplasia, posterior embryotoxon, and corneal opacities." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent eyelashes
Definition: "Lack of eyelashes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125427]

Name: Keratoconus
Definition: "A cone-shaped deformity of the cornea characterized by the presence of corneal distortion secondary to thinning of the apex." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:7767020]

Name: Lacrimal duct atresia
Definition: "A developmental disorder of the lacrimal drainage system that most often affects the lacrimal ostium and resulting in non-opening of the nasolacrimal duct. It usually results from a non-canalization of the nasolacrimal duct." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Esotropia
Definition: "A form of strabismus with one or both eyes turned inward ('crossed') to a relatively severe degree, usually defined as 10 diopters or more." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Chorioretinal coloboma
Definition: "Absence of a region of the retina, retinal pigment epithelium, and choroid." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Microphthalmia
Definition: "A developmental anomaly characterized by abnormal smallness of one or both eyes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal saccadic eye movements
Definition: "An abnormality of eye movement characterized by impairment of fast (saccadic) eye movements." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypometric saccades
Definition: "Saccadic undershoot, i.e., a saccadic eye movement that has less than the magnitude that would be required to gain fixation of the object." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:572501]

Name: Visual loss
Definition: "Loss of visual acuity (implying that vision was better at a certain time point in life). Otherwise the term reduced visual acuity should be used (or a subclass of that)." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Retinal hemorrhage
Definition: "Hemorrhage occurring within the retina." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Thick eyebrow
Definition: "Increased density/number and/or increased diameter of eyebrow hairs." [PMID:19125427]

Name: Scotoma
Definition: "A regional and pathological increase of the light detection threshold in any region of the visual field surrounded by a field of normal or relatively well-preserved vision." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Centrocecal scotoma
