Definition: "A scotoma (area of diminished vision within the visual field) located between the central point of fixation and the blind spot with a roughly horizontal oval shape." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Exotropia
Definition: "A form of strabismus with one or both eyes deviated outward." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Nasolacrimal duct obstruction
Definition: "Blockage of the lacrimal duct." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pigmentary retinopathy
Definition: "An abnormality of the retina characterized by pigment deposition. It is typically associated with migration and proliferation of macrophages or retinal pigment epithelial cells into the retina; melanin from these cells causes the pigmentary changes. Pigmentary retinopathy is a common final pathway of many retinal conditions and is often associated with visual loss." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0986-4123]

Name: Blepharophimosis
Definition: "A fixed reduction in the vertical distance between the upper and lower eyelids with short palpebral fissures." [PMID:19125427]

Name: Upslanted palpebral fissure
Definition: "The palpebral fissure inclination is more than two standard deviations above the mean for age (objective); or, the inclination of the palpebral fissure is greater than typical for age." [PMID:19125427]

Name: Band keratopathy
Definition: "An abnormality of the cornea characterized by the deposition of calcium in a band across the central cornea, leading to decreased vision, foreign body sensation, and ocular irritation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Shallow orbits
Definition: "Reduced depth of the orbits associated with prominent-appearing ocular globes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal optic nerve morphology
Definition: "Abnormality of the optic nerve." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Optic disc coloboma
Definition: "A cleft of the optic nerve that extends inferiorly." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16219745]

Name: Coloboma
Definition: "A developmental defect characterized by a cleft of some portion of the eye or ocular adnexa." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Progressive external ophthalmoplegia
Definition: "Initial bilateral ptosis followed by limitation of eye movements in all directions and slowing of saccades." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal sclera morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the sclera." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Blue sclerae
Definition: "An abnormal bluish coloration of the sclera." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal anterior chamber morphology
Definition: "Abnormality of the anterior chamber, which is the space in the eye that is behind the cornea and in front of the iris." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Shallow anterior chamber
Definition: "Reduced depth of the anterior chamber, i.e., the anteroposterior distance between the cornea and the iris is decreased." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ophthalmoparesis
Definition: "Ophthalmoplegia is a paralysis or weakness of one or more of the muscles that control eye movement." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the ear
Definition: "An abnormality of the ear." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the frontal hairline
Definition: "An anomaly in the placement or shape of the hairline (trichion) on the forehead, that is, the border between skin on the forehead that has head hair and that does not." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the pharynx
Definition: "An anomaly of the pharynx, i.e., of the tubular structure extending from the base of the skull superiorly to the esophageal inlet inferiorly." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypotelorism
Definition: "Interpupillary distance less than 2 SD below the mean (alternatively, the appearance of an decreased interpupillary distance or closely spaced eyes)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125427]

Name: Ophthalmoplegia
Definition: "Paralysis of one or more extraocular muscles that are responsible for eye movements." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Central scotoma
Definition: "An area of depressed vision located at the point of fixation and that interferes with central vision." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Supranuclear gaze palsy
Definition: "A supranuclear gaze palsy is an inability to look in a particular direction as a result of cerebral impairment. There is a loss of the voluntary aspect of eye movements, but, as the brainstem is still intact, all the reflex conjugate eye movements are normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the periorbital region
Definition: "An abnormality of the region situated around the orbit of the eye." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Macular degeneration
Definition: "A nonspecific term denoting degeneration of the retinal pigment epithelium and/or retinal photoreceptor cells of the macula lutea." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0986-4123]

Name: Optic nerve hypoplasia
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the optic nerve." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal choroid morphology
Definition: "Any structural abnormality of the choroid." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Iris coloboma
Definition: "A coloboma of the iris." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19369671]

Name: Photophobia
Definition: "Excessive sensitivity to light with the sensation of discomfort or pain in the eyes due to exposure to bright light." []

Name: Abnormal nasolacrimal system morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the nasolacrimal drainage system, which serves as a conduit for tear flow from the external eye to the nasal cavity." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_ncarter]

Name: Abnormal pupil morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the pupil." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Miosis
Definition: "Abnormal (non-physiological) constriction of the pupil." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of ocular smooth pursuit
Definition: "An abnormality of eye movement characterized by impaired smooth-pursuit eye movements." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Blindness
Definition: "Blindness is the condition of lacking visual perception defined as visual perception below 3/60 and/or a visual field of no greater than 10 degrees in radius around central fixation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8727-6592, PMID:28779882]

Name: Impaired convergence
Definition: "Reduced ability to turn the eyes inward in order to focus on a nearby object." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Dacryocystitis
Definition: "Inflammation of the nasolacrimal sac." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Entropion
Definition: "An abnormal inversion (turning inward) of the eyelid (usually the lower) towards the globe. Entropion is usually acquired as a result of involutional or cicatricial processes but may occasionally be congenital." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0986-4123, PMID:19125427]

Name: Blurred vision
Definition: "Lack of sharpness of vision resulting in the inability to see fine detail." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Supranuclear ophthalmoplegia
Definition: "A vertical gaze palsy with inability to direct the gaze of the eyes downwards." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20629667]

Name: Eyelid coloboma
Definition: "A short discontinuity of the margin of the lower or upper eyelid." [PMID:19125427]

Name: Posterior embryotoxon
Definition: "A posterior embryotoxon is the presence of a prominent and anteriorly displaced line of Schwalbe." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Periorbital fullness
Definition: "Increase in periorbital soft tissue." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Retinal arterial tortuosity
Definition: "The presence of an increased number of twists and turns of the retinal artery." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lacrimation abnormality
Definition: "Abnormality of tear production." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased lacrimation
Definition: "Abnormally decreased lacrimation, that is, reduced ability to produce tears." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Impaired ocular abduction
Definition: "An impaired ability of the eye to move in the outward direction (towards the side of the head)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Blue irides
Definition: "A markedly blue coloration of the iris." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Upper eyelid coloboma
Definition: "A short discontinuity of the margin of the upper eyelid." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Long palpebral fissure
Definition: "Distance between medial and lateral canthi is more than two standard deviations above the mean for age (objective); or, apparently increased length of the palpebral fissures." [PMID:19125427]

Name: Nystagmus
Definition: "Rhythmic, involuntary oscillations of one or both eyes related to abnormality in fixation, conjugate gaze, or vestibular mechanisms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Gaze-evoked nystagmus
Definition: "Nystagmus made apparent by looking to the right or to the left." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Dysmetric saccades
Definition: "The controller signal for saccadic eye movements has two components: the pulse that moves the eye rapidly from one point to the next, and the step that holds the eye in the new position. When both the pulse and the step are not the correct size, a dysmetric refixation eye movement results." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:572501]

Name: Red-green dyschromatopsia
Definition: "Difficulty with discriminating red and green hues." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8727-6592]

Name: Blepharospasm
Definition: "A focal dystonia that affects the muscles of the eyelids and brow, associated with involuntary recurrent spasm of both eyelids." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Amblyopia
Definition: "Reduced visual acuity that is uncorrectable by lenses in the absence of detectable anatomic defects in the eye or visual pathways." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sclerocornea
Definition: "A congenital anomaly in which a part or the whole of the cornea acquires the characteristics of sclera, resulting in clouding of the cornea." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Optic atrophy
Definition: "Atrophy of the optic nerve. Optic atrophy results from the death of the retinal ganglion cell axons that comprise the optic nerve and manifesting as a pale optic nerve on fundoscopy." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of visual evoked potentials
Definition: "An anomaly of visually evoked potentials (VEP), which are electrical potentials, initiated by brief visual stimuli, which are recorded from the scalp overlying the visual cortex." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19826847]

Name: Abnormal amplitude of pattern reversal visual evoked potentials
Diplopia
Definition: "Diplopia is a condition in which a single object is perceived as two images, it is also known as double vision." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lower eyelid coloboma
Definition: "A short discontinuity of the margin of the lower eyelid." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sparse eyelashes
Definition: "Decreased density/number of eyelashes." [PMID:19125427]

Name: Decreased light- and dark-adapted electroretinogram amplitude
Definition: "Descreased amplitude of eletrical response upon electroretinography." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ectropion
Definition: "An outward turning (eversion) or rotation of the eyelid margin." [PMID:19125427]

Name: Oculomotor apraxia
Definition: "Ocular motor apraxia is a deficiency in voluntary, horizontal, lateral, fast eye movements (saccades) with retention of slow pursuit movements. The inability to follow objects visually is often compensated by head movements. There may be decreased smooth pursuit, and cancellation of the vestibulo-ocular reflex." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20615230]

Name: Peters anomaly
Definition: "A form of anterior segment dysgenesis in which abnormal cleavage of the anterior chamber occurs. Peters anomaly is characterized by central, paracentral, or complete corneal opacity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lipemia retinalis
Definition: "A creamy appearance of the retinal blood vessels that occurs when the concentration of lipids in the blood are extremely increased, with pale pink to milky white retinal vessels and altered pale reflexes from choroidal vasculature." [PMID:10379021, PMID:16120862]

Name: Nyctalopia
Definition: "Inability to see well at night or in poor light." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Synophrys
Definition: "Meeting of the medial eyebrows in the midline." [PMID:19125427]

Name: Horizontal nystagmus
Definition: "Nystagmus consisting of horizontal to-and-fro eye movements." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Phthisis bulbi
Definition: "Atrophy of the eyeball with blindness and decreased intraocular pressure due to end-stage intraocular disease." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypodontia
Definition: "The absence of five or less teeth from the normal series by a failure to develop." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017, PMID:31468724]

Name: Carious teeth
Definition: "Caries is a multifactorial bacterial infection affecting the structure of the tooth. This term has been used to describe the presence of more than expected dental caries." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anodontia
Definition: "The absence of all teeth from the normal series by a failure to develop." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017, PMID:31468724]

Name: Macrodontia of permanent maxillary central incisor
Definition: "Increased size of the maxillary central secondary incisor tooth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Abnormality of the incisor
Definition: "An abnormality of the Incisor tooth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Oligodontia
Definition: "The absence of six or more teeth from the normal series by a failure to develop." [PMID:19125428, PMID:31468724]

Name: Dental crowding
Definition: "Changes in alignment of teeth in the dental arch" [PMID:19125428, PMID:31468724]

Name: Taurodontia
Definition: "Increased volume of dental pulp of permanent molar characterized by a crown body-root ratio equal or larger than 1:1 or an elongated pulp chambers and apical displacement of the bifurcation or trifurcation of the roots." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017, PMID:31468724]

Name: Delayed eruption of primary teeth
Definition: "Delayed tooth eruption affecting the primary dentition." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Abnormal dental enamel morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the dental enamel." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Grayish enamel
Definition: "A grey discoloration of the dental enamel." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Delayed eruption of teeth
Definition: "Delayed tooth eruption, which can be defined as tooth eruption more than 2 SD beyond the mean eruption age." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017, PMID:19125428, PMID:31468724]

Name: Hypoplasia of teeth
Definition: "Developmental hypoplasia of teeth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Widely spaced teeth
Definition: "Increased spaces (diastemata) between most of the teeth in the same dental arch." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Dental malocclusion
Definition: "Dental malocclusion refers to an abnormality of the occlusion, or alignment, of the teeth and the way the upper and lower teeth fit together, resulting in overcrowding of teeth or in abnormal bite patterns." [PMID:31468724]

Name: Agenesis of maxillary lateral incisor
Definition: "Agenesis of one or more maxillary lateral incisor, comprising the maxillary lateral primary incisor and maxillary lateral secondary incisor." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Microdontia
Definition: "Decreased size of the teeth, which can be defined as a mesiodistal tooth diameter (width) more than 2 SD below mean. Alternatively, an apparently decreased maximum width of tooth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017, PMID:19125428]

Name: Tooth malposition
Definition: "Abnormal alignment, positioning, or spacing of the teeth, i.e., misaligned teeth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Odontodysplasia
Definition: "The diagnosis odontodysplasia requires clinical and radiological exams, in which unusually large pulp chambers and large pulp room chambers with thin enamel and dentin are visible. It may affect either a single tooth or several teeth. The term regional odontodysplasia is used if several teeth are affected. It affects the deciduous and permanent dentitions in the maxilla, the mandible or both, although the maxilla is more frequently involved. A type of dental dysplasia occurring in dentinogenesis imperfecta in which the pulp chambers are enlarged and there is a reduced amount of coronal dentin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Natal tooth
Definition: "A tooth present at birth or erupting within the first month of life." [PMID:19125428, PMID:31468724]

Name: Delayed eruption of permanent teeth
Definition: "Delayed tooth eruption affecting the secondary dentition." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Conical tooth
Definition: "An abnormal conical form of the teeth, that is, a tooth whose sides converge or taper together incisally." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017, PMID:31468724]

Name: Diastema
Definition: "Increased space between two adjacent teeth in the same dental arch." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Periapical bone loss
Definition: "Radiolucency (reflecting a reduction in the bony substance) around the apex (the tip of the dental root)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Dentinogenesis imperfecta
Definition: "Developmental dysplasia of dentin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Periodontitis
Definition: "Inflammation of the periodontium." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Amelogenesis imperfecta
Definition: "A developmental dysplasia of the dental enamel." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017, PMID:18499550]

Name: Eruption failure
Definition: "A tooth which does not erupt within the teeth eruption timeline and after the loss of eruption potential." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017, PMID:31468724]

Name: Abnormality of the nervous system
Definition: "An abnormality of the nervous system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Atypical behavior
Definition: "An abnormality of mental functioning including various affective, behavioral, cognitive, and perceptual abnormalities." []

Name: Psychosis
Definition: "A condition characterized by changes of personality and thought patterns often accompanied by hallucinations and delusional beliefs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperorality
Definition: "Hyperorality is a condition characterized by an excessive preoccupation with oral sensations and behaviors, such as chewing, sucking, biting, swallowing, and excessive mouthing of objects." [PMID:29112858]

Name: Restlessness
Definition: "A state of unease characterized by diffuse motor activity or motion, subject to limited control, nonproductive, or disorganized behavior." [PMID:28332736]

Name: Emotional lability
Definition: "Unstable emotional experiences and frequent mood changes; emotions that are easily aroused, intense, and/or out of proportion to events and circumstances." [PMID:23902698]

Name: Agitation
Definition: "A state of exceeding restlessness and excessive motor activity associated with mental distress or a feeling of inner tension." [PMID:29630205]

Name: Depression
Definition: "Frequent feelings of being down, miserable, and/or hopeless; difficulty recovering from such moods; pessimism about the future; pervasive shame; feeling of inferior self-worth; thoughts of suicide and suicidal behavior." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:23902698]

Name: Autism
Definition: "Autism is a neurodevelopmental disorder characterized by impaired social interaction and communication, and by restricted and repetitive behavior. Autism begins in childhood. It is marked by the presence of markedly abnormal or impaired development in social interaction and communication and a markedly restricted repertoire of activity and interest. Manifestations of the disorder vary greatly depending on the developmental level and chronological age of the individual (DSM-IV)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6410-0882]

Name: Aggressive behavior
Definition: "Aggressive behavior can denote verbal aggression, physical aggression against objects, physical aggression against people, and may also include aggression towards oneself." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Compulsive behaviors
Definition: "Behavior that consists of repetitive acts that are characterized by the feeling that one 'has to' perform them while one is aware that these acts are not in line with one's overall goal" []

Name: Restrictive behavior
Definition: "Behavior characterized by an abnormal limitation to few interests and activities." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Dementia
Definition: "A loss of global cognitive ability of sufficient amount to interfere with normal social or occupational function. Dementia represents a loss of previously present cognitive abilities, generally in adults, and can affect memory, thinking, language, judgment, and behavior." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Impaired ability to form peer relationships
Autistic behavior
Definition: "Persistent deficits in social interaction and communication and interaction as well as a markedly restricted repertoire of activity and interest as well as repetitive patterns of behavior." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:28879490]

Name: Inflexible adherence to routines
Definition: "A need to strictly adhere to repetitive routines or patterns of behavior which are created by the environment. One becomes upset or distressed when their routines are disrupted or altered." []

Name: Abnormal repetitive mannerisms
Definition: "Use of the same abnormal action in response to certain triggers or at random. They may be used as a way to regulate one's internal state but must otherwise have no apparent functional purpose." []

Name: Disinhibition
Definition: "A lack of restraint manifested in several ways, including disregard for social conventions, impulsivity, and poor risk assessment." [PMID:23902698]

Name: Impaired social interactions
Definition: "Difficulty in social interactions related to an impairment of characteristics such as eye contact, smiling, appropriate facial expressions, and body postures and characterized by difficulty in forming peer relationships and forming friendships." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short attention span
Definition: "Reduced attention span characterized by distractibility and impulsivity." [PMID:26386541]

Name: Irritability
Definition: "A proneness to anger, i.e., a condition of being easily bothered or annoyed." [PMID:27343883]

Name: Hallucinations
Definition: "Perceptions in a conscious and awake state in the absence of external stimuli which have qualities of real perception, in that they are vivid, substantial, and located in external objective space." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Anxiety
Definition: "Intense feelings of nervousness, tenseness, or panic, often in reaction to interpersonal stresses; worry about the negative effects of past unpleasant experiences and future negative possibilities; feeling fearful, apprehensive, or threatened by uncertainty; fears of falling apart or losing control." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:23902698]

Name: Episodic paroxysmal anxiety
Definition: "Recurrent attacks of severe anxiety, whose occurence is not restricted to any particular situation or set of circumstances and is therefore unpredictable." []

Name: Frontal release signs
Definition: "Primitive reflexes traditionally held to be a sign of disorders that affect the frontal lobes." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Low frustration tolerance
Definition: "The feeling of frustration can be defined as an emotional reaction that occurs if a desired goal is not achieved. Frustration intolerance is defined as an age-inappropriate response to frustration characterized by crying or temper tantrums (in children) or aggressive or other undesirable behaviors." [PMID:21461367]

Name: Diminished motivation
Definition: "A reduction in goal-directed behavior, that is, motivation, the determinant of behavior and adaptation that allows individuals to get started, be energized to perform a sustained and directed action." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16030444]

Name: Delusions
Definition: "A false belief that is held despite evidence to the contrary." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Delayed speech and language development
Definition: "A degree of language development that is significantly below the norm for a child of a specified age." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Personality changes
Definition: "An abnormal shift in patterns of thinking, acting, or feeling." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperactivity
Definition: "Hyperactivity is a state of constantly being unusually or abnormally active, including in situations in which it is not appropriate." [PMID:26386541]

Name: Agoraphobia
Definition: "A type of anxiety disorder characterized by avoidance of public places, especially where crowds gather." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal nonverbal communicative behavior
Definition: "Abnormalities in eye contact, communicative facial expressions, gesture use, or use of other's body to communicate. These convey a shared meaning within a culture that replace or supplement verbal communication." [PMID:34981308]

Name: Abnormal peripheral nervous system morphology
Definition: "A structural abnormality of the peripheral nervous system, which is composed of the nerves that lead to or branch off from the central nervous system. This includes the cranial nerves (olfactory and optic nerves are technically part of the central nervous system)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased nerve conduction velocity
Definition: "A reduction in the speed at which electrical signals propagate along the axon of a neuron." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sensory neuropathy
Definition: "Peripheral neuropathy affecting the sensory nerves." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Peripheral axonal degeneration
Definition: "Progressive deterioration of peripheral axons." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal thorax morphology
Definition: "Any abnormality of the thorax (the region of the body formed by the sternum, the thoracic vertebrae and the ribs)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal sternum morphology
Definition: "An anomaly of the sternum, also known as the breastbone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pectus excavatum
Definition: "A defect of the chest wall characterized by a depression of the sternum, giving the chest (\"pectus\") a caved-in (\"excavatum\") appearance." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pectus carinatum
Definition: "A deformity of the chest caused by overgrowth of the ribs and characterized by protrusion of the sternum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the breast
Definition: "An abnormality of the breast." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Gynecomastia
Definition: "Abnormal development of large mammary glands in males resulting in breast enlargement." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal rib morphology
Definition: "An anomaly of the rib." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short ribs
Definition: "Reduced rib length." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Narrow chest
Definition: "Reduced width of the chest from side to side, associated with a reduced distance from the sternal notch to the tip of the shoulder." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the diaphragm
Definition: "Any abnormality of the diaphragm, the sheet of skeletal muscle that separates the thoracic cavity from the abdominal cavity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Congenital diaphragmatic hernia
Definition: "The presence of a hernia of the diaphragm present at birth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal thymus morphology
Definition: "Abnormality of the thymus, an organ located in the upper anterior portion of the chest cavity just behind the sternum and whose main function is to provide an environment for T lymphocyte maturation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplasia of the thymus
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the thymus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal scapula morphology
Definition: "Any abnormality of the scapula, also known as the shoulder blade." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Nephrolithiasis
Definition: "The presence of calculi (stones) in the kidneys." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hematuria
Definition: "The presence of blood in the urine. Hematuria may be gross hematuria (visible to the naked eye) or microscopic hematuria (detected by dipstick or microscopic examination of the urine)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Uric acid nephrolithiasis
Definition: "The presence of uric acid-containing calculi (stones) in the kidneys." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Membranoproliferative glomerulonephritis
Definition: "A type of glomerulonephritis characterized by diffuse mesangial cell proliferation and the thickening of capillary walls due to subendothelial extension of the mesangium. The term membranoproliferative glomerulonephritis is often employed to denote a general pattern of glomerular injury seen in a variety of disease processes that share a common pathogenetic mechanism, rather than to describe a single disease entity" [PMID:19908070]

Name: IgA deposition in the glomerulus
Definition: "The presence of immunoglobulin A deposits in the glomerulus." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:Eurenomics_ewuehl]

Name: Abnormality of the urethra
Definition: "An abnormality of the urethra, i.e., of the tube which connects the urinary bladder to the outside of the body." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Urethral obstruction
Definition: "Obstruction of the flow of urine through the urethra." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Oligozoospermia
Definition: "Reduced count of spermatozoa in the semen, defined as a sperm count below 20 million per milliliter semen." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Renal steatosis
Definition: "Abnormal fat accumulation in the kidneys." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Impotence
Definition: "Inability to develop or maintain an erection of the penis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Renal cortical cysts
Definition: "Cysts of the cortex of the kidney." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:Eurenomics_fschaefer]

Name: Xanthine nephrolithiasis
Definition: "The presence of xanthine-containing calculi (stones) in the kidneys." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Enuresis
Definition: "Lack of the ability to control the urinary bladder leading to involuntary urination at an age where control of the bladder should already be possible." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Penoscrotal hypospadias
Definition: "A severe form of hypospadias in which the urethral opening is located at the junction of the penis and scrotum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Urinary tract atresia
Definition: "Congenital absence of the normal opening of a structure of the urinary tract." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal internal genitalia
Definition: "An anomaly of the adnexa, uterus, and vagina (in female) or seminal tract and prostate (in male)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bicornuate uterus
Definition: "The presence of a bicornuate uterus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypergonadotropic hypogonadism
Definition: "Reduced function of the gonads (testes in males or ovaries in females) associated with excess pituitary gonadotropin secretion and resulting in delayed sexual development and growth delay." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of Krebs cycle metabolism
Definition: "An abnormality of the tricarboxylic acid cycle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Reduced eye contact
Definition: "A reduced frequency or duration of eye contact." []

Name: Abnormality of the endocrine system
Definition: "An abnormality of the endocrine system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Diabetes mellitus
Definition: "A group of abnormalities characterized by hyperglycemia and glucose intolerance." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the thyroid gland
Definition: "An abnormality of the thyroid gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypothyroidism
Definition: "Deficiency of thyroid hormone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypertension
Definition: "The presence of chronic increased pressure in the systemic arterial system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Delayed puberty
Definition: "Passing the age when puberty normally occurs with no physical or hormonal signs of the onset of puberty." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased response to growth hormone stimulation test
Definition: "Insufficient responses to growth hormone (GH) provocation tests. GH deficiency is defined as a serum peak GH concentration less than 10 ng/mL on provocation with a combination of at least two separate stimulation tests." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:25914878]

Name: Hyperinsulinemic hypoglycemia
Definition: "An increased concentration of insulin combined with a decreased concentration of glucose in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Precocious puberty
Definition: "The onset of secondary sexual characteristics before a normal age. Although it is difficult to define normal age ranges because of the marked variation with which puberty begins in normal children, precocious puberty can be defined as the onset of puberty before the age of 8 years in girls or 9 years in boys." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the parathyroid gland
Definition: "An abnormality of the parathyroid gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoparathyroidism
Definition: "A condition caused by a deficiency of parathyroid hormone characterized by hypocalcemia and hyperphosphatemia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anterior hypopituitarism
Definition: "A condition of reduced function of the anterior pituitary gland characterized by decreased secretion of one or more of the pituitary hormones growth hormone, thyroid-stimulating hormone, adrenocorticotropic hormone, prolactin, luteinizing hormone, and follicle-stimulating hormone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Insulin-resistant diabetes mellitus
Definition: "A type of diabetes mellitus related not to lack of insulin but rather to lack of response to insulin on the part of the target tissues of insulin such as muscle, fat, and liver cells. This type of diabetes is typically associated with increases both in blood glucose concentrations as well as in fasting and postprandial serum insulin levels." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:7706500]

Name: Primary hypothyroidism
Definition: "A type of hypothyroidism that results from a defect in the thyroid gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the adrenal glands
Definition: "Abnormality of the adrenal glands, i.e., of the endocrine glands located at the top of the kindneys." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Adrenal hypoplasia
Definition: "Developmental hypoplasia of the adrenal glands." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperthyroidism
Definition: "An abnormality of thyroid physiology characterized by excessive secretion of the thyroid hormones thyroxine (i.e., T4) and/or 3,3',5-triiodo-L-thyronine zwitterion (i.e., triiodothyronine or T3)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased circulating gonadotropin level
Definition: "Overproduction of gonadotropins (FSH, LH) by the anterior pituitary gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Pituitary dwarfism
Definition: "A type of reduced stature with normal proportions related to dysfunction of the pituitary gland related to either an isolated defect in the secretion of growth hormone or to panhypopituitarism, i.e., a deficit of all the anterior pituitary hormones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Adrenogenital syndrome
Definition: "Adrenogenital syndrome is also known as congenital adrenal hyperplasia, which results from disorders of steroid hormone production in the adrenal glands leading to a deficiency of cortisol. The pituitary gland reacts by increased secretion of corticotropin, which in turn causes the adrenal glands to overproduce certain intermediary hormones which have testosterone-like effects." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperactive renin-angiotensin system
Definition: "An abnormally increased activity of the renin-angiotensin system, causing hypertension by a combination of volume excess and vasoconstrictor mechanisms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperinsulinemia
Definition: "An increased concentration of insulin in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperparathyroidism
Definition: "Excessive production of parathyroid hormone (PTH) by the parathyroid glands." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated circulating growth hormone concentration
Definition: "Acromegaly is a condition resulting from overproduction of growth hormone by the pituitary gland in persons with closed epiphyses, and consists chiefly in the enlargement of the distal parts of the body. The circumference of the skull increases, the nose becomes broad, the tongue becomes enlarged, the facial features become coarsened, the mandible grows excessively, and the teeth become separated. The fingers and toes grow chiefly in thickness." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Adrenal insufficiency
Definition: "Insufficient production of steroid hormones (primarily cortisol) by the adrenal glands." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:11443143]

Name: Abnormality of renin-angiotensin system
Definition: "An abnormality of the renin-angiotensin system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased circulating renin level
Definition: "An increased level of renin in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Congenital hypothyroidism
Definition: "A type of hypothyroidism with congenital onset." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pseudohypoparathyroidism
Definition: "A condition characterized by resistance to the action of parathyroid hormone, in which there is hypocalcemia, hyperphosphatemia, and (appropriately) high levels of parathyroid hormone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Goiter
Definition: "An enlargement of the thyroid gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thyroid adenoma
Definition: "The presence of a adenoma of the thyroid gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Insulin resistance
Definition: "Increased resistance towards insulin, that is, diminished effectiveness of insulin in reducing blood glucose levels." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Irregular menstruation
Definition: "Abnormally high variation in the amount of time between periods." [PMID:29323693]

Name: Hyperaldosteronism
Definition: "Overproduction of the mineralocorticoid aldosterone by the adrenal cortex." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Parathyroid hypoplasia
Definition: "Developmental hypoplasia of the parathyroid gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Central diabetes insipidus
Definition: "A form of diabetes insipidus related to a failure of vasopressin (AVP) release from the hypothalamus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the hypothalamus-pituitary axis
Definition: "Abnormality of the pituitary gland (also known as hypophysis), which is an endocrine gland that protrudes from the bottom of the hypothalamus at the base of the brain. The pituitary gland secretes the hormones ACTH, TSH, PRL, GH, endorphins, FSH, LH, oxytocin, and antidiuretic hormone. The secretion of hormones from the anterior pituitary is under the strict control of hypothalamic hormones, and the posterior pituitary is essentially an extension of the hypothalamus, so that hypothalamus and pituitary gland may be regarded as a functional unit." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Secondary hyperparathyroidism
Definition: "Secondary hyperparathyroidism refers to the production of higher than normal levels of parathyroid hormone in the presence of hypocalcemia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19836494]

Name: Increased circulating prolactin concentration
Definition: "The presence of abnormally increased levels of prolactin in the blood. Prolactin is a peptide hormone produced by the anterior pituitary gland that plays a role in breast development and lactation during pregnancy." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Panhypopituitarism
Definition: "A pituitary functional deficit affecting all the anterior pituitary hormones (growth hormone, thyroid-stimulating hormone, follicle-stimulating hormone, luteinizing hormone, adrenocorticotropic hormone, and prolactin)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:12466332]

Name: Hashimoto thyroiditis
Definition: "A chronic, autoimmune type of thyroiditis associated with hypothyroidism." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Diabetes insipidus
Definition: "A state of excessive water intake and hypotonic (dilute) polyuria. Diabetes insipidus may be due to failure of vasopressin (AVP) release (central or neurogenic diabetes insipidus) or to a failure of the kidney to respond to AVP (nephrogenic diabetes insipidus)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Oligomenorrhea
Definition: "Infrequent menses (less than 6 per year or more than 35 days between cycles)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:22594864]

Name: 11 pairs of ribs
Definition: "Presence of only 11 pairs of ribs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short sternum
Definition: "Decreased inferosuperior length of the sternum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplastic scapulae
Definition: "Underdeveloped scapula." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thin ribs
Definition: "Ribs with a reduced diameter." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Broad ribs
Definition: "Increased width of ribs" [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Deformed rib cage
Definition: "Malformation of the rib cage." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cupped ribs
Definition: "Wide, concave rib end." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Horizontal ribs
Definition: "A horizontal (flat) conformation of the ribs, the long curved bones that form the rib cage and normally progressively oblique (slanted) from ribs 1 through 9, then less slanted through rib 12." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal clavicle morphology
Definition: "Any abnormality of the clavicles (collar bones)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Long clavicles
Definition: "Increased length of the clavicles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bifid ribs
Definition: "A bifid rib refers to cleavage of the sternal end of a rib, usually unilateral. Bifid ribs are usually asymptomatic, and are often discovered incidentally by chest x-ray." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bulging of the costochondral junction
Definition: "Abnormal outward curving (protuberance) of the junction of ribs and costal cartilage." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short clavicles
Definition: "Reduced length of the clavicles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lateral clavicle hook
Definition: "An excessive upward convexity of the lateral clavicle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:7322653]

Name: Rib exostoses
Definition: "Multiple circumscribed bony excrescences located in the ribs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Rachitic rosary
Definition: "A row of beadlike prominences at the junction of a rib and its cartilage (i.e., enlarged costochondral joints), resembling a rosary." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:26745253]

Name: Thickened ribs
Definition: "Increased thickness (diameter) of ribs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Rib fusion
Definition: "Complete or partial merging of adjacent ribs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Flaring of rib cage
Definition: "The presence of wide, concave anterior rib ends." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Progressive clavicular acroosteolysis
Definition: "Progressive bone resorption in the distal part of the clavicle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anterior rib cupping
Definition: "Wide, concave anterior rib end." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Flat glenoid fossa
Definition: "Abnormally flat configuration of the glenoid fossa, also known as the glenoid cavity, which is the articular surface of the scapula that articulates with the head of the humerus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:15163819]

Name: Sprengel anomaly
Definition: "A congenital skeletal deformity characterized by the elevation of one scapula (thus, one scapula is located superior to the other)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Posterior rib fusion
Definition: "Complete or partial merging of the posterior part of adjacent ribs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Shield chest
Definition: "A broad chest." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:22368597]

Name: Pectus excavatum of inferior sternum
Definition: "Pectus excavatum (defect of the chest wall characterized by depression of the sternum) affecting primarily the inferior region of the sternum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Broad clavicles
Definition: "Increased width (cross-sectional diameter) of the clavicles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Superior pectus carinatum
Definition: "Pectus carinatum affecting primarily the superior part of the sternum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Scapular exostoses
Definition: "The presence of multiple exostoses on the scapula. An exostosis is a benign growth the projects outward from the bone surface. It is capped by cartilage." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the costochondral junction
Definition: "Any anomaly of the costochondral junction. The costochondral junctions are located between the distal part of the ribs and the costal cartilages, which are bars of hyaline cartilage that connect the ribs to the sternum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Enlargement of the costochondral junction
Definition: "Abnormally increased size of the costochondral junctions, which are located between the distal part of the ribs and the costal cartilages, which are bars of hyaline cartilage that connect the ribs to the sternum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Missing ribs
Definition: "A developmental anomaly with absence of one or more ribs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Posterior rib cupping
Definition: "Wide, concave posterior rib end." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Beaded ribs
Definition: "The presence of a row of multiple rounded expansions (beadlike prominences) at the junction of a rib and its cartilage." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the skeletal system
Definition: "An abnormality of the skeletal system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the vertebral column
Definition: "Any abnormality of the vertebral column." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Platyspondyly
Definition: "A flattened vertebral body shape with reduced distance between the vertebral endplates." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of skeletal maturation
Definition: "The bones of the skeleton undergo a series of characteristic changes in size, shape, and calcification from fetal life until puberty. An abnormality of this process can include delayed or accelerated skeletal maturation, or deviation of some, but not all bones from the expected patterns of maturation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal skull morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the skull, the bony framework of the head which is comprised of the neurocranium (with eight cranial bones) and the viscerocranium (facial skeleton) that comprises fourteen facial bones with the mandible as its largest bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated imprint of the transverse sinuses
Thinning and bulging of the posterior fossa bones
Abnormal posterior cranial fossa morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the fossa cranii posterior (the posterior fossa), which is made up primarily of the occipital bone and which surrounds to the foramen magnum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:25970099, PMID:28295149]

Name: Posterior fossa cyst at the fourth ventricle
Chondrocalcinosis
Definition: "Radiographic evidence of articular calcification that represent calcium pyrophosphate depositions in soft tissue surrounding joints and at the insertions of tendons near joints (Entheses/Sharpey fibers) ." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Thickened cortex of long bones
Definition: "Abnormal thickening of the cortex of long bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Osteopenia
Definition: "Osteopenia is a term to define bone density that is not normal but also not as low as osteoporosis. By definition from the World Health Organization osteopenia is defined by bone densitometry as a T score -1 to -2.5." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:21234807]

Name: Osteoporosis
Definition: "Osteoporosis is a systemic skeletal disease characterized by low bone density and microarchitectural deterioration of bone tissue with a consequent increase in bone fragility. According to the WHO criteria, osteoporosis is defined as a BMD that lies 2.5 standard deviations or more below the average value for young healthy adults (a T-score below -2.5 SD)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:28293453]

Name: Abnormal diaphysis morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the structure or form of the diaphysis, i.e., of the main or mid-section (shaft) of a long bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal metaphysis morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of one or more metaphysis, i.e., of the somewhat wider portion of a long bone that is adjacent to the epiphyseal growth plate and grows during childhood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplastic ilia
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the ilium." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Dumbbell-shaped long bone
Definition: "An abnormal appearance of the long bones with resemblance to a dumbbell, a short bar with a weight at each end. That is, the long bone is shortened and displays flaring (widening) of the metaphyses." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the skin
Definition: "An abnormality of the skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Jaundice
Definition: "Yellow pigmentation of the skin due to bilirubin, which in turn is the result of increased bilirubin concentration in the bloodstream." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperpigmentation of the skin
Definition: "A darkening of the skin related to an increase in melanin production and deposition." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Single transverse palmar crease
Definition: "The distal and proximal transverse palmar creases are merged into a single transverse palmar crease." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125433]

Name: Acanthosis nigricans
Definition: "A dermatosis characterized by thickened, hyperpigmented plaques, typically on the intertriginous surfaces and neck." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1773-4011, PMID:19061584]

Name: Cafe-au-lait spot
Definition: "Cafe-au-lait spots are hyperpigmented lesions that can vary in color from light brown to dark brown with smooth borders and having a size of 1.5 cm or more in adults and 0.5 cm or more in children." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Dry skin
Definition: "Skin characterized by the lack of natural or normal moisture." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sacral dimple
Definition: "A cutaneous indentation resulting from tethering of the skin to underlying structures (bone) of the intergluteal cleft." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:28245993]

Name: Cyanosis
Definition: "Bluish discoloration of the skin and mucosa due to poor circulation or inadequate oxygenation of arterial or capillary blood." [PMID:25658213]

Name: Hyperkeratosis
Definition: "Hyperkeratosis is thickening of the outer layer of the skin, the stratum corneum, which is composed of large, polyhedral, plate-like envelopes filled with keratin which are the dead cells that have migrated up from the stratum granulosum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thin skin
Definition: "Reduction in thickness of the skin, generally associated with a loss of suppleness and elasticity of the skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Eczema
Definition: "Eczema is a form of dermatitis. The term eczema is broadly applied to a range of persistent skin conditions and can be related to a number of underlying conditions. Manifestations of eczema can include dryness and recurring skin rashes with redness, skin edema, itching and dryness, crusting, flaking, blistering, cracking, oozing, or bleeding." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cutis marmorata
Definition: "A reticular discoloration of the skin with cyanotic (reddish-blue appearing) areas surrounding pale central areas due to dilation of capillary blood vessels and stagnation of blood within the vessels. Cutis marmorata generally occurs on the legs, arms and trunk and is often more severe in cold weather." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Hypohidrosis
Definition: "Abnormally diminished capacity to sweat." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Petechiae
Definition: "Petechiae are pinpoint-sized reddish/purple spots, resembling a rash, that appear just under the skin or a mucous membrane when capillaries have ruptured and some superficial bleeding into the skin has happened. This term refers to an abnormally increased susceptibility to developing petechiae." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:29493956]

Name: Ectodermal dysplasia
Definition: "Ectodermal dysplasia is a group of conditions in which there is abnormal development of the skin, hair, nails, teeth, or sweat glands." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Edema
Definition: "An abnormal accumulation of fluid beneath the skin, or in one or more cavities of the body." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anhidrosis
Definition: "Inability to sweat." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal sweat gland morphology
Definition: "Any structural abnormality of the sweat gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Palmoplantar hyperkeratosis
Definition: "Abnormal thickening of the skin localized to the palm of the hand and the sole of the foot." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cutis laxa
Definition: "Wrinkled, redundant, inelastic and sagging skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperextensible skin
Definition: "A condition in which the skin can be stretched beyond normal, and then returns to its initial position." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Hyperhidrosis
Definition: "Abnormal excessive perspiration (sweating) despite the lack of appropriate stimuli like hot and humid weather." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Soft skin
Definition: "Subjective impression of increased softness upon palpation of the skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bruising susceptibility
Definition: "An ecchymosis (bruise) refers to the skin discoloration caused by the escape of blood into the tissues from ruptured blood vessels. This term refers to an abnormally increased susceptibility to bruising. The corresponding phenotypic abnormality is generally elicited on medical history as a report of frequent ecchymoses or bruising without adequate trauma." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Purpura
Definition: "Purpura (from Latin: purpura, meaning \"purple\") is the appearance of red or purple discolorations on the skin that do not blanch on applying pressure. They are caused by bleeding underneath the skin. This term refers to an abnormally increased susceptibility to developing purpura. Purpura are larger than petechiae." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:11515831]

Name: Pallor
Definition: "Abnormally pale skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Palmoplantar keratoderma
Definition: "Abnormal thickening of the skin of the palms of the hands and the soles of the feet." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Atypical scarring of skin
Definition: "Atypically scarred skin ." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Skin rash
Definition: "A red eruption of the skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pruritus
Definition: "Pruritus is an itch or a sensation that makes a person want to scratch. This term refers to an abnormally increased disposition to experience pruritus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Xanthomatosis
Definition: "The presence of multiple xanthomas (xanthomata) in the skin. Xanthomas are yellowish, firm, lipid-laden nodules in the skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cutaneous photosensitivity
Definition: "An increased sensitivity of the skin to light. Photosensitivity may result in a rash upon exposure to the sun (which is known as photodermatosis). Photosensitivity can be diagnosed by phototests in which light is shone on small areas of skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Molluscoid pseudotumors
Definition: "Bluish-grey, spongy nodules associated with scars over pressure points and easily traumatized areas like the elbows and knees." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Melanocytic nevus
Definition: "A oval and round, colored (usually medium-to dark brown, reddish brown, or flesh colored) lesion. Typically, a melanocytic nevus is less than 6 mm in diameter, but may be much smaller or larger." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Facial capillary hemangioma
Definition: "Hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells with small endothelial spaces, occurring in the face." []

Name: Axillary freckling
Definition: "The presence in the axillary region (armpit) of an increased number of freckles, small circular spots on the skin that are darker than the surrounding skin because of deposits of melanin." [PMID:12186179]

Name: Hypertrichosis
Definition: "Hypertrichosis is increased hair growth that is abnormal in quantity or location." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pyoderma
Definition: "Any manifestation of a skin disease associated with the production of pus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of skin pigmentation
Definition: "An abnormality of the pigmentation of the skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Multiple lentigines
Definition: "Presence of an unusually high number of lentigines (singular: lentigo), which are flat, tan to brown oval spots." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lymphedema
Definition: "Localized fluid retention and tissue swelling caused by a compromised lymphatic system." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Hirsutism
Definition: "Abnormally increased hair growth referring to a male pattern of body hair (androgenic hair)." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Telangiectasia
Definition: "Telangiectasias refer to small dilated blood vessels located near the surface of the skin or mucous membranes, measuring between 0.5 and 1 millimeter in diameter. Telangiectasia are located especially on the tongue, lips, palate, fingers, face, conjunctiva, trunk, nail beds, and fingertips." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypopigmentation of the skin
Definition: "A reduction of skin color related to a decrease in melanin production and deposition." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Multiple lipomas
Definition: "The presence of multiple lipomas (a type of benign tissue made of fatty tissue)." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Eruptive xanthomas
Definition: "Eruptive xanthomas are yellow-orange-to-red-brown papules that are often surrounded by an erythematous halo. They appear in crops on the buttocks, extensor surfaces of the extremities, and flexural creases. Acutely, variable amounts of pruritus and pain occur." [PMID:12165227, PMID:22375975]

Name: Angiokeratoma
Definition: "Angiokeratomas are hyperkeratotic papules that are characterized histologically by superficial ectatic (i.e., dilated) blood vessels with epidermal proliferation. Clinically, angiokeratoma presents as a small, raised, dark-red spot." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:8993949]

Name: Prominent superficial veins
Definition: "A condition in which superficial veins (i.e., veins just under the skin) are more conspicuous or noticable than normal." []

Name: Anemic pallor
Definition: "A type of pallor that is secondary to the presence of anemia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal palmar dermatoglyphics
Definition: "An abnormality of the dermatoglyphs, i.e., an abnormality of the patterns of ridges of the skin of palm of hand." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Erythroderma
Definition: "An inflammatory exfoliative dermatosis involving nearly all of the surface of the skin. Erythroderma develops suddenly. A patchy erythema may generalize and spread to affect most of the skin. Scaling may appear in 2-6 days and be accompanied by hot, red, dry skin, malaise, and fever." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Albinism
Definition: "An abnormal reduction in the amount of pigmentation (reduced or absent) of skin, hair and eye (iris and retina)." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Skin dimple over apex of long bone angulation
Urticaria
Definition: "Raised, well-circumscribed areas of erythema and edema involving the dermis and epidermis. Urticaria is intensely pruritic, and blanches completely with pressure." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Soft, doughy skin
Definition: "A skin texture that is unusually soft (and may feel silky), and has a malleable consistency resembling that of dough." []

Name: Hemangioma
Definition: "A hemangioma is a benign tumor characterized by blood-filled spaces lined by benign endothelial cells. A hemangioma characterized by large endothelial spaces (caverns) is called a cavernous hemangioma (in contrast to a hemangioma with small endothelial spaces, which is called capillary hemangioma)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Poikiloderma
Definition: "Poikiloderma refers to a patch of skin with (1) reticulated hypopigmentation and hyperpigmentation, (2) wrinkling secondary to epidermal atrophy, and (3) telangiectasias." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:32363096]

Name: Fragile skin
Definition: "Skin that splits easily with minimal injury." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Subcutaneous lipoma
Definition: "The presence of subcutaneous lipoma." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent distal interphalangeal creases
Definition: "Absence of the distal interphalangeal flexion creases of the fingers." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypermelanotic macule
Definition: "A hyperpigmented circumscribed area of change in normal skin color without elevation or depression of any size." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1773-4011]

Name: Parakeratosis
Definition: "Abnormal formation of the keratinocytes of the epidermis characterized by persistence of nuclei, incomplete formation of keratin, and moistness and swelling of the keratinocytes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Facial erythema
Definition: "Redness of the skin of the face, caused by hyperemia of the capillaries in the lower layers of the skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Intermittent jaundice
Definition: "Jaundice that is sometimes present, sometimes not." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Atopic dermatitis
Definition: "Atopic dermatitis (AD) or atopic eczema is an itchy, inflammatory skin condition with a predilection for the skin flexures. It is characterized by poorly defined erythema with edema, vesicles, and weeping in the acute stage and skin thickening (lichenification) in the chronic stage." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:27904186]

Name: Cavernous hemangioma
Definition: "The presence of a cavernous hemangioma. A hemangioma characterized by large endothelial spaces (caverns) is called a cavernous hemangioma." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent dorsal skin creases over affected joints
Seborrheic dermatitis
Definition: "Seborrheic dermatitis is a form of eczema which is closely related to dandruff. It causes dry or greasy peeling of the scalp, eyebrows, and face, and sometimes trunk." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Nevus flammeus
Definition: "A congenital vascular malformation consisting of superficial and deep dilated capillaries in the skin which produce a reddish to purplish discolouration of the skin." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154, PMID:22483320]

Name: Erysipelas
Definition: "Increased susceptibility to erysipelas, as manifested by a medical history of repeated episodes of erysipelas, which is a superficial infection of the skin, typically involving the lymphatic system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Milia
Definition: "Presence of multiple small cysts containing keratin (skin protein) and presenting as tiny pearly-white bumps just under the surface of the skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia cutis congenita
Definition: "A developmental defect resulting in the congenital absence of skin in multiple or solitary non-inflammatory, well-demarcated, oval or circular ulcers with a diameter of about 1 to 2 cm. Aplasia cutis congenita most commonly occurs on the scalp, but may present in the face, trunk, or limbs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Poor wound healing
Definition: "A reduced ability to heal cutaneous wounds." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pterygium
Definition: "Pterygia are 'winglike' triangular membranes occurring in the neck, eyes, knees, elbows, ankles or digits." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Axillary pterygium
Definition: "Presence of a cutaneous membrane (flap) in the armpit." []

Name: Acne
Definition: "A skin condition in which there is an increase in sebum secretion by the pilosebaceous apparatus associated with open comedones (blackheads), closed comedones (whiteheads), and pustular nodules (papules, pustules, and cysts)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Atypical nevus
Definition: "A large pigmented lesion measuring 5-15 mm in diameter with irregular, notched, and ill defined border and with color that may range from tan to dark brown to pink." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Acrocyanosis
Definition: "Bluish discoloration of the skin of the hands or feet." [PMID:32644593]

Name: Striae distensae
Definition: "Thinned, erythematous, depressed bands of atrophic skin. Initially, striae appear as flattened and thinned, pinkish linear regions of the skin. Striae tend to enlarge in length and become reddish or purplish. Later, striae tend to appear as white, depressed bands that are parallel to the lines of skin tension. Striae distensae occur most often in areas that have been subject to distension such as the lower back, buttocks, thighs, breast, abdomen, and shoulders." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Neurofibroma
Definition: "A benign peripheral nerve sheath tumor that generally appears as a soft, skin-colored papule or small subcutaneous nodule. Individuals with neurofibromatosis can have numerous neurofibromas." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:30969529]

Name: Episodic hyperhidrosis
Definition: "Intermittent episodes of abnormally increased perspiration." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Mottled pigmentation
Definition: "Patchy and irregular skin pigmentation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Angiokeratoma corporis diffusum
Definition: "Angiokeratoma corporis diffusum (ACD) is typically characterized by innumerable small red to black papules which occur in clusters and are situated symmetrically in the bathing trunks area. The number of lesions and the extension of the body increase steadily with time so that generalization and mucosal involvement are common. The single lesion begins with a minute reddish papule which enlarges to up to 10 mm in diameter, becomes dark red to black with a discrete keratotic overgrowth. Histologically, the papules are characterized by superficial dilated capillaries in papillary dermis with epidermal proliferation." []

Name: Thickened skin
Definition: "Laminar thickening of skin." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Cigarette-paper scars
Definition: "Thin (atrophic) and wide scars." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Atypical nevi in non-sun exposed areas
Atrophic scars
Definition: "Scars that form a depression compared to the level of the surrounding skin because of damage to the collagen, fat or other tissues below the skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Biliary tract abnormality
Definition: "An abnormality of the biliary tree." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cholelithiasis
Definition: "Hard, pebble-like deposits that form within the gallbladder." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cholecystitis
Definition: "The presence of inflammatory changes in the gallbladder." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ectopia lentis
Definition: "Dislocation or malposition of the crystalline lens of the eye. A partial displacement (or dislocation) of the lens is described as a subluxation of the lens, while a complete displacement is termed luxation of the lens. A complete displacement occurs if the lens is completely outside the patellar fossa of the lens, either in the anterior chamber, in the vitreous, or directly on the retina. If the lens is partially displaced but still contained within the lens space, then it is termed subluxation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Corneal arcus
Definition: "A hazy, grayish-white ring about 2 mm in width located close to but separated from the limbus (the corneoscleral junction). Corneal arcus generally occurs bilaterally, and is related to lipid deposition in the cornea. Corneal arcus can occur in elderly persons as a part of the aging process but may be associated with hypercholesterolemia in people under the age of 50 years." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Papilledema
Definition: "Papilledema refers to edema (swelling) of the optic disc secondary to any factor which increases cerebral spinal fluid pressure." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Developmental glaucoma
Definition: "Glaucoma which forms during the early years of a child's life is called developmental or congenital glaucoma." []

Name: Brushfield spots
Definition: "The presence of whitish spots in a ring-like arrangement at the periphery of the iris." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Iris atrophy
Definition: "Loss of iris tissue (atrophy)" [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormally large globe
Definition: "Diffusely large eye (with megalocornea) without glaucoma." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent lacrimal punctum
Definition: "No identifiable superior and/or inferior lacrimal punctum." [PMID:19125427]

Name: Optic nerve dysplasia
Definition: "The presence of developmental dysplasia of the optic nerve." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Iridocyclitis
Definition: "A type of anterior uveitis, in which there is Inflammation of the iris and the ciliary body." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Keratoconjunctivitis
Definition: "Inflammation of the cornea and conjunctiva." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Keratoconjunctivitis sicca
Definition: "Dryness of the eye related to deficiency of the tear film components (aqueous, mucin, or lipid), lid surface abnormalities, or epithelial abnormalities. Keratoconjunctivitis sicca often results in a scratchy or sandy sensation (foreign body sensation) in the eyes, and may also be associated with itching, inability to produce tears, photosensitivity, redness, pain, and difficulty in moving the eyelids." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal fundus morphology
Definition: "Any structural abnormality of the fundus of the eye." []

Name: Heterochromia iridis
Definition: "Heterochromia iridis is a difference in the color of the iris in the two eyes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Iritis
Definition: "Inflammation of the iris." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Angioid streaks of the fundus
Definition: "Irregular lines in the deep retina that are typically configured in a radiating fashion and emanate from the optic disc. Angioid streaks are crack-like dehiscences in abnormally thickened and calcified Bruch's membrane, resulting in atrophy of the overlying retinal pigment epithelium. They may be associated with a number of endocrine, metabolic, and connective tissue abnormalities but are frequently idiopathic." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0986-4123, PMID:30844178]

Name: Abnormal macular morphology
Definition: "A structural abnormality of the macula lutea, which is an oval-shaped highly pigmented yellow spot near the center of the retina." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16255686]

Name: Macular hypoplasia
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the macula lutea." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Retinal atrophy
Definition: "Well-demarcated area(s) of partial or complete depigmentation in the fundus, reflecting atrophy of the retinal pigment epithelium with associated retinal photoreceptor loss." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0986-4123]

Name: Periorbital hyperpigmentation
Definition: "Increased pigmentation of the skin in the region surrounding the orbit of the eye." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ocular albinism
Definition: "An abnormal reduction in the amount of pigmentation (reduced or absent) of the iris and retina." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Leber optic atrophy
Definition: "Degeneration of retinal ganglion cells and their axons." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Xanthelasma
Definition: "The presence of xanthomata in the skin of the eyelid." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Posterior polar cataract
Definition: "A polar cataract that affects the posterior pole of the lens." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Macular coloboma
Definition: "A congenital defect of the macula distinct from coloboma associated with optic fissure closure defects. Macular coloboma is characterized by a sharply defined, rather large defect in the central area of the fundus that is oval or round, and coarsely pigmented." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8727-6592, PMID:15069441]

Name: Sudden loss of visual acuity
Definition: "Severe loss of visual acuity within hours or days. This is characteristic of Leber hereditary optic neuropathy." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Juvenile cataract
Definition: "A type of cataract that is not apparent at birth but that arises in childhood or adolescence." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Keratoglobus
Definition: "Limbus-to-limbus corneal thinning, often greatest in the periphery, with globular protrusion of the cornea." [PMID:19667340]

Name: Abnormality of corneal size
Definition: "Any abnormality of the size or morphology of the cornea." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Transient unilateral blurring of vision
Definition: "Transient blurring of vision associated with the aura phase of migraine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cryptophthalmos
Definition: "Cryptophthalmos is a condition of total absence of eyelids and the skin of forehead is continuous with that of cheek, in which the eyeball is completely concealed by the skin, which is stretched over the orbital cavity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125427]

Name: Trichiasis
Definition: "Inversion and rubbing of the eyelashes against the globe of the eye." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Corneal dystrophy
Definition: "The term corneal dystrophy embraces a heterogenous group of bilateral genetically determined non-inflammatory corneal diseases that are restricted to the cornea." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lens subluxation
Definition: "Partial dislocation of the lens of the eye." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Constriction of peripheral visual field
Definition: "An absolute or relative decrease in retinal sensitivity extending from edge (periphery) of the visual field in a concentric pattern. The visual field is the area that is perceived simultaneously by a fixating eye." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0986-4123]

Name: Anterior polar cataract
Definition: "A polar cataract that affects the anterior pole of the lens." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Retinal arteriolar tortuosity
Definition: "The presence of an increased number of twists and turns of the retinal arterioles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Alternating esotropia
Definition: "Esotropia in which either eye may be used for fixation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0986-4123]

Name: Limbal dermoid
Definition: "A benign tumor typically found at the junction of the cornea and sclera (limbal epibullar dermoid)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Severely reduced visual acuity
Definition: "Severe reduction of the ability to see defined as visual acuity less than 6/60 (20/200 in US notation; 0.1 in decimal notation) but at least 3/60 (20/400 in US notation; 0.05 in decimal notation)." [PMID:28779882]

Name: Lenticonus
