Definition: "A nail that is diminished in length and width, i.e., underdeveloped nail." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125433]

Name: Hyperconvex nail
Definition: "When viewed on end (with the digit tip pointing toward the examiner's eye) the curve of the nail forms a tighter curve of convexity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125433]

Name: Anonychia
Definition: "Aplasia of the nail." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short nail
Definition: "Decreased length of nail." [PMID:19125433]

Name: Hypoplastic toenails
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the toenail." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent toenail
Definition: "Congenital absence of the toenail." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Nail pits
Definition: "Small (typically about 1 mm or less in size) depressions on the dorsal nail surface." [PMID:19125433]

Name: Hypoplastic fingernail
Definition: "Underdevelopment of a fingernail." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Onychogryposis
Definition: "Nail that appears thick when viewed on end." [PMID:19125433]

Name: Onycholysis
Definition: "Detachment of the nail from the nail bed." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ridged nail
Definition: "Longitudinal, linear prominences in the nail plate." [PMID:19125433]

Name: Fragile nails
Definition: "Nails that easily break." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Split nail
Definition: "A nail plate that has a longitudinal separation and the two sections of the nail share the same lateral radius of curvature." [PMID:19125433]

Name: Dystrophic toenail
Definition: "Toenail changes apart from changes of the color of the toenail (nail dyschromia) that involve partial or complete disruption of the various keratinous layers of the nail plate." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperconvex fingernails
Definition: "When viewed on end (with the finger tip pointing toward the examiner's eye) the curve of the fingernail forms a tighter curve of convexity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125433]

Name: Deep-set nails
Definition: "Deeply placed nails." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thin nail
Definition: "Nail that appears thin when viewed on end." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125433]

Name: Absent fingernail
Definition: "Absence of a fingernail." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Paronychia
Definition: "The nail disease paronychia is an often-tender bacterial or fungal hand infection or foot infection where the nail and skin meet at the side or the base of a finger or toenail. The infection can start suddenly (acute paronychia) or gradually (chronic paronychia)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Leukonychia
Definition: "White discoloration of the nails." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Broad nail
Definition: "Increased width of nail." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hallux valgus
Definition: "Lateral deviation of the great toe (i.e., in the direction of the little toe)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Weight loss
Definition: "Reduction of total body weight." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Genital tract atresia
Definition: "Congenital occlusion of a tube in the genital tract." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Foot polydactyly
Definition: "A kind of polydactyly characterized by the presence of a supernumerary toe or toes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Postaxial foot polydactyly
Definition: "Polydactyly of the foot most commonly refers to the presence of six toes on one foot. Postaxial polydactyly affects the lateral ray and the duplication may range from a well-formed articulated digit to a rudimentary digit." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short toe
Definition: "A toe that appears disproportionately short compared to the foot." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal metatarsal morphology
Definition: "Abnormalities of the metatarsal bones (i.e. of five tubular bones located between the tarsal bones of the hind- and mid-foot and the phalanges of the toes)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Long foot
Definition: "Increased back to front length of the foot." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Camptodactyly of toe
Definition: "Camptodactyly is a painless flexion contracture of the proximal interphalangeal (PIP) joint that is usually gradually progressive. This term refers to camptodactyly of one or more toes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Broad toe
Definition: "Visible increase in width of the non-hallux digit without an increase in the dorso-ventral dimension." [PMID:19125433]

Name: Rocker bottom foot
Definition: "The presence of both a prominent heel and a convex contour of the sole." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125433]

Name: Split foot
Definition: "A condition in which middle parts of the foot (toes and metatarsals) are missing giving a cleft appearance. The severity is very variable ranging from slightly hypoplastic 3rd toe over absent 2nd or 3rd toes as far as oligo- or monodactyl feet." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Metatarsus adductus
Definition: "The metatarsals are deviated medially (tibially), that is, the bones in the front half of the foot bend or turn in toward the body." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125433]

Name: Preaxial foot polydactyly
Definition: "Duplication of all or part of the first ray." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125433]

Name: Abnormal hallux morphology
Definition: "This term applies for all abnormalities of the big toe, also called hallux." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Overlapping toe
Definition: "Describes a foot digit resting on the dorsal surface of an adjacent digit when the foot is at rest. Initially clawing may be dynamic and only noticeable on walking. Over time the plantar plate tears, subluxation occurs at the metatarsophalangeal joint (MTPJ), and the deformity becomes permanent." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125433]

Name: Long hallux
Definition: "Increased length of the big toe." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Calcaneovalgus deformity
Definition: "This is a postural deformity in which the foot is positioned up against the tibia. The heel (calcaneus) is positioned downward (that is, the ankle is flexed upward), and the heel is turned outward (valgus)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Foot oligodactyly
Definition: "A developmental defect resulting in the presence of fewer than the normal number of toes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the tarsal bones
Definition: "An abnormality of the tarsus are the cluster of seven bones in the foot between the tibia and fibula and the metatarsus, including the calcaneus (heel) bone and the talus (ankle) bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sandal gap
Definition: "A widely spaced gap between the first toe (the great toe) and the second toe." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125433]

Name: Podagra
Definition: "Gout affecting the Metatarsophalangeal joint of big toe." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Short distal phalanx of toe
Definition: "Short distance from the end of the toe to the most distal interphalangeal crease or distal interphalangeal joint flexion point, i.e., abnormally short distal phalanx of toe." [PMID:19125433]

Name: obsolete Acral ulceration and osteomyelitis leading to autoamputation of the digits (feet)
Toe clinodactyly
Definition: "Bending or curvature of a toe in the tibial direction (i.e., towards the big toe)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Clinodactyly of the 5th toe
Definition: "Bending or curvature of a fifth toe in the tibial direction (i.e., towards the big toe)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Autoamputation of foot
Definition: "The spontaneous detachment of a foot from the body due to long standing pathology." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:31633102]

Name: Deep plantar creases
Definition: "The presence of unusually deep creases (ridges/wrinkles) on the skin of sole of foot." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of blood and blood-forming tissues
Definition: "An abnormality of the hematopoietic system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of thrombocytes
Definition: "An abnormality of platelets." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thrombocytopenia
Definition: "A reduction in the number of circulating thrombocytes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of neutrophils
Definition: "A neutrophil abnormality." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:21094463, PMID:26819959]

Name: Neutropenia
Definition: "An abnormally low number of neutrophils in the peripheral blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:25642312]

Name: Pancytopenia
Definition: "An abnormal reduction in numbers of all blood cell types (red blood cells, white blood cells, and platelets)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal erythrocyte morphology
Definition: "Any structural abnormality of erythrocytes (red-blood cells)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hemolytic anemia
Definition: "A type of anemia caused by premature destruction of red blood cells (hemolysis)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal eosinophil morphology
Definition: "An abnormal count or structure of eosinophils." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:23154224]

Name: Eosinophilia
Definition: "Increased count of eosinophils in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Abnormal leukocyte morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of leukocytes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Leukopenia
Definition: "An abnormal decreased number of leukocytes in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Talipes
Definition: "A deformity of foot and ankle that has different subtypes that are talipes equinovarus, talipes equinovalgus, talipes calcaneovarus and talipes calcaneovalgus." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Talipes calcaneovalgus
Definition: "Talipes calcaneovalgus is a flexible foot deformity (as opposed to a rigid congenital vertical talus foot deformity) that can either present as a positional or structural foot deformity depending on severity and/or causality. The axis of calcaneovalgus deformity is in the tibiotalar joint, where the foot is positioned in extreme hyperextension. On inspection, the foot has an \"up and out\" appearance, with the dorsal forefoot practically touching the anterior aspect of the ankle and lower leg." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short 2nd toe
Definition: "Underdevelopment (hypoplasia) of the second toe." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Foot osteomyelitis
Definition: "An infection of bone of the foot." []

Name: Lymphopenia
Definition: "A reduced number of lymphocytes in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Megaloblastic anemia
Definition: "Anemia characterized by the presence of erythroblasts that are larger than normal (megaloblasts)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Autoimmune hemolytic anemia
Definition: "An autoimmune form of hemolytic anemia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal bleeding
Definition: "An abnormal susceptibility to bleeding, often referred to as a bleeding diathesis. A bleeding diathesis may be related to vascular, platelet and coagulation defects." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thrombocytosis
Definition: "Increased numbers of platelets in the peripheral blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Reticulocytopenia
Definition: "A reduced number of reticulocytes in the peripheral blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Normocytic anemia
Definition: "A kind of anemia in which the volume of the red blood cells is normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased red blood cell mass
Definition: "The presence of an increased mass of red blood cells in the circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased hematocrit
Definition: "An elevation above the normal ratio of the volume of red blood cells to the total volume of blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Polycythemia
Definition: "Polycythemia is diagnosed if the red blood cell count, the hemoglobin level, and the red blood cell volume all exceed the upper limits of normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Giant platelets
Definition: "Giant platelets are larger than 7 micrometers and usually 10 to 20 micrometers. The term giant platelet is used when the platelet is larger than the size of the average red cell in the field. (Description adapted from College of American Pathologists, Hematology Manual, 1998)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anemia
Definition: "A reduction in erythrocytes volume or hemoglobin concentration." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Neutropenia in presence of anti-neutropil antibodies
Definition: "A type of neutropenia that is observed in the presence of granulocyte-specific antibodies." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:25642312]

Name: Congenital thrombocytopenia
Definition: "Thrombocytopenia with congenital onset." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thromboembolism
Definition: "The formation of a blood clot inside a blood vessel that subsequently travels through the blood stream from the site where it formed to another location in the body, generally leading to vascular occlusion at the distant site." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplastic anemia
Definition: "Anemia with varying degrees of erythrocytic hypoplasia without leukopenia or thrombocytopenia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Leukemia
Definition: "A cancer of the blood and bone marrow characterized by an abnormal proliferation of leukocytes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, NCIT:C3161]

Name: Abnormal granulocyte morphology
Definition: "Any structural abnormality or abnormal count of granulocytes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal basophil morphology
Definition: "Any structural abnormality or abnormal count of basophils." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:24075190]

Name: Granulocytopenia
Definition: "An abnormally reduced number of granulocytes in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplastic anemia
Definition: "Aplastic anemia is defined as pancytopenia with a hypocellular marrow." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:21239768]

Name: Renal amyloidosis
Definition: "A form of amyloidosis that affects the kidney. On hematoxylin and eosin stain, amyloid is identified as extracellular amorphous material that is lightly eosinophilic. These deposits often stain weakly for periodic acid Schiff (PAS), demonstrate a blue-to-gray hue on the trichrome stain and are typically negative on the Jones methenamine silver (JMS) stain. These tinctorial properties contrast with the histologic appearance of collagen, a major component of basement membranes, mesangial matrix and areas of sclerosis, which demonstrates strong positivity for PAS and JMS (See Figure 1 of PMID:25852856)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:25852856]

Name: Acute kidney injury
Definition: "Sudden loss of renal function, as manifested by decreased urine production, and a rise in serum creatinine or blood urea nitrogen concentration (azotemia)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Renal artery stenosis
Definition: "The presence of stenosis of the renal artery." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Vacuolated lymphocytes
Definition: "The presence of clear, sharply defined vacuoles in the lymphocyte cytoplasm." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20633042]

Name: Reticulocytosis
Definition: "An elevation in the number of reticulocytes (immature erythrocytes) in the peripheral blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sideroblastic anemia
Definition: "Sideroblastic anemia results from a defect in the incorporation of iron into the heme molecule. A sideroblast is an erythroblast that has stainable deposits of iron in cytoplasm (this can be demonstrated by Prussian blue staining)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Acanthocytosis
Definition: "Acanthocytosis is a type of poikilocytosis characterized by the presence of spikes on the cell surface. The cells have an irregular shape resembling many-pointed stars." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of coagulation
Definition: "An abnormality of the process of blood coagulation. That is, altered ability or inability of the blood to clot." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Reduced factor XI activity
Definition: "Decreased activity of coagulation factor XI. Factor XI, also known as plasma thromboplastin antecedent, is a serine proteinase that activates factor IX." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypochromic anemia
Definition: "A type of anemia characterized by an abnormally low concentration of hemoglobin in the erythrocytes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Subcutaneous hemorrhage
Definition: "This term refers to an abnormally increased susceptibility to bruising (purpura, petechiae, or ecchymoses)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Microcytic anemia
Definition: "A kind of anemia in which the volume of the red blood cells is reduced." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Acidosis
Definition: "Abnormal acid accumulation or depletion of base." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:24381489]

Name: Metabolic acidosis
Definition: "Metabolic acidosis (MA) is characterized by a fall in blood pH due to a reduction of serum bicarbonate concentration. This can occur as a result of either the accumulation of acids (high anion gap MA) or the loss of bicarbonate from the gastrointestinal tract or the kidney (hyperchloremic MA). By definition, MA is not due to a respirary cause." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:17936961, PMID:31418093]

Name: Hypoglycemia
Definition: "A decreased concentration of glucose in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fever
Definition: "Body temperature elevated above the normal range." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154, PMID:9759682]

Name: Ketosis
Definition: "Presence of elevated levels of ketone bodies in the body." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:28278308]

Name: Renal tubular acidosis
Definition: "Acidosis owing to malfunction of the kidney tubules with accumulation of metabolic acids and hyperchloremia, potentially leading to complications including hypokalemia, hypercalcinuria, nephrolithiasis and nephrocalcinosis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Alkalosis
Definition: "Depletion of acid or accumulation base in the body fluids." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:24381489]

Name: Respiratory alkalosis
Definition: "Alkalosis due to excess loss of carbon dioxide from the body." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Glucose intolerance
Definition: "Glucose intolerance (GI) can be defined as dysglycemia that comprises both prediabetes and diabetes. It includes the conditions of impaired fasting glucose (IFG) and impaired glucose tolerance (IGT) and diabetes mellitus (DM)." [PMID:29763085]

Name: Diabetic ketoacidosis
Definition: "A type of diabetic metabolic abnormality with an accumulation of ketone bodies." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Recurrent fever
Definition: "Periodic (episodic or recurrent) bouts of fever." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Unexplained fevers
Definition: "Episodes of fever for which no infectious cause can be identified." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Truncal obesity
Definition: "Obesity located preferentially in the trunk of the body as opposed to the extremities." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Polydipsia
Definition: "Excessive thirst manifested by excessive fluid intake." []

Name: Palpitations
Definition: "A sensation that the heart is pounding or racing, which is a non-specific sign but may be a manifestation of arrhythmia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal speech discrimination
Definition: "A type of hearing impairment prominently characterized by a difficulty in understanding speech, rather than an inability to hear speech. Poor speech discrimination is a very common symptom of high frequency hearing loss." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of metatarsal bones
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the metatarsal bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal scalp morphology
Definition: "Any anomaly of the scalp, the skin an subcutaneous tissue of the head on which head hair grows." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal glomerular mesangium morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the mesangium, i.e., of the central part of the renal glomerulus between capillaries." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19470685, PMID:20828589]

Name: Diffuse mesangial sclerosis
Definition: "Diffuse sclerosis of the mesangium, as manifestated by diffuse mesangial matrix expansion." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal tubulointerstitial morphology
Definition: "An abnormality that involves the tubules and interstitial tissue of the kidney." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Tubulointerstitial nephritis
Definition: "A form of inflammation of the kidney affecting the interstitium of the kidneys surrounding the tubules." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypersplenism
Definition: "A malfunctioning of the spleen in which it prematurely destroys red blood cells." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Macrocytic anemia
Definition: "A type of anemia characterized by increased size of erythrocytes with increased mean corpuscular volume (MCV) and increased mean corpuscular hemoglobin (MCH)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19202968]

Name: Autoimmune thrombocytopenia
Definition: "The presence of thrombocytopenia in combination with detection of antiplatelet antibodies." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7744-1790]

Name: Leukocytosis
Definition: "An abnormal increase in the number of leukocytes in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased platelet glycoprotein IIb-IIIa
Definition: "Decreased cell membrane concentration of glycoprotein IIb-IIIa." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7744-1790]

Name: Reduced antithrombin III activity
Definition: "An abnormality of coagulation related to a decreased concentration of antithrombin-III." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal thrombosis
Definition: "Venous or arterial thrombosis (formation of blood clots) of spontaneous nature and which cannot be fully explained by acquired risk (e.g. atherosclerosis)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Extramedullary hematopoiesis
Definition: "The process of hematopoiesis occurring outside of the bone marrow (in the liver, thymus, and spleen) in the postnatal organisms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Megaloblastic bone marrow
Definition: "Abnormal increased number of megaloblasts in the bone marrow." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Schistocytosis
Definition: "The presence of an abnormal number of fragmented red blood cells (schistocytes) in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sea-blue histiocytosis
Definition: "An abnormality of histiocytes, in which the cells take on a sea blue appearance due to abnormally increased lipid content. Histiocytes are a type of macrophage. Sea-blue histiocytes are typically large macrophages from 20 to 60 micrometers in diameter with a single eccentric nucleus whose cytoplasm if packed with sea-blue or blue-green granules when stained with Wright-Giemsa." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:8797061]

Name: Reduced lymphocyte surface expression of CD43
Definition: "A reduction in the expression of CD43 on the cell surface of lymphocytes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoketotic hypoglycemia
Definition: "A decreased concentration of glucose in the blood associated with a reduced concentration of ketone bodies." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperammonemia
Definition: "An increased concentration of ammonia in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Recurrent hypoglycemia
Definition: "Recurrent episodes of decreased concentration of glucose in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Fetal akinesia sequence
Definition: "Decreased fetal activity associated with multiple joint contractures, facial anomalies and pulmonary hypoplasia. Ultrasound examination may reveal polyhydramnios, ankylosis, scalp edema, and decreased chest movements (reflecting pulmonary hypoplasia)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of toe
Definition: "Absence or hypoplasia of toes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Organic aciduria
Definition: "Excretion of non-amino organic acids in urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ketoacidosis
Definition: "Acidosis resulting from accumulation of ketone bodies." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Renal Fanconi syndrome
Definition: "An inability of the tubules in the kidney to reabsorb small molecules, causing increased urinary loss of electrolytes (sodium, potassium, bicarbonate), minerals, glucose, amino acids, and water." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperchloremic acidosis
Definition: "Acidosis (pH less than 7.35) that develops with an increase in ionic chloride." [PMID:29493965]

Name: Chronic metabolic acidosis
Definition: "Longstanding metabolic acidosis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:15882309]

Name: Gout
Definition: "Recurrent attacks of acute inflammatory arthritis of a joint or set of joints caused by elevated levels of uric acid in the blood which crystallize and are deposited in joints, tendons, and surrounding tissues." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Abnormal facial shape
Definition: "An abnormal morphology (form) of the face or its components." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9602-2321]

Name: Short columella
Definition: "Reduced distance from the anterior border of the naris to the subnasale." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Deep philtrum
Definition: "Accentuated, prominent philtral ridges giving rise to an exaggerated groove in the midline between the nasal base and upper vermillion border." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Facial cleft
Definition: "A congenital malformation with a cleft (gap or opening) in the face." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Frontal bossing
Definition: "Bilateral bulging of the lateral frontal bone prominences with relative sparing of the midline." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Potter facies
Definition: "A facial appearance characteristic of a fetus or neonate due to oligohydramnios experienced in the womb, comprising ocular hypertelorism, low-set ears, receding chin, and flattening of the nose." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Morphological central nervous system abnormality
Definition: "A structural abnormality of the central nervous system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the abdominal organs
Definition: "An abnormality of the viscera of the abdomen." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Vomiting
Definition: "Forceful ejection of the contents of the stomach through the mouth by means of a series of involuntary spasmic contractions." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Diarrhea
Definition: "Abnormally increased frequency (usually defined as three or more) loose or watery bowel movements a day." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Dysphagia
Definition: "Difficulty in swallowing." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Nausea and vomiting
Definition: "Nausea is a commonly encountered symptom that has been defined as an unpleasant painless subjective feeling that one will imminently vomit. Vomiting has been defined as the forceful expulsion of the contents of the stomach, duodenum, or jejunum through the oral cavity. While nausea and vomiting are often thought to exist on a temporal continuum, this is not always the case. There are situations when severe nausea may be present without emesis and less frequently, when emesis may be present without preceding nausea." [PMID:26770271]

Name: Nausea
Definition: "A sensation of unease in the stomach together with an urge to vomit." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:26770271]

Name: Constipation
Definition: "Infrequent or difficult evacuation of feces." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Gastroesophageal reflux
Definition: "A condition in which the stomach contents leak backwards from the stomach into the esophagus through the lower esophageal sphincter." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pyloric stenosis
Definition: "Pyloric stenosis, also known as infantile hypertrophic pyloric stenosis, is an uncommon condition in infants characterized by abnormal thickening of the pylorus muscles in the stomach leading to gastric outlet obstruction. Clinically infants are well at birth. Then, at 3 to 6 weeks of age, the infants present with projectile vomiting, potentially leading to dehydration and weight loss." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:32310391]

Name: Anal atresia
Definition: "Congenital absence of the anus, i.e., the opening at the bottom end of the intestinal tract." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Malabsorption
Definition: "Impaired ability to absorb one or more nutrients from the intestine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anal stenosis
Definition: "Abnormal narrowing of the anal opening." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abdominal pain
Definition: "An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) and perceived to originate in the abdomen." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Chronic diarrhea
Definition: "The presence of chronic diarrhea, which is usually taken to mean diarrhea that has persisted for over 4 weeks." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal esophagus morphology
Definition: "A structural abnormality of the esophagus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Esophageal atresia
Definition: "A developmental defect resulting in complete obliteration of the lumen of the esophagus such that the esophagus ends in a blind pouch rather than connecting to the stomach." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Poor suck
Definition: "An inadequate sucking reflex, resulting in the difficult of newborns to be breast-fed." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal rectum morphology
Definition: "An abnormaltiy of the rectum, the final segment of the large intestine that stores solid waste until it passes through the anus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Rectal prolapse
Definition: "Protrusion of the rectal mucous membrane through the anus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hiatus hernia
Definition: "The presence of a hernia in which the upper part of the stomach, i.e., mainly the gastric cardia protrudes through the diaphragmatic esophageal hiatus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Inflammation of the large intestine
Definition: "Inflammation, or an inflammatory state in the large intestine." []

Name: Anorexia
Definition: "A lack or loss of appetite for food (as a medical condition)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Esophageal varix
Definition: "Extreme dilation of the submucusoal veins in the lower portion of the esophagus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Esophageal stricture
Definition: "A pathological narrowing of the esophagus that is caused by the development of a ring of scar tissue that constricts the esophageal lumen." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Zollinger-Ellison syndrome
Definition: "A condition in which there is increased production of gastrin by a gastrin-secreting tumor (usually located in the pancreas, duodenum, or abdominal lymph nodes) that stimulates the gastric mucosa to maximal activity, with consequent gastrointestinal mucosal ulceration." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypothermia
Definition: "Reduced body temperature due to failed thermoregulation." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Heat intolerance
Definition: "The inability to maintain a comfortable body temperature in warm or hot weather." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Malignant hyperthermia
Definition: "Malignant hyperthermia is characterized by a rapid increase in temperature to 39-42 degrees C. Malignant hyperthermia may occur in response to either inhalational anesthetics such as halothane, to muscle relaxants such as succinylcholine, or to exercise." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Renal cortical atrophy
Definition: "Atrophy of the cortex of the kidney." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Proximal renal tubular acidosis
Definition: "A type of renal tubular acidosis characterized by a failure of the proximal tubular cells to reabsorb bicarbonate, leading to urinary bicarbonate wasting and subsequent acidemia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Curved linear dimple below the lower lip
Abnormality of the glabella
Definition: "An abnormality of the glabella." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Prominent glabella
Definition: "Forward protrusion of the glabella." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125436]

Name: Myopathic facies
Definition: "A facial appearance characteristic of myopathic conditions. The face appears expressionless with sunken cheeks, bilateral ptosis, and inability to elevate the corners of the mouth, due to muscle weakness." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cerebral atrophy
Definition: "Atrophy (wasting, decrease in size of cells or tissue) affecting the cerebrum." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Abnormal cerebral morphology
Definition: "Any structural abnormality of the telencephalon, which is also known as the cerebrum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lower limb spasticity
Definition: "Spasticity (velocity-dependent increase in tonic stretch reflexes with increased muscle tone and hyperexcitable tendon reflexes) in the muscles of the lower limbs, hips, and pelvis" [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:UKT_rschuele, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Morphological abnormality of the pyramidal tract
Definition: "Any structural abnormality of the pyramidal tract, whose chief element, the corticospinal tract, is the only direct connection between the brain and the spinal cord. In addition to the corticospinal tract, the pyramidal system includes the corticobulbar, corticomesencephalic, and corticopontine tracts." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Rigidity
Definition: "Continuous involuntary sustained muscle contraction. When an affected muscle is passively stretched, the degree of resistance remains constant regardless of the rate at which the muscle is stretched. This feature helps to distinguish rigidity from muscle spasticity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Spastic gait
Definition: "Spasticity is manifested by increased stretch reflex which is intensified with movement velocity. This results in excessive and inappropriate muscle activation which can contribute to muscle hypertonia. Spastic gait is characterized by manifestations such as muscle hypertonia, stiff knee, and circumduction of the leg." [PMID:25649546]

Name: Gait ataxia
Definition: "A type of ataxia characterized by the impairment of the ability to coordinate the movements required for normal walking. Gait ataxia is characteirzed by a wide-based staggering gait with a tendency to fall." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:UKT_rschuele, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bradykinesia
Definition: "Bradykinesia literally means slow movement, and is used clinically to denote a slowness in the execution of movement (in contrast to hypokinesia, which is used to refer to slowness in the initiation of movement)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bilateral tonic-clonic seizure
Definition: "A bilateral tonic-clonic seizure is a seizure defined by a tonic (bilateral increased tone, lasting seconds to minutes) and then a clonic (bilateral sustained rhythmic jerking) phase." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:28276060]

Name: Limb ataxia
Definition: "A kind of ataxia that affects movements of the extremities." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of extrapyramidal motor function
Definition: "A neurological condition related to lesions of the basal ganglia leading to typical abnormalities including akinesia (inability to initiate changes in activity and perform volitional movements rapidly and easily), muscular rigidity (continuous contraction of muscles with constant resistance to passive movement), chorea (widespread arrhythmic movements of a forcible, rapid, jerky, and restless nature), athetosis (inability to sustain the muscles of the fingers, toes, or other group of muscles in a fixed position), and akathisia (inability to remain motionless)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Chorea
Definition: "Chorea (Greek for 'dance') refers to widespread arrhythmic involuntary movements of a forcible, jerky and restless fashion. It is a random-appearing sequence of one or more discrete involuntary movements or movement fragments. Movements appear random because of variability in timing, duration or location. Each movement may have a distinct start and end. However, movements may be strung together and thus may appear to flow randomly from one muscle group to another. Chorea can involve the trunk, neck, face, tongue, and extremities." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20589866]

Name: Increased neuronal autofluorescent lipopigment
Definition: "Lipofuscin, a generic term applied to autofluorescent lipopigment, is a mixture of protein and lipid that accumulates in most aging cells, particularly those involved in high lipid turnover (e.g., the adrenal medulla) or phagocytosis of other cell types (e g., the retinal pigment epithelium or RPE; macrophage). This term pertains if there is an increase in the neuronal accumulation of lipofuscin (also known as autofluorescent lipoprotein) more than expected for the age of the patient." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:11406682]

Name: Dysdiadochokinesis
Definition: "A type of ataxia characterized by the impairment of the ability to perform rapidly alternating movements, such as pronating and supinating his or her hand on the dorsum of the other hand as rapidly as possible." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:UKB_tklockgether, HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:zaferyueksel, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Migraine
Definition: "Migraine is a chronic neurological disorder characterized by episodic attacks of headache and associated symptoms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:15304572]

Name: Migraine with aura
Definition: "A type of migraine in which there is an aura characterized by focal neurological phenomena that usually proceed, but may accompany or occur in the absence of, the headache. The symptoms of an aura may include fully reversible visual, sensory, and speech symptoms but not motor weakness. Visual symptoms may include flickering lights, spots and lines and/or loss of vision and/or unilateral sensory symptoms such as paresthesias or numbness. At least one of the symptoms of an aura develops gradually over 5 or more minutes and/or different symptoms occur in succession." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:15304572]

Name: Truncal ataxia
Definition: "Truncal ataxia is a sign of ataxia characterized by instability of the trunk. It usually occurs during sitting." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:UKT_rschuele, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplasia of the corpus callosum
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the corpus callosum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:21263138]

Name: Intention tremor
Definition: "A type of kinetic tremor that occurs during target directed movement is called intention tremor. That is, an oscillatory cerebellar ataxia that tends to be absent when the limbs are inactive and during the first part of voluntary movement but worsening as the movement continues and greater precision is required (e.g., in touching a target such as the patient's nose or a physician's finger)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16344298]

Name: Migraine without aura
Definition: "Repeated headache attacks lasting 4-72 h fulfilling at least two of the following criteria: 1) unilateral location, 2) pulsating quality, 3) moderate or severe pain intensity, and 4) aggravation by or causing avoidance of routine physical activity such as climbing stairs. Headache attacks are commonly accompanied by nausea, vomiting, photophobia, or phonophobia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:15304572]

Name: Encephalocele
Definition: "A neural tube defect characterized by sac-like protrusions of the brain and the membranes that cover it through openings in the skull." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Occipital encephalocele
Definition: "A type of encephalocele (that is, a a protrusion of part of the cranial contents including brain tissue through a congenital opening in the cranium, typically covered with skin or mucous membrane) in the occipital region of the skull. Occipital encephalocele presents as a midline swelling over the occipital bone. It is usually covered with normal full-thickness scalp." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2972-5481]

Name: Abnormality of the respiratory system
Definition: "An abnormality of the respiratory system, which include the airways, lungs, and the respiratory muscles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the upper respiratory tract
Definition: "An abnormality of the upper respiratory tract." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal lung morphology
Definition: "Any structural anomaly of the lung." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pneumonia
Definition: "Inflammation of any part of the lung parenchyma." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Restrictive ventilatory defect
Definition: "A functional defect characterized by reduced total lung capacity (TLC) not associated with abnormalities of expiratory airflow or airway resistance. Spirometrically, a restrictive defect is defined as FEV1 (forced expiratory volume in 1 second) and FVC (forced vital capacity) less than 80 per cent. Restrictive lung disease may be caused by alterations in lung parenchyma or because of a disease of the pleura, chest wall, or neuromuscular apparatus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4546-6667, PMID:28194273]

Name: Pulmonary arterial hypertension
Definition: "Pulmonary hypertension is defined mean pulmonary artery pressure of 25mmHg or more and pulmonary capillary wedge pressure of 15mmHg or less when measured by right heart catheterisation at rest and in a supine position." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Dyspnea
Definition: "Difficult or labored breathing. Dyspnea is a subjective feeling only the patient can rate, e.g., on a Borg scale." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16914301]

Name: Respiratory distress
Definition: "Respiratory distress is objectively observable as the physical or emotional consequences from the experience of dyspnea. The physical presentation of respiratory distress is generally referred to as labored breathing, while the sensation of respiratory distress is called shortness of breath or dyspnea." []

Name: Asthma
Definition: "Asthma is characterized by increased responsiveness of the tracheobronchial tree to multiple stimuli, leading to narrowing of the air passages with resultant dyspnea, cough, and wheezing." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Recurrent aspiration pneumonia
Definition: "Increased susceptibility to aspiration pneumonia, defined as pneumonia due to breathing in foreign material, as manifested by a medical history of repeated episodes of aspiration pneumonia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal lung lobation
Definition: "A developmental defect in the formation of pulmonary lobes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pleuritis
Definition: "Inflammation of the pleura." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Abnormal pleura morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the pulmonary pleura, the thin, transparent membrane which covers the lungs and lines the inside of the chest walls." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Apnea
Definition: "Lack of breathing with no movement of the respiratory muscles and no exchange of air in the lungs. This term refers to a disposition to have recurrent episodes of apnea rather than to a single event." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hemoptysis
Definition: "Coughing up (expectoration) of blood or blood-streaked sputum from the larynx, trachea, bronchi, or lungs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pneumothorax
Definition: "Accumulation of air in the pleural cavity leading to a partially or completely collapsed lung." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Spontaneous pneumothorax
Definition: "Pneumothorax occurring without traumatic injury to the chest or lung." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bronchiectasis
Definition: "Persistent abnormal dilatation of the bronchi owing to localized and irreversible destruction and widening of the large airways." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: obsolete Restrictive deficit on pulmonary function testing
Abnormal cerebral ventricle morphology
Definition: "Any structural abnormality of the cerebral ventricles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ventriculomegaly
Definition: "An increase in size of the ventricular system of the brain." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cerebral cortical atrophy
Definition: "Atrophy of the cortex of the cerebrum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Generalized non-motor (absence) seizure
Definition: "A generalized non-motor (absence) seizure is a type of a type of dialeptic seizure that is of electrographically generalized onset. It is a generalized seizure characterised by an interruption of activities, a blank stare, and usually the person will be unresponsive when spoken to. Any ictal motor phenomena are minor in comparison to these non-motor features." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276062, PMID:28276064]

Name: Generalized myoclonic seizure
Definition: "A generalized myoclonic seizure is a type of generalized motor seizure characterised by bilateral, sudden, brief (<100 ms) involuntary single or multiple contraction of muscles or muscle groups of variable topography (axial, proximal limb, distal). Myoclonus is less regularly repetitive and less sustained than is clonus." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276064]

Name: Polymicrogyria
Definition: "Polymicrogyria is a congenital malformation of the cerebral cortex characterized by abnormal cortical layering (lamination) and an excessive number of small gyri (folds)." [http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q90573458, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:24888723]

Name: Abnormal upper motor neuron morphology
Definition: "Any structural anomaly that affects the upper motor neuron." []

Name: Episodic ataxia
Definition: "Periodic spells of incoordination and imbalance, that is, episodes of ataxia typically lasting from 10 minutes to several hours or days." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Porencephalic cyst
Definition: "A cavity within the cerebral hemisphere, filled with cerebrospinal fluid, that communicates directly with the ventricular system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:9279052]

Name: Status epilepticus
Definition: "Status epilepticus is a type of prolonged seizure resulting either from the failure of the mechanisms responsible for seizure termination or from the initiation of mechanisms which lead to abnormally prolonged seizures (after time point t1). It is a condition that can have long-term consequences (after time point t2), including neuronal death, neuronal injury, and alteration of neuronal networks, depending on the type and duration of seizures." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1735-8178, PMID:26336950, PMID:28276060]

Name: Abnormal basal ganglia morphology
Definition: "Abnormality of the basal ganglia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Basal ganglia calcification
Definition: "The presence of calcium deposition affecting one or more structures of the basal ganglia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Broad-based gait
Definition: "An abnormal gait pattern in which persons stand and walk with their feet spaced widely apart. This is often a component of cerebellar ataxia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Subarachnoid hemorrhage
Definition: "Hemorrhage occurring between the arachnoid mater and the pia mater." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Arrhinencephaly
Definition: "A defect of development of the brain characterized by congenital absence of the part of the brain that includes the olfactory bulbs, tracts, and other structures associated with the sense of smell." []

Name: Ischemic stroke
Definition: "Acute ischemic stroke (AIS) is defined by the sudden loss of blood flow to an area of the brain with the resulting loss of neurologic function. It is caused by thrombosis or embolism that occludes a cerebral vessel supplying a specific area of the brain. During a vessel occlusion, there is a core area where damage to the brain is irreversible and an area of penumbra where the brain has lost function owing to decreased blood flow but is not irreversibly injured." [PMID:32054610]

Name: Abnormal spinal cord morphology
Definition: "A structural abnormality of the spinal cord (myelon)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Tethered cord
Definition: "During normal embryological development, the spinal cord first occupies the entire length of the vertebral column but goes on to assume a position at the level of L1 due to differential growth of the conus medullaris and the vertebral column. The filum terminale is a slender, threadlike structure that remains after the normal regression of the distal embryonic spinal cord and attaches the spinal cord to the coccyx. A tethered cord results if there is a thickened rope-like filum terminale which anchors the cord at the level of L2 or below, potentially causing neurologic signs owing to abnormal tension on the spinal cord." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Frontotemporal dementia
Definition: "A dementia associated with degeneration of the frontotemporal lobe and clinically associated with personality and behavioral changes such as disinhibition, apathy, and lack of insight. The hallmark feature of frontotemporal dementia is the presentation with focal syndromes such as progressive language dysfunction, or aphasia, or behavioral changes characteristic of frontal lobe disorders." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:24966676]

Name: Hypophosphatemia
Definition: "An abnormally decreased phosphate concentration in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Hyperuricemia
Definition: "An abnormally high level of uric acid in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased serum lactate
Definition: "Abnormally increased level of blood lactate (2-hydroxypropanoic acid). Lactate is produced from pyruvate by lactate dehydrogenase during normal metabolism. The terms lactate and lactic acid are often used interchangeably but lactate (the component measured in blood) is strictly a weak base whereas lactic acid is the corresponding acid. Lactic acidosis is often used clinically to describe elevated lactate but should be reserved for cases where there is a corresponding acidosis (pH below 7.35)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:24079682]

Name: Hyperproteinemia
Definition: "An increased concentration of proteins in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Hyperkalemia
Definition: "An abnormally increased potassium concentration in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperglycinemia
Definition: "An elevated concentration of glycine in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti, PMID:16902722, PMID:4696900]

Name: Hypertriglyceridemia
Definition: "An abnormal increase in the level of triglycerides in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Homocystinuria
Definition: "An increased concentration of homocystine in the urine." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Azotemia
Definition: "An increased concentration of nitrogen compounds in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Heparan sulfate excretion in urine
Definition: "An increased concentration of heparan sulfates in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperhomocystinemia
Definition: "An increased concentration of homocystine in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Hyperlysinemia
Definition: "An increased concentration of lysine in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti, PMID:4696900]

Name: Low posterior hairline
Definition: "Hair on the neck extends more inferiorly than usual." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Nail dysplasia
Definition: "The presence of developmental dysplasia of the nail." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pterygium of nails
Definition: "Inward advance of skin over the nail plate." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Impaired vibration sensation in the lower limbs
Definition: "A decrease in the ability to perceive vibration in the legs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of speech or vocalization
Definition: "Abnormalities in the sound of a person's speech or vocalization not necessarily associated with a known physical cause or due to stuttering or stammering." []

Name: Scanning speech
Definition: "An abnormal pattern of speech in which the words are as if measured or scanned; there is a pause after every syllable, and the syllables themselves are pronounced slowly." [PMID:16247074]

Name: Clonus
Definition: "A series of rhythmic and involuntary muscle contractions (at a frequency of about 5 to 7 Hz) that occur in response to an abruptly applied and sustained stretch." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Intracranial hemorrhage
Definition: "Hemorrhage occurring within the skull." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Gliosis
Definition: "Gliosis is the focal proliferation of glial cells in the central nervous system." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Postural instability
Definition: "A tendency to fall or the inability to keep oneself from falling; imbalance. The retropulsion test is widely regarded as the gold standard to evaluate postural instability, Use of the retropulsion test includes a rapid balance perturbation in the backward direction, and the number of balance correcting steps (or total absence thereof) is used to rate the degree of postural instability. Healthy subjects correct such perturbations with either one or two large steps, or without taking any steps, hinging rapidly at the hips while swinging the arms forward as a counterweight. In patients with balance impairment, balance correcting steps are often too small, forcing patients to take more than two steps. Taking three or more steps is generally considered to be abnormal, and taking more than five steps is regarded as being clearly abnormal. Markedly affected patients continue to step backward without ever regaining their balance and must be caught by the examiner (this would be called true retropulsion). Even more severely affected patients fail to correct entirely, and fall backward like a pushed toy soldier, without taking any corrective steps." [PMID:25613349]

Name: Postural tremor
Definition: "A type of tremors that is triggered by holding a limb in a fixed position." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Spinal cord compression
Definition: "External mechanical compression of the spinal cord." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Neurodegeneration
Definition: "Progressive loss of neural cells and tissue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cerebral edema
Definition: "Abnormal accumulation of fluid in the brain." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Phonophobia
Definition: "An abnormally heightened sensitivity to loud sounds." []

Name: Neurofibrillary tangles
Definition: "Pathological protein aggregates formed by hyperphosphorylation of a microtubule-associated protein known as tau, causing it to aggregate in an insoluble form." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Apraxia
Definition: "A defect in the understanding of complex motor commands and in the execution of certain learned movements, i.e., deficits in the cognitive components of learned movements." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:34033988]

Name: Intellectual disability, profound
Definition: "Profound mental retardation is defined as an intelligence quotient (IQ) below 20." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Delayed CNS myelination
Definition: "Delayed myelination in the central nervous system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Choroid plexus cyst
Definition: "A cyst occurring within the choroid plexus within a cerebral ventricle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Progressive spasticity
Definition: "Spasticity that increases in degree with time." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pseudobulbar behavioral symptoms
Definition: "Individuals with Pseudobulbar signs often also demonstrate abnormal behavioral symptoms such as inappropriate emotional outbursts of uncontrolled laughter or weeping etc." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Delayed gross motor development
Definition: "A type of motor delay characterized by a delay in acquiring the ability to control the large muscles of the body for walking, running, sitting, and crawling." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Dysgenesis of the cerebellar vermis
Definition: "Defective development of the vermis of cerebellum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Generalized-onset seizure
Definition: "A generalized-onset seizure is a type of seizure originating at some point within, and rapidly engaging, bilaterally distributed networks. The networks may include cortical and subcortical structures but not necessarily the entire cortex." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20196795, PMID:23739099, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276064, PMID:6790275]

Name: Dilated fourth ventricle
Definition: "An abnormal dilatation of the fourth cerebral ventricle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pseudobulbar signs
Definition: "Pseudobulbar signs result from injury to an upper motor neuron lesion to the corticobulbar pathways in the pyramidal tract. Patients have difficulty chewing, swallowing and demonstrate slurred speech (often initial presentation) as well as abnormal behavioral symptoms such as inappropriate emotional outbursts of uncontrolled laughter or weeping etc." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Pleural effusion
Definition: "The presence of an excessive amount of fluid in the pleural cavity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Respiratory paralysis
Definition: "Inability to move the muscles of respiration." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pulmonary embolism
Definition: "An embolus (that is, an abnormal particle circulating in the blood) located in the pulmonary artery and thereby blocking blood circulation to the lung. Usually the embolus is a blood clot that has developed in an extremity (for instance, a deep venous thrombosis), detached, and traveled through the circulation before becoming trapped in the pulmonary artery." []

Name: Recurrent respiratory infections
Definition: "An increased susceptibility to respiratory infections as manifested by a history of recurrent respiratory infections." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pulmonary fibrosis
Definition: "Replacement of normal lung tissues by fibroblasts and collagen." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_tkuijpers, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Diffuse reticular or finely nodular infiltrations
Coarse hair
Definition: "Hair shafts are rough in texture." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sparse scalp hair
Definition: "Decreased number of hairs per unit area of skin of the scalp." [PMID:19125436, PMID:28061825]

Name: White forelock
Definition: "A triangular depigmented region of white hairs located in the anterior midline of the scalp." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fine hair
Definition: "Hair that is fine or thin to the touch." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sparse axillary hair
Definition: "Reduced number or density of axillary hair." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Premature graying of hair
Definition: "Development of gray hair at a younger than normal age." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Slow-growing hair
Definition: "Hair whose growth is slower than normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Silver-gray hair
Definition: "Hypopigmented hair that appears silver-gray." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Facial hypertrichosis
Definition: "Excessive, increased hair growth located in the facial region." []

Name: Melanin pigment aggregation in hair shafts
Absent axillary hair
Definition: "Absence of axillary hair." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent eyebrow
Definition: "Absence of the eyebrow." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Woolly hair
Definition: "The term woolly hair refers to an abnormal variant of hair that is fine, with tightly coiled curls, and often hypopigmented. Optical microscopy may reveal the presence of tight spirals and a clear diameter reduction as compared with normal hair. Electron microscopy may show flat, oval hair shafts with reduced transversal diameter." [PMID:20464096]

Name: Sparse pubic hair
Definition: "Reduced number or density of pubic hair." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: White eyebrow
Definition: "White color (lack of pigmentation) of the eyebrow." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: White eyelashes
Definition: "White color (lack of pigmentation) of the eyelashes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1773-4011]

Name: Generalized hirsutism
Definition: "Abnormally increased hair growth over much of the entire body." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sparse body hair
Definition: "Sparseness of the body hair." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Patchy alopecia
Definition: "Transient, non-scarring hair loss and preservation of the hair follicle located in in well-defined patches." []

Name: Early balding
Definition: "Loss of scalp hair at an earlier than normal age." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pili canaliculi
Definition: "A characteristic triangular, kidney- or heat-shaped diameter of hair shafts with typical longitudinal canalicular deformation as observable by scanning electron microscopy." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:8274794]

Name: Frontal upsweep of hair
Definition: "Upward and/or sideward growth of anterior hair." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Gastrointestinal hemorrhage
Definition: "Hemorrhage affecting the gastrointestinal tract." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hepatomegaly
Definition: "Abnormally increased size of the liver." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal intestine morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the intestine. The closely related term enteropathy is used to refer to any disease of the intestine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Protein-losing enteropathy
Definition: "Abnormal loss of protein from the digestive tract related to excessive leakage of plasma proteins into the lumen of the gastrointestinal tract." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal small intestine morphology
Definition: "A structural abnormality of the small intestine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Meckel diverticulum
Definition: "Meckel's diverticulum is a congenital diverticulum located in the distal ileum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal duodenum morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the duodenum, i.e., the first section of the small intestine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Duodenal atresia
Definition: "A developmental defect resulting in complete obliteration of the duodenal lumen, that is, an abnormal closure of the duodenum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hematemesis
Definition: "The vomiting of blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Melena
Definition: "The passage of blackish, tarry feces associated with gastrointestinal hemorrhage. Melena occurs if the blood remains in the colon long enough for it to be broken down by colonic bacteria. One degradation product, hematin, imbues the stool with a blackish color. Thus, melena generally occurs with bleeding from the upper gastrointestinal tract (e.g., stomach ulcers or duodenal ulcers), since the blood usually remains in the gut for a longer period of time than with lower gastrointestinal bleeding." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal large intestine morphology
Definition: "Any abnormality of the large intestine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aganglionic megacolon
Definition: "An abnormality resulting from a lack of intestinal ganglion cells (i.e., an aganglionic section of bowel) that results in bowel obstruction with enlargement of the colon." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:17965226]

Name: Colonic diverticula
Definition: "The presence of multiple diverticula of the colon." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Intermittent diarrhea
Definition: "Repeated episodes of diarrhea separated by periods without diarrhea." []

Name: Chronic rhinitis
Definition: "Chronic inflammation of the nasal mucosa." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Exaggerated cupid's bow
Definition: "More pronounced paramedian peaks and median notch of the Cupid's bow." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Focal clonic seizure
Definition: "A focal clonic seizure is a type of focal motor seizure characterized by sustained rhythmic jerking, that is regularly repetitive." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1735-8178, PMID:11580774, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276064]

Name: Exaggerated startle response
Definition: "An exaggerated startle reaction in response to a sudden unexpected visual or acoustic stimulus, or a quick movement near the face." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Paroxysmal dystonia
Definition: "A form of dystonia characterized by episodes of dystonia (often hemidystonia or generalized) lasting from minutes to hours. There are no dystonic symptoms between episodes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of neuronal migration
Definition: "An abnormality resulting from an anomaly of neuronal migration, i.e., of the process by which neurons travel from their origin to their final position in the brain." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the autonomic nervous system
Definition: "An abnormality of the autonomic nervous system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Tetraparesis
Definition: "Weakness of all four limbs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Horner syndrome
Definition: "An abnormality resulting from a lesion of the sympathetic nervous system characterized by a combination of unilateral ptosis, miosis, and often ipsilateral hypohidrosis and conjunctival injection." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Enlarged cisterna magna
Definition: "Increase in size of the cisterna magna, one of three principal openings in the subarachnoid space between the arachnoid and pia mater, located between the cerebellum and the dorsal surface of the medulla oblongata." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Gray matter heterotopia
Definition: "Heterotopia or neuronal heterotopia are macroscopic clusters of misplaced neurons (gray matter), most often situated along the ventricular walls or within the subcortical white matter." [http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q90573458, https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432, PMID:22427329, PMID:25180909, PMID:7524438]

Name: Global brain atrophy
Definition: "Unlocalized atrophy of the brain with decreased total brain matter volume and increased ventricular size." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Fair hair
Definition: "A lesser degree of hair pigmentation than would otherwise be expected." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1773-4011]

Name: Progressive alopecia
Definition: "Progressive loss of hair." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Alopecia universalis
Definition: "Loss of all hair on the entire body." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Poliosis
Definition: "Circumscribed depigmentation of the hair of the head or the eyelashes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Frontal balding
Definition: "Absence of hair in the anterior midline and/or parietal areas." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Progressive hypotrichosis
Definition: "Progressively reduced or lacking hair growth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Brittle hair
Definition: "Fragile, easily breakable hair, i.e., with reduced tensile strength." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1773-4011]

Name: Hemiplegia
Definition: "Paralysis (complete loss of muscle function) in the arm, leg, and in some cases the face on one side of the body." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Akinesia
Definition: "Inability to initiate changes in activity or movement and to perform ordinary volitional movements rapidly and easily." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Athetosis
Definition: "A slow, continuous, involuntary writhing movement that prevents maintenance of a stable posture. Athetosis involves continuous smooth movements that appear random and are not composed of recognizable sub-movements or movement fragments. In contrast to chorea, in athetosis, the same regions of the body are repeatedly involved. Athetosis may worsen with attempts at movement of posture, but athetosis can also occur at rest." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20589866]

Name: Drooling
Definition: "Habitual flow of saliva out of the mouth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:15202698]

Name: Chiari malformation
Definition: "Chiari malformation consists of a downward displacement of the cerebellar tonsils and the medulla through the foramen magnum, sometimes causing hydrocephalus as a result of obstruction of CSF outflow." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:28613730]

Name: Clumsiness
Definition: "Lack of physical coordination resulting in an abnormal tendency to drop items or bump into objects." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Degeneration of the lateral corticospinal tracts
Definition: "Deterioration of the tissues of the lateral corticospinal tracts." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Headache
Definition: "Cephalgia, or pain sensed in various parts of the head, not confined to the area of distribution of any nerve." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:15304572]

Name: Vertigo
Definition: "An abnormal sensation of spinning while the body is actually stationary." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Resting tremor
Definition: "A resting tremor occurs when muscles are at rest and becomes less noticeable or disappears when the affected muscles are moved. Resting tremors are often slow and coarse." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:22675666]

Name: Anencephaly
Definition: "Anencephaly is a developmental anomaly characterized by a fetus that has no calvarium, with a lack of most or all of the fetus' brain tissue. Anencephaly belongs to a collective group known as neural tube defects (NTD) and is a result of the neural tube failing to close in its rostral end during fetal development." [PMID:31424828, PMID:32706613]

Name: Hydranencephaly
Definition: "A defect of development of the brain characterized by replacement of greater portions of the cerebral hemispheres and the corpus striatum by cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) and glial tissue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Drowsiness
Definition: "Excessive daytime sleepiness." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Paroxysmal drowsiness
Definition: "Attacks of disabling daytime drowsiness and low alertness." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Recurrent paroxysmal headache
Definition: "Repeated episodes of headache with rapid onset, reaching a peak within minutes and of short duration (less than one hour) with pain that is throbbing, pulsating, or bursting in quality." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lack of peer relationships
Definition: "The state of not having relationships with peers outside of school or organized activity appropriate to developmental level. This may be caused by behavioral or physical barriers." []

Name: Motor deterioration
Definition: "Loss of previously present motor (i.e., movement) abilities." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal cerebellar vermis morphology
Definition: "An anomaly of the vermis of cerebellum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Agenesis of cerebellar vermis
Definition: "Congenital absence of the vermis of cerebellum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal caudate nucleus morphology
Definition: "Any structural abnormality of the caudate nucleus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cervical cord compression
Definition: "Compression of the spinal cord in the cervical region, generally manifested by paresthesias and numbness, weakness, difficulty walking, abnormalities of coordination, and neck pain or stiffness." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Intellectual disability, moderate
Definition: "Moderate mental retardation is defined as an intelligence quotient (IQ) in the range of 35-49." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Normal pressure hydrocephalus
Definition: "A form of hydrocephalus characterized by enlarged cerebral ventricles and normal cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) pressure upon lumbar puncture." [eMedicine:1135286, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Action tremor
Definition: "A tremor present when the limbs are active, either when outstretched in a certain position or throughout a voluntary movement." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Head tremor
Definition: "An unintentional, oscillating to-and-fro muscle movement affecting head movement." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Focal aware seizure
Definition: "A type of focal-onset seizure in which awareness is preserved. Awareness during a seizure is defined as the patient being fully aware of themself and their environment throughout the seizure, even if immobile." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1735-8178, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276062, PMID:28276064]

Name: Leukoencephalopathy
Definition: "This term describes abnormality of the white matter of the cerebrum resulting from damage to the myelin sheaths of nerve cells." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: EEG abnormality
Definition: "Abnormality observed by electroencephalogram (EEG), which is used to record of the brain's spontaneous electrical activity from multiple electrodes placed on the scalp." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Memory impairment
Definition: "An impairment of memory as manifested by a reduced ability to remember things such as dates and names, and increased forgetfulness." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Difficulty walking
Definition: "Reduced ability to walk (ambulate)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Writer's cramp
Definition: "A focal dystonia of the fingers, hand, and/or forearm that appears when the affected person attempts to do a task that requires fine motor movements such as writing or playing a musical instrument." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sleep disturbance
Definition: "An abnormality of sleep including such phenomena as 1) insomnia/hypersomnia, 2) non-restorative sleep, 3) sleep schedule disorder, 4) excessive daytime somnolence, 5) sleep apnea, and 6) restlessness." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Psychomotor deterioration
Definition: "Loss of previously present mental and motor abilities." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Shuffling gait
Definition: "A type of gait (walking) characterized by by dragging one's feet along or without lifting the feet fully from the ground." []

Name: Abnormal brainstem morphology
Definition: "An anomaly of the brainstem." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplasia of the brainstem
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the brainstem." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal lower motor neuron morphology
Definition: "Any structural anomaly of the lower motor neuron." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Visual hallucinations
Definition: "Visual perceptions that are not elicited by a corresponding stimulus from the outside world." []

Name: Normal interictal EEG
Definition: "Lack of observable abnormal electroencephalographic (EEG) patterns in an individual with a history of seizures. About half of individuals with epilepsy show interictal epileptiform discharges upon the first investigation. The yield can be increased by repeated studies, sleep studies, or by ambulatory EEG recordings over 24 hours. Normal interictal EEG is a sign that can be useful in the differential diagnosis." []

Name: Febrile seizure (within the age range of 3 months to 6 years)
Definition: "A febrile seizure is any type of seizure (most often a generalized tonic-clonic seizure) occurring with fever (at least 38 degrees Celsius) but in the absence of central nervous system infection, severe metabolic disturbance or other alternative precipitant in children between the ages of 3 months and 6 years." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:10353950, PMID:19125841, PMID:30078767, PMID:6779259]

Name: Hypokinesia
Definition: "Abnormally diminished motor activity. In contrast to paralysis, hypokinesia is not characterized by a lack of motor strength, but rather by a poverty of movement. The typical habitual movements (e.g., folding the arms, crossing the legs) are reduced in frequency." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Developmental regression
Definition: "Loss of developmental skills, as manifested by loss of developmental milestones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6410-0882]

Name: Hand tremor
Definition: "An unintentional, oscillating to-and-fro muscle movement affecting the hand." []

Name: Fasciculations
Definition: "Fasciculations are observed as small, local, involuntary muscle contractions (twitching) visible under the skin.
