Definition: "One or more abnormally short long bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Mesomelia
Definition: "Shortening of the middle parts of the limbs (forearm and lower leg) in relation to the upper and terminal segments." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Abnormality of the ankle
Definition: "An anomaly of the joint that connects the foot with the leg." []

Name: Ulnar bowing
Definition: "Bending of the diaphysis (shaft) of the ulna." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Diaphyseal sclerosis
Definition: "An elevation in bone density in one or more diaphyses. Sclerosis is normally detected on a radiograph as an area of increased opacity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Enlarged joints
Definition: "Increase in size of one or more joints." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fibular hypoplasia
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the fibula." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Humeroradial synostosis
Definition: "An abnormal osseous union (fusion) between the radius and the humerus." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Elbow dislocation
Definition: "Dislocation of the distal humerus out of the elbow joint, where the radius, ulna, and humerus meet." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal shoulder morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the shoulder, which is defined as the structures surrounding the shoulder joint where the humerus attaches to the scapula." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Shoulder flexion contracture
Definition: "Chronic reduction in active and passive mobility of the shoulder joint due to structural changes in muscle, tendons, ligaments, or skin that prevents normal movement." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal patella morphology
Definition: "Abnormality of the patella (knee cap)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Radial head subluxation
Definition: "Partial dislocation of the head of the radius." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Enlarged metaphyses
Definition: "Abnormal increase in size of one or more metaphyses." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Tetraamelia
Definition: "Amelia of all four limbs." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Abnormality of the humerus
Definition: "An abnormality of the humerus (i.e., upper arm bone)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Patellar hypoplasia
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the patella." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Limited knee extension
Definition: "Reduced ability to extend (straighten) the knee joint." []

Name: Madelung deformity
Definition: "An anomaly related to partial closure, or failure of development of the ulnar side of the distal radial growth plate, which results in an arrest of epiphyseal growth of the medial and volar portions of the distal radius. This leads to shortening of the radius and relative overgrowth of the ulna." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:12362035]

Name: Flattened epiphysis
Definition: "Abnormal flatness (decreased height) of epiphyses." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypercalcemia
Definition: "An abnormally increased calcium concentration in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoalbuminemia
Definition: "Reduction in the concentration of albumin in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperglycemia
Definition: "An increased concentration of glucose in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoproteinemia
Definition: "A decreased concentration of protein in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Glycosuria
Definition: "An increased concentration of glucose in the urine." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Hyperlipidemia
Definition: "An elevated lipid concentration in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Defective DNA repair after ultraviolet radiation damage
Hydroxyprolinuria
Definition: "An increased concentration of 4-hydroxy-L-proline in the urine." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Increased urinary potassium
Definition: "An increased concentration of potassium(1+) in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Dislocated radial head
Definition: "A dislocation of the head of the radius from its socket in the elbow joint." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fractures of the long bones
Definition: "An increased tendency to fractures of the long bones (Mainly, the femur, tibia, fibula, humerus, radius, and ulna)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Long fibula
Definition: "Disproportionately long fibulae." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Acromesomelia
Definition: "Small hands and feet." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:22286749]

Name: Hypoplasia of the capital femoral epiphysis
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the proximal epiphysis of the femur." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Trophic limb changes
Definition: "Trophic changes occurring in a limb." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Limited hip extension
Definition: "Limitation of the extension of the hip, i.e., decreased ability to straighten the hip joint and thereby increase the angle between torso and thigh; moving the thigh or top of the pelvis backward." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short femur
Definition: "An abnormal shortening of the femur." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fibular overgrowth
Definition: "Relatively increased growth of the fibula compared to that of the tibia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:17259417]

Name: Slender long bone
Definition: "Reduced diameter of a long bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased carrying angle
Definition: "An abnormal increase in the carrying angle, which is the angle he long axis of the extended forearm as it lies lateral to the long axis of the arm." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:18506557]

Name: Abnormal cortical bone morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of compact bone (also known as cortical bone), which forms the dense surface of bones." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Protuberances at ends of long bones
Definition: "The presence of multiple protuberances (bulges, or knobs) at the ends of the long bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Subperiosteal bone resorption
Definition: "Loss of bone mass occurring beneath the periosteum (the periosteum is the connective-tissue membrane that surrounds all bones except at the articular surfaces). This process may create a serrated and lace-like appearance in periosteal cortical bone." [PMID:24849102]

Name: Abnormal circulating cholesterol concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of cholesterol in the blood circulation." []

Name: Hyperglycinuria
Definition: "An increased concentration of glycine in the urine." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti, PMID:18901181, PMID:20240447]

Name: Hyperphosphaturia
Definition: "An increased excretion of phosphates in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of urine homeostasis
Definition: "An abnormality of the composition of urine or the levels of its components." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal blood ion concentration
Definition: "Abnormality of the homeostasis (concentration) of a monoatomic ion." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating amino acid concentration
Definition: "The presence of an abnormal decrease or increase of one or more amino acids in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypochloremia
Definition: "An abnormally decreased chloride concentration in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal EKG
Definition: "Abnormal rhythm of the heart." []

Name: Abnormal circulating hormone concentration
Definition: "Concentration of a hormone in the blood circulation outside of normal limits." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased circulating cortisol level
Definition: "Overproduction of the hormone of cortisol by the adrenal cortex, resulting in a characteristic combination of clinical symptoms termed Cushing syndrome, with truncal obesity, a round, full face, striae atrophicae and acne, muscle weakness, and other features." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Abnormal circulating lipid concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of a lipid in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Limb joint contracture
Definition: "A contracture (chronic loss of joint motion due to structural changes in muscle, tendons, ligaments, or skin) that prevent normal movement of one or more joints of the limbs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypercholesterolemia
Definition: "An increased concentration of cholesterol in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Reduced factor VIII activity
Definition: "Reduced activity of coagulation factor VIII. Factor VIII (fVIII) is a cofactor in the intrinsic clotting cascade that is activated to fVIIIa in the presence of minute quantities of thrombin. fVIIIa acts as a receptor, for factors IXa and X." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Low-molecular-weight proteinuria
Definition: "Excretion in urine of proteins of a size smaller than albumin (molecular weight 69 kD)." [PMID:95574]

Name: Hypocalciuria
Definition: "An abnormally decreased calcium concentration in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lactic acidosis
Definition: "An abnormal buildup of lactic acid in the body, leading to acidification of the blood and other bodily fluids." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal peripheral myelination
Definition: "An abnormality of the myelination of motor and sensory peripheral nerves. These are axons for motor nerves and dendrites for sensory nerves in the strict anatomic sense." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jbaets, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9102-5232]

Name: Cystinuria
Definition: "An increased concentration of cystine in the urine." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Abnormality of the spinocerebellar tracts
Definition: "An abnormality of the spinocerebellar tracts, a set of axonal fibers originating in the spinal cord and terminating in the ipsilateral cerebellum. The spinocerebellar tract convey information to the cerebellum about limb and joint position (proprioception). They comprise the ventral spinocerebellar tract, the anterior spinocerebellar tract, and the posterior spinocerebellar tract." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of peripheral nerve conduction
Definition: "An abnormality of the conduction of electrical impulses by peripheral (motor or sensory) nerves. This finding is elicited by a nerve conduction study (NCS)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Prolinuria
Definition: "Level of proline in the urine anove the upper limit of normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased blood urea nitrogen
Definition: "An increased amount of nitrogen in the form of urea in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Panhypogammaglobulinemia
Definition: "A reduction in the circulating levels of all the major classes of immunoglobulin. is characterized by profound decreases in all classes of immunoglobulin with an absence of circulating B lymphocytes." [PMID:23726535]

Name: T-wave inversion in the right precordial leads
Increased LDL cholesterol concentration
Definition: "An elevated concentration of low-density lipoprotein cholesterol in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased serum serotonin
Definition: "A increased concentration of serotonin in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased adenosylcobalamin
Definition: "Decreased concentration of adenosylcobalamin. Adenosylcobalamin is one of the active forms of vitamin B12." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypocholesterolemia
Definition: "An decreased concentration of cholesterol in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Hyperuricosuria
Definition: "An abnormally high level of uric acid in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Glutaric aciduria
Definition: "The concentration of glutaric acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Cystathioninuria
Definition: "An elevated urinary concentration of cystathionine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased circulating ACTH level
Definition: "An abnormal increased in the concentration of corticotropin, also known as adrenocorticotropic hormone (ACTH), in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated circulating alkaline phosphatase concentration
Definition: "Abnormally increased serum levels of alkaline phosphatase activity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:29083622]

Name: Hyposthenuria
Definition: "An abnormally low urinary specific gravity, i.e., reduced concentration of solutes in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperoxaluria
Definition: "Increased excretion of oxalates in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal isoelectric focusing of serum transferrin
Definition: "Glycosylated transferrin concentrations can be measured in serum as a marker of N-linked glycosylation fidelity. In the traditional nomenclature for congenital disorders of glycosylation, absence of entire glycans was designated type I, and loss of one or more monosaccharides as type II. These terms are retained for historical reasons but for new annotations the precise glycosylation defect should be recorded." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:22516080]

Name: 4-Hydroxyphenylpyruvic aciduria
Definition: "Increased relative concentration of 4-hydroxyphenylpyruvic acid in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated urinary delta-aminolevulinic acid
Definition: "An increased concentration of 5-aminolevulinic acid (CHEBI:17549) in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated circulating parathyroid hormone level
Definition: "An abnormal increased concentration of parathyroid hormone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased urinary taurine
Definition: "Increased concentration of taurine in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Carnosinuria
Definition: "An increased concentration of carnosine in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Dibasicaminoaciduria
Definition: "An increased level of a dibasic amino acid in the urine. Dibasic amino acids are usually refered to simply as basic aminoacids because they contain basic side chains at neutral pH. These are arginine (Arg), lysine (Lys), and histidine (His)." []

Name: Abnormal acetabulum morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the acetabulum, i.e., the Acetabular part of hip bone, which together with the head of the femur forms the hip joint." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal pubic bone morphology
Definition: "An anomaly of the the pubic bone, i.e., of the ventral and anterior of the three principal components (pubis, ilium, ischium) of the hip bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplastic pubic bone
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the pubis, which together with the ilium and the ischium, is one of the three bones that make up the hip bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal ischium morphology
Definition: "An anomaly of the ischium, which forms the lower and back part of the hip bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplastic ischia
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the ischium, which forms the lower and back part of the hip bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Squared iliac bones
Definition: "A shift from the normally round (convex) appearance of the iliac wing towards a square-like appearance." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Protrusio acetabuli
Definition: "Intrapelvic bulging of the medial acetabular wall." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Flat acetabular roof
Definition: "Flattening of the superior part of the acetabulum, which is a cup-shaped cavity at the base of the hipbone into which the ball-shaped head of the femur fits. The acetabular roof thereby appears horizontal rather than arched, as it normally does." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Wide pubic symphysis
Definition: "Abnormally increased width of the pubic symphysis is the midline cartilaginous joint uniting the superior rami of the left and right pubic bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased hip abduction
Definition: "Reduced ability to move the femur outward to the side." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short greater sciatic notch
Definition: "The sacroiliac joint in the bony pelvis connects the sacrum and the ilium of the pelvis, which are joined by strong ligaments. The notch is located directly superior to the joint. This term refers to a reduction in the height of the notch." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Inverted nipples
Definition: "The presence of nipples that instead of pointing outward are retracted inwards." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Breast hypoplasia
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the breast." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Long nose
Definition: "Distance from nasion to subnasale more than two standard deviations above the mean, or alternatively, an apparently increased length from the nasal root to the nasal base." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Cleft ala nasi
Definition: "The presence of a notch in the margin of the ala nasi." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152422]

Name: Allergic rhinitis
Definition: "It is characterized by one or more symptoms including sneezing, itching, nasal congestion, and rhinorrhea." [PMID:11449200]

Name: Short nasal bridge
Definition: "Decreased superior-inferior length of the nasal bridge, which is the saddle-shaped area that includes the nasal root and the lateral aspects of the nose." []

Name: Short nose
Definition: "Distance from nasion to subnasale more than two standard deviations below the mean, or alternatively, an apparently decreased length from the nasal root to the nasal tip." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152422]

Name: Myopathy
Definition: "A disorder of muscle unrelated to impairment of innervation or neuromuscular junction." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ragged-red muscle fibers
Definition: "An abnormal appearance of muscle fibers observed on muscle biopsy. Ragged red fibers can be visualized with Gomori trichrome staining as irregular and intensely red subsarcolemmal zones, whereas the normal myofibrils are green. The margins of affect fibers appear red and ragged. The ragged-red is due to the accumulation of abnormal mitochondria below the plasma membrane of the muscle fiber, leading to the appearance of a red rim and speckled sarcoplasm." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:12075011, PMID:16537564]

Name: Rhabdomyolysis
Definition: "Breakdown of muscle fibers that leads to the release of muscle fiber contents (myoglobin) into the bloodstream." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Skeletal muscle atrophy
Definition: "The presence of skeletal muscular atrophy (which is also known as amyotrophy)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Impaired oxidative burst
Definition: "In the NBT test, neutrophils change the colorless compound NBT into a compound with a deep blue color. If this test is negative (i.e., no blue color is produced), then this indicates a defect in superoxide-generating NADPH oxidase activity with inability to efficiently kill phagocytized bacteria." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Intracellular accumulation of autofluorescent lipopigment storage material
Definition: "The intracellular accumulation of autofluorescent storage material." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16455164]

Name: Curvilinear intracellular accumulation of autofluorescent lipopigment storage material
Definition: "An intracellular accumulation of autofluorescent lipopigment storage material in a curved pattern." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Arterial calcification
Definition: "Pathological deposition of calcium salts in one or more arteries." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:18519861]

Name: Fingerprint intracellular accumulation of autofluorescent lipopigment storage material
Definition: "An intracellular accumulation of autofluorescent lipopigment storage material in a trabecular or fingerprint-like pattern." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased pyruvate carboxylase activity
Definition: "A decreased rate of pyruvate carboxylase activity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased methylmalonyl-CoA mutase activity
Definition: "An abnormality of Krebs cycle metabolism that is characterized by a decreased rate of methylmalonyl-CoA mutase activity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased circulating IgE level
Definition: "An abnormally increased overall level of immunoglobulin E in blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Deficient excision of UV-induced pyrimidine dimers in DNA
Prolonged G2 phase of cell cycle
Dicarboxylic aciduria
Definition: "An increased concentration of dicarboxylic acid in the urine." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Generalized amyloid deposition
Definition: "A diffuse form of amyloidosis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperglutaminemia
Definition: "An increased concentration of glutamine in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti, PMID:4696900]

Name: Oroticaciduria
Definition: "An increased concentration of orotic acid in the urine." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarlotti]

Name: Ethylmalonic aciduria
Definition: "The concentration of ethylmalonic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of chromosome stability
Definition: "A type of chromosomal aberration characterised by reduced resistance of chromosomes to change or deterioration." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Chromosomal breakage induced by crosslinking agents
Definition: "Increased amount of chromosomal breaks in cultured blood lymphocytes or other cells induced by treatment with DNA cross-linking agents such as diepoxybutane and mitomycin C." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Decreased methylcobalamin
Definition: "Decreased concentration of methylcobalamin. Methylcobalamin is a form of vitamin B12." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased cellular sensitivity to UV light
Reduced coagulation factor V activity
Definition: "Decreased activity of coagulation factor V." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Rectilinear intracellular accumulation of autofluorescent lipopigment storage material
Definition: "An intracellular accumulation of autofluorescent lipopigment storage material in a straight or rectilinear pattern." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypernatremia
Definition: "An abnormally increased sodium concentration in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypertyrosinemia
Definition: "An increased concentration of tyrosine in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased HDL cholesterol concentration
Definition: "An decreased concentration of high-density lipoprotein cholesterol in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Decreased circulating carnitine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of carnitine in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Hypermethioninemia
Definition: "An increased concentration of methionine in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Elevated circulating creatine kinase concentration
Definition: "An elevation of the level of the enzyme creatine kinase (also known as creatine phosphokinase (CK; EC 2.7.3.2) in the blood. CK levels can be elevated in a number of clinical disorders such as myocardial infarction, rhabdomyolysis, and muscular dystrophy." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased circulating IgG level
Definition: "An abnormally increased level of immunoglobulin G in blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Phosphoethanolaminuria
Definition: "An increased level of phosphoethanolamine (synonym: O-phosphoethanolamine) in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:23093139]

Name: Increased phosphoribosylpyrophosphate synthetase level
Definition: "Abnormally elevated level of the enzyme phosphoribosyl pyrophosphatesynthetase, which catalyzes the synthesis of PP-ribose-P from ATP and ribose-5-phosphate." [PMID:4200723]

Name: External genital hypoplasia
Definition: "Underdevelopment of part or all of the external reproductive organs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Penile hypospadias
Definition: "Location of the urethral opening on the inferior aspect of the penis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Prominent scrotal raphe
Definition: "Increased size of the ridge of tissue that extends along the midline of the scrotum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Gonadal tissue inappropriate for external genitalia or chromosomal sex
Aplasia of the vagina
Definition: "Aplasia of the vagina." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of DNA repair
Definition: "An abnormality of the process of DNA repair, that is, of the process of restoring DNA after damage." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the coagulation cascade
Definition: "An abnormality of the coagulation cascade, which is comprised of the contact activation pathway (also known as the intrinsic pathway) and the tissue factor pathway (also known as the extrinsic pathway) as well as cofactors and regulators." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated circulating creatinine concentration
Definition: "An increased amount of creatinine in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Hydroxyprolinemia
Definition: "An increased concentration of hydroxyproline in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Increased circulating IgA level
Definition: "An abnormally increased level of immunoglobulin A in blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Smooth muscle antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence in serum of antibodies against smooth muscle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Neonatal hyperbilirubinemia
Definition: "A type of hyperbilirubinemia with neonatal onset." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Reduced orotidine 5-prime phosphate decarboxylase level
Definition: "An abnormal decrease in orotidine 5'-phosphate decarboxylase level." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Argininuria
Definition: "A increased concentration of arginine in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:18901181, PMID:20240447]

Name: Abdominal distention
Definition: "Distention of the abdomen." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Visceromegaly
Definition: "Abnormal increased size of the viscera of the abdomen." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal hip bone morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the hip bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hip contracture
Definition: "Lack of full passive range of motion (restrictions in flexion, extension, or other movements) of the hip joint resulting from structural changes of non-bony tissues, such as muscles, tendons, ligaments, joint capsules and/or skin." [PMID:16214063, PMID:24975760, PMID:31282072]

Name: Hypoplastic acetabulae
Definition: "Underdeveloped acetabulae." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Narrow pelvis bone
Definition: "Reduced side to side width of the pelvis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pelvic bone exostoses
Definition: "A benign growth the projects outward from the bone surface of the pelvis. Exostoses are capped by cartilage, and arise from a bone that develops from cartilage." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Square pelvis bone
Definition: "An abnormally squared appearance of the bony pelvis, a normally rounded or basin-shaped structure." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Coxa magna
Definition: "Widening of the femoral head and neck." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased circulating ferritin concentration
Definition: "Increased concentration of ferritin in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Low alkaline phosphatase
Definition: "Abnormally reduced serum levels of alkaline phosphatase." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cystathioninemia
Definition: "An increased concentration of cystathionine in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti, PMID:16902722]

Name: Abnormality of mitochondrial metabolism
Definition: "A functional anomaly of mitochondria." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Decreased serum leptin
Definition: "A decreased concentration of leptin in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16932309]

Name: obsolete Impaired FSH and LH secretion
Hyperthreoninuria
Definition: "An increased concentration of threonine in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:18901181, PMID:20240447]

Name: Hyperlysinuria
Definition: "An increased concentration of lysine in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:18901181, PMID:20240447]

Name: Spina bifida occulta
Definition: "The closed form of spina bifida with incomplete closure of a vertebral body with intact overlying skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ovoid vertebral bodies
Definition: "When viewed in lateral radiographs, vertebral bodies have a roughly rectangular configuration. This term applies if the vertebral body appears rounded or oval." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Irregular vertebral endplates
Definition: "An irregular surface of the vertebral end plates, which are normally relatively smooth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Spondylolisthesis
Definition: "Complete bilateral fractures of the pars interarticularis resulting in the anterior slippage of the vertebra." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20411054]

Name: Spondylolysis
Definition: "Spondylolysis is an osseous defect of the pars interarticularis, thought to be a developmental or acquired stress fracture secondary to chronic low-grade trauma." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20440613]

Name: Block vertebrae
Definition: "Congenital synostosis between two or more adjacent vertebrae (partial or complete fusion of adjacent vertabral bodies)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Spinal rigidity
Definition: "Reduced ability to move the vertebral column with a resulting limitation of neck and trunk flexion." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:11601420, PMID:2246660]

Name: Hyperlordosis
Definition: "Abnormally increased curvature (anterior concavity) of the lumbar or cervical spine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cervical subluxation
Definition: "A partial dislocation of one or more intervertebral joints in the cervical vertebral column." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal odontoid process morphology
Definition: "Abnormal structure of the odontoid process, which is a part of the C2 or axis vertebra and forms pivot of the structures forming the craniovertebral junction. The odontoid process is also known as the dens of the axis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:27081234]

Name: Hypoplasia of the odontoid process
Definition: "Developmental hypoplasia of the dens of the axis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal form of the vertebral bodies
Definition: "Abnormal morphology of vertebral body." []

Name: Butterfly vertebrae
Definition: "A butterfly vertebra (sagittal cleft vertebra or anterior rachischisis) is a sagittal defect in the vertebral body caused by failure of fusion of the two lateral chondrification centers during embryogenesis. The name is based on the appearance of the two hemivertebrae emerging as butterfly wings from the central cleft on x-ray." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:31448202, PMID:3693103]

Name: Abnormality of the cervical spine
Definition: "Any abnormality of the cervical vertebral column." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: C1-C2 subluxation
Definition: "A partial dislocation of the atlantoaxial joints." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Generalized muscle weakness
Definition: "Generalized weakness or decreased strength of the muscles, affecting both distal and proximal musculature." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Limb-girdle muscle weakness
Definition: "Weakness of the limb-girdle muscles (also known as the pelvic and shoulder girdles), that is, lack of strength of the muscles around the shoulders and the pelvis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Myalgia
Definition: "Pain in muscle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Axial muscle weakness
Definition: "Reduced strength of the axial musculature (i.e., of the muscles of the head and neck, spine, and ribs)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal hairshaft morphology
Definition: "An abnormal structure of the hairshaft, i.e., of the nongrowing portion of a hair that protrudes from the skin." []

Name: Hair shafts flattened at irregular intervals and twisted through 180 degrees about their axes
Abnormal bone structure
Definition: "Any anomaly in the composite material or the layered arrangement of the bony skeleton." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated circulating catecholamine level
Definition: "An abnormal increase in catecholamine concentration in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal enchondral ossification
Definition: "An abnormality of the process of endochondral ossification, which is a type of replacement ossification in which bone tissue replaces cartilage." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Reduced prothrombin consumption
Definition: "The prothrombin consumption test measures the formation of intrinsic thromboplastin by determining the residual serum prothrombin after blood clotting is complete. If there is a defect in the process, less prothrombin will be converted to thrombin than normal (less prothrombin is consumed). This test may be abnormal with conditions including deficiency of factors VIII or IX, with circulating anticoagulants, thrombocytopenia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Focal necrosis of right ventricular muscle cells
Pyrimidine-responsive megaloblastic anemia
Definition: "A type of megaloblastic anemia that improves upon administration of pyrimidine supplements such as uridylic acid and cytidylic acid." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lamina lucida cleavage
Definition: "The formation of bullae (blisters) with cleavage in the lamina lucida layer of the skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Reduced glutathione synthetase level
Definition: "Reduced level of the enzyme glutathione synthetase, which catalyzes the last step in the synthesis of glutathione and a deficiency results in low levels of glutathione. Acidosis is due to reduced feedback inhibition of gamma-glutamyl cysteine synthetase in the gamma-glutamyl cycle, which ultimately leads to overproduction and accumulation of 5-oxoproline." [PMID:17397529]

Name: 3-Methylglutaric aciduria
Definition: "An abnormally increased level of 3-hydroxy-3-methylglutaric acid in the urine." [PMID:19177531]

Name: Elevated urinary norepinephrine level
Definition: "The concentration of noradrenaline in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Impaired lymphocyte transformation with phytohemagglutinin
Definition: "Normal peripheral blood lymphocytes, when stimulated by phytohemagglutinin (PHA) are cytotoxic for homologous and heterologous cells but not for autologous cells in monolayer culture. The cytotoxic effect is thought to be indicative of the immunological competence of the lymphocytes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperalaninemia
Definition: "An increased concentration of alanine in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti, PMID:16902722, PMID:4696900]

Name: Low cholesterol esterification rate
Definition: "A reduction in the rate of cholesterol esterification." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:3378364]

Name: Decreased circulating renin level
Definition: "An decreased level of renin in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Endopolyploidy on chromosome studies of bone marrow
Definition: "An increase in the number of chromosome sets per cell in bone marrow cells." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Propionyl-CoA carboxylase deficiency
Definition: "An abnormality of amino acid metabolism characterized by a decreased level of propionyl-CoA carboxylase." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperthreoninemia
Definition: "An increased concentration of threonine in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aminoaciduria
Definition: "An increased concentration of an amino acid in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5316-1399]

Name: Thymic hormone decreased
Definition: "A reduction in the level of thymic horomone." [PMID:7058086]

Name: Elevated intracellular cystine
Definition: "An increased concentration of cystine within cells. This finding can be demonstrated on leukocytes, but is not specific to blood cells." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased urinary sulfate
Definition: "Decreased concentration of sulfate in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Tryptophanuria
Definition: "An increased concentration of tryptophan in the urine." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti, PMID:18901181]

Name: Increased VLDL cholesterol concentration
Definition: "An increase in the amount of very-low-density lipoprotein cholesterol in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Abdominal situs inversus
Definition: "A left-right reversal (or \"mirror reflection\") of the anatomical location of the viscera of the abdomen." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Arthralgia of the hip
Definition: "Joint pain affecting the hip." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal femoral neck morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the femoral neck (which is the process of bone, connecting the femoral head with the femoral shaft)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal femoral head morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the femoral head." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Flat capital femoral epiphysis
Definition: "An abnormal flattening of the proximal epiphysis of the femur." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Enlargement of the proximal femoral epiphysis
Definition: "An abnormal enlargement of the proximal epiphysis of the femur." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Narrow greater sciatic notch
Definition: "A narrowing of the sacrosciatic notch, i.e., the deep indentation in the posterior border of the hip bone at the point of union of the ilium and ischium." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Steppage gait
Definition: "An abnormal gait pattern that arises from weakness of the pretibial and peroneal muscles due to a lower motor neuron lesion. Affected patients have footdrop and are unable to dorsiflex and evert the foot. The leg is lifted high on walking so that the toes clear the ground, and there may be a slapping noise when the foot strikes the ground again." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:27770207]

Name: Axonal degeneration/regeneration
Definition: "A pattern of simultaneous degeneration and regeneration of axons (see comment)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased number of peripheral myelinated nerve fibers
Definition: "A loss of myelinated nerve fibers in the peripheral nervous system (in general, this finding can be observed on nerve biopsy)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Onion bulb formation
Definition: "Repeated episodes of segmental demyelination and remyelination lead to the accumulation of supernumerary Schwann cells around axons, which is referred to as onion bulb formation. This finding affects peripheral nerves." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Peripheral axonal atrophy
Definition: "Atrophic changes of axons of the peripheral nervous system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased number of large peripheral myelinated nerve fibers
Definition: "A reduced number of large myelinated nerve fibers." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Easy fatigability
Definition: "Increased susceptibility to fatigue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sensory axonal neuropathy
Definition: "An axonal neuropathy of peripheral sensory nerves." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Gowers sign
Definition: "A phenomenon whereby patients are not able to stand up without the use of the hands owing to weakness of the proximal muscles of the lower limbs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thenar muscle atrophy
Definition: "Wasting of thenar muscles, which are located on palm of the hand at the base of the thumb." []

Name: Muscle spasm
Definition: "Sudden and involuntary contractions of one or more muscles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Syringomyelia
Definition: "Dilated, glial-lined cavity in spinal cord. This cavity does not communicate with the central canal, and usually is between the dorsal columns unilaterally or bilaterally along the side of the cord." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Generalized hypotonia due to defect at the neuromuscular junction
Abnormal synaptic transmission at the neuromuscular junction
Definition: "Any abnormality of the neuromuscular junction, which is the synapse between the motor end plate of a motor neuron and the skeletal muscle fibers." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Basal lamina onion bulb formation
Definition: "A type of onion bulb formation prominently affecting the area of the basal lamina." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Paresthesia
Definition: "Abnormal sensations such as tingling, pricking, or numbness of the skin with no apparent physical cause." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased miniature endplate potentials
Definition: "An abnormal reduction in the amplitude of the miniature endplate potentials, i.e. the postsynaptic response to transmitter released from an individual vesicle at the neuromuscular junction." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: EMG: decremental response of compound muscle action potential to repetitive nerve stimulation
Definition: "A compound muscle action potential (CMAP) is a type of electromyography (EMG). CMAP refers to a group of almost simultaneous action potentials from several muscle fibers in the same area evoked by stimulation of the supplying motor nerve and are recorded as one multipeaked summated action potential. This abnormality refers to a greater than normal decrease in the amplitude during the course of the investigation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Distal sensory impairment of all modalities
Definition: "Reduced ability to sense pain, temperature, touch, vibration stimuli in the distal regions of the extremities." []

Name: Proximal femoral metaphyseal irregularity
Definition: "Irregularity of the normally smooth surface of the proximal metaphysis of the femur." []

Name: Atlantoaxial abnormality
Definition: "An anomaly of the atlantoaxial joint, i.e., of the joint between the first (atlas) and second (axis) cervical vertebrae." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Atlantoaxial dislocation
Definition: "Partial dislocation of the atlantoaxial joint." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Spinal canal stenosis
Definition: "An abnormal narrowing of the spinal canal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Coronal cleft vertebrae
Definition: "Frontal schisis (cleft or cleavage) of vertebral bodies." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Back pain
Definition: "An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the back." []

Name: Low back pain
Definition: "An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the lower back." []

Name: Vertebral segmentation defect
Definition: "An abnormality related to a defect of vertebral separation during development." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:23653580, PMID:23801490]

Name: CNS hypomyelination
Definition: "Reduced amount of myelin in the central nervous system resulting from defective myelinogenesis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased motor nerve conduction velocity
Definition: "A type of decreased nerve conduction velocity that affects the motor neuron." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Prolonged miniature endplate currents
Definition: "An abnormal prolongation of the miniature endplate potentials, i.e. the postsynaptic response to transmitter released from an individual vesicle at the neuromuscular junction." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent Achilles reflex
Definition: "Absence of the Achilles reflex (also known as the ankle jerk reflex), which can normally be elicited by tapping the tendon is tapped while the foot is dorsiflexed." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased size of nerve terminals
Definition: "A reduction in the size of nerve terminals." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: EMG: chronic denervation signs
Definition: "Evidence of chronic denervation on electromyography." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: EMG: neuropathic changes
Definition: "The presence of characteristic findings of denervation on electromyography (fibrillations, positive sharp waves, and giant motor unit potentials)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Axonal loss
Definition: "A reduction in the number of axons in the peripheral nervous system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased sensory nerve conduction velocity
Definition: "Reduced speed of conduction of the action potential along a sensory nerve." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cold-induced muscle cramps
Definition: "Sudden and involuntary contractions of one or more muscles brought on by exposure to cold temperatures." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Axonal regeneration
Definition: "The presence of axonal regeneration following a previous axonal lesion." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased rate of premature chromosome condensation
Definition: "An increased rate of premature chromosome condensation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Antineutrophil antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies in the serum that react against neutrophils." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Platelet antibody positive
Definition: "The presence in the serum of autoantibodies directed against thrombocytes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated circulating long chain fatty acid concentration
Definition: "Increased concentration of long-chain fatty acids in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Low urinary cyclic AMP response to PTH administration
EMG abnormality
Definition: "Abnormal results of investigations using electromyography (EMG)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:15961866, PMID:18751841]

Name: EMG: myopathic abnormalities
Definition: "The presence of abnormal electromyographic patterns indicative of myopathy, such as small-short polyphasic motor unit potentials." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Polyclonal elevation of IgM
Definition: "A heterogeneous increase in IgM immunoglobulins characterized by a diffuse band on serum electrophoresis." [PMID:11508831]

Name: Decreased circulating total IgA
Definition: "Undetectable serum immunoglobulin A level at a value < 5 mg/dL (0.05 g/L)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased urinary O-linked sialopeptides
Definition: "Excretion of peptides conjugated to sialic acid in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased extraneuronal autofluorescent lipopigment
Definition: "Lipofuscin, a generic term applied to autofluorescent lipopigment, is a mixture of protein and lipid that accumulates in most aging cells, particularly those involved in high lipid turnover (e.g., the adrenal medulla) or phagocytosis of other cell types (e g., the retinal pigment epithelium or RPE; macrophage). This term pertains if there is an increase in the extraneuronal accumulation of lipofuscin (also known as autofluorescent lipoprotein) more than expected for the age of the patient." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:11406682]

Name: Paradoxical increased cortisol secretion on dexamethasone suppression test
Atlantoaxial instability
Definition: "Abnormally increased movement at the junction between the first cervical (atlas) and the second cervical (axis) vertebrae as a result of either a bony or ligamentous anomaly." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal vertebral morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of one or more of the vertebrae." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Peripheral dysmyelination
Definition: "Defective structure and function of myelin sheaths. Dysmyelination is distinguished from demyleination where there is destruction or damage of previously normal myelination." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Paralysis
Definition: "Paralysis of voluntary muscles means loss of contraction due to interruption of one or more motor pathways from the brain to the muscle fibers. Although the word paralysis is often used interchangeably to mean either complete or partial loss of muscle strength, it is preferable to use paralysis or plegia for complete or severe loss of muscle strength, and paresis for partial or slight loss. Motor paralysis results from deficits of the upper motor neurons (corticospinal, corticobulbar, or subcorticospinal). Motor paralysis is often accompanied by an impairment in the facility of movement." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypocalcemic tetany
Definition: "Hyperexcitability of the neuromuscular system related to abnormally low level of calcium in the blood, resulting in carpopedal or generalized spasms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fatigable weakness
Definition: "A type of weakness that occurs after a muscle group is used and lessens if the muscle group has some rest. That is, there is diminution of strength with repetitive muscle actions." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Somatic sensory dysfunction
Definition: "An abnormality of the primary sensation that is mediated by peripheral nerves (pain, temperature, touch, vibration, joint position). The word hypoesthesia (or hypesthesia) refers to a reduction in cutaneous sensation to a specific type of testing." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Peripheral axonal neuropathy
Definition: "An abnormality characterized by disruption of the normal functioning of peripheral axons." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Segmental peripheral demyelination/remyelination
Definition: "A segmental pattern of demyelination and regeneration (remyelination) affecting peripheral nerves." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: EMG: axonal abnormality
Definition: "Electromyographic (EMG) findings characteristic of axonal neuropathy, with normal or slightly decreased nerve conduction velocities, normal or slightly prolonged distal latencies, but significantly reduced motor potentials and sensory amplitudes. There may be spontaneous activity upon needle EMG studies, such as increased insertional activity, positive sharp waves, and fibrillation potentials." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Upper limb muscle weakness
Definition: "Weakness of the muscles of the arms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Babinski sign
Definition: "Upturning of the big toe (and sometimes fanning of the other toes) in response to stimulation of the sole of the foot. If the Babinski sign is present it can indicate damage to the corticospinal tract." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: obsolete Defective dehydrogenation of isovaleryl CoA and butyryl CoA
Elevated urine pyrophosphate
Definition: "An abnormally increased diphosphate(4-) concentration in the urine. Diphosphate(4-), as ester with two phosphate groups, is also known as pyrophosphate." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: High urinary gonadotropin level
Definition: "An elevated concentration of a gonadotropin hormone (stimulating hormone or luteinizing hormone) in the urine, consistent with the diagnosis of primary hypogonadism." []

Name: Antinuclear antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies in the serum that react against nuclei or nuclear components." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: obsolete Loss of heterozygosity, multiple chromosomes
GM2-ganglioside accumulation
Definition: "Cellular accumulation of GM2 gangliosides." [PMID:30524313]

Name: Increased circulating IgM level
Definition: "An abnormally increased level of immunoglobulin M in blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Disproportionate short stature
Definition: "A kind of short stature in which different regions of the body are shortened to differing extents." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Mild short stature
Definition: "A mild degree of short stature, more than -2 SD but not more than -3 SD from mean corrected for age and sex." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6410-0882]

Name: Proportionate short stature
Definition: "A kind of short stature in which different regions of the body are shortened to a comparable extent." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Severe short stature
Definition: "A severe degree of short stature, more than -4 SD from the mean corrected for age and sex." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Reduced ratio of renal calcium clearance to creatinine clearance
Definition: "A reduction of the ratio of renal calcium clearance to creatinine clearance to below 0.01." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Deficiency or absence of cytochrome b(-245)
Disproportionate short-trunk short stature
Definition: "A type of disproportionate short stature characterized by a short trunk but a average-sized limbs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased methionine synthase activity
Definition: "A reduction in methionine synthase activity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Orotic acid crystalluria
Definition: "Formation of crystals owing to an increased concentration of orotic acid in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperprostaglandinuria
Definition: "An increased concentration of prostaglandin in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated circulating calcitonin concentration
Definition: "Concentration of calcitonin, a 32-amino acid polypeptide hormone that is produced primarily by the parafollicular cells of the thyroid, in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Parathormone-independent increased renal tubular calcium reabsorption
Definition: "An increase in the reabsorption of calcium by the renal tubulus that is not associated with increased parathormone levels." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:23802516]

Name: Elevated circulating glutaric acid concentration
Definition: "An increased concentration of glutaric acid in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Ornithinuria
Definition: "Level of ornithine in the urine above the upper limit of normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Reduced acetaldehyde dehydrogenase level
Definition: "Decreased level of acetaldehyde dehydrogenase (ALDH). ALDH and alcohol dehydrogenase (ADH) are the primary enzymes involved in alcohol metabolism." [PMID:17718394]

Name: Reduced xanthine dehydrogenase level
Definition: "An abnormal reduction in xanthine dehydrogenase level." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: 3-Methylglutaconic aciduria
Definition: "An increased amount of 3-methylglutaconic acid in the urine." []

Name: Decreased fumarate hydratase activity
Definition: "An abnormality of Krebs cycle metabolism that is characterized by a decreased rate of fumarate hydratase activity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypouricemia
Definition: "An abnormally low level of uric acid in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased iduronate sulfatase level
Definition: "An increased level of iduronate-2-sulfatase activity in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Impaired platelet aggregation
Definition: "An impairment in the rate and degree to which platelets aggregate after the addition of an agonist that stimulates platelet clumping. Platelet aggregation is measured using aggregometer to measure the optical density of platelet-rich plasma, whereby platelet aggregation causes the plasma to become more transparent." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7744-1790]

Name: Urinary glycosaminoglycan excretion
Definition: "Excretion of glycosaminoglycan in the urine. Glycosaminoglycans are long unbranched polysaccharides consisting of a repeating disaccharide unit." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased serum pyruvate
Definition: "An increased concentration of pyruvate in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Exercise intolerance
Definition: "A functional motor deficit where individuals whose responses to the challenges of exercise fail to achieve levels considered normal for their age and gender." [PMID:10617757]

Name: Shoulder girdle muscle weakness
Definition: "The shoulder, or pectoral, girdle is composed of the clavicles and the scapulae. Shoulder-girdle weakness refers to lack of strength of the muscles attaching to these bones, that is, lack of strength of the muscles around the shoulders." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Subsarcolemmal accumulations of abnormally shaped mitochondria
Definition: "An abnormally increased number of mitochondria in the cytoplasma adjacent to the sarcolemma (muscle cell membrane), whereby the mitochondria also possess an abnormal morphology." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of connective tissue
Definition: "Any abnormality of the soft tissues, including both connective tissue (tendons, ligaments, fascia, fibrous tissues, and fat)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Predominantly lower limb lymphedema
Definition: "Localized fluid retention and tissue swelling caused by a compromised lymphatic system, affecting mainly the legs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Difficulty climbing stairs
Definition: "Reduced ability to climb stairs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Muscle stiffness
Definition: "A condition in which muscles cannot be moved quickly without accompanying pain or spasm." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Type 2 muscle fiber atrophy
Definition: "Atrophy (wasting) affecting primary type 2 muscle fibers. This feature in general can only be observed on muscle biopsy." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Muscle fiber splitting
Definition: "Fiber splitting or branching is a common finding in human and rat skeletal muscle pathology. Fiber splitting refers to longitudinal halving of the complete fiber, while branching originates from a regenerating end of a necrotic fiber as invaginations of the sarcolemma. In fiber branching, one end of the fiber remains intact as a single entity, while the other end has several branches." [PMID:6123177]

Name: Increased variability in muscle fiber diameter
Definition: "An abnormally high degree of muscle fiber size variation. This phenotypic feature can be observed upon muscle biopsy." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Viral infection-induced rhabdomyolysis
Definition: "Rhabdomyolysis induced by a viral infection." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Muscular dystrophy
Definition: "The term dystrophy means abnormal growth. However, muscular dystrophy is used to describe primary myopathies with a genetic basis and a progressive course characterized by progressive skeletal muscle weakness and wasting, defects in muscle proteins, and histological features of muscle fiber degeneration (necrosis) and regeneration. If possible, it is preferred to use other HPO terms to describe the precise phenotypic abnormalities." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9046-3540, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased LDL cholesterol concentration
Definition: "An decreased concentration of low-density lipoprotein cholesterol in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Folate-dependent fragile site at Xq28
Definition: "The presence of a folate sensitive fragile site at chromosome Xq28." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated erythrocyte sedimentation rate
Definition: "An increased erythrocyte sedimentation rate (ESR). The ESR is a test that measures the distance that erythrocytes have fallen after one hour in a vertical column of anticoagulated blood under the influence of gravity. The ESR is a nonspecific finding. An elevation may indicate inflammation or may be caused by any condition that elevates fibrinogen." [PMID:10524488]

Name: Increased serum prostaglandin E2
Definition: "An increased concentration of prostaglandin E2 in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased glucosephosphate isomerase level
Definition: "A decreased level of glucose-6-phosphate isomerase." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Molybdenum cofactor deficiency
Definition: "Absence of molybdenum cofactor(2-), a cofactor for enzymes including sulfite oxidase, xanthine oxidoreductase, and aldehyde oxidase." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Propionic acidemia
Definition: "Increased concentration of proprionic acid in the blood circulation." [PMID:22593918]

Name: Low plasma citrulline
Definition: "A decreased concentration of citrulline in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Increased total bilirubin
Definition: "Increased concentration of total (conjugated and unconjugated) bilirubin in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Positive regitine blocking test
Definition: "A positive response to the regitine blocking test consisting of a substantial reduction in blood pressure following administration of regitine, indicative of the presence of increased levels of epinephrine and norepinephrine in the circulation, which is seen in pheochromocytoma-associated hypertension." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased intracellular sodium
Definition: "An abnormally increased sodium concentration in the cytosol." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Congenital onset
Definition: "A phenotypic abnormality that is present at birth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Adult onset
Definition: "Onset of disease manifestations in adulthood, defined here as at the age of 16 years or later." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Late onset
Definition: "A type of adult onset with onset of symptoms after the age of 60 years." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Insidious onset
Definition: "Gradual, very slow onset of disease manifestations." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Infantile onset
Definition: "Onset of signs or symptoms of disease between 28 days to one year of life." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Middle age onset
Definition: "A type of adult onset with onset of symptoms at the age of 40 to 60 years." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent urinary urothione
Definition: "Lack of urothione (the urinary metabolite of molybdenum cofactor) in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:6960353]

Name: 4-hydroxyphenylacetic aciduria
Definition: "Increased concentration of 4-hydroxyphenylacetic acid in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Foam cells with lamellar inclusion bodies
Definition: "The presence of foam cells that contain lamellar inclusion bodies." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fibroblast metachromasia
Definition: "Increased cytoplasmic staining of fibroblasts with toluidine blue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:4195824]

Name: Positive ferric chloride test
Definition: "If positive, the ferric chloride test indicates an increased concentration of phenols in the urine or blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Antiphospholipid antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of circulating autoantibodies to phospholipids." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Trimethylaminuria
Definition: "Increased concentration of trimethylamine in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Juvenile onset
Definition: "Onset of signs or symptoms of disease between the age of 5 and 15 years." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Neonatal onset
Definition: "Onset of signs or symptoms of disease within the first 28 days of life." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Amyoplasia
Definition: "Congenital lack of development of the muscles, which are then replaced by a mixture of dense fat and fibrous tissue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9046-3540, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Loss of subcutaneous adipose tissue in limbs
Definition: "Loss (disappearance) of previously present subcutaneous fat tissue in arm or leg." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Reduced 4-Hydroxyphenylpyruvate dioxygenase level
Definition: "An abnormal reduction in 4-hydroxyphenylpyruvate dioxygenase level." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated urinary epinephrine level
Definition: "The concentration of epinephrine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: CNS foam cells
Definition: "The presence of foam cells, a type of macrophage that localizes to fatty deposits on blood vessel walls, in the central nervous system." []

Name: Hemoglobinuria
Definition: "The presence of free hemoglobin in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Type I transferrin isoform profile
Definition: "Abnormal transferrin isoform profile consistent with a type I congenital disorder of glycosylation. In the traditional nomenclature for congenital disorders of glycosylation, absence of entire glycans was designated type I, and loss of one or more monosaccharides as type II." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:15105360, PMID:22516080]

Name: Sulfite oxidase deficiency
Definition: "Abnormally reduced sulfite oxidase level." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Prolonged partial thromboplastin time
Definition: "Increased time to coagulation in the partial thromboplastin time (PTT) test, a measure of the intrinsic and common coagulation pathways. Phospholipid, and activator, and calcium are mixed into an anticoagulated plasma sample, and the time is measured until a thrombus forms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bicarbonaturia
Definition: "Abnormally increased concentration of hydrogencarbonate in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Electron transfer flavoprotein-ubiquinone oxidoreductase defect
Definition: "A deficiency of the electron transfer flavoprotein-ubiquinone oxidoreductase." [PMID:2989828]

Name: Lacticaciduria
Definition: "An increased concentration of lactic acid in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of glycoside metabolism
Definition: "Abnormality of glycoside metabolism." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Foam cells
Definition: "The presence of foam cells, a type of macrophage that localizes to fatty deposits on blood vessel walls, where they ingest low-density lipoproteins and become laden with lipids, giving them a foamy appearance." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Recurrent myoglobinuria
Definition: "Recurring episodes of myoglobinuria, i.e., of the presence of myoglobin in the urine. This is usually a consequence of rhabdomyolysis, i.e., of the destruction of muscle tissue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cellular metachromasia
Definition: "Metachromasia (also known as metachromacy) is a characteristic color change which certain aniline dyes exhibit when bound to particular substances or when concentrated in solution. For example, the basic dye toluidine blue becomes distinctly pink when bound to cartilage matrix. In the sense used here, the metachromasia refers to a change in color not observed with normal tissues, anomalous staining with the cationic dyes toluidine blue O and Alcian blue resulting from excessive amounts of the polyanionic glycosaminoglycans." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:4195824]

Name: Reduced dihydropyrimidine dehydrogenase level
Definition: "An abnormal reduction in dihydropyrimidine dehydrogenase (NADP+) level." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Reduced level of N-acetylglucosaminyltransferase II
Definition: "An abnormality of glycoprotein metabolism related to a decreased level of alpha-1,6-mannosylglycoprotein 2-beta-N-acetylglucosaminyltransferase activity." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Decreased beta-glucocerebrosidase level
Definition: "Reduced level of the enzyme beta-glucosidase, an enzyme that catalyzes the hydrolysis of glucosylceramide into ceramide and glucose." []

Name: Vascular granular osmiophilic material deposition
Definition: "Accumulation of granular osmiophilic material in blood vessel walls. Osmiophilic material becomes black upon staining with osmium tetroxide. Deposition of granular osmiophilic material (GOM) is the vascular pathological hallmark of CADASIL, which is the most prevalent hereditary small vessel disease and is caused by missense mutations in the NOTCH3 gene. GOM have been shown to contain NOTCH3 ectodomain (NOTCH3ECD) and extracellular matrix proteins, and can be visualized ultrastructurally in the tunica media of small arteries and capillaries. These electron dense GOM deposits are located in the basement membrane of mural cells, i.e. vascular smooth muscle cells and pericytes. In both manifest and pre-manifest CADASIL patients, GOM deposits are present not only in brain vessels, but also in vessels of other organs, such as the skin." [PMID:17183453, PMID:31667734]

Name: Hypomethioninemia
Definition: "A decreased concentration of methionine in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Amyotrophy of the musculature of the pelvis
Definition: "Muscular atrophy affecting the muscles of the pelvis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Onset
Definition: "The age group in which disease manifestations appear." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Progressive
Definition: "Applies to a disease manifestation that increases in scope or severity over the course of time, i.e., that worsens with age." []

Name: Slowly progressive
Definition: "Applies to a disease manifestation that only slowly increases in scope or severity over the course of time." []

Name: Rapidly progressive
Definition: "Applies to a disease manifestation that quickly increases in scope or severity over the course of time." []

Name: Nonprogressive
Definition: "Applies to a disease manifestation that does not increase in scope or severity over the course of time, i.e., that does not worsen with age." []

Name: Variable progression rate
Definition: "Applies to a disease manifestation that quickly increases in scope or severity with a rate that varies. For instance, progression may be slow in one time period and rapid in another." []

Name: Centrally nucleated skeletal muscle fibers
Definition: "An abnormality in which the nuclei of sarcomeres take on an abnormally central localization (or in which this feature is found in an increased proportion of muscle cells)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20181480]

Name: Cytochrome C oxidase-negative muscle fibers
Definition: "An abnormally reduced activity of the enzyme cytochrome C oxidase in muscle tissue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Multiple mitochondrial DNA deletions
Definition: "The presence of multiple deletions of mitochondrial DNA (mtDNA)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Limb muscle weakness
Definition: "Reduced strength and weakness of the muscles of the arms and legs." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Scapular winging
Definition: "Abnormal protrusion of the scapula away from the surface of the back." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Distal amyotrophy
Definition: "Muscular atrophy affecting muscles in the distal portions of the extremities." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Late-onset proximal muscle weakness
Definition: "Lack of strength of the proximal musculature occurring late in the clinical course." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 5th finger
Definition: "Absence of the epiphysis located at the proximal end of the distal phalanx of the 5th finger." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Scapuloperoneal amyotrophy
Definition: "Muscular atrophy in the distribution of shoulder girdle and peroneal muscles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Generalized amyotrophy
Definition: "Generalized (diffuse, unlocalized) amyotrophy (muscle atrophy) affecting multiple muscles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Proximal muscle weakness
Definition: "A lack of strength of the proximal muscles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Calf muscle pseudohypertrophy
Definition: "Enlargement of the muscles of the calf due to their replacement by connective tissue or fat." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Exercise-induced muscle cramps
Definition: "Sudden and involuntary contractions of one or more muscles brought on by physical exertion." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Skeletal muscle hypertrophy
Definition: "Abnormal increase in muscle size and mass not due to training." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Muscle fiber necrosis
Definition: "Abnormal cell death involving muscle fibers usually associated with break in, or absence of, muscle surface fiber membrane and resulting in irreversible damage to muscle fibers." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Myofibrillar myopathy
Definition: "Myofibrillar structural changes characterized by abnormal intracellular accumulation of the intermediate filament desmin and other proteins." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Muscle mounding
Definition: "Percussion-induced, local prolonged contractions (mounding) in muscle persisting for several seconds." [PMID:20300641]

Name: Generalized muscle hypertrophy
Definition: "Hypertrophy (increase in size) of muscle tissue in a generalized (not localized) distribution." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Neck flexor weakness
Definition: "Weakness of the muscles involved in neck flexion (sternocleidomastoid, longus capitus, longus colli, and scalenus anterior)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Shoulder girdle muscle atrophy
Definition: "Amyotrophy affecting the muscles of the shoulder girdle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: EMG: myotonic runs
Definition: "Spontaneous, repetitive electrical activity demonstrated by electromyography (EMG)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Quadriceps muscle weakness
Definition: "Weakness of the quadriceps muscle (that is, of the muscle fasciculus of quadriceps femoris)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thigh hypertrophy
Definition: "Muscle hypertrophy affecting the thighs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Autophagic vacuoles
Definition: "The lysosomal-vacuolar pathway has a role in the controlled intracellular digestion of macromolecules such as protein complexes and organelles. This feature refers to the presence of an abnormally increased number of autophagic vacuoles in muscle tissue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:17027858]

Name: Mitochondrial myopathy
Definition: "A type of myopathy associated with mitochondrial disease and characterized by findings on biopsy such as ragged red muscle fibers." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Exercise-induced myalgia
Definition: "The occurrence of an unusually high amount of muscle pain following exercise." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Myotonia with warm-up phenomenon
Definition: "Myotonia that occurs after a period of rest and decreases with continuing exercise." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:7678441]

Name: Genetic anticipation
Definition: "A type of autosomal dominant inheritance involving a gene that exhibits anticipation, the increase in severity and/or an earlier age of onset in subsequent generations." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Genetic anticipation with paternal anticipation bias
Definition: "A type of genetic anticipation observed predominantly upon transmission from affected males." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sporadic
Definition: "Cases of the disease in question occur without a previous family history, i.e., as isolated cases without being transmitted from a parent and without other siblings being affected." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pelvic girdle muscle weakness
Definition: "Weakness of the muscles of the pelvic girdle (also known as the hip girdle), that is, lack of strength of the muscles around the pelvis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased muscle fatiguability
Definition: "An abnormal, increased fatiguability of the musculature." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Episodic flaccid weakness
Definition: "Recurrent episodes of muscle flaccidity, a type of paralysis in which a muscle becomes soft and yields to passive stretching." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Type 1 fibers relatively smaller than type 2 fibers
Definition: "The presence of abnormal muscle fiber size such that type 1 fibers are smaller than type 2 fibers." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Reduced subcutaneous adipose tissue
Definition: "A reduced amount of fat tissue in the lowest layer of the integument. This feature can be appreciated by a reduced skinfold thickness." []

Name: Hypoplasia of lymphatic vessels
Definition: "Congenital underdevelopment of lymph vessels." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Percussion-induced rapid rolling muscle contractions
