Name: Spinal stenosis with reduced interpedicular distance
Definition: "An abnormal narrowing of the spinal canal related to a reduction in the interpedicular distance (i.e., the distance measured between the pedicles on frontal [coronal] imaging)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short tibia
Definition: "Underdevelopment (reduced size) of the tibia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Posterior subluxation of radial head
Definition: "Partial dislocation of the head of the radius in the posterior direction." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Avascular necrosis of the capital femoral epiphysis
Definition: "Avascular necrosis of the proximal epiphysis of the femur occurring in growing children and caused by an interruption of the blood supply to the head of the femur close to the hip joint. The necrosis is characteristically associated with flattening of the femoral head, for which reason the term coxa plana has been used to refer to this feature in the medical literature." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:29481348, PMID:30020602]

Name: obsolete Generalized osteoporosis with pathologic fractures
Osteosclerosis of the base of the skull
Definition: "An increase in bone density affecting the basicranium (base of the skull)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lower-limb joint contracture
Definition: "A limitation in the passive range of motion of a joint of the lower limb resulting from loss of elasticity in the periarticular tissues owing to structural changes of non-bony tissues, such as muscles, tendons, ligaments, joint capsules or skin." []

Name: Neonatal epiphyseal stippling
Definition: "The presence of abnormal punctate (speckled, dot-like) calcifications in one or more epiphyses during the neonatal period." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Basilar impression
Definition: "Abnormal elevation of the floor of the posterior fossa including occipital condyles and foramen magnum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:10084535]

Name: Small flat posterior fossa
Definition: "An abnormally small and flat configuration of the posterior cranial fossa." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: 2-4 toe cutaneous syndactyly
Definition: "A soft tissue continuity in the anteroposterior axis between the toes 2, 3, and 4." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fifth finger distal phalanx clinodactyly
Definition: "Bending or curvature of the distal phalanx of little finger in the radial direction (i.e., towards the 4th finger)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the tibia
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the tibia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short forearm
Definition: "Underdevelopment of both forearm bones, the ulna and the radius, resulting in a shortened forearm." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent fourth finger distal interphalangeal crease
Definition: "Absence of the distal interphalangeal flexion creases of the fourth finger." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lumbar platyspondyly
Definition: "A flattened vertebral body shape with reduced distance beween the vertebral endplates affecting the lumbar spine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Generalized osteosclerosis
Definition: "An abnormal increase of bone mineral density with generalized involvement of the skeleton." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cortical thickening of long bone diaphyses
Definition: "Abnormal thickening of the cortex of the diaphyseal region of long bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short humerus
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the humerus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Shortening of all distal phalanges of the toes
Definition: "Abnormally short distal phalanx of toe of all toes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Posterior radial head dislocation
Definition: "A dislocation of the head of the radius from its socket in the elbow joint in an posterior direction." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent distal phalanges

Name: Supernumerary ribs

Name: Postaxial polysyndactyly of foot

Name: Short middle phalanx of finger
Definition: "Short (hypoplastic) middle phalanx of finger, affecting one or more fingers." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Clinodactyly of the 2nd toe
Definition: "Bending or curvature of a second toe in the tibial direction (i.e., towards the big toe)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Flexion contracture of toe

Name: Dysharmonic delayed bone age
Definition: "A type of dysharmonic skeletal maturation in which there is a delay in skeletal maturation whose degree differs markedly in different bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: obsolete Joint swelling onset late infancy
obsolete Joint dislocations in young adult
Calcific stippling of infantile cartilaginous skeleton
Rounded middle phalanx of finger
Definition: "An abnormally round shape of the middle phalanx of the finger." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Diffuse cerebral calcification
Definition: "Generalized deposition of calcium salts within the brain." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Multiple prenatal fractures
Definition: "The presence of bone fractures in the prenatal period that are diagnosed at birth or before." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ulnar radial head dislocation
Definition: "A dislocation of the head of the radius from its socket in the elbow joint in an ulnar direction." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Type E brachydactyly
Definition: "In type E brachydactyly, shortening of the fingers is mainly in the metacarpals and metatarsals." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pseudoarthrosis
Definition: "A pathologic entity characterized by a developmental defect in a long bone leading to bending and pathologic fracture, with inability to form a normal bony callus with subsequent fibrous nonunion, leading to the pseudarthrosis (or \"false joint\")." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Opposable triphalangeal thumb
Definition: "A form of triphalangeal thumb that can be placed opposite the fingers of the same hand." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Metaphyseal enchondromatosis
Definition: "An enchondroma is a benign growth of cartilage that develops within the medullary cavity of bone. Enchondromatosis refers to the presence of multiple enchondromas, and this term refers to the presence of multiple enchondromas within the medulla of metaphyseal bone. Radiographically an enchondroma presents a an oval, linear, or pyramidal osteolytic (radiolucent) lesion with well defined margins." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20661403]

Name: Metaphyseal chondrodysplasia
Definition: "An abnormality of skeletal development characterized by a disturbance of the metaphysis and its histological structure with relatively normal epiphyses and vertebrae." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:335375]

Name: Brachytelomesophalangy
Definition: "Disproportionately short middle and distal phalanges compared to the hand/foot." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Polysyndactyly of hallux
Definition: "Combined syndactyly and polydactyly of the great toe." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Progressive flexion contractures
Definition: "Progressively worsening joint contractures." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Enlarged sagittal diameter of the cervical canal
Congenital finger flexion contractures
Definition: "Multiple bent (flexed) finger joints that cannot be straightened actively or passively." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Metacarpophalangeal synostosis
Definition: "Fusion of a metacarpal bone with the proximal phalanx of the finger distal to it across the corresponding metacarpophalangeal joint." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent ossification of cervical vertebral bodies
Definition: "A lack of bone mineralization of one or more body of cervical vertebra." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aphalangy of the hands
Definition: "Absence of a digit or of one or more phalanges of a finger." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperostosis cranialis interna
Definition: "Bony overgrowth of the internal (endosteal) surface of the calvaria and the base of skull." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Progressive forearm bowing
Definition: "Progressive bending or abnormal curvature of the forearm skeleton." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Double first metacarpals
Definition: "Duplication of the metacarpal I bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Radial deviation of thumb terminal phalanx
Severe generalized osteoporosis
Definition: "Severe degree of osteoporosis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal cervical curvature
Definition: "The presence of an abnormal curvature of the cervical vertebral column." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Delayed pneumatization of the mastoid process
Definition: "An abnormally reduced degree of pneumatization (i.e., formation of air cells) in the mastoid process with respect to age-dependent norms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Rhomboid or triangular shaped 5th finger middle phalanx
Definition: "Rhomboid or triangular shaped 5th (little) finger middle phalanx." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Biliary atresia
Definition: "Atresia of the biliary tree." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia involving the metacarpal bones
Definition: "Aplasia or Hypoplasia affecting the metacarpal bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal metacarpal morphology
Definition: "Any abnormal shape or structure of the metacarpal bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Supernumerary metacarpal bones
Definition: "The presence of more than the normal number of metacarpal bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal finger phalanx morphology
Definition: "Abnormalities affecting the phalanx of finger." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal epiphysis morphology of the phalanges of the hand
Definition: "Abnormality of one or all of the epiphyses of the phalanges of the hand. Note that this includes the epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal. In contrast to the metacarpals 2-5, the first metacarpal is embryologically of phalangeal origin and as such equivalent to the proximal phalanges of the digits 2-5 (whereas the proximal phalanx of the thumb is equivalent to the middle phalanges of the other digits)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: obsolete Abnormal ossification of hand bones
Abnormal hand morphology
Definition: "Any structural anomaly of the hand." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal hand epiphysis morphology
Definition: "Any abnormality of the epiphyses of the phalanges or metacarpal bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal hand cortical bone morphology
Definition: "An anomaly of the outer shell (cortex) of a hand bone." []

Name: Aplasia/hypoplasia involving bones of the hand
Definition: "Absence (due to failure to form) or underdevelopment of the bones of the hand." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal epiphysis morphology
Definition: "An anomaly of epiphysis, which is the expanded articular end of a long bone that developes from a secondary ossification center, and which during the period of growth is either entirely cartilaginous or is separated from the shaft by a cartilaginous disk." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal renal corticomedullary differentiation
Definition: "An abnormality of corticomedullary differentiation (CMD) on diagnostic imaging such as magnetic resonance imaging, computer tomography, or sonography. CMD is a difference in the visualization of cortex and medulla." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:22528889]

Name: Abnormal respiratory motile cilium morphology
Definition: "Abnormal arrangement of the structures of the motile cilium." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, MP:0011050]

Name: Desquamative interstitial pneumonitis
Definition: "Diffuse filling of the distal airsspaces of the lungs, the alveoli, with macrophages. Desquamative interstitial pneumonitis (DIP) is characterized additionally by thickend alveolar septa and by a sparse inflammatory infiltrate that often includes plasma cells and occasional eosinophils. The alveoli are lined by plump cuboidal pneumocytes. Lymphoid aggregates may be present." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7371-8158, PMID:14338290, PMID:16728712, PMID:16738196, PMID:23728865, PMID:25657025]

Name: Bilateral lung agenesis
Definition: "Bilateral lack of development of the lungs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Laryngeal obstruction
Definition: "Blockage of the upper airway at the level of the larynx often accompanied by respiratory distress." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ventilator dependence with inability to wean
Decreased sensitivity to hypoxemia
Definition: "Reduced tendency to respond to a reduced concentration of oxygen in the blood by increasing respiration." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Multiple pulmonary cysts
Definition: "The presence of multiple lung cysts." [PMID:20028879]

Name: Apneic episodes in infancy
Definition: "Recurrent episodes of apnea occurring during infancy." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Laryngeal web
Definition: "A membrane-like structure that extends across the laryngeal lumen close to the level of the vocal cords." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anteroposteriorly shortened larynx
Definition: "Abnormal shortening of the larynx in the anteroposterior (front to back) axis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Impaired gluconeogenesis
Definition: "An impairment of gluconeogenesis." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Hypoargininemia
Definition: "A decreased concentration of arginine in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Intermittent hypothermia
Definition: "Episodes of reduced body termperature." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Temperature instability
Definition: "Disordered thermoregulation characterized by an impaired ability to maintain a balance between heat production and heat loss, with resulting instability of body temperature." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Respiratory acidosis
Definition: "Acidosis because of respiratory retention of carbon dioxide." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fructose intolerance
Definition: "Reduced intestinal absorption of fructose. Breath testing after ingestion of fructose has been widely adopted as a standard method of identifying fructose malabsorption and intolerance. A dose of 25 g of fructose dissolved in a 10% solution is generally accepted as the appropriate dose of fructose for clinical use of H2 and CH4 breath testing. High levels of hydrogen in exhaled breath subsequent hours indicate fructose intolerance. Presence of malabsorption and reproduction of symptoms during a breath test provides the best objective evidence and symptom correlation for fructose intolerance." [PMID:24357350]

Name: Episodic ketoacidosis
Definition: "Intermittent episodes of ketoacidosis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Type II diabetes mellitus
Definition: "A type of diabetes mellitus initially characterized by insulin resistance and hyperinsulinemia and subsequently by glucose interolerance and hyperglycemia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Metabolic ketoacidosis
Definition: "A metabolic acidosis due to accumulation of ketone bodies generally observed in the setting of poor nutritional intake." []

Name: Reduced phenylalanine hydroxylase level
Definition: "A reduction in phenylalanine 4-monooxygenase level." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated maternal serum alpha-fetoprotein
Definition: "An elevation of alpha-feto protein in the maternal serum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Multinodular goiter
Definition: "Enlargement of the thyroid gland related to multiple nodules in the thyroid gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Congenital muscular torticollis
Definition: "A congenital form of torticollis resulting from shortening of the sternocleidomastoid muscle and leading to a limited range of motion in both rotation and lateral bending." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Redundant neck skin
Definition: "Excess skin around the neck, often lying in horizontal folds." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Thyroid hypoplasia
Definition: "Developmental hypoplasia of the thyroid gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Limited neck flexion
Definition: "Reduced abilty to lower the chin towards the chest by bending the neck." []

Name: Nodular goiter
Definition: "Enlargement of the thyroid gland related to one or more nodules in the thyroid gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased adipose tissue around neck
Definition: "Reduced amount of adipose tissue in the region of the neck." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ureteral atresia
Definition: "A developmental defect defined by the failure of the formation of the lumen (tube) of the ureter." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ureteral obstruction
Definition: "Obstruction of the flow of urine through the ureter." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypotrophy of the small hand muscles
Broad phalanx
Definition: "Increased side-to-side width of one or more phalanges of the fingers or toes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cuboidal metacarpal
Definition: "Severely shortened metacarpal with a cuboidal appearance." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Delayed phalangeal epiphyseal ossification
Definition: "Delay in the process of formation and maturation of the epiphysis of one or more phalanx." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Metaphyseal cupping of metacarpals
Definition: "Metaphyseal cupping affecting the metacarpal bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Y-shaped metacarpals
Definition: "Y-shaped metacarpals are the result of a partial fusion of two metacarpal bones, with the two arms of the Y pointing in the distal direction. Y-shaped metacarpals may be seen in combination with polydactyly." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Distal widening of metacarpals
Definition: "Abnormal increase in width of the distal region of the metacarpal bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cone-shaped metacarpal epiphyses
Definition: "A cone-shaped appearance of the epiphyses of the metacarpal bones, producing a 'ball-in-a-socket' appearance. This epiphyses are located at the distal ends of the metacarpal bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Multiple carpal ossification centers
Definition: "A delay in the process of formation and maturation of the epiphysis of one or more long bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Metacarpophalangeal joint contracture
Definition: "A chronic loss of joint motion in metacarpophalangeal joints due to structural changes in muscle, tendons, ligaments, or skin that prevents normal movement." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent proximal finger flexion creases
Definition: "Absence of the proximal interphalangeal flexion creases of the fingers." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Malaligned carpal bone
Definition: "Malalignement of carpal bone angles either with respect to each other, to the corresponding metacarpals or with respect to the wrist (radius and ulna)." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: 3-4 finger syndactyly
Definition: "Syndactyly with fusion of fingers three and four." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Metacarpophalangeal joint hyperextensibility
Definition: "Increased mobility of one ore more metacarpophalangeal joint." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Finger syndactyly
Definition: "Webbing or fusion of the fingers, involving soft parts only or including bone structure. Bony fusions are referred to as \"bony\" Syndactyly if the fusion occurs in a radio-ulnar axis. Fusions of bones of the fingers in a proximo-distal axis are referred to as \"Symphalangism\"." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fingerpad telangiectases
Definition: "Telangiectasia (small dilated blood vessels) located in the fingerpads at the tips of the fingers." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Tapered metacarpals
Definition: "Metacarpal that becomes thinner toward the distal end." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent phalangeal crease
Definition: "Absence of one or more interphalangeal creases (i.e., of the transverse lines in the skin between the phalanges of the fingers)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Shortening of all middle phalanges of the fingers
Definition: "Short, hypoplastic middle phalanx of finger, affecting all fingers." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Expanded phalanges with widened medullary cavities
Multiple palmar creases
Definition: "The presence of multiple creases on the palm of the hand (more than the normal three major creases (distal transverse crease, proximal transverse crease, and thenar crease)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Shortening of all distal phalanges of the fingers
Definition: "Hypoplasia of all of the distal phalanx of finger." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Proximal tapering of metacarpals
Definition: "Some or all of the metacarpal bones (i.e., metacarpal II to V) have a pointed proximal appearance." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Acral ulceration
Definition: "A type of digital ulcer that manifests as an open sore on the surface of the skin at the tip of a finger or toe." [PMID:20862203]

Name: Long proximal phalanx of finger
Definition: "Increased length of the proximal phalanx of finger." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Drumstick terminal phalanges
Definition: "Rounding and broadening of the tufts of the distal phalanges." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Enlarged metacarpal epiphyses
Definition: "Abnormally large size of one or more growth plates (epiphyses) of the metacarpal bones (i.e., the tubular bones of the hand between the carpus and the phalanges)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Premature fusion of phalangeal epiphyses
Definition: "Fusion of the epiphysis and metaphysis of one or more phalanges prior to the normal age or stage of growth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal finger flexion crease
Definition: "Anomalous flexion crease (i.e., a transverse line that crosses the skin of a finger)." []

Name: Shortening of all proximal phalanges of the fingers
Definition: "Congenital hypoplasia of proximal phalanx of finger or all fingers." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Central Y-shaped metacarpal
Definition: "A central Y-shaped metacarpal is the result of a partial fusion of two central metacarpals (i.e., metacarpals 2-4) of the hand, with the two arms of the Y pointing in the distal direction. Central Y-shaped metacarpals may be seen as a result of a central polydactyly with partial fusion of the duplicated metacarpal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Broad metacarpal epiphyses
Definition: "Increased side-to-side width of the metacarpal epiphyses." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Swan neck-like deformities of the fingers
Definition: "A swan neck deformity describes a finger with a hyperextended PIP joint and a flexed DIP joint. The most common cause for a swan neck-like deformity is a disruption of the end of the extensor tendon. Conditions that loosen the PIP joint and allow it to hyperextend, for example conditions that weaken the volar plate, can produce a swan neck deformity of the finger. One example is rheumatoid arthritis. Another cause are conditions that tighten up the small (intrinsic) muscles of the hand and fingers, for example hand trauma or nerve disorders, such as cerebral palsy, Parkinson's disease, or stroke." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Proximal symphalangism of hands
Definition: "The term proximal symphalangism refers to a bony fusion of the middle and proximal phalanges of the digits of the hand, in other words the proximal interphalangeal joint (PIJ) is missing which can be seen either on x-rays or as an absence of the proximal interphalangeal finger creases." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Long phalanx of finger
Definition: "Increased length of multiple or a single phalanx of finger." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ulnar deviation of thumb
Definition: "Bending or curvature of a thumb towards the ulnar side (towards the ring finger)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:10955488]

Name: Mesoaxial hand polydactyly
Definition: "The presence of a supernumerary finger (not a thumb) involving the third or fourth metacarpal with associated osseous syndactyly." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Irregular metacarpals
Definition: "Irregular morphology of one or more metacarpal bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short metacarpals with rounded proximal ends
Soft tissue swelling of interphalangeal joints
Chess-pawn distal phalanges
Definition: "A morphological abnormality of distal phalanges such that they have the appearance of chess pawns." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Flattened, squared-off epiphyses of tubular bones
Metacarpal diaphyseal endosteal sclerosis
Definition: "Increase in bone density in the diaphyseal (shaft) region of a metacarpal bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Two carpal ossification centers present at birth

Name: Radial dysplasia
Definition: "Radial dysplasia, also known as radial longitudinal deficiency, includes radial clubhand and is a disfiguring, and potentially disabling, congenital limb anomaly. The entire upper limb may be involved, although the defect is most evident in the forearm and hand. Affected children suffer a variable degree of hypoplasia or absence of the preaxial skeleton and soft tissues, in particular the thumb, radius, and dorsoradial soft tissues. The hand is usually radially deviated and subluxated off the distal aspect of the ulna, the ulna may be shortened and have a bow-shaped deformity, and there is no true wrist (radiocarpal) joint in Bayne2 type-III and IV radial dysplasia." [PMID:29257019]

Name: Diverticulosis of trachea
Definition: "Tracheal diverticula are blind-ended outpouchings arising from the trachea. They are usually an incidental finding. Occasionally they can mimic pneumomediastinum. Tracheal diverticula are either congenital or acquired, in the latter case the most common causes are prolonged increased intraluminal pressure, e.g. chronic cough, COPD, tracheomalacia, and iatrogenic (e.g. post-surgical)." [PMID:18544671, PMID:27867581]

Name: Hypersensitivity pneumonitis
Definition: "Hypersensitivity pneumonitis involves inhalation of an antigen. This leads to an exaggerated immune response and a following inflammation of the alveoli within the lungs. The main feature of chronic hypersensitivity pneumonitis on lung biopsies is expansion of the interstitium by lymphocytes accompanied by an occasional multinucleated giant cell or loose granuloma. After exposure to the provoking antigen, following symptoms can be seen: fever, chills, malaise, cough, hemoptysis, chest tightness, dyspnea, rash, swelling and headache and can be completely reversible, based on the duration of the illness, categorized as acute (HP:0011009), subacute (HP:0011011), and chronic (HP:0011010)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0113-912X, PMID:15316440, PMID:16635083, PMID:18051218]

Name: Intraalveolar phospholipid accumulation

Name: Pulmonary venous occlusion

Name: Alveolar cell carcinoma
Definition: "Adenocarcinoma of the Bronchus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pulmonary lymphangiectasia
Definition: "Abnormal dilatation of the pulmonary lymphatic vessels. Lymphatic fluid in the lung is derived from normal leakage of fluid out of the blood capillaries in the lung. In pulmonary lymphangiectasia, the pulmonary lymphatics are not properly connected and become dilated with fluid." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lymphocytic interstitial pneumonia
Definition: "Lymphocytic interstitial pneumonitis is a benign lymphoproliferative disorder of the lung that is characterized by the presence of a dense, predominantly lymphocytic interstitial infiltrate (lymphocytes, plasma cells, other elements of the lymphoreticular system) that expands the alveolar septa." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:32040879]

Name: Chronic lung disease

Name: Abnormal pulmonary lymphatics
Definition: "An abnormality of the pulmonary lymphatic chain." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal pulmonary interstitial morphology
Definition: "Abnormality of the lung parenchyma extending to the pulmonary interstitium and leading to diffuse pulmonary fibrosis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Recurrent pneumonia

Name: Recurrent intrapulmonary hemorrhage

Name: Airway obstruction

Definition: "A type of pulmonary sequestration that is completely enclosed in its own pleural sac, occurring above, within, or below the diaphragm, and without communication with the tracheobronchial tree." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pulmonary arteriovenous malformation
Definition: "Pulmonary arteriovenous malformation, a condition most commonly associated with hereditary hemorrhagic telangiectasia, is an abnormal communication between the pulmonary artery and pulmonary vein without an intervening capillary communication. HRCT images usually show a coarse spidery appearance of the peripheral vascular markings in the lungs. More specific findings are obtained in the pulmonary angiogram where the normally invisible capillary phase is replaced by irregular vascular channels bridging the peripheral branches of pulmonary arteries and veins." [PMID:30386957, PMID:788535]

Name: Acute hepatic failure
Definition: "Hepatic failure refers to the inability of the liver to perform its normal synthetic and metabolic functions, which can result in coagulopathy and alteration in the mental status of a previously healthy individual. Hepatic failure is defined as acute if there is onset of encephalopathy within 8 weeks of the onset of symptoms in a patient with a previously healthy liver." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Diffuse hepatic steatosis
Definition: "A diffuse form of hepatic steatosis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased mitochondrial complex III activity in liver tissue
Definition: "Decreased activity of complex III of the mitochondrion in the liver." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hepatic calcification
Definition: "The presence of abnormal calcium deposition in the liver." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Biliary hyperplasia
Definition: "Hyperplasia of the biliary tree, as manifested by increased size of bile ducts, dilated lumen, and histologically by an increased number of epithelial cells or hyperplasia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Viral hepatitis
Definition: "Inflammation of the liver due to infection with a virus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Malformation of the hepatic ductal plate
Fluctuating hepatomegaly
Definition: "Intermittently increased size of the liver." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased hepatocellular lipid droplets
Definition: "An abnormal increase in the amount of intracellular lipid droplets in hepatocytes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased hepatic glycogen content
Definition: "An increase in the amount of glycogen stored in hepatocytes compared to normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Reduced number of intrahepatic bile ducts
Definition: "The presence of reduced numbers of intrahepatic bile duct than normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Acute hepatic steatosis
Definition: "An acute form of hepatic steatosis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Macronodular cirrhosis
Definition: "A type of cirrhosis characterized by the presence of large regenerative nodules." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Prolonged neonatal jaundice
Definition: "Neonatal jaundice refers to a yellowing of the skin and other tissues of a newborn infant as a result of increased concentrations of bilirubin in the blood. Neonatal jaundice affects over half of all newborns to some extent in the first week of life. Prolonged neonatal jaundice is said to be present if the jaundice persists for longer than 14 days in term infants and 21 days in preterm infants." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Portal fibrosis
Definition: "Fibroblast proliferation and fiber expansion from the portal areas to the lobule." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Depletion of mitochondrial DNA in liver
Definition: "An abnormal reduction in the number of mitochondria in hepatocytes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Reye syndrome-like episodes
Definition: "Repeated occurrences of acute noninflammatory encephalopathy and fatty degenerative liver failure." []

Name: Congenital pseudoarthrosis of the clavicle
Definition: "The two portions of the clavicle (corresponding to the two primary ossification centers of the clavicle) are connected by a fibrous bridge that is contiguous with the periosteum, and a synovial membrane develops, resulting in a clavicle with a bipartite appearance radiographically. Congenital pseudarthrosis of the clavicle generally presents as a painless mass or swelling over the clavicle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:22295044]

Name: Straight clavicles
Definition: "An abnormally straight configuration of the clavicle, a tubular bone which normally is doubly curved ." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Premature sternal synostosis
Definition: "Prematurely closed sternal sutures." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:13542801]

Name: Absent glenoid fossa
Definition: "Lack of development of the glenoid fossa, also known as the glenoid cavity, which is the articular surface of the scapula that articulates with the head of the humerus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Scapulohumeral synostosis
Definition: "Bony fusion between the humerus and scapula, leading to an impairment in mobility of the affected shoulder joint." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Diaphragmatic paralysis
Definition: "The presence of a paralyzed diaphragm." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:3612666]

Name: Irregular ossification at anterior rib ends
Irregular chondrocostal junctions
Definition: "Irregular surface of the normally relatively smooth border between the distal part of the ribs and the costal cartilages, which are bars of hyaline cartilage that connect the ribs to the sternum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Precocious costochondral ossification
Definition: "Early ossification of the costochondral junction, which is the joint between the ribs and costal cartilage in the front of the rib cage." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:10489169]

Name: Midclavicular hypoplasia
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the middle portion of the clavicle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Wide intermamillary distance
Definition: "A larger than usual distance between the left and right nipple." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased number of sternal ossification centers
Definition: "A less than normal number of sternal ossification centers. The sternum is initially formed from bilateral sternal plates that chondrify and begin to fuse with ribs at 10 weeks gestational age. Ossification starts in the manubrium and upper part of the sternal body at the 6th month, in the middle of the sternal body at the 7th month, in the lower part of the body during the 1st postnatal year and in the xiphoid process between years 5 and 18. The number of ossification centers vary up to six, and it is the ossification centers that are visualized by prenatal ultrasound. This term describes a reduction in the number of ossification centers compared with age-related norms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:10204210]

Name: Absent in utero rib ossification
Definition: "Lack of formation and mineralization of the ribs in utero." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anterior rib punctate calcifications
Definition: "Deposition of calcium salts in point-like foci within the anterior portion of one or more ribs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Costochondral joint sclerosis
Definition: "Abnormal increase in density of the tissue at the costochondral junctions." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Multifocal breast carcinoma
Definition: "Breast carcinoma that is bilateral or otherwise multifocal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent sternal ossification
Definition: "Lack of formation of mineralized bony tissue of the sternum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Glenoid fossa hypoplasia
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the glenoid fossa, which is the cavity in the lateral part of the scapula which articulates with the head of the humerus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Osteosclerosis of ribs
Definition: "Osteosclerosis of ribs (increased density related to increased bone mass)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Midclavicular aplasia
Definition: "Developmental defect resulting in congenital absence of the middle portion of the clavicle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Multiple rib fractures
Definition: "More than one fracture of the ribs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thin clavicles
Definition: "Abnormally reduced diameter (cross section) of the clavicles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Costal cartilage calcification
Definition: "Calcification of the costal cartilages, which are bars of hyaline cartilage found at the anterior ends of the ribs which serve to prolong the ribs forward and contribute to the elasticity of the walls of the thorax." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Costochondral pain
Definition: "Chest wall pain in the area of the costochondral junctions." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thickening of the lateral border of the scapula
Aplastic clavicle
Definition: "Absence of the clavicles as a developmental defect." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Coat hanger sign of ribs
Definition: "An abnormal morphology of the ribs consisting of shorted, abnormally curved ribs. On posteroanterior chest radiography, the ribs show a curvature resembling that of a coat hanger (clothes hanger)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:12712270, PMID:21607596]

Name: Prolonged QRS complex
Definition: "Increased time for the complex comprised of the Q wave, R wave, and S wave as measured by the electrocardiogram (EKG).. In adults, normal values are 0.06 - 0.10 sec." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Granulomatous coronary arteritis
Definition: "Inflammation of the coronary arteries involving a granulomatous response, i.e., a non-specific inflammatory response involving granulomas, defined as a compact organized collection of mature mononuclear phagocytes including epithelioid and giant cells." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:937513]

Name: Premature ventricular contraction
Definition: "Premature ventricular contractions (PVC) or ventricular extrasystoles are premature contractions of the heart that arise in response to an impulse in the ventricles rather than the normal impulse from the sinoatrial (SA) node." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:30422584, PMID:32063472, PMID:32528299]

Name: Abnormal ventricular filling
Definition: "An abnormality of filling of a ventricle with blood during diastole." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ventricular preexcitation with multiple accessory pathways
Definition: "A form of ventricular preexcitation due to the presence of multiple accessory pathways for cardiac conduction." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Endocardial fibrosis
Definition: "The presence of excessive connective tissue in the endocardium." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:29043203]

Name: Aortic tortuosity
Definition: "Abnormal tortuous (i.e., twisted) form of the aorta." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bacterial endocarditis
Definition: "A bacterial infection of the endocardium, the inner layer of the heart, which usually involves the heart valves." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Myocardial calcification
Definition: "Calcium deposition in the myocardium." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pulmonic valve myxoma
Definition: "A benign tumor of connective tissue containing mucous or gelatinous material (myxoma) localized in the pumonic valve." [PMID:35420369]

Name: Short chordae tendineae of the tricuspid valve
Definition: "Abnormally short chordae tendineae of the tricuspid valve." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Myocardial steatosis
Definition: "Steatosis in the myocardium." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Early progressive calcific cardiac valvular disease
Atrioventricular canal defect
Definition: "A defect of the atrioventricular septum of the heart." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:12632326]

Name: Dilatation of the ventricular cavity
Definition: "A localized outpouching of ventricular cavity that is generally associated with dyskinesia and paradoxical expansion during systole." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Premature atrial contractions
Definition: "A type of cardiac arrhythmia with premature atrial contractions or beats caused by signals originating from ectopic atrial sites." []

Name: Coronary artery dissection
Definition: "Acute occurrence of a dissection (tear within the tunica intima and entry of blood into the tunica media) of a coronary artery." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20448134]

Name: Abnormal coronary artery morphology
Definition: "Any structural abnormality of the coronary arteries." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal atrioventricular valve morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of an atrioventricular valve." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the hepatic vasculature
Definition: "An abnormality of the hepatic vasculature." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the clavicles
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the clavicles (collar bones)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia involving bones of the thorax
Acute lymphoblastic leukemia
Definition: "A form of acute leukemia characterized by excess lympoblasts." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pancreatic adenocarcinoma
Definition: "The presence of an adenocarcinoma of the pancreas." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: T-cell acute lymphoblastic leukemias
Definition: "Acute lymphoblastic leukemia of T-cell origin. It comprises about 15% of childhood cases and 25% of adult cases. It is more common in males than females." [NCIT:C3183]

Name: Follicular thyroid carcinoma
Definition: "The presence of an follicular adenocarcinoma of the thyroid gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Papillary renal cell carcinoma type 2
Definition: "A type of papillary renal cell carcinoma in which the papillae are covered by large eosinophilic cells with pleomorphic nuclei, prominent nucleoli, and nuclear pseudostratification." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9113-2978, PMID:12429790]

Name: Acute megakaryocytic leukemia
Definition: "A rare subtype of acute myeloid leukemia evolving from primitive megakaryoblasts." []

Name: Renal cortical adenoma
Definition: "The presence of an adenoma in the cortex of the kidney." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Extraadrenal pheochromocytoma
Definition: "Pheochromocytoma not originating from the adrenal medulla but from another source such as from chromaffin cells in or about sympathetic ganglia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Squamous cell carcinoma of the skin
Definition: "Squamous cell carcinoma of the skin is a malignant tumor of squamous epithelium." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Transitional cell carcinoma of the bladder
Definition: "The presence of a carcinoma of the urinary bladder with origin in a transitional epithelial cell." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Adrenocortical carcinoma
Definition: "A malignant neoplasm of the adrenal cortex that may produce hormones such as cortisol, aldosterone, estrogen, or testosterone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Adrenal pheochromocytoma
Definition: "Pheochromocytoma originating from the adrenal medulla." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Paraspinal neurofibroma
Definition: "A neurofibroma (benign peripheral nerve sheath tumor) localized adjacent to the spine." []

Name: Neoplasm of the stomach
Definition: "A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the stomach." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cutaneous leiomyosarcoma
Definition: "The presence of leiomyosarcoma of the skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Malignant genitourinary tract tumor
Definition: "The presence of a malignant neoplasm of the genital system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Renal pelvic carcinoma
Definition: "The presence of a carcinoma in the renal pelvis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Chondrosarcoma
Definition: "A slowly growing malignant neoplasm derived from cartilage cells." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Papillary renal cell carcinoma
Definition: "The presence of renal cell carcinoma in the renal papilla." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pituitary prolactin cell adenoma
Definition: "A type of pituitary adenoma originating in prolactin secreting cells. This kind of adenoma is characterized by overproduction of prolactin, and may cause loss of menstrual periods and breast milk production in women." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Clear cell renal cell carcinoma
Definition: "A subtype of renal cell carcinoma thought to originate from mature renal tubular cells in the proximal tubule of the nehpron." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9113-2978]

Name: Duodenal adenocarcinoma
Definition: "A malignant epithelial tumor with a glandular organization that originates in the duodenum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Renal angiomyolipoma
Definition: "A benign renal neoplasm composed of fat, vascular, and smooth muscle elements." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ovarian papillary adenocarcinoma
Definition: "The presence of a papillary adenocarcinoma of the ovary." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Multiple myeloma
Definition: "A malignant plasma cell tumor growing within soft tissue or within the skeleton." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Benign genitourinary tract neoplasm
Definition: "A non-malignant neoplasm of the genitourinary system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Parathyroid carcinoma
Definition: "A malignancy of the parathyroid glands. Parathyroid carcinoma usually secretes parathyroid hormone, leading to hyperparathyroidism." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hurthle cell thyroid adenoma
Definition: "A kind of thyroid adenoma characterized by the presence of oxyphil cells." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Paranasal sinus hypoplasia
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the paranasal sinuses." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Limb-girdle muscular dystrophy
Definition: "Muscular dystrophy affecting the muscles of the limb girdle (the hips and shoulders)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Loss of ability to walk in first decade
Abnormal anterior horn cell morphology
Definition: "Any anomaly of the anterior horn cell." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cerebral hypomyelination
Definition: "Reduced amount of myelin in the nervous system resulting from defective myelinogenesis in the white matter of the central nervous system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: White mater abnormalities in the posterior periventricular region
Focal hemiclonic seizure
Definition: "A type of focal clonic seizure characterized by sustained rhythmic jerking rapidly involves one side of the body at seizure onset." []

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the cerebellar vermis
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the vermis of cerebellum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: 4-layered lissencephaly
Definition: "A form of lissencephaly in which the cortex is thickened and has four more or less disorganized layers rather than six normal layers resulting from incomplete neuronal migration during brain development. At neuropathological examination, a 4-layered cortex consists of an upper molecular layer, a second thin cellular layer containing pyramidal neurons usually observed in layer V, a third pale poorly cellular layer and a fourth thick deep layer made up of neurons which had failed to migrate. Radiologocally would manifest as agyria or pachygyria with cortical thickness greater than 10 mm." [http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q90573458, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:28440899]

Name: Frontal polymicrogyria
Definition: "A type of polymicrogyria with a gradient of severity (anterior more severe than posterior) extending from frontal poles posteriorly to precentral gyrus and inferiorly to frontal operculum." [http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q90573458, PMID:20301504]

Name: Pallor of dorsal columns of the spinal cord
Definition: "An abnormally pale appearance of the dorsal portion of the gray substance of the spinal cord. This finding can be observed by histological examination." []

Name: Severe muscular hypotonia
Definition: "A severe degree of muscular hypotonia characterized by markedly reduced muscle tone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: obsolete Severe neonatal hypotonia in males
Developmental stagnation at onset of seizures
Definition: "A cessation of the development of a child in the areas of motor skills, speech and language, cognitive skills, and social and/or emotional skills, following the onset of epilepsy." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Congenital Horner syndrome
Definition: "A type of Horner syndrome with congenital onset." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent patellar reflexes
Definition: "Absence of the knee jerk reflex, which can normally be elicited by tapping the patellar tendon with a reflex hammer just below the patella." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypodysplasia of the corpus callosum
Definition: "Developmental defect characterized by a small and malformed corpus callosum." []

Name: Hypoplasia of the ventral pons
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the ventral portion of the pons." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Symmetric spinal nerve root neurofibromas
Definition: "Multiple neurofibromas of the spinal nerve roots with a symmetric distribution." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Episodic generalized hypotonia
Definition: "The occurrence of repeated episodes of generalized muscular hypotonia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cerebellar vermis atrophy
Definition: "Wasting (atrophy) of the vermis of cerebellum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Impaired distal proprioception
Definition: "A loss or impairment of the sensation of the relative position of parts of the body and joint position occuring at distal joints." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Severe expressive language delay
Definition: "A severe delay in the acquisition of the ability to use language to communicate needs, wishes, or thoughts." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6410-0882]

Name: Sensorimotor polyneuropathy affecting arms more than legs
Lobar holoprosencephaly
Definition: "A type of holoprosencephaly in which most of the right and left cerebral hemispheres and lateral ventricles are separated but the most rostral aspect of the telencephalon, the frontal lobes, are fused, especially ventrally." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:GC_HPE]

Name: Cerebral hypoplasia
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the cerebrum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Symmetrical progressive peripheral demyelination
Definition: "A symmetric and progressive loss of myelin from the internode regions along myelinated nerve fibers of the peripheral nervous system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pontocerebellar atrophy
Definition: "Atrophy affecting the pons and the cerebellum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cerebellar hemangioblastoma
Definition: "A hemangioblastoma of the cerebellum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Diffuse peripheral demyelination
Definition: "A diffuse loss of myelin from the internode regions along myelinated nerve fibers of the peripheral nervous system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Impaired distal vibration sensation
Definition: "A decrease in the ability to perceive vibration in the distal portions of the limbs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Intellectual disability, progressive
Definition: "The term progressive intellectual disability should be used if intelligence decreases/deteriorates over time." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Intellectual disability, borderline
Definition: "Borderline intellectual disability is defined as an intelligence quotient (IQ) in the range of 70-85." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20537050]

Name: Frontotemporal cerebral atrophy
Definition: "Atrophy (wasting, decrease in size of cells or tissue) affecting the frontotemporal cerebrum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypnopompic hallucinations
Definition: "Fleeting perceptual experiences that occur during the transition from sleep to wakefulness." [PMID:27358492]

Name: Abducens palsy
Definition: "Malfunction of the abducens nerve as manifested by impairment of the ability of the affected eye to be moved outward. Patients who develop abducens nerve palsy often present with binocular horizontal diplopia, which is a double vision when looking at objects side by side. There will be a notable weakness of the ipsilateral lateral rectus muscle leading to a deficit in of eye abduction on the affected side. Some patients may present with a constant head turning movement to maintain binocular fusion and to lessen the degree of diplopia." [PMID:29489275]

Name: Congenital intracerebral calcification
Definition: "The presence of calcium deposition within brain structures that is present already at the time of birth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Frontal cortical atrophy
Definition: "Atrophy of the frontal cortex." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Intraaxonal accumulation of curvilinear autofluorescent lipopigment storage material
Definition: "Curvilinear intracellular accumulation of autofluorescent lipopigment storage material within axons." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal aggressive, impulsive or violent behavior
Axial muscle stiffness
Definition: "Stiffness (a condition in which muscles cannot be moved quickly without accompanying pain or spasm) of the axial musculature." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Unilateral polymicrogyria
Definition: "Excessive number of small gyri (convolutions) on the surface of one side of the brain." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoglycemic encephalopathy
Definition: "Brain damage related to a lowering of blood glucose below a critical level (around 30 mg/dl), which may lead to confusion, lethargy and delirium followed by seizures and coma. Prolonged hypoglycemia may lead to irreversible brain damage." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Frontoparietal cortical dysplasia
Definition: "The presence of developmental dysplasia of the cortex of frontal lobe and the cortex of parietal lobe." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pericallosal lipoma
Definition: "Pericallosal lipomas are congenital soft masses of adipose cells encapsulated by a thin layer of fibrous tissue, appearing adjacent to the corpus callosum of the brain." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3302-4610, PMID:30104143]

Name: Congenital nystagmus
Definition: "Nystagmus dating from or present at birth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Impaired distal tactile sensation
Definition: "A reduced sense of touch (tactile sensation) on the skin of the distal limbs. This is usually tested with a wisp of cotton or a fine camel's hair brush, by asking patients to say 'now' each time they feel the stimulus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Impaired vibration sensation at ankles
Definition: "A decrease in the ability to perceive vibration at the ankles. Clinically, this is usually tested with a tuning fork which vibrates at 128 Hz and is applied to the malleoli of the ankles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abolished vibration sense
Definition: "A complete loss of the ability to perceive vibration." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Recurrent meningitis
Definition: "An increased susceptibility to meningitis as manifested by a medical history of recurrent episodes of meningitis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Olivopontocerebellar hypoplasia
Definition: "Hypoplasia of the cerebellum, pontine nuclei, and inferior olivary nucleus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: obsolete Loss of ability to walk
Abnormal auditory evoked potentials
Definition: "An abnormality of the auditory evoked potentials, which are used to trace the signal generated by a sound, from the cochlear nerve, through the lateral lemniscus, to the medial geniculate nucleus, and to the cortex." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Proximal spinal muscular atrophy
Definition: "Proximal spinal muscular atrophy, i.e., muscular weakness and atrophy related to loss of the motor neurons of the spinal cord and brainstem." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Choroid plexus calcification
Definition: "The presence of calcium deposition in the choroid plexus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Gait instability, worse in the dark
Periventricular leukomalacia
Definition: "Periventricular leukomalacia is characterized by diffuse injury of deep cerebral white matter, accompanied in its most severe form by focal necrosis. The neuropathologic hallmarks of PVL are microglial activation and focal and diffuse periventricular depletion of premyelinating oligodendroglia." [PMID:16808630, PMID:18852342, PMID:28406931]

Name: Necrotizing encephalopathy
Definition: "A type of encephalopathy (brain disease, damage, or malfunction accompanied by an altered mental state) that is characterized by evidence of necrosis of brain tissue." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:KI_phemming, PMID:23705127]

Name: Deficit in grammar
Definition: "Deficit in grammar, including syntax and morphology." []

Name: Sleep-wake cycle disturbance
Definition: "Any abnormal alteration of an individual's circadian rhythm that affects the timing of sleeping and being awake." []

Name: Progressive leukoencephalopathy
Definition: "Leukoencephalopathy that gets more severe with time." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: obsolete Distal sensory loss of all modalities
Alobar holoprosencephaly
Definition: "A type of holoprosencephaly characterized by the presence of a single ventricle and no separation of the cerebral hemisphere. The single midline ventricle is often greatly enlarged." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:GC_HPE]

Name: Dysplastic corpus callosum
Definition: "Dysplasia and dysgenesis of the corpus callosum are nonspecific descriptions that imply defective development of the corpus callosum. The term dysplasia is applied when the morphology of the corpus callosum is altered as a congenital trait. For instance, the corpus callosum may be hump-shaped, kinked, or a striped corpus callosum that lacks an anatomically distinct genu and splenium." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:21263138]

Name: Myelin-dependent gliosis
Definition: "A type of gliosis that occurs in the vicinity of injured neurons." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Basal ganglia gliosis
Definition: "Focal proliferation of glial cells in the basal ganglia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Loss of Purkinje cells in the cerebellar vermis
Motor axonal neuropathy
Definition: "Progressive impairment of function of motor axons with muscle weakness, atrophy, and cramps. The deficits are length-dependent, meaning that muscles innervated by the longest nerves are affected first, so that for instance the arms are affected at a later age than the onset of deficits involving the lower leg." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cavitation of the basal ganglia
Definition: "The formation of small cavities in the tissue of the basal ganglia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:8516046]

Name: Poor fine motor coordination
Definition: "An abnormality of the ability (skills) to perform a precise movement of small muscles with the intent to perform a specific act. Fine motor skills are required to mediate movements of the wrists, hands, fingers, feet, and toes." []

Name: Fourth cranial nerve palsy
Definition: "Paralysis of the fourth cranial (trochlear) nerve manifested as weakness of the superior oblique muscle which causes vertical diplopia that is maximal when the affected eye is adducted and directed inferiorly." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Poor gross motor coordination
Definition: "An abnormality of the ability (skills) to perform a precise movement of large muscles with the intent to perform a specific act. Gross motor skills are required to mediate movements of the arms, legs, and other large body parts." []

Name: Attention deficit hyperactivity disorder
Definition: "Attention deficit hyperactivity disorder (ADHD) manifests at age 2-3 years or by first grade at the latest. The main symptoms are distractibility, impulsivity, hyperactivity, and often trouble organizing tasks and projects, difficulty going to sleep, and social problems from being aggressive, loud, or impatient." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pain insensitivity
Definition: "Inability to perceive painful stimuli." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Antenatal intracerebral hemorrhage
Definition: "Cerebral hemorrhage that occurs before birth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pseudobulbar paralysis
Definition: "Bilateral impairment of the function of the cranial nerves 9-12, which control musculature involved in eating, swallowing, and speech. Pseudobulbar paralysis is characterized clinically by dysarthria, dysphonia, and dysphagia with bifacial paralysis, and may be accompanied by Pseudobulbar behavioral symptoms such as enforced crying and laughing." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Poorly formed metencephalon
Definition: "A morphological abnormality of the metencephalon." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cerebral berry aneurysm
Definition: "A small, sac-like aneurysm (outpouching) of a cerebral blood vessel." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cerebellar dysplasia
Definition: "Cerebellar dysplasia (abnormal growth or development) is defined by abnormal cerebellar foliation, white matter arborization, and gray-white matter junction. Cerebellar dysplasia is a neuroimaging finding that describes abnormalities of both the cerebellar cortex and white matter and is associated with variable neurodevelopmental outcome. Dysplasia may globally involve the cerebellum or affect only one cerebellar hemisphere. In addition, cerebellar dysplasia may be associated with cortical/subcortical cysts." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:25105227, PMID:27160001]

Name: Symmetric lesions of the basal ganglia
Chronic lymphocytic meningitis
Definition: "Meningitis that persists for more than 4 weeks, and lymphocytes are present in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF)." [PMID:27608867]

Name: Atrophy of the dentate nucleus
Definition: "Partial or complete wasting (loss) of dentate nucleus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Large basal ganglia
Definition: "Increased size of the basal ganglia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Proximal hyperreflexia
Definition: "Hyperactive stretch reflexes of muscles that move proximal joints (elbow, knee)." []

Name: Generalized cerebral atrophy/hypoplasia
Definition: "Generalized atrophy or hypoplasia of the cerebrum." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Aplasia of the inferior half of the cerebellar vermis
Progressive language deterioration
Definition: "Progressive loss of previously present language abilities." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Disorganization of the anterior cerebellar vermis
Proximal limb muscle stiffness
Definition: "Stiffness of the limbs (a condition in which muscles cannot be moved quickly without accompanying pain or spasm) occurring in the proximal limb muscle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Distal peripheral sensory neuropathy
Definition: "Peripheral sensory neuropathy affecting primarily distal sensation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Inferior cerebellar vermis hypoplasia
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the inferior portion of the vermis of cerebellum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16580298]

Name: Thick corpus callosum
Definition: "Increased vertical dimension of the corpus callosum. This feature can be visualized by sagittal sections on magnetic resonance tomography imaging of the brain." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:KI_phemming, PMID:10029348]

Name: Extrapyramidal muscular rigidity
Definition: "Muscular rigidity (continuous contraction of muscles with constant resistance to passive movement)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased amplitude of sensory action potentials
Definition: "A reduction in the amplitude of sensory nerve action potential. This feature is measured by nerve conduction studies." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Dilated third ventricle
Definition: "An increase in size of the third ventricle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Facial-lingual fasciculations
Definition: "Fasciculations affecting the tongue muscle and the musculature of the face." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Paroxysmal choreoathetosis
Definition: "Episodes of choreoathetosis that can occur following triggers such as quick voluntary movements." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Chiari type I malformation
Definition: "Arnold-Chiari type I malformation refers to a relatively mild degree of herniation of the posteroinferior region of the cerebellum (the cerebellar tonsils) into the cervical canal with little or no displacement of the fourth ventricle. It is characterized by one or both pointed (not rounded) cerebellar tonsils that project 5 mm below the foramen magnum, measured by a line drawn from the basion to the opisthion (McRae Line)" [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:28613730]

Name: Hypointensity of cerebral white matter on MRI
Definition: "A darker than expected signal on magnetic resonance imaging emanating from the cerebral white matter." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Infantile encephalopathy
Definition: "Encephalopathy with onset in the infantile period." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Segmental peripheral demyelination
Definition: "A loss of myelin from the internode regions along myelinated nerve fibers from segments of the peripheral nervous system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Demyelinating peripheral neuropathy
Definition: "Demyelinating neuropathy is characterized by slow nerve conduction velocities with reduced amplitudes of sensory/motor nerve conduction and prolonged distal latencies." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Temporal cortical atrophy
Definition: "Atrophy of the temporal cortex." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Subcortical dementia
Definition: "A particular type of dementia characterized by a pattern of mental defects consisting prominently of forgetfulness, slowness of thought processes, and personality or mood change." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:4819905]

Name: Proximal amyotrophy
Definition: "Amyotrophy (muscular atrophy) affecting the proximal musculature." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Acute demyelinating polyneuropathy
Definition: "Acute progressive areflexic weakness and mild sensory changes resulting from myelin breakdown and axonal degeneration." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pallidal degeneration
Definition: "Neurodegeneration involving the globus pallidus,a part of the basal ganglia that is involved in the regulation of voluntary movement." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Distal upper limb amyotrophy
Definition: "Muscular atrophy of distal arm muscles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Asymmetric limb muscle stiffness
Definition: "Stiffness of the limbs (a condition in which muscles cannot be moved quickly without accompanying pain or spasm) occurring in an asymmetric pattern." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Progressive extrapyramidal muscular rigidity
Definition: "A progressive degree of muscular rigidity (continuous contraction of muscles with constant resistance to passive movement)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Diffuse demyelination of the cerebral white matter
Definition: "A diffuse loss of myelin from nerve fibers in the central nervous system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: obsolete Corticospinal tract disease in lower limbs
Periventricular heterotopia
Definition: "A form of gray matter heterotopia were the mislocalized gray matter is typically located periventricularly, also sometimes called subependymal heterotopia. Periventricular means beside the ventricles. This is by far the most common location for heterotopia. Subependymal heterotopia present in a wide array of variations. There can be a small single node or a large number of nodes, can exist on either or both sides of the brain at any point along the higher ventricle margins, can be small or large, single or multiple, and can form a small node or a large wavy or curved mass." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:22427329]

Name: Paroxysmal dyskinesia
Definition: "Episodic bouts of involuntary movements with dystonic, choreic, ballistic movements, or a combination thereof. There is no loss of consciousness during the attacks." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent smooth pursuit
Definition: "A complete lack of the ability to track objects with the ocular smooth pursuit system, a class of rather slow eye movements that minimizes retinal target motion." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Interosseus muscle atrophy
Definition: "Atrophy of the interosseus muscles (including the palmar interossei that lie on the anterior aspect of the metacarpals, the dorsal interosseus muscles of the hand, which lie between the intercarpals, the plantar interosseus muscles, which lie underneath the metatarsal bones, and the dorsal interossei, which are located between the metatarsal bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Peripheral hypomyelination
Definition: "Reduced amount of myelin in the nervous system resulting from defective myelinogenesis in the peripheral nervous system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Focal T2 hyperintense basal ganglia lesion
Definition: "A lighter than expected T2 signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the basal ganglia. This term refers to a localized hyperintensity affecting a particular region of the basal ganglia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Focal lissencephaly
Definition: "A congenital absence of the convolutions of the cerebral cortex and a poorly formed sylvian fissure that affects a particular part of the cortex." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:KI_phemming]

Name: Congenital facial diplegia
Definition: "Facial diplegia (that is, bilateral facial palsy) with congenital onset." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Neuronal loss in the cerebral cortex
Bilateral tonic-clonic seizure on awakening
Definition: "Bilateral tonic-clonic seizure of either generalized or focal onset occurring on or soon after wakening (typically within 90 minutes of waking, regardless of the time of day)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:24395517, PMID:26948972]

Name: Cerebral artery atherosclerosis
Definition: "The formation of the formation of fibrofatty lesions in the wall of an artery located in the brain." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:31420554]

Name: Hemimegalencephaly
Definition: "Enlargement of all or parts of one cerebral hemisphere." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:17416820]

Name: Photosensitive tonic-clonic seizure
Definition: "Generalized-onset tonic-clonic seizures that are provoked by flashing or flickering light." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:28276060]

Name: Irregular myelin loops
Definition: "Presence of irregular redundant loops of focally folded myelin in a peripheral nerve." [PMID:20301641, PMID:8817346]

Name: Facial paralysis
Definition: "Complete loss of ability to move facial muscles innervated by the facial nerve (i.e., the seventh cranial nerve)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lower limb amyotrophy
Definition: "Muscular atrophy affecting the lower limb." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Periodic hyperkalemic paralysis
Definition: "Episodes of muscle weakness associated with elevated levels of potassium in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Demyelinating motor neuropathy
Definition: "Demyelination of peripheral motor nerves." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Macrogyria
Definition: "Increased size of cerebral gyri, often associated with a moderate reduction in the number of sulci of the cerebrum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Intracerebral periventricular calcifications
Definition: "The presence of calcium deposition in the cerebral white matter surrounding the cerebral ventricles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased distal sensory nerve action potential
Definition: "A reduction in the amplitude of sensory nerve action potential in distal nerve segments. This feature is measured by nerve conduction studies." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Spinocerebellar tract disease in lower limbs
Clusters of axonal regeneration
Definition: "Groups of small caliber axons in peripheral nerve biospies indicative of axonal regeneration." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jbaets]

Name: Progressive gait ataxia
Definition: "A type of gait ataxia displaying progression of clinical severity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased number of small peripheral myelinated nerve fibers
Recurrent external ophthalmoplegia
Definition: "Alternating and recurrent weakness of the external ocular muscles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal pyramidal sign
Definition: "Functional neurological abnormalities related to dysfunction of the pyramidal tract." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Severe demyelination of the white matter
Definition: "A severe loss of myelin from nerve fibers in the central nervous system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Type II lissencephaly
Definition: "A form of lissencephaly characterized by an uneven cortical surface with a so called 'cobblestone' appearace. There are no distinguishable cortical layers." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Symmetric peripheral demyelination
Definition: "A symmetric loss of myelin from the internode regions along myelinated nerve fibers of the peripheral nervous system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Spinocerebellar atrophy
Definition: "Atrophy affecting the cerebellum and the spinocerebellar tracts of the spinal cord." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent mesencephalon
Definition: "Agenesis of the midbrain." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:KI_phemming]

Name: Cerebral dysmyelination
Definition: "Defective structure and function of myelin sheaths of the white matter of the brain." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Chronic axonal neuropathy
Definition: "An abnormality characterized by chronic impairment of the normal functioning of the axons." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Spinal muscular atrophy
Definition: "Muscular weakness and atrophy related to loss of the motor neurons of the spinal cord and brainstem." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Atypical absence seizure
Definition: "An atypical absence seizure is a type of generalised non-motor (absence) seizure characterised by interruption of ongoing activities and reduced responsiveness. In comparison to a typical absence seizure, changes in tone may be more pronounced, onset and/or cessation may be less abrupt, and the duration of the ictus and post-ictal recovery may be longer. Although not always available, an EEG often demonstrates slow (<3 Hz), irregular, generalized spike-wave activity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276062, PMID:28276064, PMID:6790275]

Name: Recurrent bacterial meningitis
Definition: "An increased susceptibility to bacterial meningitis as manifested by a medical history of recurrent episodes of bacterial meningitis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Paucity of anterior horn motor neurons
Developmental stagnation
Definition: "A cessation of the development of a child in the areas of motor skills, speech and language, cognitive skills, and social and/or emotional skills." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Facial palsy secondary to cranial hyperostosis
Definition: "Paralysis of the facial nerves on the basis of overgrowth of the cranial bones causing impingement upon the seventh cranial nerve." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Horizontal jerk nystagmus
Definition: "Nystagmus consisting of horizontal to-and-fro eye movements, in which the movement in one direction is faster than in the other." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Limb fasciculations
Definition: "Fasciculations affecting the musculature of the arms and legs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Posterior fossa cyst
Definition: "A discrete posterior fossa cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) collection that does not communicate directly with the fourth ventricle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:2816648]

Name: Oromotor apraxia
