Definition: "Oral-motor apraxia is the inability to volitionally sequence oral movements of the speech structure for nonspeech tasks in the absence of neuromuscular deficits such as paralysis or muscle weakness. Oral-motor apraxia is diagnosed when, despite intact sensory motor function an individual is unable to use these effector systems under voluntary control." [PMID:26275812]

Name: CNS demyelination
Definition: "A loss of myelin from nerve fibers in the central nervous system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Deep white matter hypodensities
Definition: "Multiple areas of darker than expected signal on magnetic resonance imaging emanating from the deep cerebral white matter." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16239634]

Name: Generalized dystonia
Definition: "A type of dystonia that affects all or most of the body." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Impaired pain sensation
Definition: "Reduced ability to perceive painful stimuli." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Focal hemifacial clonic seizure
Definition: "Focal seizure characterized at onset by clonic movements affecting half of the face." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers, PMID:28276060]

Name: Hypoplasia of the frontal lobes
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the frontal lobe of the cerebrum." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Bilateral tonic-clonic seizure with focal onset
Definition: "A bilateral tonic-clonic seizure with focal onset is a focal-onset seizure which progresses into a bilateral tonic-clonic phase." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276064]

Name: Recurrent encephalopathy
Definition: "Recurrent episodes of brain dysfunction that may be triggered by factors such as metabolic disturbances or infections." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypermetric saccades
Definition: "A saccade that overshoots the target with the dynamic saccade." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:572501]

Name: Lower limb muscle weakness
Definition: "Weakness of the muscles of the legs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Diffuse swelling of cerebral white matter
Abnormal morphology of the limbic system
Definition: "Any structural anomaly of the limbic system, a set of midline structures surrounding the brainstem of the mammalian brain, originally described anatomically, e.g., hippocampal formation, amygdala, hypothalamus, cingulate cortex. Although the original designation was anatomical, the limbic system has come to be associated with the system in the brain subserving emotional functions. As such, it is very poorly defined and doesn't correspond closely to the anatomical meaning any longer. [BirnLex]." []

Name: Upper limb postural tremor
Definition: "A type of tremors that is triggered by holding an arm in a fixed position." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Focal-onset seizure
Definition: "A focal-onset seizure is a type of seizure originating within networks limited to one hemisphere. They may be discretely localized or more widely distributed, and may originate in subcortical structures." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276064]

Name: Abnormal pons morphology
Definition: "A structural abnormality of the pons." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Atrophy/Degeneration affecting the central nervous system
Atrophy/Degeneration affecting the cerebrum
Definition: "The presence of atrophy (wasting) of the cerebrum, also known as the telencephalon, the largest and most highly developed part of the human brain." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the corpus callosum
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the corpus callosum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Corpus callosum atrophy
Definition: "The presence of atrophy (wasting) of the corpus callosum." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Motor neuron atrophy
Definition: "Wasting involving the motor neuron." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal septum pellucidum morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the septum pellucidum, which is a thin, triangular, vertical membrane separating the lateral ventricles of the brain." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal choroid plexus morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the choroid plexus, which is the area in the cerebral ventricles in which cerebrospinal fluid is produced by modified ependymal cells." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of somatosensory evoked potentials
Definition: "An abnormality of somatosensory evoked potentials (SSEP), i.e., of the electrical signals of sensation going from the body to the brain in response to a defined stimulus. Recording electrodes are placed over the scalp, spine, and peripheral nerves proximal to the stimulation site. Clinical studies generally use electrical stimulation of peripheral nerves to elicit potentials. SSEP testing determines whether peripheral sensory nerves are able to transmit sensory information like pain, temperature, and touch to the brain. Abnormal SSEPs can result from dysfunction at the level of the peripheral nerve, plexus, spinal root, spinal cord, brain stem, thalamocortical projections, or primary somatosensory cortex." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Neoplasm of the gastrointestinal tract
Definition: "A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the gastrointestinal tract." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Neoplasm of the genitourinary tract
Definition: "A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the genitourinary system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Facial telangiectasia
Definition: "Telangiectases (small dilated blood vessels) located near the surface of the skin of the face." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia cutis congenita of scalp
Definition: "A developmental defect resulting in the congenital absence of skin on the scalp." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplastic sweat glands
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the sweat glands." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Postnatal-onset ichthyosiform erythroderma
Definition: "A type of ichthyosiform erythroderma with postnatal onset." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Early cutaneous photosensitivity
Definition: "Photosensitivity of the skin occurring early in life." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Axillary apocrine gland hypoplasia
Definition: "Developmental hypoplasia of the apocrine sweat glands in the region of the axilla." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Macular atrophy
Definition: "Well-demarcated area(s) of partial or complete depigmentation in the macula, reflecting atrophy of the retinal pigment epithelium with associated retinal photoreceptor loss." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0986-4123]

Name: Areas of hypopigmentation and hyperpigmentation that do not follow Blaschko lines
Nonepidermolytic palmoplantar hyperkeratosis
Definition: "Abnormal thickening of the skin on the palms and soles charactersized by hyperkeratosis of the stratum corneum with no evidence of epidermolysis characteristic of epidermolytic hyperkeratosis." [PMID:7528239]

Name: Excessive skin wrinkling on dorsum of hands and fingers
Tegumentary leishmaniasis susceptibility
Definition: "Increased susceptibility to infection by the protozan parasite of the genus Leishmania." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: obsolete Absence of subcutaneous fat over entire body except buttocks, hips, and thighs
Palmoplantar hyperhidrosis
Definition: "An abnormally increased perspiration on palms and soles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Nevus flammeus of the forehead
Definition: "Naevus flammeus localised in the skin of the forehead." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Neonatal wrinkled skin of hands and feet
Discoid lupus rash
Definition: "Cutaneous lesion that develops as a dry, scaly, red patch that evolves to an indurated and hyperpigmented plaque with adherent scale. Scarring may result in central white patches (loss of pigmentation) and skin atrophy." []

Name: Alopecia totalis
Definition: "Loss of all scalp hair." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Spontaneous hematomas
Definition: "Spontaneous development of hematomas (hematoma) or bruises without significant trauma." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2945-4463]

Name: Telangiectases of the cheeks
Definition: "Telangiectases (small dilated blood vessels) located near the surface of the skin of the cheeks." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Telangiectasia of the oral mucosa
Definition: "Telangiectasia (that is, the presence of small dilated superficial blood vessels) of the oral mucosa." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Few cafe-au-lait spots
Definition: "The presence of two to five cafe-au-lait macules." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1773-4011]

Name: Generalized edema
Definition: "Generalized abnormal accumulation of fluid beneath the skin, or in one or more cavities of the body." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Congenital ichthyosiform erythroderma
Definition: "An ichthyosiform abnormality of the skin with congenital onset." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Plaque-like facial hemangioma
Definition: "Hemangioma is a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells. This term refers to facial hemangiomas that have a plaque-like morphology." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Multiple cutaneous leiomyomas
Definition: "The presence of multiple leiomyomas of the skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Mottled pigmentation of the trunk and proximal extremities
Partial albinism
Definition: "Absence of melanin pigment in various areas, which is found at birth and is permanent. The lesions are known as leucoderma and are often found on the face, trunk, or limbs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Palmoplantar blistering
Definition: "A type of blistering that affects the skin of the palms of the hands and the soles of the feet." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Diffuse palmoplantar hyperkeratosis
Definition: "Diffuse abnormal thickening of the skin on the palms and soles." [PMID:17298101]

Name: Increased groin pigmentation with raindrop depigmentation
Ipsilateral lack of facial sweating
Definition: "Inability to sweat on the same side of the face that is affected by ptosis and miosis. This is a feature of Horner syndrome." [PMID:29763176]

Name: Flexural lichenification
Definition: "Lichenification affecting primarily flexural areas of the skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Prominent veins on trunk
Definition: "Prominent thoracic and abdominal veins." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Autoamputation of digits
Definition: "The spontaneous detachment of a digit (finger or toe) from the body due to long standing pathology." []

Name: Bitot spots of the conjunctiva
Definition: "Keratinization of the bulbar conjunctiva near the limbus (corneoscleral junction), resulting in a raised spot." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sparse facial hair
Definition: "Reduced number or density of facial hair." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Honeycomb palmoplantar hyperkeratosis
Definition: "Abnormal thickening of the skin on the palms and soles with an honeycomb pattern." [PMID:9326323]

Name: Perifollicular hyperkeratosis
Definition: "Increased amount of keratin (visible as white scales) surrounding hair follicles." [PMID:23044575]

Name: Palmoplantar cutis gyrata
Definition: "Cutis gyrata of palms and soles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Periarticular subcutaneous nodules
Definition: "Subcutaneous nodules that are located in the vicinity of joints." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Axillary and groin hyperpigmentation and hypopigmentation
Congenital bullous ichthyosiform erythroderma
Definition: "An ichthyosiform abnormality of the skin that presents at birth or shortly thereafter with generalized erythema, blistering, erosions, and peeling. In the subsequent months, erythema and blistering improves but patients go on to develop hyperkeratotic scaling that is especially prominent along the joint flexures, neck, hands and feet." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal dermatoglyphics
Definition: "An abnormality of dermatoglyphs (fingerprints), which are present on fingers, palms, toes, and soles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Congenital nonbullous ichthyosiform erythroderma
Definition: "The term collodion baby applies to newborns who appear to have an extra layer of skin (known as a collodion membrane) that has a collodion-like quality. It is a descriptive term, not a specific diagnosis or disorder (as such, it is a syndrome). Affected babies are born in a collodion membrane, a shiny waxy outer layer to the skin. This is shed 10-14 days after birth, revealing the main symptom of the disease, extensive scaling of the skin caused by hyperkeratosis. With increasing age, the scaling tends to be concentrated around joints in areas such as the groin, the armpits, the inside of the elbow and the neck. The scales often tile the skin and may resemble fish scales." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Decreased sweating due to autonomic dysfunction
Absence of subcutaneous fat
Definition: "Lack of subcutaneous adipose tissue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Diffuse telangiectasia
Definition: "Telangiectases (small dilated blood vessels) with a diffuse localization." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Linear arrays of macular hyperkeratoses in flexural areas
Discrete 2 to 5-mm hyper- and hypopigmented macules
Focal friction-related palmoplantar hyperkeratosis
Definition: "Hyperkeratosis affecting the palm of the hand and the sole of the foot in areas exposed to friction." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Recurrent staphylococcal infections
Definition: "Increased susceptibility to staphylococcal infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of staphylococcal infections." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7941-2961]

Name: Decreased number of sweat glands
Definition: "The presence of fewer than normal sweat glands." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Streaks of hyperkeratosis along each finger onto the palm
Follicular hyperkeratosis
Definition: "A skin condition characterized by excessive development of keratin in hair follicles, resulting in rough, cone-shaped, elevated papules resulting from closure of hair follicles with a white plug of sebum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Congenital absence of skin of limbs
Punctate palmar hyperkeratosis
Definition: "Tiny bumps of thickened skin (hyperkeratosis) on the palms of the hands." []

Name: Edema of the dorsum of hands
Definition: "An abnormal accumulation of fluid beneath the skin on the back of the hands." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Redundant skin on fingers
Definition: "Loose and sagging skin of the fingers." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Palmoplantar cutis laxa
Definition: "Loose, wrinkled skin of hands and feet." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: obsolete Lack of subcutaneous fatty tissue
Yellow subcutaneous tissue covered by thin, scaly skin
Congenital posterior occipital alopecia
Definition: "Loss of hair in the occipital region of the scalp with congenital onset." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia cutis congenita of midline scalp vertex
Severe photosensitivity
Definition: "A severe degree of photosensitivity of the skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Frontal cutaneous lipoma
Definition: "Presence of a cutaneous lipoma on the forehead." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent pigmentation of the ventral chest
Definition: "Lack of skin pigmentation (coloring) of the anterior chest." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Piebaldism
Definition: "Piebaldism is characterized by stable and persistent, well-circumscribed depigmented patches present at birth affecting the skin of the face, trunk, and extremities in a symmetrical distribution." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Congenital palmoplantar hyperkeratosis
Definition: "Abnormal thickening of the skin on the palms and soles that is present at birth." []

Name: obsolete Palmoplantar keratosis with erythema and scale
Desquamation of skin soon after birth
Confetti hypopigmentation pattern of lower leg skin
Plantar hyperkeratosis
Definition: "Hyperkeratosis affecting the sole of the foot." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: obsolete Telangiectases in sun-exposed and nonexposed skin
Multiple cafe-au-lait spots
Definition: "The presence of six or more cafe-au-lait spots." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1773-4011]

Name: Generalized seborrheic dermatitis
Definition: "Seborrheic dermatitis that is not localized to any one particular region." []

Name: Hyperkeratosis lenticularis perstans
Definition: "Hyperkeratosis lenticularis perstans (HLP), also known as Flegel disease, is a keratinization abnormality characterized by small, asymptomatic erythematous papules that leave characteristic punctate bleeding when they become detached. The lesions generally occur symmetrically along the top of the foot and on the legs, appearing more rarely on the arms, forearms, palms, and soles, and even on the oral mucosa." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Late onset atopic dermatitis
Definition: "A form of atopic dermatitis with onset in adulthood characterized by atopic red face, chronic lichenified eczema on the trunk, subacute or psoriasiform dermatitis." [PMID:23984225, PMID:27904186]

Name: Palmar neurofibroma
Definition: "A neurofibroma (benign peripheral nerve sheath tumor) localized in the palm of the hand." []

Name: Reticular hyperpigmentation
Definition: "Increased pigmentation of the skin with a netlike (reticular) pattern." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia cutis congenita on trunk or limbs
Definition: "A developmental defect resulting in the congenital absence of skin on the trunk or the limbs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia cutis congenita over posterior parietal area
Aplasia/Hypoplastia of the eccrine sweat glands
Definition: "Absence or developmental hypoplasia of the eccrine sweat glands." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Painful subcutaneous lipomas
Definition: "The presence of multiple subcutaneous lipoma that cause pain." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bilateral single transverse palmar creases
Definition: "The distal and proximal transverse palmar creases are merged into a single transverse palmar crease on both hands." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoproteinemic edema
Definition: "An abnormal accumulation of fluid beneath the skin, or in one or more cavities of the body because of decreased osmotic pressure of plasma (hypoproteinemia)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Spinous keratoses of palms and soles
Nevus flammeus nuchae
Definition: "Naevus flammeus localised in the skin of the neck. This is one of the most common birthmarks and present in approximately 25% of all newborns." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Subcutaneous calcification
Definition: "Deposition of calcium salts in subcutaneous tissue (i.e., the the lowermost layer of the integument)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cutaneous leiomyoma
Definition: "The presence of leiomyoma of the skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Mandibular osteomyelitis
Definition: "Osteomyelitis of the lower jaw." []

Name: Bilateral microphthalmos
Definition: "A developmental anomaly characterized by abnormal smallness of both eyes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Nonarteritic anterior ischemic optic neuropathy
Definition: "An acute condition characterized by sudden visual loss (usually discovered in the morning), optic disc edema at onset, optic disc-related visual field defects. Nonarteritic anterior ischemic optic neuropathy can be associated with flame hemorrhages on the swollen disc or nearby neuroretinal layer, and sometimes with nearby cotton-wool exudates." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:17698200]

Name: Dyschromatopsia
Definition: "A form of colorblindness in which only two of the three fundamental colors can be distinguished due to a lack of one of the retinal cone pigments." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_ncarter]

Name: Congenital stationary night blindness
Definition: "A nonprogressive (i.e., stationary) form of difficulties with night blindness with congenital onset." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Peripheral tractional retinal detachment
Definition: "Tractional retinal detachment at the periphery of the retina." []

Name: Absent lower eyelashes
Definition: "Lack of eyelashes on the lower lid." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Congenital extraocular muscle anomaly
Definition: "Congenital abnormality of the extraocular muscles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Punctate cataract
Definition: "A type of cataract with punctate opacities of the lens." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Congenital hypertrophy of retinal pigment epithelium
Definition: "Sharply demarcated, congenital hyperpigmentation of the retinal pigment epithelium." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_ncarter]

Name: Eversion of lateral third of lower eyelids
Lacrimal gland aplasia
Definition: "A congenital defect of development characterized by absence of the lacrimal gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Diffuse nuclear cataract
Definition: "Opacity of the entire lens nucleus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: obsolete Decreased retinal pigmentation with dispersion
Curly eyelashes
Definition: "Abnormally curly or curved eyelashes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Peripheral cystoid retinal degeneration
Definition: "Degenerative changes of the peripheral retina consisting of close-packed tiny cystic spaces at the outer plexiform/inner nuclear retinal level. The degeneration is very common in adult eyes and starts adjacent to the ora serrata and extends circumferentially and posteriorly." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0986-4123]

Name: Abnormal vestibulo-ocular reflex
Definition: "An abnormality of the vestibulo-ocular reflex (VOR). The VOR attempts to keep the image stable on the retina. Ideally passive or active head movements in one direction are compensated for by eye movements of equal magnitude." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:3625219]

Name: Hypoplasia of the iris
Definition: "Congenital underdevelopment of the iris." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Vitelliform-like macular lesions
Definition: "Vitelliform maculopathy is a sharply demarcated lesion caused by the accumulation of material, often lipofuscin in the subretinal space underlying the macula." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8727-6592, PMID:18289629]

Name: Lacrimal duct stenosis
Definition: "Narrowing of a tear duct (lacrimal duct)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal pupillary function
Definition: "A functional abnormality of the pupil." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Unilateral ptosis
Definition: "A unilateral form of ptosis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Undetectable light- and dark-adapted electroretinogram
Definition: "Absence of the combined rod-and-cone response on electroretinogram." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal pupillary light reflex
Definition: "An abnormality of the reflex that controls the diameter of the pupil, in response to the intensity of light that falls on the retina of the eye." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplasia of the lower eyelids
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the lower eyelid." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ocular anterior segment dysgenesis
Definition: "Abnormal development (dysgenesis) of the anterior segment of the eye globe. These structures are mainly of mesenchymal origin." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_ncarter]

Name: Paroxysmal involuntary eye movements
Definition: "Sudden-onset episode of abnormal, involuntary eye movements." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Congenital aphakia
Definition: "Absence of the crystalline lens of the eye as a result of a developmental defect." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Band-shaped corneal dystrophy
Definition: "A type of genetically determined disease of the cornea with corneal lesions with a band-like shape." []

Name: Uveal melanoma
Definition: "A malignant melanoma originating within the eye. The tumor originates from the melanocytes in the uvea (which comprises the iris, ciliary body, and choroid)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Chronic irritative conjunctivitis
Definition: "A chronic irritative conjunctivitis, which commonly presents with general irritation and redness of the eyes, with a burning, dry, or foreign-body sensation of the eyes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Flat cornea
Definition: "Cornea plana is an abnormally flat shape of the cornea such that the normal protrusion of the cornea from the sclera is missing. The reduced corneal curvature can lead to hyperopia, and a hazy corneal limbus and arcus lipoides may develop at an early age." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Saccular conjunctival dilatations
Definition: "Presence of multiple dilatations (sac-like outpouchings) in the blood vessels of the conjunctiva." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Retinal pigment epithelial atrophy
Definition: "Atrophy (loss or wasting) of the retinal pigment epithelium observed on fundoscopy or fundus imaging." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Opacification of the corneal epithelium
Definition: "Lack of transparency of the corneal epithelium." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8727-6592]

Name: Congenital miosis
Definition: "Abnormal (non-physiological) constriction of the pupil of congenital onset." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Iris hypopigmentation
Definition: "An abnormal reduction in the amount of pigmentation of the iris." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Chorioretinal dysplasia
Definition: "Abnormal development of the choroid and retina." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lacrimal gland hypoplasia
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the lacrimal gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Enlarged lacrimal glands
Definition: "Abnormally big lacrimal glands." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bone spicule pigmentation of the retina
Definition: "Pigment migration into the retina in a bone-spicule configuration (resembling the nucleated cells within the lacuna of bone)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplasia of the fovea
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the fovea centralis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Macular dystrophy
Definition: "Macular dystrophy is a nonspecific term for premature retinal cell aging and cell death, generally confied to the macula in which no clear extrinsic cause is evident." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: obsolete Slitlike anterior chamber angles in children
Opacification of the corneal stroma
Definition: "Reduced transparency of the stroma of cornea." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8727-6592]

Name: Pericentral scotoma
Definition: "A scotoma (area of diminished vision within the visual field) that surrounds the central fixation point." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Retinal telangiectasia
Definition: "Dilatation of small blood vessels of the retina." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Deep anterior chamber
Definition: "Increased depth of the anterior chamber, i.e., the anteroposterior distance between the cornea and the iris is increased." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Optic disc hypoplasia
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the optic disc, that is of the optic nerve head, where ganglion cell axons exit the eye to form the optic nerve." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Central retinal vessel vascular tortuosity
Definition: "The presence of an increased number of twists and turns of retinal blood vessels (arteries, arterioles, veins, venules)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Impaired smooth pursuit
Definition: "An impairment of the ability to track objects with the ocular smooth pursuit system, a class of rather slow eye movements that minimizes retinal target motion." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Vitreoretinopathy
Definition: "Ocular abnormality characterised by premature degeneration of the vitreous and the retina that may be associated with increased risk of retinal detachment." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0986-4123, PMID:18179896]

Name: Hypoplasia of the ciliary body
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the ciliary body." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Chorioretinal scar
Definition: "Fibrous connective tissue resulting from incomplete healing of a wound (i.e., a scar) located in the choroid and retina or the eye." []

Name: Posterior retinal neovascularization
Definition: "A type of retinal neovascularization that affects the posterior pole of the retina." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cortical pulverulent cataract
Definition: "A type of cataract characterized by punctate, dust-like opacities within the cortical region of the lens." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: obsolete Butterfly retinal pigment epithelial dystrophy
Posterior subcapsular cataract
Definition: "A type of cataract affecting the posterior pole of lens immediately adjacent to ('beneath') the Lens capsule." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Patchy atrophy of the retinal pigment epithelium
Definition: "Wasting (atrophy) of the retinal pigment epithelium present in small, isolated areas." []

Name: Granular macular appearance
Definition: "Mottled (spotted or blotched with different shades) pigmentary abnormality of the macula lutea." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anterior cortical cataract
Definition: "A cataract that affects the anterior part of the cortex of the lens." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Conjunctival whitish salt-like deposits
Definition: "The presence of whitish deposits in the conjunctiva resembling salt. May be related to calcinosis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased axial length of the globe
Definition: "Abnormal largeness of the eye with an axial length > 2.5 standard deviations from population mean." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_ncarter]

Name: Granular corneal dystrophy
Definition: "The presence of central, fine, whitish granular lesions in the stroma of the cornea. This type of corneal dystrophy is usually asymptomatic and begins in childhood and shows a slow progression. Later in the course, the corneal epithelium and Bowman's layer may be affected. Histologically, the cornea shows a uniform deposition of hyaline material." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Monochromacy
Definition: "Complete color blindness, a complete inability to distinguish colors. Affected persons cannot perceive colors, but only shades of gray." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8727-6592]

Name: Horizontal pendular nystagmus
Definition: "Nystagmus consisting of horizontal to-and-fro eye movements of equal velocity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Herpetiform corneal ulceration
Definition: "The presence of one or more dendritic corneal epithelial ulcers characterized by a treelike branching linear pattern with feathery edges and terminal bulbs. Herpetiform corneal ulcers can be identified by fluorescein staining." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Nongranulomatous uveitis
Definition: "A form of uveitis that is not associated with the formation of granulomas." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Retinal pigment epithelial mottling
Definition: "Mottling (spots or blotches with different shades) of the retinal pigment epithelium, i.e., localized or generalized fundal pigment granularity associated with processes at the level of the retinal pigment epithelium." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal distribution of retinal arterioles and venules
Horizontal supranuclear gaze palsy
Definition: "A supranuclear gaze palsy is an inability to look in a horizontal direction as a result of cerebral impairment. There is a loss of the voluntary aspect of eye movements, but, as the brainstem is still intact, all the reflex conjugate eye movements are normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Central heterochromia
Definition: "The presence of distinct colors in the central (pupillary) zone of the iris than in the mid-peripheral (ciliary) zone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Presenile cataracts
Definition: "Presenile cataract is a kind of cataract that occurs in early adulthood, that is, at an age that is younger than usual." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:17030721]

Name: Lacrimal punctal atresia
Definition: "Congenital absence or closure of the opening of the lacrimal punctum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Total ophthalmoplegia
Definition: "Paralysis of both the extrinsic and intrinsic ocular muscles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: obsolete Cataracts develop in second or third decade
Adult-onset night blindness
Definition: "Inability to see well at night or in poor light with onset in adulthood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Nonprogressive restrictive external ophthalmoplegia
Definition: "Nonprogressive restriction of movement of the external ocular muscles such that the eyes of affected individuals are partially or completely fixed in a strabismic position. Residual eye movements are significantly limited." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Progressive cataract
Definition: "A kind of cataract that progresses with age." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Progressive ptosis
Definition: "A progressive form of ptosis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Long upper eyelashes
Definition: "Increased length of the upper eyelashes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Amyloid deposition in the vitreous humor
Definition: "Deposition of hyaline extracellular material (amyloid) into the vitreous humor, which can manifest as vitreous opacities and reduced visual acuity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Punctate opacification of the cornea
Definition: "Punctate opacification (reduced transparency) of the corneal stroma." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8727-6592]

Name: Chorioretinal lacunae
Definition: "Punched out lesions in the pigmented layer of the retina." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Congenital horizontal nystagmus
Definition: "Horizontal nystagmus dating from or present at birth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Retinal calcification
Definition: "Deposition of calcium salts in the retina." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Restrictive partial external ophthalmoplegia
Definition: "Fibrosis of only some of the external ocular muscles such that the eyes of affected individuals are partially or completely fixed in a strabismic position." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Choroidal hemangioma
Definition: "The presence of multiple hemangiomas in the choroid. These are generally reddish or orange or can have increased pigmentation maiking them difficult to distinguish from choroidal melanomas." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Almond-shaped palpebral fissure
Definition: "A shape created by an acute downward arching of the upper eyelid and upward arching of the lower eyelid, toward the medial canthus, which gives the outline of the palpebral fissures the configuration of an almond. Thus, the maximum distance between the fissures is offset from, and medial to, the center point." [PMID:19125427]

Name: Congenital blindness
Definition: "Blindness with onset at birth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Allergic conjunctivitis
Definition: "Allergic Conjunctivitis is an allergic inflammation of the conjunctiva." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Slowed horizontal saccades
Definition: "An abnormally slow velocity of horizontal saccadic eye movements." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent extraocular muscles
Definition: "Congenital absence of the extraocular muscles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Iridescent posterior subcapsular cataract
Definition: "A type of posterior subcapsular cataract characterized by an iridescent color." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:7826272]

Name: Hypoplasia of the lacrimal punctum
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the lacrimal puncta." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypopigmentation of the fundus
Definition: "Reduced pigmentation of the fundus, typically generalised. Fundoscopy may reveal a low level pigment in both RPE and choroid with clear visibility of choroidal vessels (pale/albinoid) or low pigment level in the RPE with deep pigment in choroid so that visible choroidal vessels are separated by deeply pigmented zones (tesselated/tigroid)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0986-4123]

Name: Retinal nonattachment
Definition: "Failure of attachment of the retina during development." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:21441919]

Name: Vitreous hemorrhage
Definition: "Bleeding within the vitreous compartment of the eye." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2945-4463, PMID:16882398]

Name: Paravenous chorioretinal atrophy
Definition: "Chorioretinal atrophy along the retinal veins." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:15623792]

Name: Ocular hypertension
Definition: "Intraocular pressure that is 2 standard deviations above the population mean." []

Name: Reticular retinal dystrophy
Definition: "A type of of patterned retinal dystrophy that shows a reticular pattern of pigmentation." []

Name: Polymorphous posterior corneal dystrophy
Definition: "This corneal dystrophy affects the posterior limiting membrane of the cornea and is characterized by polymorphous plaques of calcium deposits in the deep stromal layers of the cornea, and occasionally by vesicular lesions of the endothelium and edema of the deep corneal stroma." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: obsolete Small anterior lens surface opacities
Tractional retinal detachment
Definition: "A type of retinal detachment arising due to a combination of contracting retinal membranes, abnormal vitreoretinal adhesions, and vitreous changes. It is usually seen in the context of diseases that induce a fibrovascular response, e.g. diabetes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, ISBN-13:978-0199679980]

Name: Lacrimal duct aplasia
Definition: "A congenital defect resulting in absence of the lacrimal duct." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal flash visual evoked potentials
Definition: "Anomaly of the visual evoked potentials elicited by a flash stimulus, generally a flash of light subtending an angle of at least 20 degrees of the visual field and presented in a dimly lit room." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Peripheral retinal detachment
Definition: "Separation of the inner layers of the retina (neural retina) from the pigment epithelium occuring near the outer limit (periphery) of the retina." []

Name: Bilateral congenital mydriasis
Definition: "Congenital abnormal dilation of the pupil on both sides." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Broad lateral eyebrow
Definition: "Regional increase in the width (height) of the lateral eyebrow." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Restrictive external ophthalmoplegia
Definition: "Fibrosis of the external ocular muscles such that the eyes of affected individuals are partially or completely fixed in a strabismic position. Residual eye movements are significantly limited." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Reticular pigmentary degeneration
Definition: "A type of retinal reticular pigmentation that forms a polygonal, netlike arrangement of hyperpigmented lines forming geometric patterns in the fundus." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:fprobst, PMID:28114409]

Name: Blue cone monochromacy
Definition: "A form of monochromacy in which vision is derived from the remaining preserved blue (S) cones and rod photoreceptors." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Limited extraocular movements
Definition: "Limited mobility of the eye within its socket." []

Name: Internal ophthalmoplegia
Definition: "Paralysis of the iris and ciliary apparatus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Congenital stapes ankylosis
Definition: "A form of stapes ankylosis with congenital onset." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Unilateral narrow palpebral fissure
Definition: "A fixed reduction in the vertical distance between the upper and lower eyelids with short palpebral fissures on one side only." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pericentral retinitis pigmentosa
Definition: "A subtype of retinitis pigmentosa in which, instead of the pathology starting in the mid-periphery like typical retinitis pigmentosa, the disease starts in the near periphery closer to the vascular arcades and tends to spare the far periphery." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0986-4123, PMID:28981474]

Name: Dense posterior cortical cataract
Definition: "A type of posterior cortical cataract characterized by dense lenticular opacities." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Peripapillary chorioretinal atrophy
Definition: "Chorioretinal atrophy concentrated around the optic papilla (i.e., the optic nerve head)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Corneal opacity
Definition: "A reduction of corneal clarity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Optic atrophy from cranial nerve compression
Pattern dystrophy of the retina
Definition: "A spectrum of fundoscopic appearances characterized by the development of a variety of patterns of deposits predominantly in the macular area. The deposits are typically bilateral, relatively symmetrical, yellow/white and associated with changes at the level of the retinal pigment epithelium. With time, retinal atrophy may occur. A number of pattern dystrophy subtypes have been described including butterfly-shaped dystrophy, reticular dystrophy (net-like pattern) and fundus pulverulentus (granular, mottled pigmentation)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0986-4123]

Name: Remnants of the hyaloid vascular system
Definition: "Persistence of the hyaloid artery, which is the embryonic artery that runs from the optic disk to the posterior lens capsule may persist; the site of attachment may form an opacity. The hyaloid artery is a branch of the ophthalmic artery, and usually regresses completely before birth. This features results from a failure of regression of the hyaloid vessel, which supplies the primary vitreous during embryogenesis and normally regresses in the third trimester of pregnancy, leading to a particular form of posterior cataract." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lamellar cataract
Definition: "A congenital cataract in which opacity is limited to layers of the lens external to the nucleus (i.e., the perinuclear region), i.e., between the nuclear and cortical layers of the lens." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Retinal dysplasia
Definition: "The presence of developmental dysplasia of the retina." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypometric horizontal saccades
Definition: "Saccadic undershoot of horizontal saccadic eye movements, i.e., a horizontal saccadic eye movement that has less than the magnitude that would be required to gain fixation of the object." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:572501]

Name: Cerulean cataract
Definition: "Cerulean cataracts are a kind of congenital cataract having peripheral bluish and white opacifications in concentric layers with occasional central lesions arranged radially. Although the opacities may be observed during fetal development and childhood, usually visual acuity is only mildly reduced until adulthood, when lens extraction is generally necessary." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19496508, PMID:9158139]

Name: Gaze-evoked horizontal nystagmus
Definition: "Horizontal nystagmus made apparent by looking to the right or to the left." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: obsolete Concentric narrowing of visual field
Electronegative electroretinogram
Definition: "A dark-adapted bright flash electroretinogram in which the b-wave that is of markedly lower amplitude than the associated a-wave (source: Holder GE., Inherited Chorioretinal Dystrophies: A Textbook and Atlas; 2014; p.17; ISBN 978-3-540-69466-3)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Retinal arteriolar occlusion
Definition: "Blockage of retinal arteriole, generally associated with interruption of blood flow and oxygen delivery to affected regions of the retina." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Macular hypopigmentation
Definition: "Decreased amount of pigmentation in the macula lutea." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_ncarter]

Name: Intraretinal exudate
Definition: "Retinal exudate within the retinal tissue itself." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplastic iris stroma
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the stroma of iris." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Malformed lacrimal duct
Definition: "Congenital malformation of the lacrimal duct associated with incomplete development of the bony nasolacrimal canal or craniofacial anomalies." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Peripheral visual field loss
Definition: "Loss of peripheral vision with retention of central vision, resulting in a constricted circular tunnel-like field of vision." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased corneal reflex
Definition: "An abnormally reduced response to stimulation of the cornea (by touch, foreign body, blowing air). The corneal reflex (also known as the blink reflex, normally results in an involuntary blinking of the eyelids." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Foveal hyperpigmentation
Definition: "Increased amount of pigmentation in the fovea centralis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of macular pigmentation
Definition: "Abnormality of macular or foveal pigmentation." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_ncarter]

Name: Peripheral opacification of the cornea
Definition: "Reduced transparency of the peripheral region of the cornea." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Central fundal arteriolar microaneurysms
Definition: "Microscopic aneurysms of the retinal arterioles near the central part of the fundus, visible as small round dark red dots on the retinal surface (not arising from visible vessels) that are by definition less than the diameter of the major optic veins as they cross the optic disc." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: obsolete Depigmented lesions of the retinal pigment epithelium
Superior lens subluxation
Definition: "Partial dislocation of the lens in a superior direction." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:5087595]

Name: Cone dystrophy
Definition: "Inherited progressive cone degeneration." []

Name: Cystoid macular degeneration
Definition: "A form of macular degeneration characterized by the presence of multiple cysts in the macula." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Posterior Y-sutural cataract
Definition: "A type of sutural cataract in which the opacity follows the posterior Y suture." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal iris pigmentation
Definition: "Abnormal pigmentation of the iris." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Retinitis pigmentosa inversa
Definition: "Retinitis pigmentosa inversa is form of retinal degeneration characterized by areas of retinal/chorioretinal degeneration with pigment migration in the macular area (in contrast to retinitis pigmentosa which, at early disease stages, predominantly affects the retinal periphery)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0986-4123, PMID:9734800]

Name: Absent anterior chamber of the eye
Definition: "Absence of the anterior chamber of the eye owing to a developmental defect." []

Name: Aplastic/hypoplastic lacrimal glands
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the lacrimal gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Retinal arteriolar constriction
Definition: "Decreased retinal arteriolar diameters, which may decrease blood flow and slow oxygen delivery to regions of the retina." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal retinal vascular morphology
Definition: "A structural abnormality of retinal vasculature." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the vasculature of the eye
Abnormal line of Schwalbe morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the line of Schwalbe." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the extraocular muscles
Definition: "An abnormality of an extraocular muscle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the palpebral fissures
Definition: "An anomaly of the space between the medial and lateral canthi of the two open eyelids." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: obsolete Abnormality of the retinal pigment epithelium
Retinal fold
Definition: "A wrinkle of retinal tissue projecting outward from the surface of the retina and visible as a line on fundoscopy." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the iris
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the iris." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal morphology of the conjunctival vasculature
Definition: "Any abnormality of the blood vessels of the conjunctiva." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia affecting the uvea
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the uvea, the pigmented middle layer of the eye consisting of the iris and ciliary body together with the choroid." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the fovea
Definition: "Congenital absence or underdevelopment of the fovea centralis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia affecting the anterior segment of the eye
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the anterior segment of the eye." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the lens
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the lens." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ichthyosis
Definition: "An abnormality of the skin characterized the presence of excessive amounts of dry surface scales on the skin resulting from an abnormality of keratinization." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal blistering of the skin
Definition: "The presence of one or more bullae on the skin, defined as fluid-filled blisters more than 5 mm in diameter with thin walls." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:31596619]

Name: Neoplasm of the skin
Definition: "A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sparse hair
Definition: "Reduced density of hairs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:14676077]

Name: Maternal hypertension
Definition: "Increased blood pressure during a pregnancy." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Maternal virilization in pregnancy
Definition: "Virilization (deepening of voice, facial hirsutism and scalp hair loss) with onset during pregnancy (usually towards the end of the first trimester) and regression several months post-partum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Low maternal circulating estriol concentration
Definition: "An abnormally low concentration of serum conjugated estriol as compared to normal values for gestational-age." [PMID:19038077]

Name: Osteoporotic tarsals
Definition: "Reduction in bone mineral density affecting any or all of the tarsal bones, seven bones of the foot comprising the calcaneus, talus, cuboid, navicular, and the cuneiform bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent fifth metatarsal
Definition: "A developmental abnormality characterized by the absence of the fifth metatarsal bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hallux varus
Definition: "Medial deviation of the great toe owing to a deformity of the great toe joint causing the hallux to deviate medially." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pes valgus
Definition: "An outward deviation of the foot at the talocalcaneal or subtalar joint." []

Name: Nonossified fifth metatarsal
Definition: "The presence of a fifth metatarsal bone that has not undergone ossification at an age when ossification is usually visible." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the fifth metatarsal bone
Definition: "An anomaly of the fifth metatarsal bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short 4th toe
Definition: "Underdevelopment (hypoplasia) of the fourth toe." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Widely spaced toes
Definition: "An overall widening of the spaces between the digits." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125433]

Name: Osteolysis of talus
Definition: "Osteolysis affecting the talus." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Medially deviated second toe
Definition: "Medial deviation of the second toe." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Expanded metatarsals with widened medullary cavities
Delayed tarsal ossification
Definition: "Delayed maturation and calcification of any of the tarsal bones, seven bones of the foot comprising the calcaneus, talus, cuboid, navicular, and the cuneiform bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Plantar crease between first and second toes
Definition: "The presence of unusually deep creases (ridges/wrinkles) on the skin of sole of foot located between the first and second toe." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Advanced tarsal ossification
Definition: "Precocious (accelerated) maturation and calcification of any of the tarsal bones, seven bones of the foot comprising the calcaneus, talus, cuboid, navicular, and the cuneiform bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Plantar flexion contracture
Definition: "A type of contracture in which the plantar flexion muscles are contracted." []

Name: Metatarsal diaphyseal endosteal sclerosis
Definition: "Osteosclerosis of the endosteal surface of the diaphyses (shafts) of the metatarsal bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Clinodactyly of the 3rd toe
Definition: "Bending or curvature of a third toe in the tibial direction (i.e., towards the big toe)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Flexion limitation of toes
Definition: "Limitation of the ability to bend the toes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Calcaneonavicular fusion
Definition: "Synostosis of the calcaneus with the navicular bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Talipes calcaneovarus
Definition: "A congenital deformity characterized by a dorsiflexed, inverted, and adducted foot, i.e., a combination of talipes calcaneus and talipes varus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bipartite calcaneus
Definition: "A two-part calcaneus, a finding that probably results from delayed coalescence of two primary calcaneal centers of ossification." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Tarsal stippling
Definition: "The presence of abnormal punctate (speckled, dot-like) calcifications in one or more tarsal bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Medial rotation of the medial malleolus
Irregular tarsal ossification
Definition: "Defective ossification in an irregular pattern of the seven bones of the foot comprising the calcaneus, talus, cuboid, navicular, and the cuneiform bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Equinus calcaneus
Definition: "Abnormal plantar flexion of the calcaneus relative to the longitudinal axis of the tibia. This results in the angle between the long axis of the tibia and the long axis of the heel bone (calcaneus) being greater than 90 degrees." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Delayed calcaneal ossification
Definition: "Delayed maturation and calcification of the calcaneus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Impaired epinephrine-induced platelet aggregation
Definition: "Abnormal response to epinephrine as manifested by reduced or lacking aggregation of platelets upon addition of epinephrine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7744-1790]

Name: Elevated serum transaminases during infections
Definition: "Elevations of the levels of SGOT (serum glutamic oxaloacetic transaminase) and SGPT (serum glutamic pyruvic transaminase) that occur during infections." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Prolonged prothrombin time
Definition: "Increased time to coagulation in the prothrombin time test, which is a measure of the extrinsic pathway of coagulation. The results of the prothrombin time test are often expressed in terms of the International normalized ratio (INR), which is calculated as a ratio of the patient's prothrombin time (PT) to a control PT standardized for the potency of the thromboplastin reagent developed by the World Health Organization (WHO) using the formula: INR is equal to Patient PT divided by Control PT." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:26351955, PMID:29939529]

Name: Periodic hypokalemic paresis
Definition: "Episodes of muscle weakness associated with reduced levels of potassium in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Mucopolysacchariduria
Definition: "Excessive amounts of mucopolysaccharide in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperapobetalipoproteinemia
Definition: "Hyperapobetalipoproteinemia is defined as the combination of a normal low density lipoprotein (LDL) cholesterol in the face of an increased LDL apolipoprotein B (apoB) protein." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:6579550]

Name: 3-hydroxydicarboxylic aciduria
Definition: "The concentration of 2-hydroxydicarboxylic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Absent leukocyte alkaline phosphatase
Definition: "Alkaline phosphatase levels measured within leukocytes is below detectable levels." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Asymptomatic hyperammonemia
Definition: "An increased concentration of ammonia in the blood not associated with symptoms such as encephalopathy." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased circulating cortisol level
Definition: "Abnormally reduced concentration of cortisol in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased helper T cell proportion
Definition: "Reduced proportion of helper T cells relative to the total number of T cells." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased beta-galactosidase activity
Definition: "Abnormally decreased rate of beta-galactosidase activity. Beta-galactosidase activity can be measured in leukocyte, fibroblast, or plasma." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Very long chain fatty acid accumulation
Reduced factor VII activity
Definition: "Reduced activity of coagulation factor VII. Factor VII is part of the extrinsic coagulation pathway, which is initiated at the site of injury in response to the release of tissue factor (fIII). Tissue factor and activated factor VII catalyze the activation of factor X." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased Arden ratio of electrooculogram
Definition: "An abnormal reduction in the Arden ratio, which is the ratio between the light peak and the dark trough of the smoothed (physiologic) EOG record." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abetalipoproteinemia
Definition: "An absence of low-density lipoprotein cholesterol in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Precocious puberty in males
Definition: "The onset of puberty before the age of 9 years in boys." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Adrenocortical cytomegaly
Definition: "The presence of large polyhedral cells with eosinophilic granular cytoplasm and enlarged nuclei in the adrenal cortex." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absence of secondary sex characteristics
Definition: "No secondary sexual characteristics are present at puberty." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Insulin insensitivity
Definition: "Decreased sensitivity toward insulin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thyroid agenesis
Definition: "The congenital absence of the thyroid gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:2918525]

Name: Multiple pancreatic beta-cell adenomas
Definition: "The presence of multiple pancreatic islet cell adenomas." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Congenital hypoparathyroidism
Definition: "Deficiency of parathyroid hormone with congenital onset." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Primary hyperparathyroidism
Definition: "A type of hyperparathyroidism caused by a primary abnormality of the parathyroid glands (e.g., adenoma, carcinoma, hyperplasia). Primary hyperparathyroidism is associated with hyercalcemia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Reduced circulating prolactin concentration
Definition: "A reduced level of prolactin in the blood circulation. Prolactin is a protein hormone that is secreted by lactotrophs in the anterior pituitary and that stimulates mammary gland development and milk production." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:23378139]

Name: Precocious puberty with Sertoli cell tumor
Insulin-dependent but ketosis-resistant diabetes
Definition: "Ketosis-resistant diabetes is a synonym for type II diabetes. This term thus refers to a form of type II diabetes in which patients are dependent on insulin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Primary adrenal insufficiency
Definition: "Insufficient production of steroid hormones (primarily cortisol) by the adrenal glands as a result of a primary defect in the glands themselves." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Parathyroid hyperplasia
Definition: "Hyperplasia of the parathyroid gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Premature ovarian insufficiency
Definition: "Amenorrhea due to loss of ovarian function before the age of 40. Primary ovarian inssuficiency (POI) is a state of female hypergonadotropic hypogonadism. It can manifest as primary amenorrhea with onset before menarche or secondary amenorrhea." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Parathyroid agenesis
Definition: "Aplasia of the parathyroid gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Gonadotropin deficiency
Definition: "A reduced ability to secrete gonadotropins, which are protein hormones secreted by gonadotrope cells of the anterior pituitary gland, including the hormones follitropin (FSH) and luteinizing hormone (LH)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Decreased serum estradiol
Definition: "A reduction below normal concentration of estradiol in the circulation." []

Name: Adrenal gland dysgenesis
Definition: "Abnormal development of the adrenal gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Adrenal hyperplasia
Definition: "Enlargement of the adrenal gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Compensated hypothyroidism
Definition: "Condition associated with a raised serum concentration of thyroid stimulating hormone (TSH) but a normal serum free thyroxine (FT4)." [PMID:28406057]

Name: Androgen insufficiency
Definition: "Insufficient amount of androgenic activity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pituitary resistance to thyroid hormone
Definition: "A condition in which the pituitary gland is partially resistant to thyroid hormone, so that it continues to secrete thyroid-stimulating hormone (TSH) until the blood level of thyroid hormone rises higher than normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thyroid lymphangiectasia
Definition: "The presence of lymphangiectasis of the thyroid gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated circulating follicle stimulating hormone level
Definition: "An elevated concentration of follicle-stimulating hormone in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased circulating progesterone
Definition: "An reduced concentration of progesterone in the blood." []

Name: Hypothalamic hypothyroidism
Definition: "A type of hypothyroidism that results from a defect in thyrotropin-releasing hormone activity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:18731015]

Name: Adrenal medullary hypoplasia
Definition: "Developmental hypoplasia of the adrenal medulla." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pseudohypoaldosteronism
Definition: "A state of renal tubular unresponsiveness or resistance to the action of aldosterone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Congenital adrenal hypoplasia
Definition: "A type of adrenal hypoplasia with congenital onset." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pituitary hypothyroidism
Definition: "A type of hypothyroidism that results from a defect in thyroid-stimulating hormone secretion." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Euthyroid hyperthyroxinemia
Definition: "Increased levels of thyroxine without evidence of clinical thyroid disease." [eMedicine:118562, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thyroid hyperplasia
Definition: "Hyperplasia of the thyroid gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Congenital goiter
Definition: "An enlargement of the thyroid gland with congenital onset." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Adrenocortical adenoma
Definition: "Adrenocortical adenomas are benign tumors of the adrenal cortex." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:17287480]

Name: Congenital adrenal hyperplasia
Definition: "A type of adrenal hyperplasia with congenital onset." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Adrenocorticotropin receptor defect
Definition: "Adrenal insufficiency secondary to a defect in the ACTH receptor." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Pancreatic islet cell adenoma
Definition: "The presence of an adenoma of the pancreas with origin in a pancreatic B cell." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thyroid defect in oxidation and organification of iodide
Neutrophil inclusion bodies
Definition: "The presence of intracellular inclusion bodies (aggregates of stainable substances, usually proteins) in neutrophils. Cytoplasmic neutrophil inclusions (oval, basophilic) are also known as Doehle bodies." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased red cell hemolysis by shear stress
Abnormal cartilage collagen
Definition: "Abnormal morphology of collagen fibers in cartilage. In cartilage, collagen II, actually a collagen II:IX:XI heterofibril, is by far the most important type of collagen. A number of abnormalities may be appreciated by electron micrography or biochemical investigations, including sparse collagen fibers in the cartilage matrix." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:11879535, PMID:7757081, PMID:9468540]

Name: Abnormal blood zinc concentration
Definition: "An abnormality of zinc ion homeostasis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cerebellar cortical atrophy
Definition: "Atrophy (wasting) of the cerebellar cortex." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Acute hyperammonemia
Definition: "An increased concentration of ammonia in the blood with sudden onset." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Unconjugated hyperbilirubinemia
Definition: "An increased amount of unconjugated (indirect) bilurubin in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fasting hyperinsulinemia
Definition: "An increased concentration of insulin in the blood in the fasting state, i.e., not as the response to food intake." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Partial complement factor H deficiency
Definition: "A partial reduction in level of the complement component Factor H in circulation." [https://emedicine.medscape.com/article/135478-overview]

Name: Pituitary corticotropic cell adenoma
Definition: "A type of pituitary adenoma that produces adrenocorticotropic hormone (ACTH)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Long-chain dicarboxylic aciduria
Definition: "An increase in the level of long-chain dicarboxylic acid in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Transient hyperphenylalaninemia
Definition: "A condition of not having consistently high levels of phenylalanine in the blood but of experiencing temporary hyperphenylalaninemia following ingestion of large quantities of phenylalanine (for instance, following an oral loading test with phenylalanine)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Dermatan sulfate excretion in urine
Definition: "An increased concentration of dermatan sulfate in the urine." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Olivary degeneration
Definition: "Degeneration of the olivary bodies, prominent oval structures in the medulla oblongata." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Exercise-induced myoglobinuria
Definition: "Presence of myoglobin in the urine following exercise." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Medium chain dicarboxylic aciduria
Definition: "An increase in the level of medium chain dicarboxylic acid in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Spinal cord posterior columns myelin loss
Decreased activity of mitochondrial complex II
Definition: "A reduction in the activity of the mitochondrial respiratory chain complex II, which is part of the electron transport chain in mitochondria." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased plasma free carnitine
Definition: "A decreased concentration of free (unbound) carnitine in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal mitochondria in muscle tissue
Definition: "An abnormality of the mitochondria in muscle tissue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated leukocyte alkaline phosphatase
Definition: "Increased alkaline phosphatase measured within leukocytes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Impaired collagen-induced platelet aggregation
Definition: "Abnormal response to collagen or collagen-mimetics as manifested by reduced or lacking aggregation of platelets upon addition collagen or collagen-mimetics." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4381-2442]

Name: Reduced factor X activity
Definition: "Reduced activity of coagulation factor X. The extrinsic and intrinsic pathways converge at factor X (fX). The extrinsic pathway activates fX by means of d factor VII with its cofactor, tissue factor. The intrinsic pathway activates fX by means of the tenase complex (Ca2+ and factors VIIIa, IXa and X) on the surface of activated platelets. Factor Xa in turn activates prothrombin (factor II) to thrombin (factor IIa)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal mitochondrial morphology
Definition: "Any structural anomaly of the mitochondria." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal light- and dark-adapted electroretinogram
Definition: "An abnormality of the combined rod-and-cone response on electroretinogram." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Reduced circulating vitamin B6 level
Definition: "An abnormally decreased concentration of vitamin B6 in the blood circulation." []

Name: Microscopic nephrocalcinosis
Definition: "The presence of microscopic crystalline calcium precipitates in the form of oxalate and/or phosphate in the renal parenchyma." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Reduced von Willebrand factor activity
Definition: "Decreased activity of von Willebrand factor. Von Willebrand factor mediates the adhesion of platelets to the collagen exposed on endothelial cell surfaces." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19694940]

Name: Partial functional complement factor D deficiency
Definition: "A partial reduction in level of the complement component Factor D in circulation." []

Name: Diaminoaciduria
Definition: "An increased urine level of any amino acid carrying two amino groups (Asparagine, glutamine and lysine, cystine, ornithine)." []

Name: Distal renal tubular acidosis
Definition: "A type of renal tubular acidosis characterized by a failure of acid secretion by the alpha intercalated cells of the cortical collecting duct of the distal nephron. The urine cannot be acidified below a pH of 5.3, associated with acidemia and hypokalemia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated circulating branched chain amino acid concentration
Definition: "Concentration of a branched chain amino acid in the blood above the upper limit of normal." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Hypoplasia of the iris dilator muscle
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the dilatator pupillae." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased activity of mitochondrial complex IV
Definition: "A reduction in the activity of the mitochondrial respiratory chain complex IV, which is part of the electron transport chain in mitochondria." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased circulating IgG2 level
Definition: "A reduction in immunoglobulin levels of the IgG2 subclass in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Impaired platelet adhesion
Definition: "An abnormality of adhesion of thrombocytes. Normally, platelets adhere to collagen in the vascular subendothelium within seconds of injury via a receptor made up of glycoprotein Ia and IIa and GPVI and to vWF via receptor GPIb/IX/V. The adherent platelets then release granules that lead to platelet activation and aggregation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Neutral hyperaminoaciduria
Definition: "The presence of an abnormally increased concentration of neutral amino acids in the urine. The neutral amino acids are tryptophan, alanine, asparagine, glutamine, histidine, isoleucine, leucine, phenylalanine, serine, threonine, tyrosine and valine." [PMID:30177408]

Name: Factor X activation deficiency
Definition: "Reduced ability to transform factor X into its activated form factor Xa." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Reduced factor XIII activity
Definition: "Decreased activity of coagulation factor XIII (also known as fibrin stabilizing factor). Activated Factor XIII cross-links fibrin polymers solidifying the clot." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperprolinemia
Definition: "An increased concentration of proline in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Neonatal hypoproteinemia
Definition: "A neonatal decreased concentration of proteins in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the hallux
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the big toe." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the tarsal bones
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the tarsal bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the calcaneus
Definition: "An abnormality of the calcaneus, also known as the heel bone, one of the or heel bone, one of the components of the tarsus of the foot which make up the heel." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal talus morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the talus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Foot joint contracture
Definition: "Contractures of one or more joints of the feet meaning chronic loss of joint motion due to structural changes in non-bony tissue." []

Name: Tarsal synostosis
Definition: "Synostosis (bony fusion) involving one or more bones of the tarsus (calcaneus, talus, cuboid, navicular, cuneiiform bones)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal tarsal ossification
Definition: "An abnormality of the formation and mineralization of any of the tarsal bones, seven bones of the foot comprising the calcaneus, talus, cuboid, navicular, and the cuneiform bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal metatarsal ossification
Definition: "Any abnormal process of ossification of the metatarsal bones, which normally are each ossified from two centers: one for the body, and one for the head (metatarsal II,III,IV, and V) and one for the body and one for the base (metatarsal I). The ossification process begins in the center of the body about the ninth week, and extends toward either extremity. The center for the base of the first metatarsal appears about the third year, and the centers for the heads of the other bones between the fifth and eighth years. They join the bodies between the eighteenth and twentieth years." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Slow-growing nails
Definition: "Nails whose growth is slower than normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the nails
Definition: "Aplasia or developmental hypoplasia of the nail." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal toenail morphology
Definition: "An anomaly of the toenail." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Recurrent loss of toenails and fingernails
Definition: "Repeated loss, or shedding, of the nails of the fingers and toes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1773-4011]

Name: Dystrophic fingernails
Definition: "The presence of misshapen or partially destroyed nail plates, often with accumulation of soft, yellow keratin between the dystrophic nail plate and nail bed, resulting in elevation of the nail plate." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Subungual hyperkeratosis
Definition: "A thickening of the stratum corneum in the region beneath the nails." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Congenital curved nail of fourth toe
Chronic monilial nail infection
Definition: "Chronic infection of the nails by Candida species." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplastic fifth fingernail
Definition: "A nail of the fifth finger that is diminished in length and width, i.e., underdeveloped nail of little finger." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Circumungual hyperkeratosis
Definition: "A thickening of the stratum corneum, the outer layer of the skin, in the region surrounding the nails." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Onycholysis of distal fingernails
Definition: "Detachment of the distal fingernails from the nail bed." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Onychogryposis of toenails
Definition: "Thickened toenails." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ridged fingernail
Definition: "Longitudinal, linear prominences in the fingernail plate." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125433]

Name: Nail dystrophy
Definition: "Onychodystrophy (nail dystrophy) refers to nail changes apart from changes of the color (nail dyschromia) and involves partial or complete disruption of the various keratinous layers of the nail plate." [PMID:19675700]

Name: Vertebral hypoplasia
Definition: "Small, underdeveloped vertebral bodies." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]
