Name: Intervertebral disc degeneration
Definition: "The presence of degenerative changes of intervertebral disk." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Punctate vertebral calcifications
Definition: "The presence of punctiform calcification of the bone of the vertebral bodies." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Vertebral wedging
Definition: "An abnormal shape of the vertebral bodies whereby the vertebral bodies are thick on one side and taper to a thin edge at the other." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Spinal dysplasia
Definition: "The presence of developmental dysplasia of the vertebral column." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Vertebral clefting
Definition: "Schisis (cleft or cleavage) of vertebral bodies." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anterior beaking of lumbar vertebrae
Definition: "Anterior tongue-like protrusions of the vertebral bodies of the lumbar spine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anterior wedging of L1
Definition: "An abnormality of the shape of the lumbar vertebra L1 such that it is wedge-shaped (narrow towards the front)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent in utero ossification of vertebral bodies
Vertebral arch anomaly
Definition: "A morphological abnormality of the vertebral arch, i.e., of the posterior part of a vertebra." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lumbar hemivertebrae
Definition: "Absence of one half of the vertebral body in the lumbar spine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: C1-C2 vertebral abnormality
Definition: "Any abnormality of the atlas and the axis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Herniation of intervertebral nuclei
Definition: "The presence of one or more herniated nucleus pulposus of intervertebral disk." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Vertebral hyperostosis
Definition: "Excessive growth of the bones of the vertebral bodies." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Neuropathic spinal arthropathy
Definition: "A progressive disorder of vertebral joint degeneration that occurs in the setting of any condition characterized by decreased afferent innervation, involving loss of deep pain and proprioceptive sensation in the vertebral column. Patients most commonly present with symptoms of lower back pain, sitting imbalance, progressive spinal deformity (usually kyphosis), and an audible clicking sound on changing postures." [PMID:29755231]

Name: Posterior wedging of vertebral bodies
Definition: "An abnormality of the shape of vertebrae, such that they are wedge-shaped (narrow towards the back)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cervical spinal canal stenosis
Definition: "An abnormal narrowing of the cervical spinal canal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Narrow vertebral interpedicular distance
Definition: "A reduction of the distance between vertebral pedicles, which are the two short, thick processes, which project backward, one on either side, from the upper part of the vertebral body, at the junction of its posterior and lateral surfaces." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lumbar kyphosis
Definition: "Over curvature of the lumbar region." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Dysplastic sacrum
Definition: "A developmental defect of the sacrum characterized by partial or disordered development of the sacrum in which portions of the sacrum, which normally is formed by fusion of five sacral vertebrae S1-S5, fail to form or fail to form normally." []

Name: C2-C3 subluxation
Definition: "A partial dislocation of the intervertebral joint between the second and third cervical vertebrae." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Caudal interpedicular narrowing
Definition: "Narrowing (becoming gradually narrower) of the distance between vertebral pedicles that gets progressively more severe towards to caudal (lower) end of the vertebral column. Note that normally, the interpedicular distances get progressively wider as one proceeds down the spine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Progressive congenital scoliosis
Definition: "A progressive form of scoliosis with congenital onset." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cervical vertebral agenesis
Definition: "Agenesis of one or more vertebrae of the cervical vertebral column." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent spinous processes of lower thoracic and lumbar vertebrae
Absent vertebra
Definition: "A developmental defect characterized by agenesis of one or more vertebral bodies." [PMID:26167231]

Name: Thoracic hemivertebrae
Definition: "Absence of one half of the vertebral body in the thoracic spine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal sacral segmentation
Definition: "An abnormality related to a defect of vertebral separation of sacral vertebrae during development." []

Name: Cervical vertebral dysplasia
Definition: "Dysplasia of the cervical vertebral column." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lower thoracic interpediculate narrowness
Definition: "A reduction of the distance between the lower thoracic vertebral pedicles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Narrow anterio-posterior vertebral body diameter
Definition: "An abnormal reduction of the anterioposterior diameter of the vertebral body." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Poorly ossified cervical vertebrae
Definition: "Decreased ossification of the cervical vertebral bodies, i.e., of the Cervical vertebrae set." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cervical spondylosis
Definition: "Arthrosis, i.e., of degenerative joint disease, affecting the cervical vertebral column." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cervical vertebral bodies with decreased anteroposterior diameter
Thoracolumbar interpediculate narrowness
Definition: "A reduction of the distance between thoracolumbar vertebral pedicles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lumbar interpedicular narrowing
Definition: "Narrowing (becoming gradually narrower) of the distance between lumbar vertebral pedicles that gets progressively more severe towards to caudal (lower) end of the vertebral column." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Spondylolisthesis at L5-S1
Definition: "Complete bilateral fractures of the pars interarticularis resulting in the anterior slippage of the fifth lumbar vertebral body (L5) onto the sacrum (level S1)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Premature anterior fontanel closure
Definition: "Early closure (ossification) of the anterior fontanelle, which generally undergoes closure around the 18th month of life." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Inferior lens subluxation
Definition: "Partial displacement of the lens in the inferior direction." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: High hypermetropia
Definition: "A severe form of hypermetropia with over +5.00 diopters." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_ncarter, https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0986-4123]

Name: Median cleft lip and palate
Definition: "Cleft lip or palate affecting the midline region of the palate." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Moderate sensorineural hearing impairment
Definition: "The presence of a moderate form of sensorineural hearing impairment." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Central posterior corneal opacity
Definition: "Reduced transparency of the central posterior portion of the corneal stroma." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bilateral conductive hearing impairment
Definition: "A bilateral type of conductive hearing impairment." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the vertebral spinous processes
Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the sacrum
Definition: "Aplasia or developmental hypoplasia of the sacral bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal coccyx morphology
Definition: "Any structural abnormality of the coccyx." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Posterior helix pit
Definition: "Permanent indentation on the posteromedial aspect of the helix that may be sharply or indistinctly delineated." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Congenital sensorineural hearing impairment
Definition: "A type of hearing impairment caused by an abnormal functionality of the cochlear nerve with congenital onset." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Long hairs growing from helix of pinna
Absence of acoustic reflex
Definition: "Absence of the acoustic reflex, an involuntary contraction of the stapedius muscle that occurs in response to high-intensity sound stimuli." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cleft at the superior portion of the pinna
Low-frequency hearing loss
Definition: "A type of hearing impairment affecting primarily the low frequencies of sound (125 Hz to 1000 Hz)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormally folded helix
Definition: "Any structural anomaly of the border of the helix, which usually forms a rolled rim but is highly variable in shape." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Microtia
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the external ear." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152421, PMID:3270622]

Name: Cochlear malformation
Definition: "The presence of a malformed cochlea." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent vestibular function
Definition: "Complete lack of functioning of the vestibular apparatus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Vestibular areflexia
Definition: "Vestibular areflexia can be measured as the absence of the caloric nystagmus response in electronystagmography." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:26918204]

Name: Microtia, second degree
Definition: "Median longitudinal length of the ear more than two standard deviations below the mean in the presence of some, but not all, parts of the normal ear." [eom:ae27d9699faef13a, PMID:19152421]

Name: External ear malformation
Definition: "A malformation of the auricle of the ear." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Low-frequency sensorineural hearing impairment
Definition: "A form of sensorineural hearing impairment that affects primarily the lower frequencies." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Underfolded helix
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the helix that either affects the entire helix, or is localized." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Underfolded superior helices
Definition: "A condition in which the superior portion of the helix is folded over to a lesser degree than normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplasia of the cochlea
Definition: "Developmental hypoplasia of the cochlea." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Mild neurosensory hearing impairment
Definition: "The presence of a mild form of sensorineural hearing impairment." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Slit-like opening of the exterior auditory meatus
Definition: "A type of stenosis of the external auditory meatus in which the opening of the external auditory meatus appears as a vertical slit." [PMID:12843316]

Name: Hypoplastic helices
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the helix, i.e., of the outer rim of the pinna." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Congenital conductive hearing impairment
Definition: "A type of conductive deafness with congenital onset." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Prominent antitragus
Definition: "Increased anterosuperior prominence of the area between the bottom of the incisura and the inner margin of the antihelix." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152421]

Name: Postlingual sensorineural hearing impairment
Definition: "A form of sensorineural hearing impairment with onset after the acquisition of speech." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Mild conductive hearing impairment
Definition: "A mild form of conductive hearing impairment." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Supraauricular pit
Definition: "Benign congenital lesion of the supraauricular soft tissue consisting of a blind-ending narrow tube or pit." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Progressive conductive hearing impairment
Definition: "A progressive type of conductive deafness." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Morphological abnormality of the middle ear
Definition: "An abnormality of the morphology or structure of the middle ear." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_mbitner-glidicz]

Name: Infantile sensorineural hearing impairment
Definition: "A form of sensorineural hearing impairment with infantile onset." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Adult onset sensorineural hearing impairment
Definition: "The presence of sensorineural deafness with late onset." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bilateral sensorineural hearing impairment
Definition: "A bilateral form of sensorineural hearing impairment." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Severe sensorineural hearing impairment
Definition: "A severe form of sensorineural hearing impairment." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the stapes
Definition: "An abnormality of the stapes, a stirrup-shaped ossicle in the middle ear." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pulsatile tinnitus
Definition: "Pulsatile tinnitus is generally classified a kind of objective tinnitus, meaning that it is not only audible to the patient but also to the examiner on auscultation of the auditory canal and/or of surrounding structures with use of an auscultation tube or stethoscope. Usually, pulsatile tinnitus is heard as a lower pitched thumping or booming, a rougher blowing sound which is coincidental with respiration, or as a clicking, higher pitched rhythmic sensation." [PMID:23885280]

Name: Ureteral dysgenesis
Definition: "A developmental anomaly of the ureter." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Agonadism
Definition: "Absence of sex glands (gonads are the organs that produce gametes; testis in males and ovary in females)." []

Name: Hypertrophy of the urinary bladder
Definition: "Abnormal enlargement of the urinary bladder." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Nephroblastomatosis
Definition: "Presence of persistent islands of renal blastema in the postnatal kidney. Nephroblastomatosis represents a complex abnormality of nephrogenesis and has been defined as the persistence of metanephricblastema into infancy and childhood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:10707720]

Name: Uric acid urolithiasis independent of gout
Autonomic erectile dysfunction
Definition: "Impotence (inability to develop or maintain an erection) resulting from abnormal functioning of the autonomic nervous system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Crescentic glomerulonephritis
Definition: "A type of extracapillary glomerulonephritis characterized by the formation of crescent-like cellular proliferation." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:Eurenomics_ewuehl]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the fallopian tube
Definition: "Aplasia or developmental hypoplasia of the fallopian tube." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Multiple small medullary renal cysts
Definition: "The presence of many cysts in the medulla of the kidney." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:Eurenomics_ewuehl]

Name: Renotubular dysgenesis
Definition: "A developmental defect characterized by absence or poor development of proximal renal tubules." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Urethral stenosis
Definition: "Abnormal narrowing of the urethra." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Renal sarcoma
Definition: "A sarcoma of the kidney." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Clitoral hypertrophy
Definition: "Hypertrophy of the clitoris." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Gonadal dysgenesis, male

[https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

At obstetric US examination, views of the fetal neck demonstrate a dilated trachea filled with trapped fluid. Each nerve has distinct nuclei within the brainstem. The vestibular nerve is primarily responsible for maintaining body balance and eye movements, while the cochlear nerve is responsible for hearing." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:30726044]

Name: Abnormality of the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the thumb
Definition: "This term applies if the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the thumb, which is located at the proximal end of the phalanx, does not appear in concordance with gender and age dependant norms as seen on x-rays. In contrast to the proximal phalanges of the digits 2-5, the proximal phalanx of the thumb is embryologically equivalent to the middle phalanges of the other digits, whereas the first metacarpal is embryologically of phalangeal origin and as such equivalent to the proximal phalanges of the other digits." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cone-shaped epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the thumb
Definition: "A cone-shaped appearance of the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the thumb of the hand, producing a 'ball-in-a-socket' appearance. This epiphysis is located at the proximal end of the phalanx and is normally nearly flat. The related entity 'angel-shaped' epiphysis refers to a pronounced cone-shaped epiphysis in combination with a pseudoepiphysis at the distal end of the phalanx. In contrast to the proximal phalanges of the digits 2-5, the proximal phalanx of the thumb is embryologically equivalent to the middle phalanges of the other digits, whereas the first metacarpal is embryologically of phalangeal origin and as such equivalent to the proximal phalanges of the other digits." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Enlarged epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the thumb
Definition: "Abnormally large size of the epiphysis located at the proximal end of the proximal phalanx of the thumb with respect to age-dependent norms. In contrast to the proximal phalanges of the digits 2-5, the proximal phalanx of the thumb is embryologically equivalent to the middle phalanges of the other digits, whereas the first metacarpal is embryologically of phalangeal origin and as such equivalent to the proximal phalanges of the other digits." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fragmentation of the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the thumb
Definition: "Epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the thumb having multiple bony fragments." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Irregular epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the thumb
Definition: "Irregular radiographic opacity of the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the thumb. In contrast to the proximal phalanges of the digits 2-5, the proximal phalanx of the thumb is embryologically equivalent to the middle phalanges of the other digits, whereas the first metacarpal is embryologically of phalangeal origin and as such equivalent to the proximal phalanges of the other digits." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ivory epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the thumb
Definition: "Sclerosis of the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the thumb, leading to an increased degree of radiopacity (white or ivory appearance) in X-rays." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pseudoepiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the thumb
Definition: "A pseudoepiphysis (which is a secondary ossification center distinct from the normal epiphysis) of the proximal phalanx of the thumb." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Small epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the thumb
Definition: "Abnormally small size of the epiphysis located at the proximal end of the proximal phalanx of the thumb with respect to age-dependent norms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Stippling of the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the thumb
Definition: "The presence of abnormal punctate (speckled, dot-like) calcifications in the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the thumb. In contrast to the proximal phalanges of the digits 2-5, the proximal phalanx of the thumb is embryologically equivalent to the middle phalanges of the other digits, whereas the first metacarpal is embryologically of phalangeal origin and as such equivalent to the proximal phalanges of the other digits." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Triangular epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the thumb
Definition: "A triangular appearance of the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the thumb of the hand. This epiphysis is located at the proximal end of the phalanx and is normally nearly flat. In contrast to the proximal phalanges of the digits 2-5, the proximal phalanx of the thumb is embryologically equivalent to the middle phalanges of the other digits, whereas the first metacarpal is embryologically of phalangeal origin and as such equivalent to the proximal phalanges of the other digits." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the thumb
Definition: "Absence of the epiphysis located at the proximal end of the distal phalanx of the thumb." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bracket epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the thumb
Definition: "An abnormality of the distal phalanx of the thumb in which the epiphysis surrounds a phalangeal bone, having a bracket-like form and reaching from the proximal side of a phalanx to the distal side." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cone-shaped epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the thumb
Definition: "A cone-shaped appearance of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the thumb of the hand, producing a 'ball-in-a-socket' appearance. This epiphysis is located at the proximal end of the phalanx and is normally nearly flat. The related entity 'angel-shaped' epiphysis refers to a pronounced cone-shaped epiphysis in combination with a pseudoepiphysis at the distal end of the phalanx." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Enlarged epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the thumb
Definition: "Abnormally large size of the epiphysis located at the proximal end of the distal phalanx of the thumb with respect to age-dependent norms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fragmentation of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the thumb
Definition: "Epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the thumb having multiple bony fragments." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Irregular epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the thumb
Definition: "Uneven radiographic opacity of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the thumb." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ivory epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the thumb
Definition: "Sclerosis of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the thumb, leading to an increased degree of radiopacity (white or ivory appearance) in X-rays." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pseudoepiphysis of the distal phalanx of the thumb
Definition: "A pseudoepiphysis (which is a secondary ossification center distinct from the normal epiphysis) of the distal phalanx of the thumb." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Small epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the thumb
Definition: "Abnormally small size of the epiphysis located at the proximal end of the distal phalanx of the thumb with respect to age-dependent norms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Stippling of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the thumb
Definition: "The presence of abnormal punctate (speckled, dot-like) calcifications in the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the thumb." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Triangular epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the thumb
Definition: "A triangular appearance of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the thumb of the hand. This epiphysis is located at the proximal end of the phalanx and is normally nearly flat." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent epiphyses of the thumb
Definition: "Absence of one or more epiphyses of the thumb." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bracket epiphyses of the thumb
Definition: "An abnormality of the thumb in which the epiphysis surrounds a phalangeal bone, having a bracket-like form and reaching from the proximal side of a phalanx to the distal side." [PMID:24432108]

Name: Cone-shaped epiphysis of the thumb
Definition: "A cone-shaped appearance of the epiphyses of the thumb, producing a 'ball-in-a-socket' appearance. The related entity 'angel-shaped' epiphysis refers to a pronounced cone-shaped epiphysis in combination with a pseudoepiphysis at the distal end of a phalanx." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Enlarged thumb epiphysis
Definition: "Abnormally large size of the epiphyses of the thumb with respect to age-dependent norms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fragmentation of thumb epiphysis
Definition: "Epiphysis of the thumb having multiple bony fragments." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Irregular thumb epiphysis
Definition: "Uneven radiographic opacity of the one or more epiphyses of the thumb." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ivory epiphysis of the thumb
Definition: "Sclerosis of one or more of the epiphyses of the thumb, leading to an increased degree of radiopacity (white or ivory appearance) in X-rays." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pseudoepiphysis of the thumb
Definition: "A pseudoepiphysis (which is a secondary ossification center distinct from the normal epiphysis) of one or more phalanges of the thumb." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Small thumb epiphysis
Definition: "Abnormally small size of one or more of the epiphyses of the thumb with respect to age-dependent norms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Stippling of thumb epiphysis
Definition: "The presence of abnormal punctate (speckled, dot-like) calcifications in one or more of the epiphyses of the thumb." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Contracture of the distal interphalangeal joint of the fingers
Definition: "Chronic loss of joint motion in one or more distal interphalangeal joints of the fingers." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Osteolytic defects of the hand bones
Finger symphalangism
Definition: "An abnormal union between bones or parts of bones of the fingers. The synonymous term \"symphalangism of the hand\" may be translated as fusions of bones of varying digree, that involve at least one phalangeal bone of the hand. If bony fusions are referred to as \"Symphalangism\" the fusion occurs in a proximo-distal axis. Fusions of bones of the fingers in a radio-ulnar axis are referred to as \"bony\" Syndactyly." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Metacarpal synostosis
Definition: "Fusion involving two or more metacarpal bones (A synostosis of the first metacarpal and the proximal phalanx of the thumb can also be observed, note that the first metacarpal bone corresponds to a proximal phalanx)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Carpal synostosis
Definition: "Synostosis (bony fusion) involving one or more bones of the carpus (scaphoid, lunate, triquetrum, trapezium, trapezoid, capitate, hamate, pisiform)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Synostosis involving the 1st metacarpal
Definition: "Fusion of the 1st metacarpal with another bone. In contrast to the proximal phalanges of the digits 2 to 5, the proximal phalanx of the thumb is embryologically equivalent to the middle phalanges of the other digits, whereas the first metacarpal is embryologically of phalangeal origin and as such equivalent to the proximal phalanges of the other digits." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Chronic CSF lymphocytosis
Definition: "Chronic cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) lymphocytosis is defined as the finding, in at least two serial CSF examinations, of more than 5 cells per cubic millimeter." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased CSF interferon alpha
Definition: "Increased concentration of interferon alpha in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Chilblains
Definition: "Chilblains, also called perniosis, are an inflammatory skin condition related to an abnormal vascular response to the cold. We are unaware of a reliable estimate of incidence. It typically presents as tender, pruritic red or bluish lesions located symmetrically on the dorsal aspect of the fingers, toes, ears and nose. Less commonly, reports describe involvement of the thighs and buttocks. The lesions present hours after exposure to cold and usually resolve spontaneously in one to three weeks." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:1832531, PMID:22025653]

Name: Retinal capillary hemangioma
Definition: "A benign vascular tumor of the retina without any neoplastic characteristics." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Spinal hemangioblastoma
Definition: "A hemangioblastoma of the spinal cord." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal epididymis morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the epididymis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Papillary cystadenoma of the epididymis
Definition: "A cystadenoma, an epithelial tumor, that originates within the head of the epididymis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:24441657]

Name: Subependymal nodules
Definition: "Small nodular masses which originate in the subependymal region of the lateral ventricles and protrude into the ventricular cavity. They may represent subependymal hamartomas of tuberous sclerosis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1735-8178]

Name: Cortical tubers
Definition: "Cortical tubers in the brain are hamartomatous lesions typically located at the gray-white matter interface, commonly in the frontal and parietal lobes. Cortical tubers are composed of abnormal glial and neural cells, and the size, number, and location vary among patients." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Subependymal giant-cell astrocytoma
Definition: "A demarcated, largely intraventricular tumor in the region of the foramen of Monro composed of spindle to large plump or ganglion-like cells with eosinophilic to amphophilic cytoplasm and somewhat pleomorphic nuclei with occasional prominent nucleoli. These tumors are almost always associated with tuberous sclerosis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypomelanotic macule
Definition: "Hypomelanotic macules (\"ash leaf spots\") are white or lighter patches of skin that may appear anywhere on the body and are caused by a lack of melanin. White ash leaf-shaped macules are considered to be characteristic of tuberous sclerosis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:10695583]

Name: Adenoma sebaceum
Definition: "The presence of a sebaceous adenoma with origin in the sebum secreting cells of the skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Shagreen patch
Definition: "A plaque representing a connective-tissue nevus. Connective tissue naevi are uncommon skin lesions that occur when the deeper layers of the skin do not develop correctly or the components of these layers occur in the wrong proportion. Shagreen patches are oval-shaped and nevoid, skin-colored or occasionally pigmented, smooth or crinkled. The word shagreen refers to a type of roughened untanned leather." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:10695583]

Name: Dental enamel pits
Definition: "The presence of small depressions in the dental enamel." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the subungual region
Definition: "A lesion located beneath a fingernail or toenail." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Subungual fibromas
Definition: "The presence of fibromata beneath finger or toenails." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bladder neoplasm
Definition: "The presence of a neoplasm of the urinary bladder." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Renal neoplasm
Definition: "The presence of a neoplasm of the kidney." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Achromatic retinal patches
Definition: "Areas of the retina lacking pigmentation. Punched out areas of chorioretinal hypopigmentation less than 1 disc diameter in size and tending to be located in the midperiphery of the retina." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:11264130]

Name: Neoplasm of striated muscle
Definition: "A benign or malignant neoplasm (tumor) originating in striated muscle, either skeletal muscle or cardiac muscle." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Cardiac rhabdomyoma
Definition: "A benign tumor of cardiac striated muscle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Rhabdomyoma
Definition: "A benign tumor of striated muscle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cerebral hamartoma
Definition: "The presence of a hamartoma of the cerebrum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Plexiform neurofibroma
Definition: "A neurofibroma in which Schwann cells proliferate inside the nerve sheath, producing an irregularly thickened, distorted, tortuous structure." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Glioma
Definition: "The presence of a glioma, which is a neoplasm of the central nervous system originating from a glial cell (astrocytes or oligodendrocytes)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Optic nerve glioma
Definition: "A glioma originating in the optic nerve or optic chiasm." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Spinal neurofibroma
Definition: "A neurofibroma (benign peripheral nerve sheath tumor) localized in the spine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Tibial pseudarthrosis
Definition: "Pseudarthrosis, or \"false joint\" of the tibia is the result of a developmental failure in the tibia progressing to spontaneous fracture and subsequent fibrous nonunion. The fracture is rarely present at birth but commonly develops during the first 18 months of life." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:30996736]

Name: Lisch nodules
Definition: "The presence of pigmented, oval and dome-shaped raised hamartomatous nevi of the iris.." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal antihelix morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the antihelix." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplasia of the antihelix
Definition: "Developmental hypoplasia of the antihelix." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia of the parotid gland
Definition: "Absence of the parotid gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Nephrosclerosis
Definition: "Nephrosclerosis refers to thickening or scarring (\"sclerosis\") resulting from damage to the renal arterioles, also referred to as arteriosclerosis of the kidney arteries." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Stiff shoulders
Definition: "Shoulder joint stiffness is a perceived sensation of tightness in shoulders when attempting to move them after a period of inactivity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Distichiasis
Definition: "Double rows of eyelashes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal spinal dura mater morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the spinal dura mater, which is the outermost of the three layers of the meninges surrounding the spinal cord." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Spinal arachnoid cyst
Definition: "Presence of arachnoid cysts of the spinal canal extradurally in the epidural space." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thick nasal septum
Definition: "Abnormally increased thickness of the nasal septum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lumbosacral hirsutism
Definition: "Abnormally increased hair growth in the lumbosacral region." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Large earlobe
Definition: "Increased volume of the earlobe, that is, abnormally prominent ear lobules." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152421]

Name: Aplasia of the pectoralis major muscle
Definition: "Absence of the pectoralis major muscle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cleft in skull base
Definition: "A bony defect in the skull base." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fibrous syngnathia
Definition: "Complete or nearly complete soft tissue fusion of the alveolar ridges." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Ankyloblepharon
Definition: "Partial fusion of the upper and lower eyelid margins by single or multiple bands of tissue." [PMID:18125427]

Name: Popliteal pterygium
Definition: "A pterygium (or pterygia) occurring in the popliteal region (the back of the knee)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Intercrural pterygium
Definition: "A pterygium (or pterygia) in the intercrural (groin) region." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pyramidal skinfold extending from the base to the top of the nails
Definition: "Pyramidal skinfold extending from the base to the top of the nails is a rare and distinctive anomaly seen in popliteal pterygia syndrome." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Neck pterygia
Definition: "Pterygia affecting the neck." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Antecubital pterygium
Definition: "Pterygium affecting the elbow. This is a cutaneous web that can lead to severe flexion contracture of the elbow joint. Antecubital pterygium can be unilateral, bilateral, symmetric, or asysmmetric." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anterior clefting of vertebral bodies
Definition: "Anterior schisis (cleft or cleavage) of vertebral bodies." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Facial wrinkling
Definition: "Excessive wrinkling of the skin of the face." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Limb pain
Definition: "Chronic pain in the limbs with no clear focal etiology." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Low hanging columella
Definition: "Columella extending inferior to the level of the nasal base, when viewed from the side." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the phalanges of the hand
Definition: "Small or missing phalangeal bones of the fingers of the hand." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Broad phalanges of the hand
Definition: "Increased width of the phalanges of the hand." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bullet-shaped phalanges of the hand
Definition: "The presence of short and wide phalanges which taper distally (\"bullet shaped\")." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Osteolytic defects of the phalanges of the hand
Definition: "Dissolution or degeneration of bone tissue of the phalanges of the hand." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Patchy sclerosis of finger phalanx
Definition: "Uneven (irregular) increase in bone density of one or more of the phalanges of the hand." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Symphalangism affecting the phalanges of the hand
Definition: "Fusion of two or more phalangeal bones of the hand." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Triangular shaped phalanges of the hand
Amniotic constriction ring
Definition: "Annular constrictions around the digits, limbs, or trunk, occurring congenitally (sometimes causing intrauterine autoamputation) and also associated with a wide variety of disorders. Constrictive amniotic bands are the result of primary amniotic rupture, which can lead to entanglement of fetal tissue (especially limbs) in fibrous amniotic strands." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Adactyly
Definition: "The absence of all phalanges of all the digits of a limb and the associated soft tissues." [PMID:19125433]

Name: Absent thumb
Definition: "Absent thumb, i.e., the absence of both phalanges of a thumb and the associated soft tissues." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125433]

Name: Short thumb
Definition: "Hypoplasia (congenital reduction in size) of the thumb." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: 3-4 toe syndactyly
Definition: "Syndactyly with fusion of toes three and four." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Iliac horns
Definition: "Horn-like malformations of the iliac crests with symmetrical bilateral central posterior iliac processes. A characteristic finding in the Nail-Patella syndrome. Iliac horns are visible on X-ray and may be palpable, but are asymptomatic." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lester's sign
Definition: "A zone of darker pigmentation around the central part of the iris with a roughly cloverleaf or flower shape." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the biceps
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the biceps muscle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Biceps aplasia
Definition: "Absence of the biceps muscle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the triceps
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the triceps muscle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Triceps aplasia
Definition: "Absence of the triceps muscle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the musculature of the thigh
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment involving the musculature of the thigh." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the quadriceps
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the quadriceps muscle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Quadriceps aplasia
Definition: "Absence of the quadriceps muscle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Perianal abscess
Definition: "The presence of an abscess located around the anus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hemisacrum
Definition: "A hemisacral defect involving the sacral vertebrae S2 to S5. In hemisacrum, the first sacral vertebra is intact and there is agenesis involving only S2-S5." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bifid sacrum
Definition: "Presence of a bifid sacral bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Teratoma
Definition: "The presence of a teratoma." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Presacral teratoma
Definition: "A type of sacrococcygeal teratoma located anterior to the sacrum and entirely inside the body (Altman type IV)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Branchial anomaly
Definition: "Congenital developmental defect arising from the primitive branchial apparatus." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Branchial fistula
Definition: "A congenital fistula in the neck resulting from incomplete closure of a branchial cleft." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Branchial cyst
Definition: "A branchial cyst is a remnant of embryonic development resulting from a failure of obliteration of a branchial cleft and consists of a subcutaneous cystic mass. Cysts are located anterior or posterior to the ear or in the submandibular region." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Cholesteatoma
Definition: "Cholesteatoma is a benign but potentially destructive growth consisting of keratinizing epithelium located in the middle ear and/or mastoid process. In cholesteatoma, a skin cyst grows into the middle ear and mastoid. The cyst is not cancerous but can erode tissue and cause destruction of the ear." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Euthyroid goiter
Definition: "A goiter that is not associated with functional thyroid abnormalities." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Supernumerary spleens
Definition: "The presence of two or more accessory spleens." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Maternal diabetes
Definition: "Maternal diabetes can either be a gestational, mostly type 2 diabetes, or a type 1 diabetes. Essential is the resulting maternal hyperglycemia as a non-specific teratogen, imposing the same risk of congenital malformations to pregnant women with both type 1 and type2 diabetes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia of the phalanges of the hand
Definition: "Absence of one or more of the phalanges of the hand." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short phalanx of finger
Definition: "Short (hypoplastic) phalanx of finger, affecting one or more phalanges." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Tooth agenesis
Definition: "The absence of one or more teeth from the normal series by a failure to develop" [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154, PMID:31468724]

Name: Low-output congestive heart failure
Definition: "A form of heart failure characterized by reduced cardiac output. This may be seen in patients with heart failure owing to ischemic heart disease, hypertension, cardiomyopathy, and other causes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Nephrogenic diabetes insipidus
Definition: "A form of diabetes insipidus caused by failure of the kidneys to respond to vasopressin (AVP)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anomaly of the upper limb diaphyses
Definition: "A structural abnormality of a diaphysis of the arm." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:UToronto_htrang]

Name: Abnormal upper limb metaphysis morphology
Definition: "An anomaly of one or more metaphyses of the arms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the elbow
Definition: "An anomaly of the joint that connects the upper and the lower arm." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Amelia involving the upper limbs
Definition: "Amelia of one or both upper limbs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Upper limb phocomelia
Definition: "Missing or malformed long bones of the upper limbs with the distal parts (the hands) connected to the variably shortened or even absent upper extremity, leading to a flipper-like appearance, as opposed to other forms of limb malformations were either the whole limb is missing (such as amelia), or the distal part of a limb is absent (peromelia)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Upper limb peromelia
Definition: "Peromelia affecting only the upper limbs. That is, the distal parts of the arm are missing leading to stump formation." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Aplasia/hypoplasia of the extremities
Definition: "Absence (due to failure to form) or underdevelopment of the extremities." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lower limb undergrowth
Definition: "Leg shortening because of underdevelopment of one or more bones of the lower extremity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia involving bones of the lower limbs
Amelia involving the lower limbs
Definition: "Amelia of one or both legs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lower limb phocomelia
Definition: "Phocomelia affecting only the lower limbs." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Lower limb peromelia
Definition: "Peromelia affecting only the lower limbs. That is, the distal parts of the leg are missing leading to stump formation." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Forearm undergrowth
Definition: "Forearm shortening because of underdevelopment of one or more bones of the forearm." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia involving bones of the upper limbs
Upper limb undergrowth
Definition: "Arm shortening because of underdevelopment of one or more bones of the upper extremity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia involving bones of the extremities
Limb undergrowth
Definition: "Limb shortening because of underdevelopment of one or more bones of the extremities." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Amelia
Definition: "Congenital absence (aplasia) of one or more limbs." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Peromelia
Definition: "The distal parts of the limbs are missing leading to a stump formation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Phocomelia
Definition: "Missing or malformed long bones of the extremities with the distal parts (such as hands and/or feet) connected to the variably shortened or even absent extremity, leading to a flipper-like appearance, as opposed to other forms of limb malformations were either the hole limb is missing (such as amelia), or the distal part of a limb is absent (peromelia)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Peripheral neuropathy
Definition: "Peripheral neuropathy is a general term for any disorder of the peripheral nervous system. The main clinical features used to classify peripheral neuropathy are distribution, type (mainly demyelinating versus mainly axonal), duration, and course." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Mononeuropathy
Definition: "A focal lesion of a single peripheral nerve. Damage to a sensory nerve is accompanied by sensory impairment of all modalities in the affected anatomic distribution." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal distal phalanx morphology of finger
Definition: "Any anomaly of distal phalanx of finger." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal middle phalanx morphology of the hand
Definition: "An anomaly of middle phalanx of finger." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal proximal phalanx morphology of the hand
Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the distal phalanges of the hand
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the distal phalanges." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Broad distal phalanx of finger
Definition: "Abnormally wide (broad) distal phalanx of finger." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Bullet-shaped distal phalanges of the hand
Definition: "Short and wide distal phalanges that taper distally. Bullet-shaped phalanges lack the normal diaphyseal constriction." []

Name: Curved distal phalanges of the hand
Osteolytic defects of the distal phalanges of the hand
Patchy sclerosis of distal phalanx of finger
Definition: "Uneven (irregular) increase in bone density of the distal phalanges of the hand." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the middle phalanges of the hand
Broad middle phalanx of finger
Definition: "Increased width of the middle phalanx of finger." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bullet-shaped middle phalanges of the hand
Definition: "Any of the middle phalanges with short and wide phalanx that tapers distally. Bullet-shaped phalanges lack the normal diaphyseal constriction." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Curved middle phalanges of the hand
Osteolytic defects of the middle phalanges of the hand
Patchy sclerosis of middle phalanx of finger
Definition: "Uneven (irregular) increase in bone density of one or more of the middle phalanges of the hand." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Symphalangism of middle phalanx of finger
Definition: "Fusion of a middle phalanx of a finger with another bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Triangular shaped middle phalanges of the hand
Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the proximal phalanges of the hand
Broad proximal phalanges of the hand
Definition: "Increased width of the proximal phalanges of the finger." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bullet-shaped proximal phalanges of the hand
Definition: "Short and wide proximal phalanges that taper distally . Bullet-shaped phalanges lack the normal diaphyseal constriction." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Curved proximal phalanges of the hand
Osteolytic defects of the proximal phalanges of the hand
Patchy sclerosis of proximal phalanx of finger
Definition: "Uneven increase in bone density of the proximal phalanges of the hand." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Symphalangism affecting the proximal phalanges of the hand
Triangular shaped proximal phalanges of the hand
Triangular shaped distal phalanges of the hand
Cerebellar ataxia associated with quadrupedal gait
Definition: "The presence of cerebellar signs and symptoms such as lack of balance associated with quadrupedal gait (locomotion on all four extremities with a 'bear-like' gait with the legs held straight)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Simplified gyral pattern
Definition: "An abnormality of the cerebral cortex with fewer gyri but with normal cortical thickness. This pattern is usually often associated with congenital microcephaly." [http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q90573458, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:22427329]

Name: Broad distal phalanges of all fingers
Definition: "Abnormally wide (broad) distal phalanx of finger of all fingers." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia of the distal phalanges of the hand
Short distal phalanx of finger
Definition: "Short distance from the end of the finger to the most distal interphalangeal crease or the distal interphalangeal joint flexion point. That is, hypoplasia of one or more of the distal phalanx of finger." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125433]

Name: Duplication of the distal phalanx of hand
Definition: "This term applies if one or more of the distal phalanges of the hand are either partially duplicated, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance of the phalanges, or completely duplicated." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Tapered distal phalanges of finger
Definition: "A reduction in diameter of the distal phalanx of finger towards the distal end." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Trichorrhexis nodosa
Definition: "Trichorrhexis nodosa is the formation of nodes along the hair shaft through which breakage readily occurs. It is thus a focal defect in the hair fiber that is characterized by thickening or weak points (nodes) that cause the hair to break off easily. The result is defective, abnormally fragile hair." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of hair pigmentation
Definition: "An abnormality of hair pigmentation (color)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of secondary sexual hair
Definition: "Abnormality of the growth of secondary sexual hair, which normally ensues during puberty. In males, secondary sexual hair usually comprises body hair, including underarm, abdominal, chest, and pubic hair. In females, secondary sexual hair usually comprises a lesser degree of body hair, most prominently underarm and pubic hair." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Localized hirsutism
Definition: "Abnormally increased hair growth with a localized distribution." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: High anterior hairline
Definition: "Distance between the hairline (trichion) and the glabella (the most prominent point on the frontal bone above the root of the nose), in the midline, more than two SD above the mean. Alternatively, an apparently increased distance between the hairline and the glabella." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Underdeveloped supraorbital ridges
Definition: "Flatness of the supraorbital portion of the frontal bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125436]

Name: Anotia
Definition: "Complete absence of any auricular structures." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125421]

Name: Telangiectasia of the ear
Definition: "The presence of telangiectasia of the ear." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thickened ears
Definition: "Increased thickness of the external ear." []

Name: Abnormality of the crus of the helix
Definition: "An abnormality of the crus of the helix, which is the horizontal piece of cartilage located outside the ear canal that divides the upper and lower parts of the ear." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal antitragus morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the antitragus, which is a small tubercle opposite to the tragus of the ear. The antitragus and the tragus are separated by the intertragic notch." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Horizontal crus of helix
Definition: "An abnormal horizontal axis orientation of the crus of the helix. That is, the main axis of the crus of the helix is perpendicular to the medial longitudinal axis of the ear, instead of sloping inferoposteriorly." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152421]

Name: Underdeveloped crus of the helix
Definition: "Developmental hypoplasia of the crus of the helix. That is, flatter and/or shorter crus helix than average." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152421]

Name: Prominent crus of helix
Definition: "The presence of an abnormally prominent of the crus of the helix. That is, development of the crus helix to the same degree as an average antihelix stem or helix." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152421]

Name: Unilateral deafness
Definition: "A unilateral absence of sensory perception of sound." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Crumpled ear
Definition: "Distortion of the course of the normal folds of the ear and the appearance of supernumerary crura and folds." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Cleft helix
Definition: "A notched form of the helix of the ear. That is, a defect in the continuity of the helix, which may occur at any point along its length." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152421]

Name: Conjunctival nodule
Definition: "Presence of nodules in the conjunctiva of the eye." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Prominent ear helix
Definition: "Abnormally prominent ear helix." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thin ear helix
Definition: "Decreased thickness of the helix of the ear." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the earlobes
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the ear lobes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Attached earlobe
Definition: "Attachment of the lobe to the side of the face at the lowest point of the lobe without curving upward." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Anterior creases of earlobe
Definition: "Sharply demarcated, typically linear and approximately horizontal, indentations in the outer surface of the ear lobe." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Uplifted earlobe
Definition: "An abnormal orientation of the earlobes such that they point out- and upward. That is, the lateral surface of ear lobe faces superiorly." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152421]

Name: Aplasia of the middle ear ossicles
Definition: "Absence of the middle ear ossicles, malleus, incus, and stapes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal temporal bone morphology
Definition: "Abnormality of the temporal bone of the skull, which is situated at the sides and base of the skull roughly underlying the region of the face known as the temple." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal tragus morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the tragus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the tragus
Definition: "Aplasia or developmental hypoplasia of the tragus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cyclopia
Definition: "Cyclopia is a congenital abnormality in which there is only one eye. That eye is centrally placed in the area normally occupied by the root of the nose." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_ncarter]

Name: Corneal asymmetry
Definition: "The presence of a size difference between the left and right cornea." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anisocoria
Definition: "Anisocoria, or unequal pupil size, may represent a benign physiologic variant or a manifestation of disease." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Persistent pupillary membrane
Definition: "The presence of remnants of a fetal membrane that persist as strands of tissue crossing the pupil." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ectopia pupillae
Definition: "A malposition of the pupil owing to a developmental defect of the iris." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8727-6592, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Retinoblastoma
Definition: "A tumor of the eye originating from cells of the retina." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Nevus of Ota
Definition: "A dermal melanocytic hamartoma that presents as bluish hyperpigmentation on the face along the first or second branches of the trigeminal nerve. Nevus of Ota may involve the sclera." [PMID:14673306]

Name: Duane anomaly
Definition: "A condition associated with a limitation of the horizontal ocular movement with retraction of the globe and narrowing of the palpebral fissure on adduction" [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Vascular remnant arising from the disc
Definition: "Persistence of the hyaloid artery, which is the embryonic artery that runs from the optic disk to the posterior lens capsule may persist; the site of attachment may form an opacity. The hyaloid artery is a branch of the ophthalmic artery, and usually regresses completely before birth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:23772130]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia involving the nose
Definition: "Underdevelopment or absence of the nose or parts thereof." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Epiphora
Definition: "Abnormally increased lacrimation, that is, excessive tearing (watering eye)." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_ncarter, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0986-4123, PMID:28003974]

Name: Aplasia of the nose
Definition: "Complete absence of all nasal structures." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thick nasal alae
Definition: "Increase in bulk of the ala nasi." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Abnormal columella morphology
Definition: "A structural abnormality of the columella." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Asymmetry of the nares
Definition: "Asymmetry or size difference between the left and right nostril." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Enlarged naris
Definition: "Increased aperture of the nostril." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Single naris
Definition: "The presence of only a single nostril." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Narrow naris
Definition: "Slender, slit-like aperture of the nostril." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Supernumerary naris
Definition: "The presence of more than two nostrils." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the nasal septum
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the nasal septum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Narrow nasal septum
Definition: "Abnormally narrow nasal septum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Facial hirsutism
Definition: "Excess facial hair." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sunken cheeks
Definition: "Lack or loss of the soft tissues between the zygomata and mandible." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Mandibular aplasia
Definition: "Absence of the mandible." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Asymmetry of the mandible
Definition: "Lack of symmetry between the left and right mandible." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Asymmetry of the mouth
Definition: "The presence of an asymmetric mouth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Duplication of thumb phalanx
Definition: "Complete or partial duplication of the phalanges of the thumb. Depending on the severity, the appearance on x-ray can vary from a notched phalanx (the duplicated bone is almost completely fused with the phalanx), a partially fused appearance of the two bones (bifid), two separate bones appearing side to side, or completely duplicated phalanges (proximal and distal phalanx of the thumb and/or 1st metacarpal). In contrast to the phalanges of the digits 2-5 (proximal, middle and distal), the proximal phalanx of the thumb is embryologically equivalent to the middle phalanges of the other digits, whereas the first metacarpal is embryologically of phalangeal origin and as such equivalent to the proximal phalanges of the other digits." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Complete duplication of thumb phalanx
Definition: "A complete duplication affecting one or more of the phalanges of the thumb. As opposed to a partial duplication were there is still a variable degree of fusion between the duplicated bones, a complete duplication leads to two separate bones appearing side to side (radio-ulnar axis) as seen on x-rays. A duplication leading to an accesory bone appearing in the proximo-distal axis on x-rays, this is actually a different entity called a Pseudoepiphyses (see according terms) sometimes also referred to as Hyperphalangism." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Partial duplication of thumb phalanx
Definition: "A partial duplication, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance, affecting one or more of the phalanges of the thumb. As opposed to a complete duplication there is still a variable degree of fusion between the duplicated bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Definition: "This term applies if one or more of the phalanges of the 2nd finger are either partially duplicated, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance of the phalanges, or completely duplicated." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Definition: "A partial duplication, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance, affecting one or more of the phalanges of the 2nd finger. As opposed to a complete duplication there is still a variable degree of fusion between the duplicated bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Complete duplication of the phalanges of the 2nd finger
Definition: "A complete duplication affecting one or more of the phalanges of the 2nd finger. As opposed to a partial duplication were there is still a variable degree of fusion between the duplicated bones, a complete duplication leads to two separate bones appearing side to side (radio-ulnar axis) as seen on x-rays. Name: Abnormal 1st metacarpal morphology
Definition: "A structural anomaly of the first metacarpal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal 2nd metacarpal morphology
Definition: "Any abnormality of the second metacarpal bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal 3rd metacarpal morphology
Definition: "Any abnormality of the third metacarpal bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal 4th metacarpal morphology
Definition: "Any abnormality of the fourth metacarpal bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal 5th metacarpal morphology
Definition: "Any abnormality of the fifth metacarpal bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal
Definition: "In contrast to the metacarpals 2-5, the first metacarpal is embryologically of phalangeal origin and as such equivalent to the proximal phalanges of the digits 2-5 (whereas the proximal phalanx of the thumb is equivalent to the middle phalanges of the other digits). The epiphysis of the first metacarpal is localized at the proximal end (as seen in the proximal phalanges of the other digits), whereas the epiphyses of the other metacarpal bones are located at the distal end. This term applies if the epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal is in any way abnormal, referring to age and gender depending norms, as seen on x-rays." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bracket epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal
Definition: "An epiphysis that curves around from its transverse orientation to a longitudinal one from proximal to distal along one side of the phalanx, thus resembling the letter 'C' and forming a bracket around the diaphysis. This results in a so called delta phalanx characterized by a triangular or trapezoidal shaped bone with a C-shaped epiphyseal plate." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:24432108]

Name: Cone-shaped epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal
Definition: "A cone-shaped appearance of the epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal, producing a 'ball-in-a-socket' appearance." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Enlarged epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal
Definition: "Abnormally large size of the epiphyses of the 1st metacarpal with respect to age-dependent norms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fragmentation of the epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal
Definition: "Epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal having multiple bony fragments." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Irregular epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal
Definition: "Uneven radiographic opacity of the epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ivory epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal
Definition: "The epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal appears hard and dense like ivory. An ivory epiphysis has a uniformly dense appearance on radiographs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pseudoepiphysis of the 1st metacarpal
Definition: "The epiphysis of the first metacarpal is localized at the proximal end of the metacarpal bone although an accessory epiphysis may be located at the distal end of the metacarpal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Small epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal
Definition: "Abnormally small size of the epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal with respect to age-dependent norms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Epiphyseal stippling of the first metacarpal
Definition: "The presence of abnormal punctate (speckled, dot-like) calcifications in the epiphyses of the first metacarpal bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the 1st metacarpal
Definition: "Aplasia or Hypoplasia affecting the 1st metacarpal. In contrast to the metacarpals 2-5, the first metacarpal is embryologically of phalangeal origin and as such equivalent to the proximal phalanges of the digits 2-5 (whereas the proximal phalanx of the thumb is equivalent to the middle phalanges of the other digits)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Broad 1st metacarpal
Definition: "Increased width of the 1st metacarpal. In contrast to the proximal phalanges of the digits 2-5, the proximal phalanx of the thumb is embryologically equivalent to the middle phalanges of the other digits, whereas the first metacarpal is embryologically of phalangeal origin and as such equivalent to the proximal phalanges of the other digits." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cleft lower lip
Definition: "A gap in the lower lip." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thin lower lip vermilion
Definition: "Height of the vermilion of the medial part of the lower lip more than 2 SD below the mean. Alternatively, an apparently reduced height of the vermilion of the lower lip in the frontal view (subjective)." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Intra-oral hyperpigmentation
Definition: "Increased pigmentation, either focal or generalized, of the mucosa of the mouth." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Oral synechia
Definition: "Fibrous band between the mucosal surfaces of the upper and lower alveolar ridges." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Abnormal salivary gland morphology
Definition: "Any abnormality of the salivary glands, the exocrine glands that produce saliva." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the submandibular glands
Definition: "Any abnormality of the submandibular glands, which are the salivary glands that are located beneath the floor of the mouth, superior to the digastric muscles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the sublingual glands
Definition: "Any abnormality of the sublingual glands, which are the salivary glands that are located beneath the floor of the mouth anterior to the submandibular glands." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cleft maxillary alveolar ridge
Definition: "A gap (cleft) affecting one of the alveolar ridges, which are the protuberances in the mouth that contain the sockets (alveoli) of the teeth. An alveolar cleft can affect all structures of the alveolar ridge, including the gingiva, other mucosa, periosteum, alveolar bone, and teeth. Alveolar cleft occurs in response to divergence from normal development during frontonasal prominence growth, contact, and fusion. The most common alveolar portion of the cleft is located between the lateral incisor and the canine." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:mengelstad, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short hard palate
Definition: "Distance between the labial point of the incisive papilla to the midline junction of the hard and soft palate more than 2 SD below the mean (objective) or apparently decreased length of the hard palate (subjective)." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Prominent palatine ridges
Definition: "Increased size and/or number of soft tissue folds on the palatal side of the maxillary alveolar ridge." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Absent uvula
Definition: "Lack of the uvula." [PMID:19125428]

Definition: "Underdevelopment or absence of the uvula." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Palate fistula
Definition: "A fistula which connects the oral cavity and the pharyngeal area via the aspects of the soft palate." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the tongue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ankyloglossia

Name: Bifid tongue
Definition: "Tongue with a median apical indentation or fork." [PMID:19125428]

Abnormality of the middle phalanx of the 3rd toe
Abnormal morphology of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd toe
Definition: "An anomaly of the proximal phalanx of third toe." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the phalanges of the 4th toe
Bullet-shaped 4th toe phalanx
Definition: "An abnormal morphology of one or more phalanges of the fourth toe, with a short and wide phalanx that tapers distally. Bullet-shaped phalanges lack the normal diaphyseal constriction." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Curved 4th toe phalanx
Definition: "A deviation from the normal straight form of one or more phalanges of the fourth toe." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Osteolytic defects of the phalanges of the 4th toe
Patchy sclerosis of 4th toe phalanx
Definition: "Patchy (irregular) increase in bone density of one or more of the phalanges of the fourth toe. This can take on many forms depending on severity and distribution as can be seen on x-rays." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Symphalangism affecting the phalanges of the 4th toe
Triangular shaped phalanges of the 4th toe
Duplication of phalanx of the 4th toe

Name: Curved 5th toe phalanx
Definition: "A deviation from the normal straight form of one or more phalanges of the fifth toe." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Patchy sclerosis of 5th toe phalanx

Aplasia/hypoplasia of the proximal phalanx of the 2nd toe

Bullet-shaped proximal phalanx of the 2nd toe

Short phalanx of the 2nd toe
Definition: "Reduced length of one or more phalanx of second toe as a result of developmental hypoplasia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Short proximal phalanx of the 2nd toe
Definition: "Reduced length of the proximal phalanx of second toe as a result of developmental hypoplasia." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Abnormal ventricular septum morphology
Definition: "A structural abnormality of the interventricular septum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ectopic accesory toe-like appendage
Definition: "In contrast to forms of polydactyly where the supernumerary digit (this can either be a rudimentary or a completely 'normal' digit) is either located postaxial (on the fibular side of the foot, next top the little toe), preaxial (on the tibial side of the foot, next to the big toe) or mesoaxial (somewhere central, between big and little toe), a supernumerary digit may also be placed ectopically, meaning anywhere else except post-,meso- or preaxial. In the literature this is sometimes referred to as Disorganisation-like Syndrome (OMIM223200)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ectopic accessory finger-like appendage
Definition: "In contrast to forms of polydactyly where the supernumerary digit (this can either be a rudimentary or a completely 'normal' digit) is either located postaxial (on the ulnar side of the hand, next to the little finger), preaxial (on the radial side of the hand, next to the thumb) or mesoaxial (somewhere central, between thumb and little finger), a supernumerary digit may also be placed ectopically, meaning anywhere else except post-,meso- or preaxial. In the literature this is sometimes referred to as Disorganisation-like Syndrome (OMIM223200)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Polydactyly
Definition: "A congenital anomaly characterized by the presence of supernumerary fingers or toes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bifid femur
Definition: "A bifid or bifurcated appearance of the femur as seen on x-rays, possible appearing as a more or less severe bowing of the upper leg. Might be associated with hip dysplasia on the affected side." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pulmonary insufficiency
Definition: "The retrograde (backwards) flow of blood through the pulmonary valve into the right ventricle during diastole." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3302-4610, PMID:32491496]

Name: Primum atrial septal defect
Definition: "An ostium primum atrial septal defect is located in the most anterior and inferior aspect of the atrial septum. The ostium primum refers to an anterior and inferior opening (ostium) within the septum primum, which divides the rudimentary atrium during fetal development. The ostium primum is normally sealed by fusion of the superior and inferior endocardial cushions around 5 weeks' gestation. Ostium primum defects result from a failure of the fusion of the embryologic endocardial cushion and septum primum." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_dbrown, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Tricuspid stenosis
Definition: "A narrowing of the orifice of the tricuspid valve of the heart." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:18222317]

Name: Anal fistula
Definition: "An abnormal connection between the epithelialised surface of the anal canal and the perianal skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Colonic atresia
Definition: "A developmental defect resulting in complete obliteration of the lumen of the colon. That is, there is an abnormal closure, or atresia of the tubular structure of the colon." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Esophageal stenosis
Definition: "An abnormal narrowing of the lumen of the esophagus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the spleen
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the spleen." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ectopia of the spleen
Definition: "An abnormal (non-anatomic) location of the spleen." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pelvic bone asymmetry
Definition: "Pelvic asymmetry refers to asymmetric positioning of landmarks on the two sides of the pelvis and may have a structural or functional etiology." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Acetabular spurs
Definition: "The presence of osteophytes (bone spurs), i.e., of bony projections originating from the acetabulum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Steep acetabular roof
Definition: "An exaggeration of the normal arched form of the acetabular roof such that it takes on a steep appearance." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal greater sciatic notch morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the sacrosciatic notch, i.e., the deep indentation in the posterior border of the hip bone at the point of union of the ilium and ischium." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: obsolete Widening of the sacrosciatic notch
Female pseudohermaphroditism
Definition: "Hermaphroditism refers to a discrepancy between the morphology of the gonads and that of the external genitalia. In female pseudohermaphroditism, the genotype is female (XX) and the gonads are ovaries, but the external genitalia are virilized." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: True hermaphroditism
