Definition: "The presence of both ovarian and testicular tissues either in the same or in opposite gonads. Affected persons have ambiguous genitalia and may have 46,XX or 46,XY karyotypes or 46,XX/XY mosaicism." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:11327376]

Name: Abnormality of the female genitalia
Definition: "Abnormality of the female genital system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the male genitalia
Definition: "Abnormality of the male genital system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the ovary
Definition: "Aplasia or developmental hypoplasia of the ovary." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia of the ovary
Definition: "Aplasia, that is failure to develop, of the ovary." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Streak ovary
Definition: "A developmental disorder characterized by the progressive loss of primordial germ cells in the developing ovaries of an embryo, leading to hypoplastic ovaries composed of wavy connective tissue with occasional clumps of granulosa cells, and frequently mesonephric or hilar cells." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Precocious puberty in females
Definition: "The onset of puberty before the age of 8 years in girls." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the testes
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the testes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent testis
Definition: "Testis not palpable in the scrotum or inguinal canal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:23650202]

Name: Supernumerary testes
Definition: "The presence of more than two testes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Oligosacchariduria
Definition: "Increased urinary excretion of oligosaccharides (low molecular weight carbohydrate chains composed of at least three monosaccharide subunits), derived from a partial degradation of glycoproteins." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating porphyrin concentration
Definition: "An abnormality in the synthesis or catabolism of heme. Heme is composed of ferrous iron and protoporphyrin IX and is an essential molecule as the prosthetic group of hemeproteins such as hemoglobin, myoglobin, mitochondrial and microsomal cytochromes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Porphyrinuria
Definition: "Abnormally increased excretion of porphyrins in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bladder stones
Definition: "Buildups of minerals that form in the urinary bladder." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cloacal exstrophy
Definition: "Cloacal exstrophy is a severe anterior abdominal wall defect in which the two hemibladders are visible and are separated by a midline intestinal plate, an omphalocele, and an imperforate anus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the bladder
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the urinary bladder." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia of the bladder
Definition: "Aplasia (absence) of the urinary bladder." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the urachus
Definition: "Abnormality of the urachus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Patent urachus
Definition: "Persistence of the urachal canal resulting in a canal between the bladder and the umbilicus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Urethral fistula
Definition: "The presence of an abnormal connection between the urethra and another organ or the skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Urethral valve
Definition: "The presence of an abnormal membrane obstructing the urethra." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Acromelia of the upper limbs
Definition: "Shortening of the arms predominantly affecting terminal parts of the arm in relation to the upper and middle limb segments." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Amniotic constriction rings of arms
Definition: "Amniotic constriction rings affecting the arms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypertrophy of the upper limb
Definition: "Abnormal increase in size of the upper limbs (due to an increase of the size of cells)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperextensibility at elbow
Definition: "The ability of the elbow joint to move beyond its normal range of motion." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the hypothenar eminence
Definition: "An abnormality of the hypothenar eminence, i.e., of the muscles on the ulnar side of the palm of the hand (i.e., on the side of the little finger)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Small hypothenar eminence
Definition: "Reduced muscle mass on the ulnar side of the palm, that is, reduction in size of the hypothenar eminence." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125433]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the palmar creases
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the palmar creases." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent palmar crease
Definition: "The absence of the major creases of the palm (distal transverse crease, proximal transverse crease, or thenar crease)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125433]

Name: Abnormality of the palmar creases
Definition: "An abnormality of the creases of the skin of palm of hand." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Digital constriction ring
Definition: "A narrow segment of significantly reduced circumference of a digit." [PMID:19125433]

Name: Osseous finger syndactyly
Definition: "Webbing or fusion of the fingers, involving soft parts and including fusion of individual finger bones. Bony fusions are referred to as \"bony\" Syndactyly if the fusion occurs in a radio-ulnar axis. Fusions of bones of the fingers in a proximo-distal axis are referred to as \"Symphalangism\"." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Long metacarpals
Definition: "An abnormally increased length of the metacarpal bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Acromelia of the lower limbs
Definition: "Shortening of the legs predominantly affecting terminal parts of the leg in relation to the upper and middle arm segments." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Amniotic constriction rings of legs
Definition: "Amniotic constriction rings affecting the legs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypertrophy of the lower limb
Definition: "Abnormal increase in size of the lower limbs (due to an increase of the size of cells)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sirenomelia
Definition: "A developmental defect in which the legs are fused together." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bipartite patella
Definition: "A developmental defect that occurs if the two halves of the patella fail to fuse in early childhood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Patellar subluxation
Definition: "The kneecap normally is located within the groove termed trochlea on the distal femur and can slide up and down in it. Patellar subluxation refers to an unstable kneecap that does not slide centrally within its groove, i.e., a partial dislocation of the patella." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperextensibility of the knee
Definition: "The ability of the knee joint to extend beyond its normal range of motion (the lower leg is moved beyond a straight position with respect to the thigh)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Limitation of knee mobility
Definition: "An abnormal limitation of knee joint mobility." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fibular bowing
Definition: "A bending or abnormal curvature of the fibula." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fibular duplication
Definition: "Duplication of the fibula. This may occur as a part of diplopodia (accessory tarsal or metatarsal bone). Diplopodia with double fibula is an extremely rare condition." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased length of the tibia
Definition: "An abnormal increase in the length of the tibia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Limitation of movement at ankles
Definition: "An abnormal limitation of the mobility of the ankle joint." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal plantar dermatoglyphics
Definition: "An abnormality of dermatoglyphs on the toes and soles, i.e., an abnormality of the patterns of ridges of the skin of sole of foot." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Foot asymmetry
Definition: "A difference in size or shape between the left and right foot." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Metatarsus valgus
Definition: "A condition in which the anterior part of the foot rotates outward away from the midline of the body and the heel remains straight." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia of the tarsal bones
Definition: "Absence of the tarsal bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypermobility of toe joints
Definition: "An ability of the toe joints to move beyond their normal range of motion." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Long toe
Definition: "Toes that appear disproportionately long compared to the foot." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125433]

Name: Adrenal calcification
Definition: "Calcification within the adrenal glands." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pituitary calcification
Definition: "Deposition of calcium salts in the pituitary gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperpituitarism
Definition: "Hypersecretion of one or more pituitary hormones. This can occur in conditions in which deficiency in the target organ leads to decreased hormonal feedback, or as a primary condition most usually in connection with a pituitary adenoma." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the thymus
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the thymus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thymus hyperplasia
Definition: "Enlargement of the thymus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ectopic thymus tissue
Definition: "The presence of ectopic thymus tissue. Normally, cells of the ventral bud of the third pharyngeal pouch detach and migrate in the eighth gestational week caudally and medially towards the location of the mature thyroid. They migrate further retrosternally into the superior mediastinum. There are two main ways ectopic thymus tissue can develop. Either cells detach along the descensus path and proliferate, thereby forming accessory thymus tissue, or the entire gland fails to descend." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thyroglossal cyst
Definition: "An abnormality of the thyroid gland owing to the presence of a fibrous cyst resulting from the persistence of the thyroglossal duct." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased fetal movement
Definition: "An abnormal increase in quantity or strength of fetal movements." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Gait apraxia
Definition: "Gait apraxia affecting the ability to make walking movements with the legs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Dyslexia
Definition: "A learning disorder characterized primarily by difficulties in learning to read and spell. Dyslectic children also exhibit a tendency to read words from right to left and to confuse letters such as b and d whose orientation is important for their identification. Children with dyslexia appear to be impaired in phonemic skills (the ability to associate visual symbols with the sounds they represent)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Alexia
Definition: "An acquired type of sensory aphasia where damage to the brain leads to the loss of the ability to read." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Agnosia
Definition: "Inability to recognize objects not because of sensory deficit but because of the inability to combine components of sensory impressions into a complete pattern. Thus, agnosia is a neurological condition which results in an inability to know, to name, to identify, and to extract meaning from visual, auditory, or tactile impressions." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Finger agnosia
Definition: "An inability or difficulty differentiating among the fingers of either hand as well as the hands of others." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Dysgraphia
Definition: "A writing disability in the absence of motor or sensory deficits of the upper extremities, resulting in an impairment in the ability to write regardless of the ability to read and not due to intellectual impairment." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Astereognosia
Definition: "Inability to recognize the form of objects by touch without visual input. That is, an impairment in the recognition of objects based only on the texture, size, weight and three-dimensional form of the object in the absence of any major somatosensory deficit." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Prosopagnosia
Definition: "Inability to recognize faces of familiar persons." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Echolalia
Definition: "The repetition of words or phrases that are odd or used in a nonsocial manner. These can be words or phrases the person has heard or invented." []

Name: Palatal tremor
Definition: "Palatal tremor (PT) is an involuntary, rhythmic and oscillatory movement of the soft palate. PT is a rare type of tremor involving the soft palate. It can be unilateral or bilateral." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:33101766]

Name: Spinal myoclonus
Definition: "Spinal myoclonus is generally due to a tumor, infection, injury, or degenerative process of the spinal cord, and is characterized by involuntary rhythmic muscle contractions, usually at a rate of more than one per second. Myoclonus occurs synchronously in several muscles and can be increased in severity and frequency by fatigue or stress, but is usually unaffected by sensory stimuli. Spinal myoclonus ceases during sleep or anesthesia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Paroxysmal vertigo
Definition: "Paroxysmal episodes of vertigo." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Spasmus nutans
Definition: "The combination of pendular nystagmus, head nodding, and torticollis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:7499100]

Name: Transient global amnesia
Definition: "A paroxysmal, transient loss of memory function with preservation of immediate recall and remote memory but with a severe impairment of memory for recent events and ability to retain new information." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sleep apnea
Definition: "An intermittent cessation of airflow at the mouth and nose during sleep. Apneas of at least 10 seconds are considered important, but persons with sleep apnea may have apneas of 20 seconds to up to 2 or 3 minutes. Patients may have up to 15 events per hour of sleep." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Central sleep apnea
Definition: "Sleep apnea resulting from a transient abolition of the central drive to the ventilatory muscles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Wide cranial sutures
Definition: "An abnormally increased width of the cranial sutures for age-related norms (generally resulting from delayed closure)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Small sella turcica
Definition: "An abnormally small sella turcica." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thin calvarium
Definition: "The presence of an abnormally thin calvarium." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Advanced pneumatization of cranial sinuses
Definition: "A degree of pneumatization that is increased compared to age-related norms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cutis gyrata of scalp
Definition: "The presence of convoluted folds and furrows formed from thickened skin of the scalp, resembling cerebriform pattern. The scalp has convoluted and elevated folds, 1 to 2 cm in thickness. The convolutions generally cannot be flattened by traction." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Vestibular nystagmus
Definition: "Nystagmus due to disturbance of the vestibular system; eye movements are rhythmic, with slow and fast components." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Opsoclonus
Definition: "Bursts of large-amplitude multidirectional saccades without intersaccadic interval" [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0986-4123]

Name: Vertical nystagmus
Definition: "Vertical nystagmus may present with either up-beating or down-beating eye movements or both. When present in the straight-ahead position of gaze it is referred to as upbeat nystagmus or downbeat nystagmus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Downbeat nystagmus
Definition: "Downbeat nystagmus is a type of fixation nystagmus with the fast phase beating in a downward direction. It generally increases when looking to the side and down and when lying prone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:21505601]

Name: Muscle fibrillation
Definition: "Fine, rapid twitching of individual muscle fibers with little or no movement of the muscle as a whole. If a motor neuron or its axon is destroyed, the muscle fibers it innervates undergo denervation atrophy. This leads to hypersensitivity of individual muscle fibers to acetyl choline so that they may contract spontaneously. Isolated activity of individual muscle fibers is generally so fine it cannot be seen through the intact skin, although it can be recorded as a short-duration spike in the EMG." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Muscle flaccidity
Definition: "A type of paralysis in which a muscle becomes soft and yields to passive stretching, which results from loss of all or practically all peripheral motor nerves that innervated the muscle. Muscle tone is reduced and the affected muscles undergo extreme atrophy within months of the loss of innervation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Percussion myotonia
Definition: "A localized myotonic contraction in a muscle in reaction to percussion (tapping with the examiner's finger, a rubber percussion hammer, or a similar object)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Weakness due to upper motor neuron dysfunction
Definition: "Paralysis of voluntary muscles means loss of contraction due to interruption of one or more motor pathways from the brain to the muscle fibers. Although the word paralysis is often used interchangeably to mean either complete or partial loss of muscle strength, it is preferable to use paralysis or plegia for complete or severe loss of muscle strength, and paresis for partial or slight loss. Paralysis due to lesions of the principle motor tracts is related to a lesion in the corticospinal, corticobulbar or brainstem descending (subcorticospinal) neurons." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Paraplegia
Definition: "Severe or complete weakness of both lower extremities with sparing of the upper extremities." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Paraplegia/paraparesis
Definition: "Weakness of both lower extremities with sparing of the upper extremities. Paraplegia refers to a severe or complete loss of strength, whereas paraparesis refers to a relatively mild loss of strength." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Oculogyric crisis
Definition: "An acute dystonic reaction with blepharospasm, periorbital twitches, and protracted fixed staring episodes. There may be a maximal upward deviation of the eyes in the sustained fashion. Oculogyric crisis can be triggered by a number of factors including neuroleptic medications." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cutaneous finger syndactyly
Definition: "A soft tissue continuity in the A/P axis between two fingers that extends distally to at least the level of the proximal interphalangeal joints, or a soft tissue continuity in the A/P axis between two fingers that lies significantly distal to the flexion crease that overlies the metacarpophalangeal joint of the adjacent fingers." [PMID:19125433]

Name: Overlapping fingers
Definition: "A finger resting on the dorsal surface of an adjacent digit when the hand is at rest." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125433]

Name: Abnormality of the clivus
Definition: "An abnormality of the clivus, which is the inclined bony region of the posterior cranial fossa located between the sella turcica and the foramen magnum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Vertical clivus
Definition: "An abnormal vertical orientation of the clivus (which normally forms a kind of slope from the sella turcica down to the region of the foramen magnum)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Undulate clavicles
Definition: "An abnormally wavy surface or edge of the clavicles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Undulate ribs
Definition: "An abnormally wavy surface or edge of the ribs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bifid epiglottis
Definition: "A midline anterior-posterior cleft of the epiglottis that involves at least two-thirds of the epiglottic leaf. It is a useful feature for clinical diagnosis because it appears to be very rare in syndromes other than Pallister-Hall-Syndrome and is also rare as an isolated malformation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the Epiglottis
Definition: "This term applies if the Epiglottis is absent or hypoplastic." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hamartoma
Definition: "A disordered proliferation of mature tissues that is native to the site of origin, e.g., exostoses, nevi and soft tissue hamartomas. Although most hamartomas are benign, some histologic subtypes, e.g., neuromuscular hamartoma, may proliferate aggressively such as mesenchymal cystic hamartoma, Sclerosing epithelial hamartoma, Sclerosing metanephric hamartoma." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Y-shaped metatarsals
Definition: "Y-shaped metatarsals are the result of a partial fusion of two metatarsal bones, with the two arms of the Y pointing in the distal direction. Y-shaped metatarsals may be seen in combination with polydactyly." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hamartoma of the eye
Definition: "A hamartoma (disordered proliferation of mature tissues) which can originate from any tissue of the eye." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated circulating 7-dehydrocholesterol concentration
Definition: "Concentration of 7-dehydrocholesterol in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Low maternal circulating alpha-fetoprotein concentration
Definition: "An abnormally low concentration of serum alpha-fetoprotein as compared to normal values for gestational-age." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated circulating phytanic acid concentration
Definition: "An abnormal elevation of phytanic acid." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the epiphysis of the femoral head
Definition: "Any abnormality of the proximal epiphysis of the femur." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Dysplasia of the femoral head
Definition: "The presence of developmental dysplasia of the femoral head." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Intracranial cystic lesion
Definition: "A cystic lesion originating within the brain." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cone-shaped epiphysis
Definition: "Cone-shaped epiphyses (also known as coned epiphyses) are epiphyses that invaginate into cupped metaphyses. That is, the epiphysis has a cone-shaped distal extension resulting from increased growth of the central portion of the epiphysis relative to its periphery." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Enlarged epiphyses
Definition: "Increased size of epiphyses." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Irregular epiphyses
Definition: "An alteration of the normally smooth contour of the epiphysis leading to an irregular appearance." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ivory epiphyses
Definition: "Sclerosis of the epiphyses, leading to an increased degree of radiopacity (white or ivory appearance) in X-rays." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Small epiphyses
Definition: "Reduction in the size or volume of epiphyses." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Premature epimetaphyseal fusion
Definition: "Stop of growth at the epiphyseal plate the hyaline cartilage plate in the metaphysis at each end of a long bone, at an earlier than normal age, resulting in growth arrest and shortening of the involved bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:12624140]

Name: Abnormality of the distal femoral epiphysis
Definition: "Any abnormality of the distal epiphysis of the femur." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the proximal tibial epiphysis
Definition: "Any abnormality of the proximal epiphysis of the tibia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the distal tibial epiphysis
Abnormality of the proximal fibular epiphysis
Definition: "Any abnormality of the proximal epiphysis of the fibula." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the distal fibular epiphysis
Definition: "Any abnormality of the distal epiphysis of the fibula." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the proximal radial epiphysis
Definition: "Any abnormality of the proximal epiphysis of the radius." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the distal radial epiphysis
Definition: "Any abnormality of the distal epiphysis of the radius." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the proximal humeral epiphysis
Definition: "Any abnormality of the proximal epiphysis of the humerus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the distal humeral epiphysis
Definition: "Any abnormality of the distal epiphysis of the humerus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal distal ulnar epiphysis morphology
Definition: "Any abnormality of the distal epiphysis of the ulna." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal proximal ulnar epiphysis morphology
Definition: "Any abnormality of the proximal epiphysis of the ulna." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Type 2 muscle fiber predominance
Definition: "An abnormal predominance of type II muscle fibers (in general, this feature can only be observed on muscle biopsy)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Odontogenic keratocysts of the jaw
Definition: "A benign uni- or multicystic, intraosseous tumor of odontogenic origin, with a characteristic lining of parakeratinized stratified squamous epithelium and potential for aggressive, infiltrative behaviour." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:18353202]

Name: Chalazion
Definition: "A chronic epithelioid cell granulomatous inflammation of the meibomian gland caused by inflammation of a blocked meibomian gland. A chalazion or meibomian cyst appears as a painless tuberous swelling in the upper lid without loss of eyelashes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hordeolum
Definition: "An acute purulent infection of the sebaceous glands of Zeis at the base of the eyelashes, of the apocrine sweat glands of Moll or the meibomian sebacious glands often caused by staphylococcus infections. Hordeola can either occur as Hordeola externa affecting the sebaceous glands of Zeis or the apocrine sweat glands of Moll or as Hordeola interna affecting the meibomian sebacious glands. In contrast to chalazia, hordeola are extremely painful and can cause extreme local swelling." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Hordeolum externum
Definition: "Hordeola externa are acute purulent infections affecting the sebaceous glands of Zeis or the apocrine sweat glands of Moll, often caused by staphylococcus infections. In contrast to chalazia, hordeola are extremely painfull and can cause extreme local swelling." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hordeolum internum
Definition: "Hordeola interna are acute purulent infections affecting the meibomian sebacious glands, often caused by staphylococcus infections. In contrast to chalazia (chronic epithelioid cell granulomatous inflammation of the meibomian gland caused by inflammation of a blocked meibomian gland), hordeola are extremely painfull and can cause extreme local swelling." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Skin tags
Definition: "Cutaneous skin tags also known as acrochorda or fibroepithelial polyps are small benign tumors that may either form secondarily over time primarily in areas where the skin forms creases, such as the neck, armpit or groin or may also be present at birth, in which case they usually occur in the periauricular region." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Plantar pits
Definition: "The presence of multiple pits (small, pinpoint-large indentations on the surface of the skin) located on the skin of sole of foot." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fibroma
Definition: "Benign tumors that are composed of fibrous or connective tissue. They can grow in all organs, arising from mesenchyme tissue. The term \"fibroblastic\" or \"fibromatous\" is used to describe tumors of the fibrous connective tissue. When the term fibroma is used without modifier, it is usually considered benign, with the term fibrosarcoma reserved for malignant tumors." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Angiofibromas
Definition: "Angiofibroma consist of many often dilated vessels." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lung fibroma
Definition: "The presence of a lung fibroma, a benign neoplasm that can present as a mass causing airway obstruction, cough, and hemoptysis, or present without symptoms as a solitary pulmonary nodule." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cardiac fibroma
Definition: "A fibroma of the heart." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ovarian fibroma
Definition: "The presence of a fibroma of the ovary." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fibroadenoma of the breast
Definition: "A benign biphasic tumor of the breast with epithelial and stromal components." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:23396888]

Name: Malar prominence
Definition: "Prominence of the malar process of the maxilla and infraorbital area appreciated in profile and from in front of the face." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9602-2321]

Name: Cutaneous syndactyly of toes
Definition: "A soft tissue continuity in the anteroposterior axis between adjacent foot digits that involves at least half of the proximodistal length of one of the two involved digits; or, a soft tissue continuity in the A/P axis between two digits of the foot that does not meet the prior objective criteria." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125433]

Name: Neoplasm of the skeletal system
Definition: "A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the skeleton." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplastic/hypoplastic toenail
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the toenail." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anterior pituitary dysgenesis
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the anterior pituitary gland, also known as the adenohypophysis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anterior pituitary agenesis
Definition: "Absence of the anterior pituitary gland resulting from a developmental defect." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5316-1399]

Name: Anterior pituitary hypoplasia
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the anterior pituitary gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Facial palsy
Definition: "Facial nerve palsy is a dysfunction of cranial nerve VII (the facial nerve) that results in inability to control facial muscles on the affected side with weakness of the muscles of facial expression and eye closure. This can either be present in unilateral or bilateral form." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Abnormal morphology of the cortex of the humerus
Definition: "Any abnormality affecting the cortex of the humerus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal metatarsal epiphysis morphology
Definition: "Any abnormality of a metatarsal bone epiphysis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the epiphyses of the feet
Definition: "Any abnormality of the epiphyses of the feet." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Total anosmia
Definition: "Inability to detect any qualitative olfactory sensation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Partial anosmia
Definition: "Inability to perceive certain odorants (implies that the sense of smell is maintained for other classes of odorants)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Total hyposmia
Definition: "Reduced ability to detect any qualitative olfactory sensation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Partial hyposmia
Definition: "Reduced ability to perceive certain odorants (implies that the sense of smell is maintained for other classes of odorants)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Schizencephaly
Definition: "The presence of a cleft in the cerebral cortex unilaterally or bilaterally, usually located in the frontal area." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Conjunctival amyloidosis
Definition: "A form of amyloidosis that affects the conjunctiva." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated alkaline phosphatase of hepatic origin
Definition: "An abnormally increased level of liver isoforms of alkaline phosphatase, tissue-nonspecific isozyme in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated alkaline phosphatase of bone origin
Definition: "An abnormally increased level of bone isoforms of alkaline phosphatase, tissue-nonspecific isozyme in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the nasal cavity
Definition: "Abnormality of the nasal cavity (the cavity includes and starts at the nares and reaches all the way through to the and includes the choanae, the posterior nasal apertures)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the midnasal cavity
Definition: "Abnormality of the midnasal cavity which includes the cavity between the nares and the choanae." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Midnasal atresia
Definition: "Absence or abnormal closure of the midnasal cavity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Midnasal stenosis
Definition: "Abnormal narrowing (stenosis) of the midnasal cavity, i.e., of the middle nasal meatus, which in neonates can cause respiratory distress." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia of the distal phalanges of the toes
Definition: "Absence of the distal phalanges of the toes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cervical spine instability
Definition: "An abnormal lack of stability of the cervical spine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal elasticity of skin
Definition: "Any abnormal increase or reduction in skin elasticity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1773-4011]

Name: Dermal translucency
Definition: "An abnormally increased ability of the skin to permit light to pass through (translucency) such that subcutaneous structures such as veins display an increased degree of visibility." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Flat nasal alae
Definition: "An abnormal degree of flatness of the Ala of nose, which can be defined as a reduced nasal elevation index (lateral depth of the nose from the tip of the nose to the insertion of the nasal ala in the cheek x 100 divided by the side-to-side breadth of the nasal alae)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplasia of the premaxilla
Definition: "An abnormality of the premaxilla (the embryonic structure that forms the anterior part of the maxilla) causing it to appear relatively small in size compared to the other parts of the maxilla or other facial structures." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5889-4463, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125436]

Name: Abnormal meningeal morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the Meninges, including any abnormality of the Dura mater, the Arachnoid mater, and the Pia mater." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal dura mater morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the Dura mater." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the falx cerebri
Definition: "An abnormality of the Falx cerebri." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia of the falx cerebri
Definition: "A developmental defect characterized by aplasia of the Falx cerebri." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Epiphyseal stippling
Definition: "The presence of abnormal punctate (speckled, dot-like) calcifications in one or more epiphyses." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal epiphyseal ossification
Definition: "An abnormality of the formation and mineralization of an epiphysis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Patchy reduction of bone mineral density
Definition: "Patchy (irregular) reduction in bone density. This can take on many forms depending on severity and distribution as can be seen on x-rays." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Patchy changes of bone mineral density
Definition: "Patchy (irregular) changes in bone mineral density. These changes can either be patchy reduction or increase of mineral density as seen on x-rays. Depending on the pathomechanism and the underlying disease, these changes can either appear solely as reduction or increase or as a combination of both (patches of bone showing an increased density while others are affected by reduction of mineral density)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Patchy variation in bone mineral density
Definition: "Patchy (irregular) changes in bone mineral density with patches of bone showing an increased density side to side with patches that are affected by reduction of mineral density. This is sometimes referred to as a moth-eaten appearance on x-rays." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal hand bone ossification
Definition: "An abnormality of the formation and mineralization of any bone of the skeleton of hand." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absence of the third cerebral ventricle
Definition: "A developmental defect characterized by the absence of the third ventricle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the diencephalon
Definition: "An abnormality of the Diencephalon, which together with the cerebrum (telencephalon) makes up the forebrain." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of thalamus morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the thalamus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fusion of the left and right thalami
Definition: "A developmental defect characterized by fusion of the left and right halves of the thalamus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bilateral coxa valga
Definition: "The presence of bilateral coxa valga." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplasia of the anterior nasal spine
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the anterior nasal spine of maxilla." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia of the maxilla
Definition: "A congenital defect characterized by absence of the Maxilla." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal zygomatic bone morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the zygomatic bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplasia of the zygomatic bone
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the zygomatic bone. That is, a reduction in size of the zygomatic bone, including the zygomatic process of the temporal bone of the skull, which forms part of the zygomatic arch." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5889-4463, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125436]

Name: Abnormality of the third metatarsal bone
Definition: "An abnormality of the third metatarsal bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal curvature of the vertebral column
Definition: "The presence of an abnormal curvature of the vertebral column." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal foot bone ossification
Definition: "An abnormality of the formation and mineralization of any bone of the skeleton of foot." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Enuresis nocturna
Definition: "Enuresis occurring during sleeping hours." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Enuresis diurna
Definition: "Enuresis occurring during waking hours of the day." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Elevated tissue non-specific alkaline phosphatase
Definition: "An abnormally increased level of alkaline phosphatase, tissue-nonspecific isozyme in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated alkaline phosphatase of renal origin
Definition: "An abnormally increased level of kidney isoforms of alkaline phosphatase, tissue-nonspecific isozyme in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated intestinal alkaline phosphatase
Definition: "An abnormally increased level of alkaline phosphatase, intestinal type in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated placental alkaline phosphatase
Definition: "An abnormally increased level of alkaline phosphatase, placental type in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Low tissue non-specific alkaline phosphatase
Definition: "An abnormally reduced level of alkaline phosphatase, tissue-nonspecific isozyme in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Low alkaline phosphatase of bone origin
Definition: "An abnormally reduced level of bone isoforms of alkaline phosphatase in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Low alkaline phosphatase of renal origin
Definition: "An abnormally reduced level of kidney isoforms of alkaline phosphatase in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Low alkaline phosphatase of hepatic origin
Definition: "An abnormally reduced level of liver isoforms of alkaline phosphatase in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Low intestinal alkaline phosphatase
Definition: "An abnormally reduced level of alkaline phosphatase, intestinal type in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Low placental alkaline phosphatase
Definition: "An abnormally reduced level of alkaline phosphatase, placental type in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Mirror image polydactyly
Definition: "A hand or foot with more than five digits that has a recognizable A/P axis of symmetry. The axis can lie within a normally formed or partially duplicated digit resembling a middle finger, index finger, thumb, toe, or hallux. Alternatively, the axis can be in an interdigital space with a flanking pair of digits that resemble a middle finger, index finger, thumb, toe or hallux. The most lateral digits on each side of the hand/foot typically resemble fifth fingers/toes." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154, PMID:19125433]

Name: Mirror image hand polydactyly
Definition: "Mirror image duplication of digits affecting the hands only." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Mirror image foot polydactyly
Definition: "Mirror image duplication of digits affecting the feet." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: 2-5 finger syndactyly
Definition: "Syndactyly with fusion of fingers two to five." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Pulverulent cataract
Definition: "A kind of congenital cataract that is characterized by a hollow sphere of punctate opacities involving the fetal nucleus and that usually occurs bilaterally." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:vkumar, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lamellar pulverulent cataract
Definition: "A Lamellar cataract with a pulverulent (punctate, \"dust-like\" opacities) appearance." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sutural cataract
Definition: "A type of congenital cataract in which the opacity follows the anterior or posterior Y suture." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Polar cataract
Definition: "A type of Congenital cataract in which the opacities occupy the subcapsular cortex at the anterior or posterior pole of the lens." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anterior pyramidal cataract
Definition: "A type of anterior polar cataract which projects as a conical opacity into the anterior chamber." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Nuclear pulverulent cataract
Definition: "A type of nuclear cataract involving congenital dust-like (pulverulent) opacity of the embryonal and fetal nucleus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:10634616, PMID:14059288]

Name: Triangular nuclear cataract
Definition: "A nuclear cataract with a triangular form." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:18483562]

Name: Abnormal immunoglobulin level
Definition: "An abnormal deviation from normal levels of immunoglobulins in blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased circulating antibody level
Definition: "An increased level of gamma globulin (immunoglobulin) in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: 1-2 finger syndactyly
Definition: "Syndactyly with fusion of fingers one and two." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: 4-5 finger syndactyly
Definition: "Syndactyly with fusion of fingers four and five." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: 1-3 finger syndactyly
Definition: "Syndactyly with fusion of fingers one to three." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: 1-4 finger syndactyly
Definition: "Syndactyly with fusion of fingers one to four." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: 1-5 finger syndactyly
Definition: "Syndactyly with fusion of fingers one to five (complete syndactyly of all fingers of the hand)." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: 2-4 finger syndactyly
Definition: "Syndactyly with fusion of the fingers two to four." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: 3-5 finger syndactyly
Definition: "Syndactyly with fusion of fingers three to five." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: 1-2 toe syndactyly
Definition: "Syndactyly with fusion of toes one and two." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: 1-4 toe syndactyly
Definition: "Syndactyly with fusion of toes one to four." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: 1-5 toe syndactyly
Definition: "Syndactyly with fusion of toes one to five (complete syndactyly of all toes of the foot)." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: 2-4 toe syndactyly
Definition: "Syndactyly with fusion of toes two to four." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: 2-5 toe syndactyly
Definition: "Syndactyly with fusion of toes two to five." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: 3-5 toe syndactyly
Definition: "Syndactyly with fusion of toes three to five." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Osseous syndactyly of toes
Definition: "Webbing or fusion of the toes, involving soft parts and including fusion of individual bones of the toes. Bony fusions are referred to as \"bony\" Syndactyly if the fusion occurs in a tibial-fibular axis. Fusions of bones of the toes in a proximo-distal axis are referred to as \"Symphalangism\"." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Abnormality of hair texture
Definition: "An abnormality of the texture of the hair." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal hair pattern
Definition: "An abnormality of the distribution of hair growth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal hair whorl
Definition: "An abnormal hair whorl (that is, a patch of hair growing in the opposite direction of the rest of the hair)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Asymmetry of the ears
Definition: "An asymmetriy, i.e., difference in size, shape or position between the left and right ear." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Advanced pneumatization of the mastoid process
Definition: "An abnormally advanced degree of pneumatization (i.e., formation of air cells) in the mastoid process with respect to age-dependent norms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Prominent corneal nerve fibers
Definition: "Abnormal prominence of the corneal nerve fibers." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_ncarter, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Spontaneous rupture of the globe
Definition: "Rupture of the eyeball not due to trauma." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia of the retina
Definition: "A developmental defect characterized by absence of the retina." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cherry red spot of the macula
Definition: "Pallor of the perifoveal macula of the retina with appearance of a small circular reddish choroid shape as seen through the fovea centralis due to relative transparancy of the macula." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Double eyebrow
Definition: "This may present as a partial or complete duplication of the eyebrows." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Extension of eyebrows towards upper eyelid
Definition: "The eyebrows extend towards - or even all the way down to - the margin of the upper eyelid." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Nodular changes affecting the eyelids
Definition: "Nodular changes affecting the eyelids may have many different causes such as cystic lesions (chalaziae, hordeolae), lipogranulomas, melanomas, infectious diseases (Molluscum contagiosum) and many more." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Naevus flammeus of the eyelid
Definition: "Naevus flammeus localised in the skin of the eyelid." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Fibrous dysplasia of the bones
Definition: "Tumor-like growths that consist of replacement of the medullary bone with fibrous tissue, causing the expansion and weakening of the areas of bone involved. Especially when involving the skull or facial bones, the lesions can cause externally visible deformities. The skull is often, but not necessarily, affected, and any other bone or bones may be involved. Fibrous dysplasia can either effect isolated bones (Monostotic fibrous dysplasia) or also generalized all bones of the body (Polyostotic fibrous dysplasia)." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Polyostotic fibrous dysplasia
Definition: "Fibrous dysplasia of the bones were lesions are localized in many bones throughout of the body. Polyostotic fibrous dysplasia is a cardinal feature of McCune-Albright syndrome." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Monostotic fibrous dysplasia
Definition: "Fibrous dysplasia of the bones were lesions are localized in only one bone." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Osteopoikilosis
Definition: "Osteopoikilosis is a benign, asymptomatic sclerotic dysplasia of the bones. It affects both male and female and may be seen at any age. Radiographically sclerotic circular or ovoid lesions are usually symmetrically distributed in a periarticular location. Lesions can increase or decrease in size and number in serial radiographs or even disappear and do not have increased bone radiotracer uptake." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Osteopathia striata
Definition: "A lamellar pattern visible on radiographs and mainly localized at the metaphyses of the long tubular bones. Pathologic-anatomical studies revealed that these benign signs on x-rays are the result of a juvenile metaphyseal bone necrosis. Calcifications in the necrotic marrow lead to this lamellar or lattice-like appearance." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Pedal edema
Definition: "An abnormal accumulation of excess fluid in the lower extremity resulting in swelling of the feet and extending upward to the lower leg." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Edema of the upper limbs
Definition: "An abnormal accumulation of fluid beneath the skin of the arms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short metatarsal
Definition: "Diminished length of a metatarsal bone, with resultant proximal displacement of the associated toe." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125433]

Name: Absent metatarsal bone
Definition: "A developmental abnormality characterized by the absence (aplasia) of a metatarsal bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia of the phalanges of the toes
Definition: "Absence of a digit or of one or more phalanges of a toe." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplasia of the phalanges of the toes
Medial flaring of the eyebrow
Definition: "An abnormal distribution of eyebrow hair growth in the medial direction." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ectopic lacrimal punctum
Definition: "Positioning of a lacrimal punctum other than at the medial margins of the eyelid." [PMID:19125427]

Name: Blepharochalasis
Definition: "Blepharochalasis is characterized by recurrent, non-painful, nonerythematous episodes of eyelid edema. It has been divided into hypertrophic and atrophic forms. In the hypertrophic form recurrent edema results in orbital fat herniation through a weakened orbital septum. Most patients who have blepharochalasis present in an atrophic condition with atrophy of redundant eyelid skin and superior nasal fat pads." [PMID:3207663]

Name: Dermatochalasis
Definition: "Loss of elasticity of the upper and lower eyelids causing the skin to sag and bulge." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Dimple chin
Definition: "A persistent midline depression of the skin over the fat pad of the chin." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Cleft mandible
Definition: "Midline deficiency of the mandible and some or all overlying tissues." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Abnormality of the temporomandibular joint
Definition: "An anomaly of the temporomandibular joint." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Asymmetry of the maxilla
Definition: "Asymmetry between the left and right sides of the maxilla." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5889-4463]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the premaxilla
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the premaxilla." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia of the premaxilla
Definition: "Absence of the premaxilla, which is the embryonic structure that forms the anterior part of the maxilla." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the premaxilla
Definition: "An abnormality of the premaxilla, the most anterior part of the maxilla that usually bears the central and lateral incisors and includes the anterior nasal spine and inferior aspect of the piriform rim. The premaxilla contains the bone and teeth of the primary palate." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5889-4463, https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Prominence of the premaxilla
Definition: "Prominent positioning of the premaxilla in relation to the rest of the maxilla, the facial skeleton, or mandible. Not necessarily caused by an increase in size (hypertrophy of) the premaxilla." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5889-4463, https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154, PMID:19125436]

Name: Absent toe
Definition: "Aplasia of a toe. That is, absence of all phalanges of a non-hallux digit of the foot and the associated soft tissues." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Broad columella
Definition: "Increased width of the columella." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Chordoma
Definition: "A chordoma is a tumor that arises from embryonic remnants of the notochord along the length of the neuraxis. Chordomas generally occur in the sacrum, intracranially at the clivus, or along the spinal axis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Low insertion of columella
Definition: "Insertion of the posterior columella below the nasal base." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Short eyelashes
Definition: "Decreased length of the eyelashes (subjective)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Palmar hyperkeratosis
Definition: "Abnormal thickening of the skin localized to the palm of the hand." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ectopic calcification
Definition: "Deposition of calcium salts in a tissue or location in which calcification does not normally occur." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sacrococcygeal pilonidal abnormality
Definition: "The presence of a cyst, fistula, or abscess in the sacrococcygeal region (gluteal crease) characteristically accompanied by hair and skin folds." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pilonidal sinus
Definition: "A sinus in the coccygeal region (the region of the intergluteal cleft). A pilonidal sinus often contains hair and skin debris." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pilonidal abscess
Definition: "A hair-containing cyst or sinus usually in the coccygeal region." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anomalous pulmonary venous return
Definition: "A developmental defect characterized by abnormal connection of one or more pulmonary veins to the superior or inferior vena cava, the right atrium, or the coronary sinus, resulting in a left-to-right shunt of oxygenated blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Partial anomalous pulmonary venous return
Definition: "A form of anomalous pulmonary venous return in which not all pulmonary veins drain abnormally. Partial anomalous pulmonary venous return frequently involves one or both of the veins from one lung." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cor triatriatum
Definition: "The presence of an additional membrane in the left or right cardiac atrium which results in the subdivision of the affected atrium (and thus in total three atria, whence the name)." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_dbrown, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Vascular ring
Definition: "A developmental defect of the aortic arch system in which the trachea and esophagus are completely encircled by connected segments of the aortic arch and its branches. This occurs if the normal process of regression and persistence of the bilateral embryonic aortic arches fails." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Tracheobronchmegaly
Definition: "Marked widening of the trachea and major bronchi that may be predispose to chronic respiratory tract infection." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bronchomegaly
Definition: "Marked widening of the major bronchi that may be predispose to chronic respiratory tract infection." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Tracheomegaly
Definition: "Marked widening of the trachea." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Large pelvis bone
Definition: "The presence of an abnormally large pelvis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperacusis
Definition: "Over-sensitivity to certain frequency ranges of sound." [PMID:14645606, PMID:14647932, PMID:31669363]

Name: Skin dimple
Definition: "Skin dimples are cutaneous indentations that are the result of tethering of the skin to underlying structures (bone) causing an indentation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Shoulder dimple
Definition: "A subtype of skin dimples occurring in the shoulder region." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:22679172]

Name: Erythema
Definition: "Redness of the skin, caused by hyperemia of the capillaries in the lower layers of the skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6548-5200]

Name: Uterine neoplasm
Definition: "A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the uterus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Gonadal neoplasm
Definition: "A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of a gonad." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Urinary tract neoplasm
Definition: "The presence of a neoplasm of the urinary system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Genital neoplasm
Definition: "A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the genital system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Testicular neoplasm
Definition: "The presence of a neoplasm of the testis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplasia of the Leydig cells
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the interstitial (Leydig) cells of the testis. These cells produce testosterone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperplasia of the Leydig cells
Definition: "Hypertrophy or overdevelopment of the interstitial (Leydig) cells of the testis. These cells produce testosterone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bifid nail
Definition: "A digit with two nails, with at least some soft tissue between them." [PMID:19125433]

Name: Impaired visuospatial constructive cognition
Definition: "Reduced ability affecting mainly visuospatial cognition which may be tested using pattern construction (for example by Differential Ability Scales, which test a person's strengths and weaknesses across a range of intellectual abilities)." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154, PMID:10521286]

Name: Cerebellar glioma
Definition: "A glioma affecting the cerebellum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Brainstem glioma
Definition: "A glioma affecting the brainstem." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hemangioblastoma
Definition: "A hemangioblastoma is a benign vascular neoplasm that arises almost exclusively in the central nervous system. Hemangioblastomas consist of a tightly packed cluster of small blood vessels forming a mass of up to 1 or 2 cm in diameter." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lip freckle
Definition: "Increased focal pigmentation of the vermilion of the lips." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Pinealoma
Definition: "A neoplasm of the pineal gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent cupid's bow
Definition: "Lack of paramedian peaks and median notch of the upper lip vermilion." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Underdeveloped nasolabial fold
Definition: "Reduced bulkiness of the crease or fold of skin running from the lateral margin of the nose, where nasal base meets the skin of the face, to a point just lateral to the corner of the mouth (cheilion or commissure)." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Perioral hyperpigmentation
Definition: "Increased pigmentation, either focal or generalized, of the skin surrounding the vermilion of the lips." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Everted upper lip vermilion
Definition: "Inner aspect of the upper lip vermilion (normally apposing the teeth) visible in a frontal view, i.e., the presence of an everted upper lip." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125428]

Name: Tented upper lip vermilion
Definition: "Triangular appearance of the oral aperture with the apex in the midpoint of the upper vermilion and the lower vermilion forming the base." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Upturned corners of mouth
Definition: "Oral commissures positioned superior to the midline labial fissure." [PMID:19125428]

Name: U-Shaped upper lip vermilion
Definition: "Gentle upward curve of the upper lip vermilion such that the center is placed well superior to the commissures." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Open bite
Definition: "Visible space between the dental arches in occlusion." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Protruding tongue
Definition: "Tongue extending beyond the alveolar ridges or teeth at rest." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Broad uvula
Definition: "Increased width of the uvula (subjective finding)." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Long uvula
Definition: "Increased length of the uvula." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Narrow uvula
Definition: "Decreased width of the uvula." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Short uvula
Definition: "Decreased length of the uvula." [PMID:19125428]

Name: Abnormal number of hair whorls
Definition: "More than two clockwise hair whorls." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Abnormal position of hair whorl
Definition: "Hair growth from a single point on the scalp in any location other than lateral to the midline and close to the vertex of the skull." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Nevus sebaceous
Definition: "A congenital, hairless plaque consisting of overgrown epidermis, sebaceous glands, hair follicles, apocrine glands and connective tissue. They are a variant of epidermal naevi. Sebaceous naevi most often appear on the scalp, but they may also arise on the face, neck or forehead. At birth, a sevaceous nevus typically appears as a solitary, smooth, yellow-orange hairless patch. Sebaceous naevi become more pronounced around adolescence, often appearing bumpy, warty or scaly." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Epidermal nevus
Definition: "Epidermal naevi are due to an overgrowth of the epidermis and may be present at birth (50%) or develop during childhood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20542174]

Name: Linear nevus sebaceous
Definition: "A type of nevus sebaceous with a linear form, raised borders and yellowish color." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Generalized tonic seizure
Definition: "A generalized tonic seizure is a type of generalized motor seizure characterised by bilateral limb stiffening or elevation, often with neck stiffening without a subsequent clonic phase. The tonic activity can be a sustained abnormal posture, either in extension or flexion, sometimes accompanied by tremor of the extremities." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:11580774, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276064]

Name: Atonic seizure
Definition: "Atonic seizure is a type of motor seizure characterized by a sudden loss or diminution of muscle tone without apparent preceding myoclonic or tonic event lasting about 1 to 2 seconds, involving head, trunk, jaw, or limb musculature." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1735-8178, PMID:11580774]

Name: Focal emotional seizure with crying
Definition: "Focal emotional seizure with crying (dacrystic) is characterized by the presence of stereotyped crying, this may be accompanied by lacrimation, sad facial expression and sobbing. The subjective emotion of sadness may or may not be present." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:28276060, PMID:993803]

Name: Focal emotional seizure with laughing
Definition: "Focal emotional seizure with laughing (gelastic) is characterized by bursts of laughter or giggling, usually without appropriate related emotion of happiness, and described as 'mirthless'." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276064]

Name: Scintillating scotoma
Definition: "A scintillating scotoma is a common visual aura that can preced a migraine, whereby a spot of flickering light near the center of the visual fields occurs. The spot prevents vision, and is thus termed scotoma. The scotoma can extend into one or more shimmering arcs of white or colored flashing lights." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ridged cranial sutures
Definition: "An overlap of the bony plates of the skull in an infant, with or without early closure." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal fifth cranial nerve morphology
Definition: "Any structural abnormality of the fifth cranial nerve." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the eleventh cranial nerve
Definition: "Abnormality of the eleventh cranial nerve." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the twelfth cranial nerve
Definition: "Abnormality of the twelfth cranial nerve." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the seventh cranial nerve
Definition: "Abnormality of the seventh cranial nerve sometimes also referred to as the facial nerve." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hemifacial spasm
Definition: "Intermittent clonic or tonic contraction of muscles supplied by facial nerve. Muscles are relaxed in between contractions." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:12145388]

Name: Impaired temperature sensation
Definition: "A reduced ability to discriminate between different temperatures." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Impaired tactile sensation
Definition: "A reduced sense of touch (tactile sensation). This is usually tested with a wisp of cotton or a fine camel's hair brush, by asking patients to say 'now' each time they feel the stimulus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Impaired proprioception
Definition: "A loss or impairment of the sensation of the relative position of parts of the body and joint position." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of pain sensation
Definition: "Pain is an unpleasant sensation that can range from mild, localized discomfort to agony, whereby the physical part of pain results from nerve stimulation and is often accompanied by an emotional component. This term groups abnormalities in pain sensation presumed to result from abnormalities related to the specific nerve fibers that carry the pain impulses to the brain." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Spontaneous pain sensation
Definition: "Spontaneous pain is a kind of neuropathic pain which occurs without an identifiable trigger." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Trophic changes related to pain
Definition: "Trophic changes is a term used to describe abnormalities in the area of pain that include primarily wasting away of the skin, tissues, or muscle, thinning of the bones, and changes in how the hair or nails grow, including thickening or thinning of hair or brittle nails." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Dissociated sensory loss
Definition: "A pattern of sensory loss with selective loss of touch sensation and proprioception without loss of pain and temperature, or vice-versa." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating copper concentration
Definition: "An abnormal concentration of copper." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased circulating ceruloplasmin concentration
Definition: "Decreased concentration of ceruloplasmin in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:32119309]

Name: High nonceruloplasmin-bound serum copper
Definition: "An increased concentration of non ceruloplasmin bound copper in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased urinary copper concentration
Definition: "An increased concentration of copper in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Multifocal epileptiform discharges
Definition: "An abnormality in cerebral electrical activity recorded along the scalp by electroencephalography (EEG) and being identified at multiple locations (foci)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: EEG with focal slow activity
Definition: "Focal (localized) slow activity reflects focal dysfunction, not diffuse dysfunction (i.e., encephalopathy)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: EEG with multifocal slow activity
Definition: "Multifocal slowing of cerebral electrical activity recorded along the scalp by electroencephalography (EEG)." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with generalized slow activity
Definition: "Diffuse slowing of cerebral electrical activity recorded along the scalp by electroencephalography (EEG)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: EEG with persistent abnormal rhythmic activity
EEG with spike-wave complexes (<2.5 Hz)
Definition: "The presence of complexes of slow spikes and slow waves (<2.5 Hz) in electroencephalography (EEG)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: EEG with spike-wave complexes (2.5-3.5 Hz)
Definition: "The presence of complexes of spikes and waves (2.5-3.5 Hz) in electroencephalography (EEG)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: EEG with spike-wave complexes (>3.5 Hz)
Definition: "The presence of complexes of spikes and waves (>3.5 Hz) in electroencephalography (EEG)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: EEG with spike-wave complexes
Definition: "Complexes of spikes (<70 ms) and sharp waves (70-200 ms), which are sharp transient waves that have a strong association with epilepsy, in cerebral electrical activity recorded along the scalp by electroencephalography (EEG)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: EEG with burst suppression
Definition: "The burst suppression pattern in electroencephalography refers to a characteristic periodic pattern of low voltage (<10 microvolts) suppressed background and a relatively shorter pattern of higher amplitude slow, sharp, and spiking complexes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:22323592]

Name: EEG with photoparoxysmal response
Definition: "EEG abnormalities (epileptiform discharges) evoked by flashing lights or black and white striped patterns." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: EEG with periodic lateralized epileptiform discharges
Definition: "Periodic lateralized epileptiform discharges (PLEDs)are periodic, lateralized, and epileptiform. PLEDs show a relatively constant interval between discharges (0.5 to 3 seconds)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: EEG with generalized low amplitude activity
Definition: "An abnormal generalized reduction in amplitude of the cerebral electrical activity recorded along the scalp by electroencephalography (EEG)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: EEG with localized low amplitude activity
Definition: "An abnormal localized reduction in amplitude of the cerebral electrical activity recorded along the scalp by electroencephalography (EEG)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: EEG with periodic complexes
Definition: "Periodically occurring generalized periodic complexes." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with periodic abnormalities
Definition: "Periodically recurring abnormalities in the EEG." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: EEG with hyperventilation-induced epileptiform discharges
Definition: "Epileptiform discharges induced by hyperventilation (overbreathing) in cerebral electrical activity recorded along the scalp by electroencephalography (EEG)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Frank breech presentation
Definition: "A kind of breech presentation in which the hips are flexed and the knees are extended." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Complete breech presentation
Definition: "A kind of breech presentation in which the hips are flexed and the knees are flexed." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Incomplete breech presentation
Definition: "A kind of breech presentation in which one or both hips are extended and one or both of the fetus' feet are pointing down and entering the birth canal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Delayed fine motor development
Definition: "A type of motor delay characterized by a delay in acquiring the ability to control the fingers and hands." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Receptive language delay
Definition: "A delay in the acquisition of the ability to understand the speech of others." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Intellectual disability, severe
Definition: "Severe mental retardation is defined as an intelligence quotient (IQ) in the range of 20-34." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Oppositional defiant disorder
Definition: "An enduring pattern of uncooperative, defiant, and hostile behavior toward authority figures that does not involve major antisocial violations, is not accounted for by the child's developmental stage, and results in significant functional impairment. A certain level of oppositional behavior is common in children and adolescents." [DSM:313.81, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abdominal wall defect
Definition: "An incomplete closure of the abdominal wall." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Dyssynergia
Definition: "A type of ataxia characterized by the impairment of the ability to smoothly perform the elements of a voluntary movement in the appropriate order and speed. With dyssynergia, a voluntary movement appears broken down into its component parts." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ocular dyssynergia
Definition: "A type of dyssynergia affecting eye movements and characterized by the inability to smoothly follow a visual target across the visual field." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Asynergia
Definition: "A type of dyssynergy characterized by the lack of the ability to smoothly perform the elements of a voluntary movement in the appropriate order and speed." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sensory ataxia
Definition: "Incoordination of movement caused by a deficit in the sensory nervous system. Sensory ataxia can be distinguished from cerebellar ataxia by asking the patient to close his or her eyes. Persons with cerebellar ataxia show only a minimal worsening of symptoms, whereas persons with sensory ataxia show a marked worsening of symptoms." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: T-wave inversion
Definition: "An inversion of the T-wave (which is normally positive)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cervical spinal cord atrophy
Definition: "Atrophy of the cervical segment of the spinal cord." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Tendon xanthomatosis
Definition: "The presence of xanthomas (intra-and extra-cellular accumulations of cholesterol) extensor tendons (typically over knuckles, Achilles tendon, knee, and elbows)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Chaddock reflex
Definition: "A diagnostic reflex elicited by stimulation of the skin over the surface of the lateral malleolus of the foot. The Chaddock refelx is present if there is extension of one or more or all of the toes with or without fanning of them when the external inframalleolar skin is stimulated. The Chaddock sign, similar to the Babinski sign, is taken to be an indication of disease of the spinocortical (pyramidal) tract." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating protein concentration
Definition: "An abnormal level of a circulating protein in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Monocular strabismus
Definition: "A type of strabismus in which the fixating eye is always the same one, while the other eye is constantly deviated. Monocular strabismus is to be distinguished from alternating strabismus, in which either of the eyes 'squints' at different times." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fetal cystic hygroma
Definition: "The presence during the prenatal period of a cystic mass with multiple septa with multiple, asymmetric, thin-walled cysts near the posterior aspect of the neck. Fetal cystic hygroma can be defined as nuchal translucency with or without septations measuring greater than 3.0 mm. Increased NT refers to a measurement above the 95th centile, and the term is used irrespective of whether the collection of fluid is septated or not, and whether it is confined to the neck or envelopes the whole fetus. After 14 weeks, increased NT usually resolves, but in some cases it evolves into nuchal edema or cystic hygromas." [eMedicine:402757, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased nuchal translucency
Definition: "Nuchal translucency is the sonographic appearance of subcutaneous accumulation of liquid in the back of the fetal neck in the first trimester of pregnancy (11-14 gestational weeks of pregnancy)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:12751779, PMID:15846173, PMID:28511453]

Name: Abnormality of the umbilical cord
