Definition: "An abnormality of the umbilical cord, which is the cord connecting the developing embryo or fetus to the placenta." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pulmonary valve atresia
Definition: "A congenital disorder of the pulmonary valve in which the orifice of the valve fails to develop." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aortic valve atresia
Definition: "A congenital disorder of the aortic valve in which the orifice of the valve fails to develop." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Acromelia
Definition: "Shortening of the extremities affecting primarily the distal parts of the limbs (hands and feet) in relation to the other segments of the limbs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Avascular necrosis
Definition: "A disease where there is cellular death (necrosis) of bone components due to interruption of the blood supply." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Osteochondritis dissecans
Definition: "A joint disorder caused by blood deprivation in the subchondral bone causing the subchondral bone to die in a process called avascular necrosis. The bone is then reabsorbed by the body, leaving the articular cartilage it supported prone to damage. The result is fragmentation (dissection) of both cartilage and bone, and the free movement of these osteochondral fragments within the joint space, causing pain and further damage." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Morbus Koehler
Definition: "Morbus Koehler is a Juvenile aseptic necrosis affecting the Os naviculare pedis." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Morbus Kienboeck
Definition: "Morbus Kienboeck is a Juvenile aseptic necrosis affecting the Os lunatum." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Morbus Osgood-Schlatter
Definition: "Morbus Osgood-Schlatter is a Juvenile aseptic necrosis affecting the Tuberositas tibiae." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Morbus Scheuermann
Definition: "A developmental growth retardation of the vertebral end plates that may lead to secondary destruction of the vertebral end plates and protrusion of the nucleus pulposus into the vertebral body (so called Schmorl's nodes as seen on x-rays)." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Abnormal circulating branched chain amino acid concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of a branched chain family amino acid in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating phenylalanine concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of phenylalanine in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating serine family amino acid concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of a serine family amino acid in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating glycine concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of glycine in the blood circulation." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Hypersarcosinemia
Definition: "An elevated plasma concentration of sarcosine." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Hypersarcosinuria
Definition: "An elevated urinary concentration of sarcosine." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Abnormal circulating sarcosine concentration
Definition: "An deviation from the normal concentration of sarcosine in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating aspartate family amino acid concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of an aspartate family amino acid in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating threonine concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of threonine in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating methionine concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of methionine in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating glutamine family amino acid concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of a glutamine family amino acid in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating glutamine concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of glutamine in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating histidine concentration
Definition: "An abnormality of a histidine metabolic process." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperhistidinemia
Definition: "An increased concentration of histidine in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Abnormal circulating proline concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of proline or a proline metabolite in the blood circulation." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Abnormal circulating lysine concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of lysine in the blood circulation." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Abnormal circulating arginine concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of arginine in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypervalinemia
Definition: "An increased concentration of valine in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Hyperleucinemia
Definition: "An increased concentration of leucine in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Abnormal circulating isoleucine concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of isoleucine in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperisoleucinemia
Definition: "An increased concentration of isoleucine in the blood." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Abnormal circulating valine concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal circulation of valine in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating pyruvate family amino acid concentration
Definition: "An abnormality of a pyruvate family amino acid metabolic process." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating alanine concentration
Definition: "An abnormality of an alanine metabolic process." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Abnormal circulating tyrosine concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of tyrosine in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating cysteine concentration
Definition: "An abnormality of a cysteine metabolic process." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating homocysteine concentration
Definition: "An abnormality of a homocysteine metabolic process." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Zonular cataract
Definition: "Zonular cataracts are defined to be cataracts that affect specific regions of the lens." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:vkumar, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:18035564]

Name: Coralliform cataract
Definition: "A 'coral-like' pattern of opacity in the lens of the eye. That is, a cataract with an irregular, stellate form." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:vkumar, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Membranous cataract
Definition: "A form of cataract in which the lens substance has shrunk, leaving a collapsed, flattened capsule with little or no cortex or epithelium on the lens." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:17539799]

Name: Anterior subcapsular cataract
Definition: "A type of cataract affecting the anterior pole of lens immediately adjacent to ('beneath') the lens capsule." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Posterior cortical cataract
Definition: "A cataract that affects the posterior part of the cortex of the lens." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aculeiform cataract
Definition: "A kind of nuclear cataract characterized by fiberglasslike or needlelike crystals projecting in different directions, through or close to the axial region of the lens." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:10521291, PMID:9718335]

Name: Abnormal blood inorganic cation concentration
Definition: "An abnormality of divalent inorganic cation homeostasis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: obsolete Increased urinary orotic acid concentration
Abnormal blood cation concentration
Definition: "An abnormality of cation homeostasis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal blood monovalent inorganic cation concentration
Definition: "An abnormality of monovalent inorganic cation homeostasis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal blood sodium concentration
Definition: "An abnormal concentration of sodium." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating nucleobase concentration
Definition: "An abnormality of a nucleobase metabolic process." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperxanthinemia
Definition: "An increased level of xanthine in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:9153281]

Name: Xanthinuria
Definition: "An increased concentration of xanthine in the urine." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Abnormality of the upper urinary tract
Definition: "An abnormality of the upper urinary tract." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the lower urinary tract
Definition: "An abnormality of the lower urinary tract." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal nasal skeleton morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the nasal skeleton." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal external nose morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the external nose." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal nasal bone morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the nasal bone, comprising the left nasal bone and the right nasal bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the nasal bone
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the nasal bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia of the nasal bone
Definition: "Absence of the nasal bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Echogenic intracardiac focus
Definition: "A finding of a focus of increased echogenicity upon prenatal ultrasound examination of the fetus. The foci may be present in one or both ventricles. Echogenic intracardiac focus (EICF) is defined as a focus of echogenicity comparable to bone, in the region of the papillary muscle in either or both ventricles of the fetal heart." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16100637, PMID:9527573]

Name: Echogenic fetal bowel
Definition: "Echogenic bowel is defined as fetal bowel with homogenous areas of echogenicity that are equal to or greater than that of surrounding bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16100637, PMID:20175047]

Name: Abnormal renal pelvis morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the renal pelvis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fetal pyelectasis
Definition: "Mild pyelectasis is defined as a hypoechoic spherical or elliptical space within the renal pelvis that measures at least 5mm and not more than 10 mm. The measurement is taken on a transverse section through the fetal renal pelvis using the maximum anterior-to-posterior measurement." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16100637]

Name: Dilatation of the renal pelvis
Definition: "The presence of dilatation of the renal pelvis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of ductus venosus blood flow
Definition: "A first-trimester prenatal ultrasound finding of abnormal blood flow in the ductus venosus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16449256, PMID:21048453]

Name: Abnormal fetal cardiovascular morphology
Definition: "A structural abnormality of the fetal circulation system. Terms in this subhierarchy are restricted to findings that can only be observed in the prenatal period. Other HPO terms can also be used to describe fetal phenotypes." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_dbrown, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of umbilical vein blood flow
Definition: "A first-trimester prenatal ultrasound finding of abnormal blood flow in the umbilical vein." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal fourth ventricle morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the fourth ventricle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal third ventricle morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the third ventricle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Mild fetal ventriculomegaly
Definition: "A kind of ventriculomegaly occurring in the fetal period and usually diagnosed by prenatal ultrasound. Cerebral ventriculomegaly is defined by atrial measurements 10 mm or more. Mild ventriculomegaly (MVM) is defined as measurements between 10 and 15 mm. Measurements are obtained from an axial plane at the level of the thalamic nuclei just below the standard image to measure the BPD (PMID:16100637)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16100637]

Name: Noncommunicating hydrocephalus
Definition: "A form of hydrocephalus in which the flow of cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) within the cerebral ventricular system or in the outlets of the CSF to the arachnoid space is obstructed." [eMedicine:1135286, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplastic right heart
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the right-sided structures of the heart." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Dilatation of the bladder
Definition: "The presence of a dilated urinary bladder." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fetal megacystis
Definition: "Fetal megacystis is an abnormally enlarged bladder identified at any gestational age." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20837325]

Name: Congenital posterior urethral valve
Definition: "A developmental defect resulting in an obstructing membrane in the posterior male urethra." [eMedicine:1016086, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bilateral renal agenesis
Definition: "A bilateral form of agenesis of the kidney." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Congenital pulmonary airway malformation
Definition: "Congenital pulmonary airway malformation (CPAM) - previously known as congenital cystic adenomatoid malformation (CCAM) - is a relatively rare developmental malformation of the lower respiratory tract. It is a hamartomatous, dysplastic developmental abnormality of the lung characterized by abnormal airway patterning during lung branching morphogenesis and is formed by abnormal branching of the immature bronchioles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:28638495]

Name: Bronchopulmonary sequestration
Definition: "The presence of microscopic cystic masses of nonfunctioning pulmonary tissue that lack an obvious communication with the tracheobronchial tree." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20610189]

Name: Intralobar sequestration
Definition: "A kind of bronchopulmonary sequestration that is incorporated into the normal surrounding lung." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20610189]

Name: Extralobar sequestration
Definition: "A kind of bronchopulmonary sequestration that is completely discrete from the normal lung and is surrounded by separate pleura." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20610189]

Name: Absence of stomach bubble on fetal sonography
Definition: "By the 14th week of gestation it is nearly always possible to visualized the fluid-filled fetal stomach bubble on prenatal sonography. This term refers to the absence of a normal fetal stomach bubble on fetal ultrasonography performed at around 16 to 20 weeks' gestation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20538709]

Name: Abnormal circulating long-chain fatty-acid concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of a long-chain fatty acid in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating phytanic acid concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of phytanic acid in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating fatty-acid anion concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of a fatty acid anion in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating carnitine concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of carnitine in the blood circulation." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Abnormality of liposaccharide metabolism
Definition: "An abnormality of liposaccharide metabolism." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of glycolipid metabolism
Definition: "An abnormality of glycolipid metabolism." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Blood group antigen abnormality
Definition: "An abnormality of an erythrocyte cell surface molecule." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absence of Lutheran antigen on erythrocytes
Definition: "Absence of the Lutheran antigen (a type I integral membrane glycoprotein) from the surface of red blood cells." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anemia of inadequate production
Definition: "A kind of anemia characterized by inadequate production of erythrocytes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal myeloid leukocyte morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of myeloid leukocytes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal B cell count
Definition: "A deviation from the normal count of B cells, i.e., the cells that are formed in the bone marrow, migrate to the peripheral lymphatic system, and mature into plasma cells or memory cells." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, MP:0002458]

Name: B lymphocytopenia
Definition: "An abnormal decrease from the normal count of B cells." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal phagocytosis
Definition: "An abnormal functioning of phagocytosis. Phagocytosis is an elegant but complex process for the ingestion and elimination of pathogens, but it is also important for the elimination of apoptotic cells and hence fundamental for tissue homeostasis. Phagocytosis can be divided into four main steps: (i) recognition of the target particle, (ii) signaling to activate the internalization machinery, (iii) phagosome formation, and (iv) phagolysosome maturation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:28691037]

Name: Abnormality of immune system physiology
Definition: "A functional abnormality of the immune system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, MP:0001790]

Name: Abnormality of lipoprotein cholesterol concentration
Definition: "An abnormal increase or decrease in the level of lipoprotein cholesterol in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperlipoproteinemia
Definition: "An abnormal increase in the level of lipoprotein cholesterol in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypolipoproteinemia
Definition: "An abnormal decrease in the level of lipoprotein cholesterol in the blood." []

Name: Polygenic inheritance
Definition: "A mode of inheritance that depends on a mixture of major and minor genetic determinants possibly together with environmental factors. Diseases inherited in this manner are termed complex diseases." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, ISBN:978-0192628961]

Name: Oligogenic inheritance
Definition: "A type of multifactorial inheritance governed by the simultaneous action of a few gene loci. It is recommended this term be used for traits governed by three loci, although it is noted that usage of this term in the literature is not uniform." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, ISBN:978-0192628961]

Name: Digenic inheritance
Definition: "A type of multifactorial inheritance governed by the simultaneous action of two gene loci." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, ISBN:978-0192628961]

Name: Abnormal cellular immune system morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the morphology or counts of the cells that make up the immune system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the extrinsic pathway
Definition: "An abnormality of the extrinsic pathway (also known as the tissue factor pathway) of the coagulation cascade." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the intrinsic pathway
Definition: "An abnormality of the intrinsic pathway (also known as the contact activation pathway) of the coagulation cascade." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the common coagulation pathway
Definition: "An abnormality of blood coagulation, common pathway." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal morphology of the abdominal musculature
Definition: "An abnormality of the abdominal musculature." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Stress urinary incontinence
Definition: "Involuntary urine leakage synchronous with exertion, or actions such as sneezing, or coughing." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:12559262]

Name: Abnormal cerebral subcortex morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the cerebral subcortex." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal corpus striatum morphology
Definition: "Abnormality of the striatum, which is the largest nucleus of the basal ganglia, comprising the caudate, putamen and ventral striatum, including the nucleus accumbens." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:21469956]

Name: Abnormal circulating dicarboxylic acid concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of a dicarboxylic acid in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating monocarboxylic acid concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of a monocarboxylic acid in the blood circulation." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:gcarletti]

Name: Chromosomal breakage induced by ionizing radiation
Definition: "Increased amount of chromosomal breaks in cultured blood lymphocytes or other cells induced by treatment with ionizing radiation." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154, PMID:16814619]

Name: Increased susceptibility to spontaneous sister chromatid exchange
Definition: "An increase in the number of spontaneous sister chromatid exchanges observed in cell culture of lymphocytes or other cells." [https://orcid.org/0009-0006-4530-3154]

Name: Increased bone mineral density
Definition: "An abnormal increase of bone mineral density, that is, of the amount of matter per cubic centimeter of bones which is often referred to as osteosclerosis. Osteosclerosis can be detected on radiological examination as an increased whiteness (density) of affected bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Osteopetrosis
Definition: "Abnormally increased formation of dense trabecular bone tissue. Despite the increased density of bone tissue, osteopetrotic bones tend to be more fracture-prone than normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: High myopia
Definition: "A severe form of myopia with greater than -6.00 diopters." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_ncarter]

Name: Abnormal systemic arterial morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the systemic arterial tree, which consists of the aorta and other systemic arteries." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Mixed cirrhosis
Definition: "A type of cirrhosis characterized by the presence of regenerative nodules of a variety of sizes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal morphology of the musculature of the neck
Definition: "An abnormality of the neck musculature." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Temporal pattern
Definition: "The speed at which disease manifestations appear and develop." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Acute

Name: Chronic

Name: Subacute
Definition: "Somewhat rapid onset and change of disease manifestations." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of blood circulation
Definition: "An abnormality of blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Impairment of fructose metabolism
Definition: "An impairment of a fructose metabolic process." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Amyloidosis
Definition: "The presence of amyloid deposition in one or more tissues. Amyloidosis may be defined as the extracellular deposition of amyloid in one or more sites of the body." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:21039326]

Name: Abnormal renal cortex morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the cortex of the kidney." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of renal excretion
Definition: "An altered ability of the kidneys to void urine and/or specific substances." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased urine output
Definition: "A decreased rate of urine production." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal renal tubular resorption
Definition: "An abnormality of renal absorption." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal helix morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the helix. The helix is the outer rim of the ear that extends from the insertion of the ear on the scalp (root) to the termination of the cartilage at the earlobe." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal intrahepatic bile duct morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the intrahepatic bile duct." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the cervical spine
Definition: "Aplasia or developmental hypoplasia of the cervical vertebral column." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal blood potassium concentration
Definition: "An abnormal concentration of potassium." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating adrenocorticotropin concentration
Definition: "An abnormal concentration of corticotropin in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal number of permanent teeth
Definition: "The presence of an altered number of of permanent teeth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Agenesis of permanent maxillary central incisor
Definition: "Agenesis of upper secondary incisor." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Agenesis of primary maxillary central incisor
Definition: "Agenesis of upper central primary incisor." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Agenesis of primary mandibular central incisor
Definition: "Agenesis of lower primary incisor." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Agenesis of permanent mandibular central incisor
Definition: "Agenesis of lower secondary incisor." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Agenesis of primary maxillary lateral incisor
Definition: "Agenesis of one or more maxillary lateral incisor, comprising the maxillary lateral primary incisor." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Agenesis of permanent maxillary lateral incisor
Definition: "Agenesis of one or more upper lateral secondary incisor." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Agenesis of premolar
Definition: "Agenesis of premolar tooth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Agenesis of maxillary premolar
Definition: "Agenesis of maxillary premolar." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Agenesis of permanent molar
Definition: "Agenesis of secondary molar tooth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Agenesis of first permanent molar tooth
Definition: "Agenesis of either maxillary first permanent molar or mandibular first permanent molar or both." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Agenesis of second permanent molar
Definition: "Agenesis of either mandibular second permanent molar or maxillary second permanent molar." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Generalized periodontitis
Definition: "A generalized form of periodontitis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Localized periodontitis
Definition: "A localized form of periodontitis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Dentinogenesis imperfecta limited to primary teeth
Definition: "Developmental dysplasia of dentin affecting only the primary dentition." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Abnormality of dental structure
Definition: "An abnormality of the structure or composition of the teeth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Misalignment of incisors
Definition: "Misaligned incisor." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Abnormal incisor morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of morphology of the incisor tooth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Abnormal number of incisors
Definition: "The presence of an altered number of the incisor teeth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Conical incisor
Definition: "An abnormal conical morphology of the incisor tooth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Mesiodens
Definition: "A supernumerary tooth in the midline between the maxillary central incisors." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017, PMID:18262485, PMID:31468724]

Name: Odontoma
Definition: "The presence of an odontoma." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Supernumerary tooth
Definition: "The presence of one or more teeth additional to the normal number." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017, PMID:31468724]

Name: Abnormal molar morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of morphology of molar tooth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Abnormality of permanent molar morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of morphology of permanent molar." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Abnormality of dental color
Definition: "A developmental defect of tooth color." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Localized hypoplasia of dental enamel
Definition: "A localized form of developmental hypoplasia of the dental enamel." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Green teeth
Definition: "A green staining of teeth." [PMID:12686928]

Name: Abnormality of premolar
Definition: "An abnormality of premolar tooth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Abnormality of molar
Definition: "An abnormality of molar tooth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Abnormality of canine
Definition: "An abnormality of canine tooth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Impacted tooth
Definition: "A tooth that has not erupted because of local impediments (overcrowding or fibrous gum overgrowth)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Abnormal premolar morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of morphology of premolar tooth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Incisor macrodontia
Definition: "Increased size of the incisor tooth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Conical primary incisor
Definition: "An abnormal conical morphology of the primary incisor." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Conical maxillary incisor
Definition: "An abnormal conical morphology of either maxillary primary incisor tooth or maxillary permanent incisor tooth or both." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Hypocalcification of dental enamel
Definition: "A form of hypomineralization of enamel characterized by reduced calcification." [PMID:18499550]

Name: Hypomature dental enamel
Definition: "A form of hypomineralization of enamel characterized by a chalky appearance of the enamel with orange, brown, or white color." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Dentinogenesis imperfecta of primary and permanent teeth
Definition: "Developmental dysplasia of dentin or both the primary dentition and the permanent dentition." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Talon cusp
Definition: "Talon cusp is an accessory cusp located near the cingulum (the portion of the lingual or palatal aspect of the tooth that forms a convex protuberance at the cervical third of the anatomic crown)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Dens in dente
Definition: "An abnormality of the incisor characterized by invagination of the enamel, giving a radiographic appearance that suggests a tooth within a tooth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017, PMID:31468724]

Name: Double tooth
Definition: "Fusion of two adjacent teeth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017, PMID:31468724]

Name: Fused teeth
Definition: "The union of two separately developing tooth germs typically leading to one less tooth than normal in the affected dental arch." [PMID:18167487]

Name: Gemination
Definition: "The development of two teeth from a single tooth bud, leading to a larger fused tooth." [PMID:18167487]

Name: Mulberry molar
Definition: "Mulberry molars are irregular teeth generally affecting the first molars and are characterized by a grossly deformed crown imitating, as the name implies, the surface of a mulberry." []

Name: Molarization of premolar
Definition: "Increased size and molar morphology of premolar tooth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017, PMID:15587104]

Name: Increased overbite
Definition: "Maxillary teeth cover the mandibular teeth when biting to an increased degree. The feature is defined as a vertical overlap of the maxillary incisors over the mandibular incisors that exceeds 2 mm." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017, PMID:31468724]

Name: Overjet
Definition: "An abnormal anteroposterior extension of the maxillary teeth beyond the plane of the mandibular teeth upon jaw closure." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9338-3017]

Name: Peripheral demyelination
Definition: "A loss of myelin from the internode regions along myelinated nerve fibers of the peripheral nervous system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Epileptic spasm
Definition: "A sudden flexion, extension, or mixed extension-flexion of predominantly proximal and truncal muscles that is usually more sustained than a myoclonic movement but not as sustained as a tonic seizure. Limited forms may occur: Grimacing, head nodding, or subtle eye movements. Epileptic spasms frequently occur in clusters. Infantile spasms are the best known form, but spasms can occur at all ages" [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers, PMID:28276060]

Name: Speech apraxia
Definition: "A type of apraxia that is characterized by difficulty or inability to execute speech movements because of problems with coordination and motor problems, leading to incorrect articulation. An increase of errors with increasing word and phrase length may occur." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Spastic hemiparesis
Definition: "Unilateral paresis (weakness) with spasticity of the affected muscles and increased tendon reflexes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Intestinal atresia
Definition: "An abnormal closure, or atresia of the tubular structure of the intestine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ileal atresia
Definition: "An abnormal closure, or atresia of the tubular structure of the ileum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal left ventricular outflow tract morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the outflow tract of the left ventricle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of blood volume homeostasis
Definition: "An abnormality in the amount of volume occupied by intravascular blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypervolemia
Definition: "An increase in the amount of intravascular fluid, particularly in the volume of the circulating blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypovolemia
Definition: "An decrease in the amount of intravascular fluid, particularly in the volume of the circulating blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Recurrent aphthous stomatitis
Definition: "Recurrent episodes of ulceration of the oral mucosa, typically presenting as painful, sharply circumscribed fibrin-covered mucosal defects with a hyperemic border." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Recurrent sinusitis
Definition: "A recurrent form of sinusitis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Chronic sinusitis
Definition: "A chronic form of sinusitis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Recurrent tonsillitis
Definition: "Inflammation of the tonsils that has occurred repeatedly. The definition of recurrent may vary somewhat, but the criteria used recently as a measure of severity were five or more episodes of true tonsillitis per year, symptoms recurring for at least a year, and episodes that are disabling and that prevent normal functioning. In some cases recurrent tonsillitis may be related to immunosusceptibility. Evidence exists for a genetic predisposition for recurrent tonsillitis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:15897415]

Name: Abnormality of immune serum protein physiology
Definition: "An abnormality of the concentration or function of circulating immune proteins." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of serum cytokine level
Definition: "Abnormality of the cytokine levels in the blood, i.e., an abnormality of any of the non-antibody proteins made by inflammatory leukocytes and some non-leukocytic cells that affect the behavior of other cells." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of cytokine secretion
Definition: "An abnormality in the production or cellular release of a cytokine (i.e., any of the non-antibody proteins made by inflammatory leukocytes and some non-leukocytic cells that affect the behavior of other cells)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Defective production of NFKB1-dependent cytokines
Definition: "An impairment in the production by leukocytes of NFKB1-dependent cytokines such as tumor necrosis factor-alpha and interferon-alpha." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of chemokine secretion
Definition: "An abnormality in the production or cellular release of a chemokine (a class of cytokines)." []

Name: Abnormality of interferon secretion
Definition: "An abnormality in the production or cellular release of interferons (a class of cytokines)." []

Name: Abnormality of interleukin secretion
Definition: "An abnormality in the production or cellular release of interleukins (a class of cytokines)." []

Name: Abnormality of tumor necrosis factor secretion
Definition: "An abnormality in the production or cellular release of tumor necrosis factor." []

Name: Abnormal nasal dorsum morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the nasal dorsum, also known as the nasal ridge." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152422]

Name: Concave nasal ridge
Definition: "Nasal ridge curving posteriorly to an imaginary line that connects the nasal root and tip." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152422]

Name: Abnormality of skin morphology
Definition: "Any morphological abnormality of the skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of skin physiology
Definition: "Any abnormality of the physiological function of the skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Inflammatory abnormality of the skin
Definition: "The presence of inflammation of the skin. That is, an abnormality of the skin resulting from the local accumulation of fluid, plasma proteins, and leukocytes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal epidermal morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the morphology of the epidermis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of dermal melanosomes
Definition: "An abnormality of the melanosomes, i.e., of the cellular organelles in which melanin pigments are synthesized and stored within melanocytes (the cells that produce pigment in the dermis)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Nephroptosis
Definition: "A significant descent of the kidney as the patient moves from the supine to the erect position." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:18990154]

Name: Perioral eczema
Definition: "A type of eczema that occurs in the lips and perioral area." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Acute esophageal necrosis
Definition: "A condition characterized by necrosis of the mucosal and submucosal layers of the esophagus not related to ingestion of caustic or other injurious agents. Endoscopically, there is a dark lesion ('black esophagus') distributed in a circumferential manner in the distal one-third of the esophagus with or without exudates. There is involvement of the distal esophagus ending sharply at the gastroesophageal junction." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:17322991]

Name: Bilateral fetal pyelectasis
Definition: "A bilateral form of fetal pyelectasis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal renal calyx morphology
Definition: "Any abnormality of the morphology of the major calices or minor calices of the kidney." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Perianal dermatitis
Definition: "The presence of a rash (change of color and texture) of the perianal skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Chronic furunculosis
Definition: "A furuncle (boil) is a skin infection involving an entire hair follicle and nearby skin tissue. Chronic furunculosis refers to recurrent episodes of furuncles, often caused by recurrent staphylococcus infection." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased sensitivity to ionizing radiation
Definition: "An abnormally increased sensitivity to the effects of ionizing radiation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Low-grade fever
Definition: "Mild fever that does not exceed 38.5 degrees centigrade." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the sweat glands
Definition: "Absence or developmental hypoplasia of the sweat glands." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aplasia of the sweat glands
Definition: "Absence of the sweat glands." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Non-pruritic urticaria
Definition: "Pale reddish slightly elevated papules and plaques of 0.5-3 cm in diameter and not accompanied by pruritus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of skin adnexa morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the skin adnexa (skin appendages), which are specialized skin structures located within the dermis and focally within the subcutaneous fatty tissue, comprising three histologically distinct structures: (1) the pilosebaceous unit (hair follicle and sebaceous glands); (2) the eccrine sweat glands; and (3) the apocrine glands." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Gastric duplication
Definition: "Gastric duplication is a usually cystic malformation of gastrointestinal tract, usually attached to the greater curvature of the stomach and has no communication with the stomach." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Gastrointestinal duplication
Definition: "A spherical hollow structure with a smooth muscle coat, lined by a mucous membrane, and attached to any part of the gastrointestinal tract, from the base of the tongue to the anus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:21218094]

Name: Age-related cataract
Definition: "A type of cataract (opacification of the lens) that forms during the course of aging." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:15708105]

Name: Age-related nuclear cataract
Definition: "A type of age-related cataract that primarily affects the nucleus of the lens." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:15708105]

Name: Age-related cortical cataract
Definition: "A type of age-related cataract that primarily affects the cortex of the lens." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:15708105]

Name: Age-related posterior subcapsular cataract
Definition: "A type of age-related cataract consisting of granular opacities occurring mainly in the central posterior cortex just under the posterior capsule." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:15708105]

Name: Symptomatic seizures
Definition: "A seizure that occurs in the context of a brain insult (systemic, toxic, or metabolic) and may not recur when the underlying cause has been removed or the acute phase has elapsed." [PMID:18184148]

Name: Dialeptic seizure
Definition: "A dialeptic seizure is a type of seizure characterised predominantly by reduced responsiveness or awareness and with subsequent at least partial amnesia of the event." [PMID:9738682]

Name: Typical absence seizure
Definition: "A typical absence seizure is a type of generalised non-motor (absence) seizure characterised by its sudden onset, interruption of ongoing activities, a blank stare, possibly a brief upward deviation of the eyes. Usually the patient will be unresponsive when spoken to. Duration is a few seconds to half a minute with very rapid recovery. Although not always available, an EEG would usually show 3 Hz generalized epileptiform discharges during the event." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276062, PMID:28276064, PMID:6790275]

Name: obsolete Absence seizures with special features
Absence seizure with eyelid myoclonia
Definition: "An absence with eyelid myoclonia seizure is a type of generalized non-motor (absence) seizure characterised by forced upward jerking of the eyelids during an absence seizure." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers, PMID:19469840, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276062, PMID:28276064]

Name: Myoclonic absence seizure
Definition: "Myoclonic absence seizure is a type of generalized non-motor (absence) seizure characterised by an interruption of ongoing activities, a blank stare and rhythmic three-per-second myoclonic movements, causing ratcheting abduction of the upper limbs leading to progressive arm elevation, and associated with 3 Hz generalized spike-wave discharges on the electroencephalogram. Duration is typically 10-60 s. Whilst impairment of consciousness may not be obvious the ILAE classified this seizure as a generalized non-motor seizure in 2017." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8486-0558, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276062, PMID:28276064, PMID:9637609]

Name: Atypical absence status epilepticus
Definition: "Atypical absence status epilepticus is a type of generalized non-convulsive status epilepticus without coma that is semiologically a prolonged atypical absence seizure." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: Early onset absence seizures
Definition: "Typical absence seizures starting before the age of 4 years." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8486-0558]

Name: Focal motor seizure
Definition: "A type of focal-onset seizure characterized by a motor sign as its initial semiological manifestation." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1735-8178, PMID:11580774, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276064]

Name: Focal autonomic seizure
Definition: "An autonomic seizure is a type of focal non-motor seizure characterized by alteration of autonomic nervous system function as the initial semiological feature." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276064]

Name: obsolete Focal autonomic seizures with altered responsiveness
obsolete Focal autonomic seizures without altered responsiveness
Focal sensory seizure
Definition: "A focal sensory seizure is a type seizure beginning with a subjective sensation." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1511-5893, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276062, PMID:28276064]

Name: Focal sensory seizure with auditory features
Definition: "A seizure characterized by elementary auditory phenomena including buzzing, ringing, drumming or single tones as its first clinical manifestation." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers, PMID:28276062, PMID:28276064]

Name: Focal autonomic seizure with epigastric sensation/nausea/vomiting/other gastrointestinal phenomena
Definition: "A type of focal autonomic seizure characterised by symptoms or signs pertaining to the gastrointestinal system as the initial semiological feature." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers, PMID:28276060]

Name: Focal sensory seizure with gustatory features
Definition: "A seizure characterized by taste phenomena including acidic, bitter, salty, sweet, or metallic tastes as its first clinical manifestation." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers, PMID:28276060]

Name: Focal sensory seizure with olfactory features
Definition: "Seizures characterized by olfactory phenomena as its first clinical manifestation." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: Focal sensory seizure with somatosensory features
Definition: "A seizure characterized by sensory phenomena including tingling, numbness, electric-shock like sensation, pain, sense of movement, or desire to move as its first clinical manifestation." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers, PMID:28276060]

Name: Focal sensory seizure with visual features
Definition: "A seizure characterized by elementary visual hallucinations such as flashing or flickering lights/colours, or other shapes, simple patterns, scotomata, or amaurosis as its first clinical manifestation." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: Focal myoclonic seizure
Definition: "A type of focal motor seizure characterized by sudden, brief (<100 ms) involuntary single or multiple contraction(s) of muscles(s) or muscle groups of variable topography (axial, proximal limb, distal). Myoclonus is less regularly repetitive and less sustained than is clonus." [PMID:11580774, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276064]

Name: Focal tonic seizure
Definition: "A type of focal motor seizure characterized by sustained increase in muscle contraction, lasting a few seconds to minutes." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers, PMID:11580774, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276064]

Name: Focal seizure with eyelid myoclonia
Definition: "Focal seizure with eyelid myoclonia, not eyelid myoclonias in the context of absence seizures." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8486-0558]

Name: Generalized clonic seizure
Definition: "Generalized clonic seizure is a type of generalized motor seizure characterised by sustained bilateral jerking, either symmetric or asymmetric, that is regularly repetitive and involves the same muscle groups." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276064]

Name: Generalized myoclonic-atonic seizure
Definition: "A generalized myoclonic-atonic seizure is a type of generalized motor seizure characterized by a myoclonic jerk followed by an atonic motor component." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276064]

Name: Simple febrile seizure
Definition: "A short generalized seizure, of a duration of <15 min, not recurring within 24 h, occurring during a febrile episode not caused by an acute disease of the nervous system intracranial infection or severe metabolic disturbance." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers, PMID:19125841, PMID:6779259, PMID:972656]

Name: Complex febrile seizure
Definition: "A febrile seizure that has any of the following features: focal semiology (or associated with post-ictal neurologic abnormalities beyond drowsiness, such as a Todd's paresis), prolonged seizure beyond 15 minutes, or recurring (occurring more than once) in a 24 hour period." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers, PMID:19125841, PMID:972656]

Name: Focal behavior arrest seizure
Definition: "A type of focal non-motor seizure characterized by an arrest or pause of activities, freezing, or immobilization as the predominant semiological feature throughout the seizure." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers, PMID:28276060]

Name: Focal hyperkinetic seizure
Definition: "A focal seizure characterized at onset by predominantly proximal limb or axial muscles producing irregular sequential ballistic movements, such as pedaling, pelvic thrusting, thrashing, rocking movements." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers, PMID:11580774, PMID:28276060, PMID:28276064]

Name: Focal motor seizure with version
Definition: "A type of focal motor seizure characterised by sustained, forced conjugate ocular, cephalic, and/or truncal rotation or lateral deviation from the midline as the initial semiological manifestation." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with constitutional variants
Definition: "An EEG with constitutional variants contains waves that are rare or unusual but not generally pathologic." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with 4-5/second background activity
Definition: "EEG background activity at 4-5/second." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: Alpha-EEG
Definition: "EEG dominated by diffuse alpha-waves (8-13Hz)." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: Beta-EEG
Definition: "EEG dominated by diffuse beta-waves (>13 Hz)." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: Partial beta-EEG
Definition: "EEG dominated by diffuse beta waves (>13 Hz) with occipitally localized alpha waves (8-13 Hz)." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: Low voltage EEG
Definition: "EEG with an amplitude less than 30 microvolts without observable occipital alpha rhythm (8-13 Hz)." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: Interictal epileptiform activity
Definition: "Epileptiform activity refers to distinctive EEG waves or complexes distinguished from background activity found in in a proportion of human subjects with epilepsy, but which can also be found in subjects without seizures. Interictal epileptiform activity refers to such activity that occurs in the absence of a clinical or subclinical seizure." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: EEG with hyperventilation-induced focal epileptiform discharges
Definition: "Focal epileptiform discharges induced by hyperventilation (overbreathing) in cerebral electrical activity recorded along the scalp by electroencephalography (EEG)." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with hyperventilation-induced generalized epileptiform discharges
Definition: "Generalized epileptiform discharges induced by hyperventilation (overbreathing) in cerebral electrical activity recorded along the scalp by electroencephalography (EEG)." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with focal epileptiform discharges
Definition: "EEG discharges recorded in particular areas of a localized (focal) abnormality in cerebral electrical activity recorded along the scalp by electroencephalography (EEG)." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: Focal epileptiform discharges with limited propagation to contralateral hemisphere
Definition: "Focal epileptiform discharges with spreading to contralateral hemisphere but without secondary generalization." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: Focal EEG discharges with propagation to ipsilateral hemisphere
Definition: "Focal epileptiform discharges with spreading to the hemisphere on the same side of the brain." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: Focal EEG discharges with secondary generalization
Definition: "Focal EEG discharges that secondarily spread to both hemispheres and can then be recorded over the entire scalp." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: Bilateral multifocal epileptiform discharges
Definition: "Epileptiform discharges being identified at multiple locations in both hemispheres." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: Uni- and bilateral multifocal epileptiform discharges
Definition: "Epileptiform discharges identified at multiple locations temporarily in both hemispheres and temporarily in one hemisphere." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: Unilateral multifocal epileptiform discharges
Definition: "Epileptiform discharges being identified at multiple locations in one hemisphere." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: Polymorphic focal epileptiform discharges
Definition: "Focal epileptiform discharges of different shapes and frequencies." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with focal spikes
Definition: "EEG with focal sharp transient waves of a duration less than 80 msec." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with series of focal spikes
Definition: "Focal spikes occurring for several seconds." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with focal sharp slow waves
Definition: "EEG with focal sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec followed by a slow wave." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with focal sharp waves
Definition: "EEG with focal sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with focal spike waves
Definition: "EEG with focal sharp transient waves of a duration less than 80 msec followed by a slow wave." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with generalized epileptiform discharges
Definition: "EEG discharges recorded on the entire scalp typically seen in persons with epilepsy." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with generalized sharp slow waves
Definition: "EEG with generalized sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec followed by a slow wave." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with generalized polymorphic epileptiform discharges
Definition: "Generalized epileptiform discharges of different shapes and frequencies." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with changes in voltage
Definition: "EEG with abnormal amplitude." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with diffuse acceleration
Definition: "EEG frequency is abnormally increased." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: EEG with abnormally slow frequencies
Definition: "EEG with abnormally slow frequencies." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with continuous slow activity
Definition: "EEG showing diffuse slowing without interruption." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with intermittent slow activity
Definition: "Non-continuous diffuse slowing of electroencephalographic patterns." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with generalized slow activity grade 1
Definition: "Slowing at frequencies between 7.5 and 8.5 Hz." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with generalized slow activity grade 2
Definition: "Generalized slowing of EEG activity at frequencies between 4-7 Hz." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with generalized slow activity grade 3
Definition: "Generalized slowing of EEG activity at frequencies between 0.5-3 Hz." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with generalized slow activity grade 4
Definition: "EEG without electrical activity." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with occipital slowing
Definition: "Slowing in occipital areas of the scalp EEG." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with photoparoxysmal response grade I
Definition: "Occurrence of epileptiform discharges in occipital regions during photic stimulation." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with photoparoxysmal response grade II
Definition: "Occurence of epileptiform discharges in occipital and central regions during photic stimulation." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with photoparoxysmal response grade III
Definition: "Occurrence of epileptiform discharges in occipital, central, temporal and parietal regions during photic stimulation." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with photoparoxysmal response grade IV
Definition: "Occurrence of generalized epileptiform discharges during photic stimulation." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: Hemihypsarrhythmia
Definition: "Hypsarrhythmia occurring in one hemisphere." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: Abnormal shape of the occiput
Definition: "An abnormal shape of occiput." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal shape of the frontal region
Definition: "An abnormal shape of the frontal part of the head." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short face
Definition: "Facial height (length) is more than two standard deviations below the mean (objective); or an apparent decrease in the height (length) of the face (subjective)." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Prominent forehead
Definition: "Forward prominence of the entire forehead, due to protrusion of the frontal bone." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Vertical forehead creases
Definition: "Vertical soft tissue creases in the midline of the forehead, often extending from the hairline to the brow, and seen with facial expression or when the face is at rest." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Depressed glabella
Definition: "Posterior positioning of the glabella, i.e., of the midline forehead between the supraorbital ridges." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125436]

Name: Metopic depression
Definition: "Linear vertical groove in the midline of the forehead, extending from hairline to glabella." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Ablepharon
Definition: "Absent eyelids." [PMID:19125427]

Name: Epiblepharon
Definition: "Redundant eyelid skin pressing the eyelashes against the cornea and/or conjunctiva." [PMID:19125427]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the eyelid
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the eyelid." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated circulating C-reactive protein concentration
Definition: "An abnormal elevation of the C-reactive protein level in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:28722873]

Name: Horizontal eyebrow
Definition: "An eyebrow that extends straight across the brow, without curve." [PMID:19125427]

Name: Broad eyebrow
Definition: "Regional increase in the width (height) of the eyebrow." [PMID:19125427]

Name: Laterally extended eyebrow
Definition: "An eyebrow that extends laterally beyond the orbital rim rather than turning gently downward at that location." [PMID:19125427]

Name: Prominent eyelashes
Definition: "Eyelashes that draw the attention of the viewer due to increased density and/or length and/or curl without meeting the criteria of trichomegaly." [PMID:19125427]

Name: Infra-orbital fold
Definition: "Elevated ridge(s) of skin starting well below the medial aspect of the lower lid that curves gradually upward toward and/or across the nasal bridge." [PMID:19125427]

Name: Antihelical shelf
Definition: "Antihelix protrusion directed more anteriorly than laterally, forming a shelf overlying the posterior concha." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Absent antihelix
Definition: "No discernible ridge between concha and triangular fossa and helix." []

Name: Additional crus of antihelix
Definition: "Supernumerary ridge or crus of the ear arising from the antihelix." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Angulated antihelix
Definition: "Antihelical ridge that forms an acute angle between the antitragus and its bifurcation (stem) instead of a gently curving arc." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Broad inferior crus of antihelix
Definition: "Increased width of the inferred cross-section of the inferior crus." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Prominent inferior crus of antihelix
Definition: "Increased protrusion of the inferior crus relative to the prominence of the antihelix stem." []

Name: Underdeveloped inferior crus of antihelix
Definition: "Decreased protrusion of the inferior crus relative to the prominence of the antihelix stem." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Prominent stem of antihelix
Definition: "Increased protrusion of the antihelical ridge, proximal to its bifurcation, relative to the prominence of the helix." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Serpiginous stem of antihelix
Definition: "Posterior curving of the antihelix from its origin at the antitragus, traveling initially almost perpendicular to the descending helix and obscuring some of the concha." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Underdeveloped stem of antihelix
Definition: "Decreased protrusion of the antihelical ridge, proximal to its bifurcation, relative to the prominence of a normal helix." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Abnormality of inferior crus of antihelix
Definition: "An abnormality of the inferior crus of the antihelix is the lower cartilaginous ridge arising at the bifurcation of the antihelix that ends beneath the fold of the ascending helix, and separates the concha from the triangular fossa." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152421]

Name: Abnormality of stem of antihelix
Definition: "An abnormality of the stem of the antihelix, which is the part below the bifurcation of the antihelix into the inferior and superior crura." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of superior crus of antihelix
Definition: "An abnormality of the superior crus of the antihelix is the upper cartilaginous ridge arising at the bifurcation of the antihelix that ends beneath the fold of the ascending helix, and separates the concha from the triangular fossa." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152421]

Name: Underdeveloped superior crus of antihelix
Definition: "Decreased protrusion of the superior crus relative to the prominence of a normal antihelix stem." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Prominent superior crus of antihelix
Definition: "Increased protrusion of the superior crus relative to the prominence of a normal antihelix stem." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Everted antitragus
Definition: "Positioning of the antitragus at an angle perpendicular to the plane of the ear (oriented away from the plane of the ear)." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Absent antitragus
Definition: "Absence of the anterosuperior prominence of the area between the bottom of the incisura and the inner margin of the antihelix." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Bifid antitragus
Definition: "Double rather than single peak of the antitragus." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Underdeveloped antitragus
Definition: "Reduction in the anterosuperior prominence of the area between the bottom of the incisura and the inner margin of the antihelix." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152421]

Name: Cryptotia
Definition: "Invagination of the superior part of the auricle under a fold of temporal skin." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Type I cryptotia
Definition: "A type of cryptotia associated with reduction in size of the antihelix and superior crus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Type II cryptotia
Definition: "A type of cryptotia associated with reduction in size of the antihelix and inferior crus that are affected." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent crus of helix
Definition: "Continuum between the tragus and ascending helix, without any evidence of a posterior extension (crus) towards the concha." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Crus of helix connected to antihelix
Definition: "Extension of the ridge of the crus helix across the ear and connection of the crus to the antihelix." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Serpiginous crus of helix
Definition: "Curving course of the crus of the helix, approaching or joining the antitragus." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Tragal bridge of crus of helix
Definition: "The anterior origin of the crus encompasses the superior margin of the tragus, the crus overrides the upper portion of the conchal cavum and ends at the antihelix." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Expanded terminal portion of crus of helix
Definition: "Widening, rather than tapering, of the crus at its posterior border near the antihelix." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Darwin notch of helix
Definition: "Small defect of the helical fold that lies at the junction of the superior and descending portions of the helix." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Darwin tubercle of helix
Definition: "Small expansion of the helical fold at the junction of the superior and descending portions of the helix." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Crimped helix
Definition: "Linear, circumferential indentation in the convexity of the outer surface of the helix." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Forward facing earlobe
Definition: "Positioning of the anterior surface of the ear lobe in a more coronal plane than the remainder of the ear." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19152421]

Name: Discontinuous ascending root of helix
Definition: "Interruption between the ascending helix and the crus helix, allowing the ascending helix to be attached directly to the mastoid." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Cleft earlobe
Definition: "Discontinuity in the convexity of the inferior margin of the lobe." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Microtia, first degree
Definition: "Presence of all the normal ear components and the median longitudinal length more than two standard deviations below the mean." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Microtia, third degree
Definition: "Presence of some auricular structures, but none of these structures conform to recognized ear components." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Absent tragus
Definition: "Lack of convexity or prominence of the contour of the ridge between the bottom of the incisura and the confluence of the ascending helix and crus helix." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Bifid tragus
Definition: "Increased height of the tragal ridge with a shallow indentation at the apex, giving the appearance of a double peak." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Duplicated tragus
Definition: "A complete or partial duplication of the tragus; expected to lie anterior to the normal tragus." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Prominent tragus
Definition: "Increase posterolateral protrusion of the tragus." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Underdeveloped tragus
Definition: "Decreased posterolateral protrusion of the tragus." [PMID:19152421]

Name: Anisocytosis
Definition: "Abnormally increased variability in the size of erythrocytes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Recurrent mycobacterial infections
Definition: "Increased susceptibility to mycobacterial infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of mycobacterial infection." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Recurrent mycobacterium avium complex infections
Definition: "Increased susceptibility to mycobacterial avium complex infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of mycobacterial infection." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the urinary system physiology
Intrapulmonary sequestration
Definition: "A type of pulmonary sequestration that occurs within the visceral pleura of normal lung tissue, usually without communication with the tracheobronchial tree." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of urine bicarbonate level
Definition: "An abnormal amount of hydrogencarbonate in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of urine calcium concentration
Definition: "An abnormality of calcium concentration in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of urine catecholamine level
Definition: "An abnormal amount of urinary catecholamine concentration." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal hindbrain morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the hindbrain, also known as the rhombencephalon." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal metencephalon morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the metencephalon. The metencephalon is the part of the hindbrain that consists of the pons and the cerebellum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short-segment aganglionic megacolon
Definition: "A type of aganglionic megacolon in which the aganglionic segment does not extend beyond the upper sigmoid." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:17965226]

Name: Long-segment aganglionic megacolon
Definition: "A type of aganglionic megacolon in which the aganglionic segment extends proximal to the sigmoid." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Total colonic aganglionosis
Definition: "A type of aganglionic megacolon in which the aganglionic segment comprises the entire colon." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: EEG with occipital sharp slow waves
Definition: "EEG with sharp slow waves in the occipital region. Sharp slow waves are focal sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec followed by a slow wave." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with parietal sharp slow waves
Definition: "EEG with sharp slow waves in the parietal region. Sharp slow waves are focal sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec followed by a slow wave." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with temporal sharp slow waves
Definition: "EEG with sharp slow waves in the temporal region. Sharp slow waves are focal sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec followed by a slow wave." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with frontal sharp slow waves
Definition: "EEG with sharp slow waves in the frontal region. Sharp slow waves are focal sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec followed by a slow wave." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with central sharp slow waves
Definition: "EEG with sharp slow waves in the central region. Sharp slow waves are focal sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec followed by a slow wave." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with occipital sharp waves
Definition: "EEG with sharp waves in the occipital region, i.e., sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with central sharp waves
Definition: "EEG with sharp waves in the central region, i.e., sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with frontal sharp waves
Definition: "EEG with sharp waves in the frontal region, i.e., sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with parietal sharp waves
Definition: "EEG with sharp waves in the parietal region, i.e., sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with temporal sharp waves
Definition: "EEG with sharp waves in the temporal region, i.e., sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: Abnormal digit morphology
Definition: "A morphological abnormality of a digit, i.e., of a finger or toe." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Prominent digit pad
Definition: "A soft tissue prominence of the ventral aspects of the fingertips or toe tips." [PMID:19125433]

Name: Partial absence of finger
Definition: "The absence of a phalangeal segment of a finger." [PMID:19125433]

Name: Broad fingertip
Definition: "Increased width of the distal segment of a finger." [PMID:19125433]

Name: Absent foot
Definition: "The total absence of the foot, with no bony elements distal to the tibia or fibula." [PMID:19125433]

Name: Long palm
Definition: "For children from birth to 16 years of age the length of the palm is more than the 97th centile; or, the length of the palm appears relatively long compared to the finger length or the limb length." [PMID:19125433]

Name: Convex contour of sole
Definition: "The contour of the foot in lateral profile has a convex shape." [PMID:19125433]

Name: Broad thumb
Definition: "Increased thumb width without increased dorso-ventral dimension." [PMID:19125433]

Name: Partial absence of toe
Definition: "The absence of a phalangeal segment of a toe or hallux." [PMID:19125433]

Name: Splayed toes
Definition: "Divergence of digits along the anteroposterior axis (in the plane of the sole)." [PMID:19125433]

Name: Slender toe
Definition: "Toes that are disproportionately narrow (reduced girth) for the hand/foot size or build of the individual." [PMID:19125433]

Name: Tapered toe
Definition: "The gradual reduction in girth of the toe from proximal to distal." [PMID:19125433]

Name: Bridged palmar crease
Definition: "A crease that connects the proximal and distal transverse palmar creases." [PMID:19125433]

Name: Sydney crease
Definition: "Extension of the proximal transverse crease (five finger crease) to the ulnar edge of the palm." [PMID:19125433]

Name: Fused nails
Definition: "A nail plate that has a longitudinal separation with partially separated nails, each with a separate lateral radius of curvature." [PMID:19125433]

Name: Narrow nail
Definition: "Decreased width of nail." [PMID:19125433]

Name: Abnormal long bone morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of size or shape of the long bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Unicoronal synostosis
Definition: "Synostosis affecting only one of the coronal sutures." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2972-5481]

Name: Left unicoronal synostosis
Definition: "Synostosis affecting only the left coronal suture." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2972-5481]

Name: Right unicoronal synostosis
Definition: "Unicoronal synostosis affecting only the right coronal suture." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2972-5481]

Name: Bicoronal synostosis
Definition: "Synostosis affecting the right and the left coronal suture." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2972-5481]

Name: Bilambdoid synostosis
Definition: "Premature synostosis of both lambdoid sutures." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2972-5481]

Name: Unilambdoid synostosis
Definition: "Premature synostosis of only one lambdoid suture." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2972-5481]

Name: Left unilambdoid synostosis
Definition: "Premature synostosis of only the left lambdoid suture." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2972-5481]

Name: Right unilambdoid synostosis
Definition: "Premature synostosis of only the right lambdoid suture." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2972-5481]

Name: Cleft of chin
Definition: "Incomplete fusion of the chin, resulting from a developmental defect and manifesting as a midline cleft or fissure of the chin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9602-2321]

Name: Multiple suture craniosynostosis
Definition: "Craniosynostosis involving at least 2 cranial sutures, where the exact pattern of sutures fused has not been precisely specified." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2972-5481]

Name: Pansynostosis
Definition: "Craniosynostosis of all calvarial sutures." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2972-5481]

Name: Anterior plagiocephaly
Definition: "Asymmetry of the anterior part of the skull." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2972-5481]

Name: Posterior plagiocephaly
Definition: "Asymmetry of the posterior part of the skull." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2972-5481, PMID:10876272]

Name: Abnormality of fontanelles
Definition: "An abnormality of the fontanelle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:12825844]

Name: Abnormality of cranial sutures
Definition: "Any anomaly of a cranial suture, that is one of the six membrane-covered openings in the incompletely ossified skull of the fetus or newborn infant." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Metopic synostosis
Definition: "Premature fusion of the metopic suture." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2972-5481]

Name: Hemifacial atrophy
Definition: "Unilateral atrophy of facial tissues, including muscles, bones and skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2972-5481]

Name: Hemifacial hypoplasia
Definition: "Unilateral underdevelopment of the facial tissues, including muscles and bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2972-5481]

Name: Asymmetric crying face
Definition: "Asymmetry observed in the face of a neonate or infant whose face appears symmetric at rest and asymmetric during crying as the mouth is pulled downward on one side while not moving on the other side." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2958-5076]

Name: Frontal hirsutism
Definition: "Excessive amount of hair growth on forehead." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9602-2321]

Name: Bitemporal forceps marks
Definition: "Bilateral temporal scarlike defects, which are said to resemble forceps marks." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9602-2321, PMID:1401310]

Name: Abnormality of mouth shape
Definition: "An abnormality of the outline, configuration, or contour of the mouth." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_jhurst]

Name: Abnormality of upper lip vermillion
Definition: "An abnormality of the vermilion border, the sharp demarcation between the lip (red colored) and the adjacent normal skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Incomplete cleft of the upper lip
Definition: "A subtle unilateral cleft of the upper lip, which may appear as a small indentation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9602-2321]

Name: Long upper lip
Definition: "Increased width of the upper lip." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_jhurst]

Name: Mild global developmental delay
Definition: "A mild delay in the achievement of motor or mental milestones in the domains of development of a child." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6410-0882]

Name: Moderate global developmental delay
Definition: "A moderate delay in the achievement of motor or mental milestones in the domains of development of a child." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6410-0882]

Name: Severe global developmental delay
Definition: "A severe delay in the achievement of motor or mental milestones in the domains of development of a child." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6410-0882]
