Definition: "Junctional ectopic tachycardia (JET) is a unique type of supraventricular arrhythmia defined by narrow QRS complex and atrioventricular (AV) dissociation or retrograde atrial conduction in a 1:1 pattern." [PMID:22826742]

Name: Atrioventricular reentrant tachycardia
Definition: "Accessory pathway-related atrioventricular reentrant tachycardia (AVRT) involves an abnormal electrical conduction of the accessory pathway. The accessory pathway connecting impulses between the atrium and the ventricle can be seen at any site in the AV groove." []

Name: Abnormality of the pulmonary veins
Definition: "An abnormality of the pulmonary veins." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Supracardiac total anomalous pulmonary venous connection
Definition: "Type 1 total anomalous pulmonary venous connection." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_dbrown]

Name: Cardiac total anomalous pulmonary venous connection
Definition: "Type 2 total anomalous pulmonary venous connection." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_dbrown]

Name: Infracardiac total anomalous pulmonary venous connection
Definition: "Type 3 total anomalous pulmonary venous connection." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_dbrown]

Name: Mixed total anomalous pulmonary venous connection
Definition: "Type 4 total anomalous pulmonary venous connection." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_dbrown]

Name: Congenital malformation of the right heart
Definition: "Defect or defects of the morphogenesis of the right heart identifiable at birth." []

Name: Uhl's anomaly
Definition: "Uhl anomaly of the right ventricle refers to the almost complete absence of right ventricular myocardium, normal tricuspid valve, and preserved septal and left ventricular myocardium." [PMID:10859296, PMID:16322929]

Name: Persistent fetal circulation
Definition: "Systemic desaturation of a liveborn baby resulting from persistent pulmonary hypertension with a patent ductus arteriosus and patent foramen ovale, such that the circulation in postnatal life follows the fetal course." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_dbrown]

Name: Peroneal muscle weakness
Definition: "Weakness of the peroneal muscles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elbow clonus
Definition: "Clonus at the elbow joint, i.e., an exaggerated phasic stretch reflex characterized by repetitive, rhythmic contractions at the elbow, generated by rapid passive stretch at the elbow joint." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of joint mobility
Definition: "An abnormality in the range and ease of motion of joints across their normal range." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal central sensory function
Definition: "An abnormality of sensation related to CNS function. Assuming the primary sensory modalities are intact and the patient is alert and cooperative, the presence of an abnormality of sensory function may indicate a lesion of a parietal cortex, the thalamocortical projections to the parietal cortex, or the spinal cord." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of circulating cortisol level
Definition: "An abnormality of the concentration of cortisol in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of adrenal morphology
Definition: "Any structural anomaly of the adrenal glands." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of adrenal physiology
Definition: "A functional abnormality of the adrenal glands." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Central adrenal insufficiency
Definition: "A form of adrenal insufficiency related to a lack of ACTH, which leads to a decrease in the production of cortisol by the adrenal glands. Aldosterone production is not usually affected." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Adrenocorticotropin deficient adrenal insufficiency
Definition: "Adrenal insufficiency secondary to a defect in ACTH production." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Primary hyperaldosteronism
Definition: "A form of hyperaldosteronism caused by a defect within the adrenal gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Corticotropin-releasing hormone deficient adrenal insufficiency
Definition: "Adrenal insufficiency secondary to a defect in corticotropin-releasing hormone production." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Corticotropin-releasing hormone receptor defect
Definition: "Adrenal insufficiency secondary to a defect in the corticotropin-releasing hormone receptor." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Dexamethasone-suppressible primary hyperaldosteronism
Definition: "A form of primary hyperaldosteronism in which the overproduction of aldosterone can be suppressed by the administration of dexamethasone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Glucocortocoid-insensitive primary hyperaldosteronism
Definition: "A form of primary hyperaldosteronism in which the overproduction of aldosterone cannot be suppressed by the administration of dexamethasone or similar glucocorticoids." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Secondary hyperaldosteronism
Definition: "A form of hyperaldosteronism caused by abnormally increased renin levels." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Ectopic adrenal gland
Definition: "Abnormal anatomical location of the adrenal gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Adrenal gland agenesis
Definition: "Absent development of the adrenal gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Secondary hypercortisolism
Definition: "Hypercortisolemia associated with a overproduction of ACTH (often from a tumor), leading secondarily to overproduction of cortisol." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Non-secretory adrenocortical adenoma
Definition: "An hormonally inactive adrenocortical adenoma, that is, an adenoma that does not secrete excessive amounts of adrenal hormones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Secretory adrenocortical adenoma
Definition: "An hormonally active adrenocortical adenoma, that is, an adenoma that secretes excessive amounts of adrenal hormones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Abnormality of the anterior pituitary
Definition: "An abnormality of the adenohypophysis, which is also known as the anterior lobe of the pituitary gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Adrenocorticotropic hormone deficiency
Definition: "A reduced ability to secrete adrenocorticotropic hormone (ACTH), a hormone that stimulates the adrenal cortex to secrete of glucocorticoids such as cortisol." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Adrenocorticotropic hormone excess
Definition: "Overproduction of adrenocorticotropic hormone (ACTH), which generally leads secondarily to overproduction of cortisol by the adrenal cortex." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Neoplasm of the anterior pituitary
Definition: "A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the adenohypophysis, which is also known as the anterior lobe of the pituitary gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Abnormal posterior pituitary morphogenesis
Definition: "An abnormality of the neurohypophysis, which is also known as the posterior lobe of the hypophysis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Neoplasm of the posterior pituitary
Definition: "The presence of a neoplasm (tumor) in the neurohypophysis, which is also known as the posterior lobe of the hypophysis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Posterior pituitary dysgenesis
Definition: "Abnormal development of the neurohypophysis during embryonic growth and development." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Pituicytoma
Definition: "A solid, low grade, spindle cell, glial neoplasm of adults that originates in the neurohypophysis or infundibulum. Clinical signs and symptoms include visual disturbance, headache and features of hypopituitarism. Pituicytomas are well-circumscribed, solid masses that can measure up to several centimeters. Histologically, they show a compact architecture consisting of elongate, bipolar spindle cells arranged in interlacing fascicles or assuming a storiform pattern." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547, PMID:17618441, PMID:19109577]

Name: Ectopic posterior pituitary
Definition: "An abnormal anatomical location of the posterior lobe of the hypophysis, also known as the neurohypophysis. The posterior pituitary is normally present in the dorsal portion of the sella turcica, but when ectopic is usually near the median eminence. This defect is likely to be due to abnormal migration during embryogenesis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Posterior pituitary agenesis
Definition: "Absence of the neurohypophysis owing to a developmental defect." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Posterior pituitary hypoplasia
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the neurohypophysis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Pituitary gonadotropic cell adenoma
Definition: "A type of pituitary adenoma that produces gonadotropins." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Pituitary growth hormone cell adenoma
Definition: "A type of pituitary adenoma that produces growth hormone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Pituitary null cell adenoma
Definition: "A type of pituitary adenoma that is of unknown cellular origin and that lacks immunocytochemical or fine structural markers. Null cell adenomas are not associated with hormone excess." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Pituitary thyrotropic cell adenoma
Definition: "A type of pituitary adenoma that produces thyroid stimulating hormone (TSH)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Pituitary carcinoma
Definition: "A pituitary tumor with subarachnoid, brain, or systemic metastasis. The diagnosis of a pituitary carcinoma requires evidence of metastatic disease, either outside the central nervous system (CNS) or as separate noncontiguous foci within the CNS." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547, NCIT:C4536, PMID:15741248]

Name: Pituitary spindle cell oncocytoma
Definition: "A spindled-to-epithelioid, oncocytic, nonendocrine neoplasm of the anterior hypophysis that manifests in adults and follows a benign clinical course. Pituitary spindle cell oncocytomas are firm, fibrous, and adherent to surrounding structures and are highly vascular." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547, PMID:21886889]

Name: Abnormality of the parathyroid morphology
Definition: "A structural abnormality of the parathyroid gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the parathyroid physiology
Definition: "A functional abnormality of the parathyroid gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Parathyroid dysgenesis
Definition: "Abnormal embryonic development of the parathyroid gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Ectopic parathyroid
Definition: "An abnormal anatomical location of the parathyroid gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Tertiary hyperparathyroidism
Definition: "A type of hyperparathyroidism that occurs following kidney transplantation, which is a treatment for secondary hyperparathyroidism. Although kidney transplantation leads to a normalization of serum calcium and parathyroid hormone in most patients. The state of persistent hypercalcemia and hyperparathyroidism is referred to as tertiary hyperparathyroidism." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Autoimmune hypoparathyroidism
Definition: "A type of hypoparathyroidism with circulating antiparathyroid or anti-calcium sensing receptor antibodies indicative of autoimmunity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547, PMID:19328421]

Name: Abnormal thyroid morphology
Definition: "A structural abnormality of the thyroid gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Uninodular goiter
Definition: "Enlargement of the thyroid gland related to a singular nodule in the thyroid gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Thyroid hemiagenesis
Definition: "Absence of a lobe of the thyroid gland related to a failure of its embryologic development." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Thyroid C cell hyperplasia
Definition: "An abnormal growth of parafollicular (C-cells) cells." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thyrotoxicosis with toxic single thyroid nodule
Central hypothyroidism
Definition: "A type of hypothyroidism due to an insufficient stimulation of an otherwise normal thyroid gland. Central hypothyroidism is caused by either pituitary (secondary hypothyroidism) or hypothalamic (tertiary hypothyroidism) defects." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547, PMID:18415684]

Name: Increased circulating free T3
Definition: "An elevated concentration of free 3,3',5-triiodo-L-thyronine in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Impaired sensitivity to thyroid stimulating hormone
Definition: "Reduced sensitivity of thyroid follicle cells to stimulation by biologically active thyroid-stimulating hormone (TSH)." [PMID:28648507]

Name: Activating thyroid-stimulating hormone receptor defect
Definition: "Gain-of-function thyroid-stimulating hormone receptor (TSHR) defect." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Inactivating thyroid-stimulating hormone receptor defect
Definition: "Loss-of-function thyroid-stimulating hormone receptor (TSHR) defect." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0538-4547]

Name: Neoplasm by histology
Definition: "Neoplasm categorized according to type of histological abnormality." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9113-2978]

Name: Neoplasm by anatomical site
Definition: "Neoplasm categorized according to the anatomical site of origin of the neoplasm." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9113-2978]

Name: Embryonal renal neoplasm
Definition: "The presence of an embryonal neoplasm of the kidney that primarily affects children." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9113-2978]

Name: Intralobar nephroblastomatosis
Definition: "Presence of persistent islands of renal blastema in the postnatal kidney, anywhere within a renal lobe (a portion of a kidney consisting of a renal pyramid and the renal cortex above it)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9113-2978]

Name: Perilobar nephroblastomatosis
Definition: "Abnormally persistent foci of embryonal immature blastema located in the superficial cortical region (perilobar)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9113-2978]

Name: Papillary renal cell carcinoma type 1
Definition: "A type of papillary renal cell carcinoma that is characterized by small cuboidal cells covering thin papillae with a single line of uniform nuclei and small nucleoli." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9113-2978, PMID:12429790]

Name: Renal oncocytoma
Definition: "A renal tumor originating from an oncocyte, which is an epithelial cell characterized by an excessive amount of mitochondria, resulting in an abundant acidophilic, granular cytoplasm." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9113-2978]

Name: Midface retrusion
Definition: "Posterior positions and/or vertical shortening of the infraorbital and perialar regions, or increased concavity of the face and/or reduced nasolabial angle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9602-2321, PMID:19125436]

Name: Enlargement of parotid gland
Definition: "Increased size of the parotid gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9602-2321]

Name: Hamartoma of tongue
Definition: "A benign (noncancerous) tumorlike malformation made up of an abnormal mixture of cells and tissues that originates in the tongue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:17667541]

Name: Bifid nose
Definition: "Visually assessable vertical indentation, cleft, or depression of the nasal bridge, ridge and tip." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Abnormal muscle physiology
Definition: "A functional abnormality of a skeletal muscle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal skeletal muscle morphology
Definition: "A structural abnormality of a skeletal muscle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Type 1 muscle fiber atrophy
Definition: "Atrophy (wasting) affecting primary type 1 muscle fibers. This feature in general can only be observed on muscle biopsy." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased patellar reflex
Definition: "Decreased intensity of the patellar reflex (also known as the knee jerk reflex)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Paradoxical myotonia
Definition: "A type of myotonia that worsens with repeated muscle contractions." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:7678441]

Name: Impaired two-point discrimination
Definition: "A reduced ability to distinguish tactile sensations at points that are very close to one another. This can be tested by using special calipers whose points can be set from 2mm to several centimeters apart." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Impaired touch localization
Definition: "A reduced ability to identify precisely the site of a touch. This test is usually carried out by asking a patient, whose eyes are closed or covered, to touch the same site with a fingertip." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Agraphesthesia
Definition: "Impaired ability to recognize letters or numbers drawn by an examiner's fingertip on the patient's skin (the patients eyes are closed or covered throughout this examination)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased cerebral lipofuscin
Definition: "Lipofuscin (age pigment) is a brown-yellow, electron-dense, autofluorescent material that accumulates progressively over time in lysosomes of postmitotic cells, such as neurons and cardiac myocytes. This term pertains if there is an increase in the accumulation of lipofuscin (also known as autofluorescent lipoprotein) more than expected for the age of the patient." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:9531959]

Name: Increased urinary hypoxanthine level
Definition: "The concentration of hypoxanthine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cephalocele
Definition: "A congenital defect in the skull, whereby there is a protrusion of part of the cranial contents through a congenital defect in the cranium, usually covered with skin or mucous membrane. The term encephalocele refers to a subclass of these lesions in which brain tissue protrudes through the defect." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:24931720]

Name: Parietal encephalocele
Definition: "An encephalocele located between bregma and lambda." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2972-5481, PMID:2773494]

Name: Basal encephalocele
Definition: "Basal encephalocele is an encephalocele that occurs along the cribriform plate or through the sphenoid bone. The mass may appear in the nasal cavity, nasopharynx, epipharynx, sphenoid sinus, posterior orbit, or pterygopalatine fossa. The important distinction from other types is that no external tumor is visible except in those rare instances of herniations so large that they protrude through the mouth or nares." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:4966739]

Name: Submucous cleft soft palate
Definition: "A cleft of the muscular (soft) portion of the palate that is covered by mucous membrane. Soft-palate submucous clefts are characterized by a midline deficiency or lack of muscle tissue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Membranous choanal atresia
Definition: "Absence of the normal opening of the choana (the posterior nasal aperture) as a result of an obstructing choanal membrane that may be thin and strandlike or thick and pluglike." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_jhurst]

Name: Abnormal facial skeleton morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of one or more of the set of bones that make up the facial skeleton." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2972-5481]

Name: Broad chin
Definition: "Increased width of the midpoint of the mandible (mental protuberance) and overlying soft tissue." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Chin with horizontal crease
Definition: "Horizontal crease or fold situated below the vermilion border of the lower lip and above the fatty pad of the chin, with the face at rest." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Chin with H-shaped crease
Definition: "H-shaped crease in the fat pad of the chin." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Tented philtrum
Definition: "Prominence of a triangular soft tissue area of the philtrum with the apex to the columella." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Philtrum with midline raphe
Definition: "Narrow ridge in the midline of the philtral groove." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Malaligned philtral ridges
Definition: "Absence of the usual parallel position of philtral ridges." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Midline sinus of philtrum
Definition: "Pit in the midline of the philtral groove." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Narrow philtrum
Definition: "Distance between the philtral ridges, measured just above the vermilion border, more than 2 standard deviations below the mean. Alternatively, an apparently decreased distance between the ridges of the philtrum." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Abnormal oral mucosa morphology
Definition: "Abnormality of the oral mucosa." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Deviated nasal tip
Definition: "Nasal tip positioned to one side of the midline." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Narrow nasal tip
Definition: "Decrease in width of the nasal tip." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Overhanging nasal tip
Definition: "Positioning of the nasal tip inferior to the nasal base." [PMID:19152422]

Name: Moyamoya phenomenon
Definition: "A noninflammatory, progressive occlusion of the intracranial carotid arteries owing to the formation of netlike collateral arteries arising from the circle of Willis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent scaphoid
Definition: "Congenital absence of the scaphoid.." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_jcampbell]

Name: Delayed talus ossification
Definition: "Delayed maturation and calcification of the talus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Partial IgA deficiency
Definition: "Detectable but decreased IgA levels that are more than 2 standard deviations below normal age-adjusted means." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sclerodactyly
Definition: "Localized thickening and tightness of the skin of the fingers or toes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal T cell count
Definition: "A deviation from the normal count of T cells." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of T cell physiology
Definition: "A functional anomaly of T cells." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ventricular flutter
Definition: "A potentially lethal cardiac arrhythmia characterized by an extremely rapid, hemodynamically unstable ventricular tachycardia (150-300 beats/min) with a large oscillating sine-wave appearance." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal skeletal morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the form, structure, or size of the skeletal system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal musculoskeletal physiology
Definition: "An abnormality of the function of the skeletal system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal appendicular skeleton morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the appendicular skeletal system, consisting of the of the limbs, shoulder and pelvic girdles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short second metatarsal
Definition: "Short (hypoplastic) second metatarsal bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Osteoblastoma
Definition: "A benign, painful, tumor of bone characterized by the formation of osteoid tissue, primitive bone and calcified tissue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Giant cell tumor of bone
Definition: "A bone tumor composed of cellular spindle-cell stroma containing scattered multinucleated giant cells resembling osteoclasts." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abdominal colic
Definition: "A type of abdominal pain that comes and goes in waves, most often starting and ending suddenly and being of severe intensity." []

Name: Abnormal bone ossification
Definition: "Any anomaly in the formation of bone or of a bony substance, or the conversion of fibrous tissue or of cartilage into bone or a bony substance." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:18157903]

Name: Parotitis
Definition: "Inflammation of the parotid gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hemopericardium
Definition: "Accumulation of blood within the pericardial sac." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:10882282]

Name: Chylopericardium
Definition: "Accumulation of chyle (the whitish fluid taken up by the lacteals in the intestine, consisting of an emulsion of lymph and triglyceride fat thatpasses into the veins by the thoracic duct) in the pericardium. Chylopericardium is generally caused by obstruction of or trauma to the thoracic duct." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Serous pericardial effusion
Definition: "Accumulation of serous fluid (pale yellow and transparent fluid) in the pericardial sac." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hemoperitoneum
Definition: "Accumulation of blood in the peritoneal cavity owing to internal hemorrhage." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pharyngeal edema
Definition: "Abnormal accumulation of fluid leading to swelling of the pharynx." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pica
Definition: "An appetite for and the persistent ingestion of non-food substances such as clay. In order to diagnose pica, this behavior must have persisted over a period of at least one month." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Plasmacytoma
Definition: "A discrete mass of neoplastic monoclonal plasma cells either in the bone marrow or in an extramedullary location." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Reduced factor IX activity
Definition: "Decreased activity of coagulation factor IX. Factor IX, which itself is activated by factor Xa or factor VIIa to form factor IXa, activates factor X into factor Xa." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Punctate keratitis
Definition: "A type of keratitis characterized by inflammation in pinpoint areas of the corneal epithelium." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Metaphyseal dappling
Definition: "The presence of spots or rounded patches of abnormally increased density of metaphyseal bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bilateral trilobed lung
Definition: "Both lungs have three lobes. Normally, the left lung has two lobes, whereas the right lung has three lobes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal bone collagen fibril morphology
Definition: "Any structural anomaly of the connective tissue bundles in the extracellular matrix of bone tissue that are composed of collagen, and play a role in tissue strength and elasticity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, MP:0011642]

Name: Abnormal sternal ossification
Definition: "Any anomaly in the formation of the bony substance of the sternum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated plasma pyrophosphate
Definition: "An abnormally increased diphosphate(4-) concentration in the blood. Diphosphate(4-), as ester with two phosphate groups, is also known as pyrophosphate." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal iliac wing morphology
Definition: "An anomaly of the ilium ala. This is the large expanded portion of the ilum which bounds the greater pelvis laterally." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sciatica
Definition: "Pain in the lower back and hip radiating in the distribution of the sciatic nerve." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:17872935]

Name: Abnormal platelet function
Definition: "Any anomaly in the function of thrombocytes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Impaired arachidonic acid-induced platelet aggregation
Definition: "Abnormal response to arachidonic acid as manifested by reduced or lacking aggregation of platelets upon addition of arachidonic acid." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7744-1790]

Name: Impaired ristocetin-induced platelet aggregation
Definition: "Abnormal response to ristocetin as manifested by reduced or lacking aggregation of platelets upon addition of ristocetin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7744-1790]

Name: Impaired thrombin-induced platelet aggregation
Definition: "Abnormal response to thrombin or thrombin mimetics as manifested by reduced or lacking aggregation of platelets upon addition of thrombin (or thrombin mimetics)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7744-1790]

Name: Abnormal platelet count
Definition: "Abnormal number of platelets per volume of blood. In a healthy adult, a normal platelet count is between 150,000 and 450,000 per microliter of blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4381-2442]

Name: Heparin-induced thrombocytopenia
Definition: "Low platelet count following administration of unfractionated or (less commonly) low-molecular weight heparin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16928996]

Name: Abnormal platelet morphology
Definition: "An anomaly in platelet form, ultrastructure, or intracellular organelles." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4381-2442]

Name: Abnormal platelet volume
Definition: "Anomalous size of platelets. Most normal sized platelets are 1.5 to 3 micrometers in diameter. Large platelets are 4 to 7 micrometers. Giant platelets are larger than 7 micrometers and usually 10 to 20 micrometers." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased mean platelet volume
Definition: "Average platelet volume above the upper limit of the normal reference interval." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7744-1790]

Name: Abnormal platelet membrane protein expression
Definition: "Presence of reduced amount of a membrane protein on the cell membrane of platelets. This feature is typically measured by flow cytometry." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7744-1790]

Name: Decreased platelet glycoprotein Ib-IX-V
Definition: "Decreased cell membrane concentration of the glycoprotein complex Ib-IX-V." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7744-1790, PMID:10605725]

Name: Acute disseminated intravascular coagulation
Definition: "An acute form of disseminated intravascular coagulation. Acute DIC can occur following sudden exposure of blood to procoagulants, with the compensatory hemostatic mechanisms becoming overwhelmed." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased platelet glycoprotein VI
Definition: "Decreased cell membrane concentration of glycoprotein VI." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7744-1790]

Name: Decreased platelet P2Y12 receptor
Definition: "Decreased cell membrane concentration of P2Y12 receptor." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7744-1790, PMID:14755328]

Name: Abnormal platelet granules
Definition: "An anomaly of alpha or dense granules or platelet lysosomes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7744-1790, PMID:18041654]

Name: Abnormal umbilical stump bleeding
Definition: "Abnormal bleeding of the umbilical stump following separation of the cord at approximately 7-10 days after birth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2945-4463]

Name: Hemorrhage of the eye
Definition: "Bleeding from vessels of the various tissues of the eye." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2945-4463]

Name: Hyphema
Definition: "Bleeding in the anterior chamber of the eye." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Choroid hemorrhage
Definition: "Hemorrhage from the vessels of the choroid." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bleeding requiring red cell transfusion
Definition: "Bleeding sufficiently severe as to require red cell transfusion (WHO Grade 3 or 4)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2945-4463]

Name: Bleeding with minor or no trauma
Definition: "Significant bleeding or hemorrhage without significant precipitating factor." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4381-2442]

Name: Prolonged bleeding following procedure
Definition: "Prolonged or protracted bleeding following an invasive procedure or intervention." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2945-4463]

Name: Post-partum hemorrhage
Definition: "Significant maternal haemorrhage/blood loss following deilvery of a child." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2945-4463]

Name: Low levels of vitamin K
Definition: "A reduced concentration of vitamin K." []

Name: Abnormal leukocyte count
Definition: "Number of leukocytes per volume of blood beyond normal limits." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Impaired thromboxane A2 agonist-induced platelet aggregation
Definition: "Abnormal response to thromboxane as manifested by reduced or lacking aggregation of platelets upon addition of thromboxane A2 receptor agonists." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7744-1790]

Name: Anemia due to reduced life span of red cells
Definition: "A type of anemia related to a reduction in the average life span of red blood cells in the peripheral circulation, which is normally around 120 days." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2945-4463]

Name: Subconjunctival hemorrhage
Definition: "Bleeding beneath the mucous membrane that lines the inner surface of the eyelid." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2945-4463]

Name: Neutrophilia
Definition: "Increased number of neutrophils circulating in blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2945-4463]

Name: Abnormality of circulating fibrinogen
Definition: "An abnormality of the level of activity of circulating fibrinogen." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2945-4463]

Name: Hyperfibrinogenemia
Definition: "Increased concentration of fibrinogen in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2945-4463]

Name: Hypofibrinogenemia
Definition: "Decreased concentration of fibrinogen in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Dysfibrinogenemia
Definition: "Qualitatively abnormal fibrinogen." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2945-4463]

Name: Abnormal hemoglobin
Definition: "Anomaly in the level or the function of hemoglobin, the oxygen-carrying protein of erythrocytes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: HbH hemoglobin
Definition: "Hemoglobin H (HbH) contains four beta-globin chains. It is normally not present at all in blood, but may make up about 1-40 percent of all hemoglobin in HbH disease, a subform of alpha thalassemia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:21345100]

Name: Persistence of hemoglobin F
Definition: "Hemoglobin F (HbF) contains two globin alpha chains and two globin gamma chains. It is the main form of hemoglobin in the fetus during the last seven months of intrauterine development and in the half year of postnatal life. In adults it normally makes up less than one percent of all hemoglobin. This term refers to an increase in HbF above this limit. In beta thalassemia major, it may represent over 90 percent of all hemoglobin, and in beta thalassemia minor it may make up between 0.5 to 4 percent." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Reduced hemoglobin A
Definition: "Hemoglobin A (HbA) contains two globin alpha chains and two globin beta chains. HbA is normally the main adult hemoglobin, representing about 96-98 percent of all hemoglobin. This term represents a decreased in the proportion of HbA below this limit, and can be seen in various forms of thalassemia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Reduced beta/alpha synthesis ratio
Definition: "A reduction in the ratio of production of beta globin to that of alpha globin. This is the major abnormality in the various forms of beta thalassemia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:1060068]

Name: Reduced alpha/beta synthesis ratio
Definition: "A reduction in the ratio of production of alpha globin to that of beta globin. This is the major abnormality in the various forms of alpha thalassemia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Unilateral radial aplasia
Definition: "Missing radius bone on one side only associated with congenital failure of development." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Flattened metacarpal heads
Definition: "Abnormally flat shape of the heads of the metacarpal bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Shortening of all phalanges of fingers
Definition: "Abnormal reduction in length affecting all phalanges." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal metacarpophalangeal joint morphology
Definition: "An anomaly of a metacarpophalangeal joint." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the glenoid fossa
Definition: "An anomaly of the glenoid fossa, also known as the glenoid cavity, which is the articular surface of the scapula that articulates with the head of the humerus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lumbar hypertrichosis
Definition: "Excessive, increased hair growth located in the lumbar region." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Thoracic hypertrichosis
Definition: "Excessive, increased hair growth located in the thoracic region." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cardiovascular calcification
Definition: "Abnormal calcification in the cardiovascular system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Toe extensor amyotrophy
Definition: "Atrophy of the extensor digitorum longus muscles, which mediate extension of the toes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short 5th toe
Definition: "Underdevelopment (hypoplasia) of the fifth toe." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Clinodactyly of the 4th toe
Definition: "Bending or curvature of a fourth toe in the tibial direction (i.e., towards the big toe)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pleural empyema
Definition: "Accumulation of pus in the pleural cavity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Transudative pleural effusion
Definition: "A type of pleural effusion with a transudate (extravascular fluid with low protein content and a low specific gravity). Pleural effusions can be classified as transudates or exudates based on Light's criteria, which classify an effusion as exudate if one or more of the following are present: (1) the ratio of pleural fluid protein to serum protein is greater than 0.5, (2) the ratio of pleural fluid lactate dehydrogenase (LDH) to serum LDH is greater than 0.6, or (3) the pleural fluid LDH level is greater than two thirds of the upper limit of normal for serum LDH." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_tkuijpers, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16623208]

Name: Exudative pleural effusion
Definition: "A type of pleural effusion with a exudate (extravascular fluid that has exuded out of a tissue or its capillaries due to injury or inflammation). Pleural effusions can be classified as transudates or exudates based on Light's criteria, which classify an effusion as exudate if one or more of the following are present: (1) the ratio of pleural fluid protein to serum protein is greater than 0.5, (2) the ratio of pleural fluid lactate dehydrogenase (LDH) to serum LDH is greater than 0.6, or (3) the pleural fluid LDH level is greater than two thirds of the upper limit of normal for serum LDH." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_tkuijpers, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16623208]

Name: Abnormal activity of mitochondrial respiratory chain
Definition: "An increased or decreased activity of the mitochondrial respiratory chain." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased activity of mitochondrial complex I
Definition: "A reduction in the activity of the mitochondrial respiratory chain complex I, which is part of the electron transport chain in mitochondria." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased activity of mitochondrial complex III
Definition: "A reduction in the activity of the mitochondrial respiratory chain complex III, which is part of the electron transport chain in mitochondria." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased activity of mitochondrial ATP synthase complex
Definition: "A reduction in the activity of the mitochondrial proton-transporting ATP synthase complex, which makes ATP via oxidative phosphorylation, and is sometimes described as Complex V of the electron transport chain." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Proximal placement of hallux
Definition: "Proximal mislocalization of the big toe from its normal position." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short digit
Definition: "One or more digit that appears disproportionately short compared to the hand/foot, whereby either the entire digit or a specific phalanx is shortened." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Short proximal phalanx of toe
Definition: "Developmental hypoplasia (shortening) of proximal phalanx of toe." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypersegmentation of proximal phalanx of third finger
Definition: "Presence of an additional phalanx-like bone, producing an extra, wedge-shaped bone at the base of the proximal phalanx of the third finger." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal cerebellar peduncle morphology
Definition: "An anomaly of the cerebellar peduncles. The superior, middle, and inferior cerebellar peduncles emerge from the cerebellum. The superior cerebellar penduncles connect the cerebellum to the midbrain, the middle cerebellar peduncles connect the cerebellum to the pons, and the inferior cerebellar peduncle connects the medulla spinalis and medulla oblongata with the cerebellum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal superior cerebellar peduncle morphology
Definition: "An anomaly of the superior cerebellar peduncle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elongated superior cerebellar peduncle
Definition: "Increased length of the superior cerebellar peduncle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Dilatation of mesenteric artery
Definition: "Abnormal outpouching or sac-like dilatation in the wall of the inferior mesenteric artery or superior mesenteric artery ." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased urinary urate
Definition: "Decreased concentration of urate in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased plasma total carnitine
Definition: "A decreased concentration of total carnitine in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplastic fifth toenail
Definition: "Underdeveloped nails of the fifth toes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: 3-4 finger cutaneous syndactyly
Definition: "A soft tissue continuity in the A/P axis between fingers 3 and 4." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anterior wedging of T12
Definition: "An abnormality of the shape of the thoracic vertebra T12 such that it is wedge-shaped (narrow towards the front)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anterior wedging of L2
Definition: "An abnormality of the shape of the lumbar vertebra L2 such that it is wedge-shaped (narrow towards the front)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased urinary sulfite level
Definition: "The concentration of SO3(2-), i.e., sulfite, in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased urinary thiosulfate
Definition: "Increased concentration of thiosulfate(2-) in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Small vessel vasculitis
Definition: "A type of vasculitis (inflammation of blood vessel walls) that affects blood vessels that are smaller than arteries, i.e., arterioles, venules, and capilllaries." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:9366584]

Name: Bronchiolitis obliterans organizing pneumonia
Definition: "Bronchiolitis obliterans organizing pneumonia (BOOP) is and interstitial lung abnormalitiy characterized histopathologically by plugs of granulation tissue lying within small airways, alveolar ducts, and alveoli and by chronic inflammatory cell infiltration in alveolar walls. Patients with BOOP generally present with subacute illness, including shortness of breath, fever, malaise, and weight loss." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_tkuijpers, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20858818]

Name: Bronchiolitis obliterans
Definition: "Inflammation and fibrosis of the bronchioles leading to partial or complete obstruction of these airways." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Respiratory tract infection
Definition: "An infection of the upper or lower respiratory tract." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Recurrent acute respiratory tract infection
Definition: "A history of repeated acute infections of the upper or lower respiratory tract." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_tkuijpers]

Name: Acute infectious pneumonia
Definition: "Acute inflammation of the lung due to an infection." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_tkuijpers]

Name: Bronchiolitis
Definition: "Inflammation of the bronchioles." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_tkuijpers]

Name: Aspiration pneumonia
Definition: "Pneumonia due to the aspiration (breathing in) of food, liquid, or gastric contents into the upper respiratory tract." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Acute aspiration pneumonia
Definition: "An acute episode of pneumonia due to the aspiration (breathing in) of food, liquid, or gastric contents into the upper respiratory tract." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pulmonary lymphoma
Definition: "Lung parenchymal involvement with lymphoma." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:DDD_tkuijpers]

Name: Nodular regenerative hyperplasia of liver
Definition: "Diffuse benign transformation of the hepatic parenchyma into small regenerative nodules with minimal or no fibrosis." [PMID:21472097]

Name: Hepatic granulomatosis
Definition: "The presence of multiple granulomas in the liver as based on pathological examination. Granulomas are small 0.5 to 2 mm collections of modified macrophages called epithelioid cells usually surrounded by lymphocytes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Intestinal lymphoid nodular hyperplasia
Definition: "A lymphoproliferative abnormality of the intestine characterized by numerous visible mucosal nodules measuring up to, and rarely exceeding, 0.5 cm in diameter Histologically, hyperplastic lymphoid follicles with large germinal centres are seen in the lamina propria and superficial submucosa. There is enlargement of the mucosal B cell follicles caused by hyperplasia of the follicle centres; surrounded by a normal appearing mantle zone. Disease may involve the stomach, the entire small intestine, and the large intestine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:21481240]

Name: Abnormal pectoral muscle morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the pectoral muscle, comprising the pectoralis major, a thick, fan-shaped muscle of the anterior chest and the pectoralis minor, a thin, triangular muscle situated underneath the pectoralis major." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Retinal perforation
Definition: "A small hole through the whole thickness of the retina." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Unilateral hypoplasia of pectoralis major muscle
Definition: "Hypoplasia (underdevelopment) of the pectoralis minor on only one side of the chest." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Substantia nigra gliosis
Definition: "Focal proliferation of glial cells in the substantia nigra." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Non-obstructive azoospermia
Definition: "Absence of any measurable level of sperm in his semen, resulting from a defect in the production of spermatozoa in the testes. This can be differentiated from obstructive azoospermia on the basis of testicular biopsy." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20514278]

Name: Obstructive azoospermia
Definition: "Absence of any measurable level of sperm in his semen, resulting from post-testicular obstruction or retrograde ejaculation. This can be differentiated from obstructive azoospermia on the basis of testicular biopsy." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20514278]

Name: Pretesticular azoospermia
Definition: "Absence of any measurable level of sperm in his semen, due to a hypothalamic or pituitary abnormality diagnosed with hypo-gonadotropic-hypogonadism. The diagnosis is made on the basis of low LH and FSH levels and low or normal testosterone levels." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20514278]

Name: Intermittent painful muscle spasms
Definition: "History of repeated intermittent involuntary muscle contractions that were painful." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating citrulline concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of citrulline in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated plasma citrulline
Definition: "An increased concentration of citrulline in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased circulating copper concentration
Definition: "A reduced concentration of copper in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Feeding difficulties
Definition: "Impaired ability to eat related to problems gathering food and getting ready to suck, chew, or swallow it." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6647-5493]

Name: Elevated circulating luteinizing hormone level
Definition: "An elevated concentration of luteinizing hormone in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cerebral amyloid angiopathy
Definition: "Amyloid deposition in the walls of leptomeningeal and cortical arteries, arterioles, and less often capillaries and veins of the central nervous system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:21519520]

Name: Dermatographic urticaria
Definition: "An exaggerated whealing tendency when the skin is stroked, that is, formation of red, itchy bumps and lines on the skin as a result of pressure on the skin (for instance, stroking the skin with a pen or tongue depressor)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoglycorrhachia
Definition: "Abnormally low glucose concentration in the cerebrospinal fluid." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Paroxysmal lethargy
Definition: "Repeated episodes of sudden-onset and transient lethargy." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Myelofibrosis
Definition: "Replacement of bone marrow by fibrous tissue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aminoglycoside-induced hearing loss
Definition: "Partial or complete loss of hearing following ingestion of aminoglycoside antibiotics." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:2669624]

Name: Elevated urinary catecholamine level
Definition: "The concentration of a catecholamine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated urinary homovanillic acid
Definition: "An increased concentration of homovanillic acid in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:27830764]

Name: Elevated urinary vanillylmandelic acid
Definition: "An increased concentration of vanillylmandelic acid in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated urinary dopamine level
Definition: "The concentration of dopamine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cholesterol gallstones
Definition: "Gallstones composed primarily of cholesterol, usually about 2-3 cm in length with an oval form and a yellow or green/brown color." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:12950109, PMID:16844493]

Name: Pigment gallstones
Definition: "Gallstones composed primarily of bilirubin and calcium salts (calcium bilirubinate) with a low cholesterol concentration." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:12950109]

Name: Black pigment gallstones
Definition: "A type of pigment gallstone that is hard and black, containing calcium carbonate and calcium phosphates." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:12950109]

Name: Brown pigment gallstones
Definition: "A type of pigment gallstone that is brown, containing calcium fatty acids. These stones are softer than black pigment gallstones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:12950109]

Name: Atretic gallbladder
Definition: "Failure of formation of the lumen of the gallbladder, often associated with gallbladder hypoplasia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Acholic stools
Definition: "Clay colored stools lacking bile pigment." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ectopic ossification
Definition: "Formation of abnormal, extraskeletal bony tissue, i.e., the presence of bone in soft tissue where bone normally does not exist." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ectopic ossification in muscle tissue
Definition: "Formation of abnormal bony tissue within muscle tissue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ectopic ossification in tendon tissue
Definition: "Formation of abnormal bony tissue within tendon tissue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ectopic ossification in ligament tissue
Definition: "Formation of abnormal bony tissue within ligament tissue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of neutrophil physiology
Definition: "A functional abnormality of neutrophils." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal neutrophil count
Definition: "A deviation from the normal range of neutrophil cell counts in the circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of neutrophil morphology
Definition: "An abnormal form or size of neutrophils." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Impaired neutrophil bactericidal activity
Definition: "A reduction in the ability of neutrophils to kill bacteria." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal atrial septum morphology
Definition: "An abnormality of the interatrial septum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Atrial septal dilatation
Definition: "A bulging of the interatrial septum towards one side. In adults, atrial septal aneurysm can be defined as a protrusion of the aneurysm of >10 mm beyond the plane of the atrial septum as measured by transesophageal echocardiography." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:7758185]

Name: Elevated coagulation factor V activity
Definition: "Increased activity of coagulation factor V, Factor V, which is activated to factor Va by means of minute amounts of thrombin (and inactivated by larger amounts of thrombin). Activated factor V (fVa) is a cofactor in the formation of the prothrombinase complex." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Postprandial hyperlactemia
Definition: "Abnormally increased level of blood lactate following a meal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Postprandial hyperglycemia
Definition: "An increased concentration of glucose in the blood following a meal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Paranoia
Definition: "A persecutory delusion of supposed hostility of others." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: EEG with generalized spikes
Definition: "EEG with generalized sharp transient waves of a duration less than 80 msec." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with generalized polyspikes
Definition: "EEG with repetitive generalized sharp transient waves of a duration less than 80 msec." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: Experiential epileptic aura
Definition: "Affective, mnemonic or composite perceptual auras with subjective qualities similar to those experienced in life but are recognized by the subject as occurring outside of actual context." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Affective epileptic aura
Definition: "Affective auras with subjective qualities similar to those experienced in life but are recognized by the subject as occurring outside of actual context." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Focal cognitive seizure with deja vu/jamais vu
Definition: "A focal cognitive seizure characterized by memory phenomena such as feelings of familiarity (deja vu) and unfamiliarity (jamais vu) as the initial semiological manifestation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:28276060]

Name: Deja vu aura
Definition: "A subjective feeling that an experience which is occurring for the first time has been experienced before." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Jamais vu aura
Definition: "A subjective feeling that an experience which has occurred before is being experienced for the first time." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Focal cognitive seizure with hallucination
Definition: "A focal cognitive seizure characterized by hallucination as the initial semiological manifestation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:28276060]

Name: Focal cognitive seizure with illusion
Definition: "A focal cognitive seizure characterized by an alteration of actual perception involving visual, auditory, somatosensory, olfactory, and/or gustatory phenomena as the initial semiological manifestation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:28276060]

Name: EEG with central focal spike waves
Definition: "EEG with focal sharp transient waves in the central region, i.e., focal sharp waves of a duration less than 80 msec followed by a slow wave." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with frontal focal spike waves
Definition: "EEG with focal sharp transient waves in the frontal region, i.e., focal sharp waves of a duration less than 80 msec followed by a slow wave." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with occipital focal spike waves
Definition: "EEG with focal sharp transient waves in the occipital region, i.e., focal sharp waves of a duration less than 80 msec followed by a slow wave." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with parietal focal spike waves
Definition: "EEG with focal sharp transient waves in the parietal region, i.e., focal sharp waves of a duration less than 80 msec followed by a slow wave." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with temporal focal spike waves
Definition: "EEG with focal sharp transient waves in the temporal region, i.e., focal sharp waves of a duration less than 80 msec followed by a slow wave." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with central focal spikes
Definition: "EEG with focal sharp transient waves of a duration less than 80 msec in the central region." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with frontal focal spikes
Definition: "EEG with focal sharp transient waves of a duration less than 80 msec in the frontal region." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with occipital focal spikes
Definition: "EEG with focal sharp transient waves of a duration less than 80 msec in the occipital region." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with parietal focal spikes
Definition: "EEG with focal sharp transient waves of a duration less than 80 msec in the parietal region." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: EEG with temporal focal spikes
Definition: "EEG with focal sharp transient waves of a duration less than 80 msec in the temporal region." [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR:jalbers]

Name: Lens luxation
Definition: "Complete dislocation of the lens of the eye." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Right aortic arch
Definition: "Aorta descends on right instead of on the left." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Persistent patent ductus venosus
Definition: "Persistence of blood flow through the ductus venosus for longer than the normal time after birth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16449256]

Name: Congenital portosystemic venous shunt
Definition: "A congenital defect of the vasculature such that there is a shunt (by-pass) of blood directly from the portal vein to the vena cava (i.e., the blood from the portal vein is not filtered through the liver)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Galactosuria
Definition: "Elevated concentration of galactose in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypergalactosemia
Definition: "Elevated concentration of galactose in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating ornithine concentration
Definition: "Deviation from the normal concentration of ornithine in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperornithinemia
Definition: "Increased concentration of ornithine in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Laryngeal edema
Definition: "An abnormal accumulation of fluid and swelling in the tissues of the larynx." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hepatocellular adenoma
Definition: "A benign tumor of the liver of presumably epithelial origin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal urine hormone level
Definition: "An abnormal concentration of a hormone in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased urinary cortisol level
Definition: "Abnormally increased concentration of cortisol in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lipoma
Definition: "Benign neoplasia derived from lipoblasts or lipocytes of white or brown fat. May be angiomatous or hibernomatous." [MPATH:417]

Name: Sacral lipoma
Definition: "Presence of a lipoma in the region of the sacrum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Liposarcoma
Definition: "Malignant neoplasms which probably originate in primitive mesenchymal stem cell populations differentiating down a lipomatous pathway." [MPATH:418]

Name: Steatocystoma multiplex
Definition: "Multiple, localized or widespread, asymptomatic or inflammatory dermal cysts involving the pilosebaceous units. Lesions can appear anywhere on the body, but steatocystoma multiplex is more commonly involved with those areas of the skin with a high density of developed pilosebaceous units (e.g., the axilla, groin, neck, and proximal extremities)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20631281]

Name: Sternocleidomastoid amyotrophy
Definition: "Wasting of the sternocleidomastoid muscle, the muscle in the anterior part of the neck that acts to flex and rotate the head." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pectoralis amyotrophy
Definition: "Wasting of the pectoral muscles, i.e., of the pectoralis major and pectoralis minor." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Corneal guttata
Definition: "Corneal guttata are droplet-like accumulations of non-banded collagen on the posterior surface of Descemet's membrane. The presence of focal thickenings of Descemet's membrane histologically named guttae. Cornea guttata can be easily diagnosed in vivo and ex vivo by means of specular microscopy as it gives dark areas where no endothelial cells are visible." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:10611102, PMID:11222329]

Name: Descemet Membrane Folds
Definition: "Presence of folds in the Descemet membrane, which is the basement membrane of the endothelial (inner) cell layer of the cornea. Descemet membrane folds are generally a manifestation of inflammation or edema of the cornea." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Corneal stromal edema
Definition: "Abnormal accumulation of fluid and swelling of the stroma of cornea." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aspirin-induced asthma
Definition: "A type of asthma in which aspirin and other nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs) that inhibit cyclooxygen-ase 1 (COX-1) exacerbate bronchoconstriction." [PMID:12743549]

Name: Pendular nystagmus
Definition: "Rhythmic, involuntary sinusoidal oscillations of one or both eyes. The waveform of pendular nystagmus may occur in any direction." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Seesaw nystagmus
Definition: "Seesaw nystagmus is a type of pendular nystagmus where a half cycle consists of the elevation and intorsion of one eye, concurrently with the depression and extortion of the fellow eye. In the other half cycle, there is an inversion of the ocular movements." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Retinal flecks
Definition: "Presence of multiple yellowish-white lesions of various size and configuration on the retina not related to vascular lesions." [PMID:7952338]

Name: Areflexia of upper limbs
Definition: "Inability to elicit tendon reflexes in the upper limbs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hemeralopia
Definition: "A visual defect characterized by the inability to see as clearly in bright light as in dim light. The word hemeralopia literally means day blindness." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Oromandibular dystonia
Definition: "A kind of focal dystonia characterized by forceful contractions of the face, jaw, and/or tongue causing difficulty in opening and closing the mouth and often affecting chewing and speech." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Laryngeal dystonia
Definition: "A form of focal dystonia that affects the vocal cords, associated with involuntary contractions of the vocal cords causing interruptions of speech and affecting the voice quality and often leading to patterned, repeated breaks in speech." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anasarca
Definition: "An extreme form of generalized edema with widespread and massive edema due to effusion of fluid into the extracellular space." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Reactive hypoglycemia
Definition: "Hypoglycermia following a meal (or more generally, after intake of glucose)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Low serum calcitriol
Definition: "A reduced concentration of calcitriol in the blood. Calcitriol is also known as 1,25-dihydroxycholecalciferol or 1,25-dihydroxyvitamin D3." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased circulating calcifediol concentration
Definition: "A reduced concentration of calcifediol in the blood. Calcifediol is also known as calcidiol, 25-hydroxycholecalciferol and 25-Hydroxyvitamin D3." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Choroidal melanoma
Definition: "Malignant tumor of melanocytes of the choroid. The classic appearance of choroidal melanoma is a pigmented dome-shaped or collar button-shaped tumor with an associated exudative retinal detachment. Choroidal melanoma is usually pigmented, but can be variably pigmented and even amelanotic (non-pigmented)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:22557869]

Name: Ciliary body melanoma
Definition: "Malignant tumor of melanocytes of the ciliary body." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cutaneous melanoma
Definition: "The presence of a melanoma of the skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Superficial spreading melanoma
Definition: "A type of melanoma that is flat and irregular in shape and color, with different shades of black and brown." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Nodular melanoma
Definition: "A type of melanoma that starts as a raised area that is usually dark blackish-blue or bluish-red but may not have any color." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Lentigo maligna melanoma
Definition: "A subtype of melanoma in situ that typically develops on sun-damaged skin. The lesion is typically a large, irregularly pigmented macule that has developed from an ordinary lentigo (a small pigmented spot on the skin with a clearly-defined edge). Change to a malignant lentigo typically takes place over 20 years or more, and many patients accept the change as a consequence of aging." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Acral lentiginous melanoma
Definition: "A type of cutaneous melanoma localized to the palm, sole, or beneath the nail (subungual melanoma). Acral lentiginous melanoma starts as a slowly-enlarging flat patch of discoloured skin and usually displays a size above 6 mm and often several centimetres or more in diameter upon diagnosis and variable pigmentation with a mixutre of colors including brown, and blue-grey, black and red. The surface of the lesion is initially smooth but later in the course may become thicker and irregular, and may ulcerate or bleed." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Urinary excretion of sialylated oligosaccharides
Definition: "Excretion of oligosaccharides conjugated to sialic acid in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bone cyst
Definition: "A fluid filled cavity that develops with a bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aneurysmal bone cyst
Definition: "Radiographic features include a dilated, radiolucent lesion typically located eccentrically within the metaphyseal portion of the bone, with fluid levels visible on magnetic resonance imaging." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:22474093, PMID:7863874]

Name: Unicameral bone cyst
Definition: "A benign fluid filled simple cyst of bone filled with serous fluid." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Multiple bony cystic lesions
Definition: "Presence of multiple cystic changes in multiple areas or multiple bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased urinary disaccharide excretion
Definition: "Increased concentration of disaccharide in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Glycopeptiduria
Definition: "Increased excretion of glycopeptides in the urine. Glycopeptides are peptides with carbohydrate moieties covalently attached to the side chains of the amino acid residues." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Aspartylglucosaminuria
Definition: "Excretion of excess amounts of aspartylglucosamine in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Keratan sulfate excretion in urine
Definition: "An increased concentration of keratan sulfate in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Chondroitin sulfate excretion in urine
Definition: "An increased concentration of chondroitin sulfate (CHEBI:37397) in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating acylcarnitine concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration in the blood circulation of an acylcarnitine, which is produced by reversible esterification of the 3-hydroxyl group of carnitine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:18281923, PMID:23258903, PMID:6348429]

Name: Aciduria
Definition: "Excretion of urine with an acid pH, i.e., having an increased hydrogen ion concentration." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal urinary acylglycine profile
Definition: "An abnormal distribution of N-acylglycines in the urine. There are numerous different N-acylglycines, and this term refers to pathological alterations in their level or distribution." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:10870848]

Name: Tonic pupil
Definition: "An abnormality of the pupillary light reaction characterized by a marked slowing of the light reaction of usually just one pupil. The pupil tends to be relatively dilated, and there is reduced accommodation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Personality disorder
Definition: "An abnormality of mental functioning affecting the personality and behavioural tendencies of an individual and characterized by a rigid and unhealthy pattern of thinking and behavior. The definition of a personal disorder implies that the abnormality is not the result of damage or insult to the brain or from another psychiatric disorder." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Borderline personality disorder
Definition: "A personality disorder characterized by impulsive behavior and unpredictable and capricious mood. Affected individuals show a liability to outbursts of emotion and an incapacity to control the behavioural explosions." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Histrionic personality disorder
Definition: "A personality disorder characterized by shallow and labile affectivity, self-dramatization, theatricality, exaggerated expression of emotions, suggestibility, egocentricity, self-indulgence, lack of consideration for others, easily hurt feelings, and continuous seeking for appreciation, excitement and attention." [ICD-10:F60.4]

Name: Motor conduction block
Definition: "Blockade of impulses at a focal site along the course of a motor axon." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of central motor conduction
Definition: "Any anomaly of the conduction of motor nerve impulses in the central nervous system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:3572430]

Name: Cerebellar granular layer atrophy
Definition: "Atrophy of the cerebellum affecting primarily the granular cell layer." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Enlarged cerebellum
Definition: "An abnormally increased size of the cerebellum compared to other brain structures." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cerebellar Purkinje layer atrophy
Definition: "Atrophy of the cerebellum affecting primarily the Purkinje cell layer." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ubiquitin-positive cerebral inclusion bodies
Definition: "Nuclear or cytoplasmic aggregates that show positive staining with antibodies against ubiquitin within cells of the brain." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of skeletal muscle fiber size
Definition: "Any abnormality of the size of the skeletal muscle cell." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pyuria
Definition: "The presence of 10 or more white cells per cubic millimeter in a urine specimen, 3 or more white cells per high-power field of unspun urine, a positive result on Gram staining of an unspun urine specimen, or a urinary dipstick test that is positive for leukocyte esterase." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:25760357]

Name: Abnormal urinary color
Definition: "An abnormal color of the urine, that is, the color of the urine appears different from the usual straw-yellow color." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal mitochondrial shape
Definition: "An anomaly in the surface contour of mitochondria." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, MP:0011633]

Name: Abnormal urinary odor
Definition: "A deviation from the normal odor of the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Arteritis
Definition: "Arterial inflammation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of pancreas physiology
Definition: "An anomaly of the function of the pancreas." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of exocrine pancreas physiology
Definition: "A functional anomaly of the acinar gland portion of the pancreas that secretes digestive enzymes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of endocrine pancreas physiology
Definition: "A function abnormality of the endocrine pancreas." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal pancreas size
Definition: "A deviation from the normal size of the pancreas." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Multiple joint dislocation
Definition: "Dislocation of many joints." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Intracranial epidermoid cyst
Definition: "A congenital inclusion cysts that arises from ectodermal cells that normally form skin cells being left behind in the nervous system during development." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16714456]

Name: Intracranial dermoid cyst
Definition: "A congenital inclusion cysts that arises from the inclusion of ectodermally committed cells at the time of neural tube closure (3rd-5th week of embryogenesis). The capsule of dermoid cysts consists of simple epithelium supported by collagen. In thicker parts, the lining is supplemented with dermis containing hair follicles, sebaceous glands, and apocrine glands." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16714456]

Name: Edema of the dorsum of feet
Definition: "An abnormal accumulation of fluid beneath the skin on the back of the feet." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of circulating catecholamine level
Definition: "An abnormal catecholamine concentration in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating creatinine concentration
Definition: "An abnormal concentration of creatinine in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased serum creatinine
Definition: "An abnormally reduced amount of creatinine in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal mitochondrial number
Definition: "A deviation from the normal number of mitochondria per cell." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the mitochondrion
Definition: "An anomaly of the mitochondrion, the membranous cytoplasmic organelle the interior of which is subdivided by cristae. The mitochondrion is a self replicating organelle that is the site of tissue respiration." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Parietal cortical atrophy
Definition: "Atrophy of the parietal cortex." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Occipital cortical atrophy
Definition: "Atrophy of the occipital cortex." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Rhizomelic leg shortening
Definition: "Disproportionate shortening of the proximal segment of the leg (i.e. the femur)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased fibular diameter
Definition: "Increased width of the cross sectional diameter of the fibula." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, MP:0008159]

Name: Open angle glaucoma
Definition: "A type of glaucoma defined by an open, normal appearing anterior chamber angle and raised intraocular pressure," [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:11815354]

Name: Angle closure glaucoma
Definition: "A type of glaucomatous optic neuropathy in an eye that has evidence of angle closure (i.e. significant iridotrabecular contact)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0986-4123, PMID:11815354]

Name: Hypoplasia of the pons
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the pons." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of circulating glucocorticoid level
Definition: "An abnormality of the concentration of a glucocorticoid in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating corticosterone level
Definition: "An abnormality of the concentration of corticosterone in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating creatine concentration
Definition: "A deviation from the normal concentration of creatine in the blood circulation. Creatine is a derivative of glycine having methyl and amidino groups attached to the nitrogen. Creatine is naturally produced from amino acids, primarily in liver and kidney, and acts as an energy source for cells, primarly for muscle cells." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Endometrial carcinoma
Definition: "A carcinoma of the endometrium, the mucous lining of the uterus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, NCIT:C7558]

Name: Hepatitis
Definition: "Inflammation of the liver." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating albumin concentration
Definition: "Deviation from normal concentration of albumin in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperalbuminemia
Definition: "Elevation in the concentration of albumin in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Laryngeal carcinoma
Definition: "A carcinoma of the larynx." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, NCIT:C4855]

Name: Methemoglobinemia
Definition: "Abnormally increased levels of methemoglobin in the blood. In this form of hemoglobin, there is an oxidized ferric iron (Fe +3) rather than the reduced ferrous form (Fe 2+) that is normally found in hemoglobin. Methemoglobin has a reduced affinity for oxygen, resulting in a reduced ability to release oxygen to tissues." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Methylmalonic aciduria
