Definition: "Increased concentration of methylmalonic acid in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Panuveitis
Definition: "Inflammation of the uveal tract in which inflammation affects the anterior chamber, vitreous, retina or choroid." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anterior uveitis
Definition: "Inflammation of the uveal tract in which the primary site of inflammation is the anterior chamber." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Posterior uveitis
Definition: "Inflammation of the uveal tract in which the primary site of inflammation is the retina or choroid." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Intermediate uveitis
Definition: "Inflammation of the uveal tract in which the primary site of inflammation is the vitreous." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Prostate cancer
Definition: "A cancer of the prostate." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Stomach cancer
Definition: "A cancer arising in any part of the stomach." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Uraciluria
Definition: "Increased concentration of uracil in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Basal ganglia necrosis
Definition: "Death of cells in the basal ganglia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of bone marrow stromal cells
Abnormal erythroid lineage cell morphology
Definition: "An anomaly of erythroid lineage cells, that is, of the erythropoietic cells in the lineage leading to and including erythrocytes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2945-4463]

Name: Abnormal number of erythroid precursors
Definition: "A deviation from the normal count of erythroid precursor cells, that is, erythroid lineage cells in the bone marrow." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2945-4463]

Name: Erythroid hyperplasia
Definition: "Increased count of erythroid precursor cells, that is, erythroid lineage cells in the bone marrow." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2945-4463]

Name: Erythroid hypoplasia
Definition: "Decreased count of erythroid precursor cells, that is, erythroid lineage cells in the bone marrow." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2945-4463]

Name: Abnormal granulocytopoietic cell morphology
Definition: "An anomaly of cells involved in the formation of a granulocytes, that is, of the granulocytopoietic cell." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2945-4463]

Name: Granulocytic hypoplasia
Definition: "Decreased number of granulocyte precursors in the bone marrow." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2945-4463]

Name: obsolete Abnormality of cells of the lymphoid lineage
Pancreatic squamous cell carcinoma
Definition: "A subtype of ductal pancreatic carcinoma that is thought to originate from squamous metaplasia of pancreatic ductal epithelium." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19079631]

Name: Abnormal megakaryocyte morphology
Definition: "Any structural anomaly of megakaryocytes. Mature blood platelets are released from the cytoplasm of megakaryocytes, which are bone-marrow resident cells." []

Name: Abnormal monocyte morphology
Definition: "Any structural anomaly of a myeloid mononuclear recirculating leukocyte that can act as a precursor of tissue macrophages, osteoclasts and some populations of tissue dendritic cells." []

Name: Abnormality of multiple cell lineages in the bone marrow
Abnormality of von Willebrand factor
Definition: "Decreased quantity or activity of von Willebrand factor. Von Willebrand factor mediates the adhesion of platelets to the collagen exposed on endothelial cell surfaces." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2945-4463]

Name: Reduced quantity of Von Willebrand factor
Definition: "Decreased quantity of von Willebrand factor." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2945-4463]

Name: Multiple lineage myelodysplasia
Definition: "Myelodysplasia with dysplastic changes in two or more of the myeloid lineages: erythroid, granulocytic, megakaryocytic." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2945-4463]

Name: Bilineage myelodysplasia
Definition: "Myelodysplasia with dysplastic changes in two of the myeloid lineages: erythroid, granulocytic, megakaryocytic." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2945-4463]

Name: Single lineage myelodysplasia
Definition: "Abnormality/dysplasia of a single myeloid cell (erythroid, granulocytic, or megakaryocytic)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2945-4463]

Name: Hemothorax
Definition: "The presence of blood in the pleural space." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Foveoschisis
Definition: "Splitting of the retinal layers in the macula." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypotriglyceridemia
Definition: "An decrease in the level of triglycerides in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anhedonia
Definition: "Inability to experience pleasure activities usually found enjoyable." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased corneal sensation
Definition: "Reduced ability of the cornea to respond to stimulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hemophagocytosis
Definition: "Phagocytosis by macrophages of erythrocytes, leukocytes, platelets, and their precursors in bone marrow and other tissues." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:25328776]

Name: Subcortical cerebral atrophy
Definition: "Atrophy of the cerebral subcortical white and gray matter, termed subcortical atrophy, reflects loss of nerve cells in the basal ganglia or fibers in the deep white matter." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20813998]

Name: Carotid artery dissection
Definition: "A separation (dissection) of the layers of the carotid artery wall." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Internal carotid artery dissection
Definition: "A separation (dissection) of the layers of the internal carotid artery wall." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Intracranial internal carotid artery dissection
Definition: "A separation (dissection) of the layers of the intracranial portion of the internal carotid artery wall." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: External carotid artery dissection
Definition: "A separation (dissection) of the layers of the external carotid artery wall." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Common carotid artery dissection
Definition: "A separation (dissection) of the layers of the common carotid artery wall." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Carotid artery dilatation
Definition: "A dilatation (balooning or bulging out of the vessel wall) of a carotid artery." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Asterixis
Definition: "A clinical sign indicating a lapse of posture and is usually manifest by a bilateral flapping tremor at the wrist, metacarpophalangeal, and hip joints." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Oligodactyly
Definition: "A developmental defect resulting in the presence of fewer than the normal number of digits." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Skin-picking
Definition: "Repetitive and compulsive picking of skin which results in tissue damage." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20575652]

Name: Hair-pulling
Definition: "A phenomenon in which persons repetitively pull out their own hair, resulting in noticeable hair loss." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Head-banging
Definition: "Habitual striking of one's own head against a surface such as a mattress or wall of a crib." []

Name: Self-biting
Definition: "Habitual biting of one's own body." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Nail-biting
Definition: "Habitual biting of one's own fingernails." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Stereotypical hand wringing
Definition: "Habitual clasping and wringing of the hands in the middle of the body, similar to a hand-washing movement." [PMID:28838622]

Name: Stereotypical body rocking
Definition: "Habitual repetitive movement of the entire body, front to back or side to side." []

Name: Orthostatic tachycardia
Definition: "An increase in heart rate with standing of 30 beats per minute or more." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:9244228]

Name: Glioblastoma multiforme
Definition: "A tumor arising from glia in the central nervous system with macroscopic regions of necrosis and hemorrhage. Microscopically, glioblastoma multiforme is characterized by regions of pseudopalisading necrosis, pleomorphic nuclei and cells, and microvascular proliferation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, NCIT:C3058, PMID:10841526]

Name: Resistance to activated protein C
Definition: "Poor anticoagulant response to activated protein C. A plasma is termed 'APC resistant' when the addition of exogenous APC fails to prolong its clotting time in an activated partial thromboplastin time assay." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:14976057]

Name: Abnormal natural killer cell morphology
Definition: "An anomaly of the natural killer cell, which is a lymphocyte that can spontaneously kill a variety of target cells without prior antigenic activation via germline encoded activation receptors. It also regulates immune responses via cytokine release and direct contact with other cells." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:21212348]

Name: Abnormal natural killer cell physiology
Definition: "A functional anomaly of the natural killer cell." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Reduced natural killer cell activity
Definition: "Reduced ability of the natural killer cell to function in the adaptive immune response." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Craniofacial dystonia
Definition: "A form of focal dystonia affecting the face and especially the jaw that is induced by the act of speaking. It is an involuntary contraction of the masticatory muscles, resulting in dysarthria or dysphagia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cystic medial necrosis
Definition: "A disorder of large arteries, in particular the aorta, characterized by an accumulation of basophilic ground substance in the media with cyst-like lesions associated with degenerative changes of collagen, elastin and the vascular smooth muscle cells." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Entrapment neuropathy
Definition: "Malfunction of a peripheral nerve resulting from mechanical compression of the nerve roots from internal or external causes and leading to a conduction block or axonal loss." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Oropharyngeal squamous cell carcinoma
Definition: "A squamous cell carcinoma that originates in the oropharnyx." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperplastic colonic polyposis
Definition: "Presence of multiple hyperplastic polyps in the colon. Hyperplastic polyps are generally about 5 mm in size and show hyperplastic mucosal proliferation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased HDL cholesterol concentration
Definition: "An elevated concentration of high-density lipoprotein cholesterol (HDL) in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Constrictive median neuropathy
Definition: "Injury to the median nerve caused by its entrapment at the wrist as it traverses through the carpal tunnel. Clinically, constrictive median neuropathy is characterized by pain, paresthesia, and weakness in the median nerve distribution of the hand." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Entrapment neuropathy of the ulnar nerve at elbow
Definition: "An entrapment neuropathy of the ulnar nerve in the cubital tunnel (in the elbow) characterized by numbness in the ring and little fingers and weakness of the intrinsic muscles in the hand." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased erythrocyte protoporphyrin concentration
Definition: "Concentration of protoporphyrins in erythrocytes above the upper limit of normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:18760763]

Name: Hyperemesis gravidarum
Definition: "Excessive vomiting in early pregnancy, leading to the loss of 5% or more of body weight." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, OMIM:603373]

Name: Hodgkin lymphoma
Definition: "A type of lymphoma characterized microscopically by multinucleated Reed-Sternberg cells." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: T-cell lymphoma
Definition: "A type of lymphoma that originates in T-cells." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: B-cell lymphoma
Definition: "A type of lymphoma that originates in B-cells." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cutaneous T-cell lymphoma
Definition: "A type of T-cell lymphoma that exhibits malignant infiltration of the skin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anaplastic large-cell lymphoma
Definition: "A type of T-cell lymphoma that is characterized by so-called hallmark cells with a pleomorphic appearance that express the CD30 antigen, are lobulated, and have indented nuclei." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Episodic hemiplegia
Definition: "Transient episodes of weakness of the arm, leg, and in some cases the face on one side of the body." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Irregular respiration
Definition: "Uneven rhythm of breathing." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cheyne-Stokes respiration
Definition: "An abnormal pattern of respiration characterized by cycles of respiration that are increasingly deeper then shallower with possible periods of apnea. Affected patients may display a 10 to 20 second episode of hypoventilation or apnea, followed by respiration of increased depth and frequency over the course of about one minute. The cycle repeats every 45 seconds to 3 minutes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Insulinoma
Definition: "A type of tumor of the pancreatic beta cells that secretes excess insulin and can result in hypoglycemia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, NCIT:C95598]

Name: Juvenile colonic polyposis
Definition: "The presence of more than 5 juvenile polyps of the colon. The term juvenile polyps refer to a special histopathology and not the age of onset as the polyp might be diagnosed at all ages. The juvenile polyp has a spherical appearance and is microscopically characterized by overgrowth of an oedematous lamina propria with inflammatory cells and cystic glands." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:17768394, PMID:25022750]

Name: Cluster headache
Definition: "A type of headache characterized by repeated attacks of unilateral pain lasting 15 to 180 minutes and associated with local autonomic signs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:21912573]

Name: Abnormality of prothrombin
Definition: "An anomaly of clotting factor II, which is known as prothrombin, a vitamin K-dependent proenzyme that functions in the blood coagulation cascade." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased serum bile acid concentration
Definition: "An increase in the concentration of bile acid in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Onychomycosis
Definition: "A fungal infection of the toenails or fingernails that tends to cause the nails to thicken, discolor, disfigure, and split." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Recurrent vulvovaginal candidiasis
Definition: "Recurrent infection involving the vulva, vagina, and adjacent crural areas, whereby the causative agent belongs to the genus Candida." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Globozoospermia
Definition: "Any structural anomaly of the acrosome resulting in a round sperm head." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, MP:0002686]

Name: Abnormal sperm motility
Definition: "An anomaly of the mobility of ejaculated sperm." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Reduced sperm motility
Definition: "An abnormal reduction in the mobility of ejaculated sperm." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Immotile sperm
Definition: "A lack of mobility of ejaculated sperm." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Juvenile myelomonocytic leukemia
Definition: "Juvenile myelomonocytic leukemia (JMML) is a lethal myeloproliferative disease of young childhood characterized clinically by overproduction of myelomonocytic cells and by the in vitro phenotype of hematopoietic progenitor hypersensitivity to granulocyte-macrophage colony-stimulating factor." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:18954903]

Name: Abnormal renal morphology
Definition: "Any structural anomaly of the kidney." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal renal physiology
Definition: "An abnormal functionality of the kidney." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal glomerular filtration rate
Definition: "An abnormally increased or reduced amount of fluid filtered out of plasma through glomerular capillary walls into Bowman's capsules per unit of time." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:25710660]

Name: Decreased glomerular filtration rate
Definition: "An abnormal reduction in the volume of fluid filtered out of plasma through glomerular capillary walls into Bowman's capsules per unit of time." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:25710660]

Name: Increased glomerular filtration rate
Definition: "An abnormal rise in the volume of water filtered out of plasma through glomerular capillary walls into Bowman's capsules per unit of time." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Testicular microlithiasis
Definition: "The deposition of calcium phosphate microliths within the seminiferous tubules." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Entrapment neuropathy of suprascapular nerve
Definition: "An entrapment neuropathy of the suprascapular nerve, presenting with shoulder weakness confined to the supraspinatus muscle (this muscle initiates shoulder abduction) or to the infraspinatus (this muscle externally rotates the arm), as well as with pain in the posterior part of the shoulder and upper periscapular region." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased urinary porphobilinogen
Definition: "The concentration of porphobilinogen in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:11861450]

Name: Alveolar soft part sarcoma
Definition: "A type of soft tissue sarcoma with a histological appearance reminiscent of alveoli because of its reticulated fibrous stroma enclosing groups of sarcoma cells, which resemble epithelial cells and are enclosed in alveoli walled with connective tissue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:11244503]

Name: Erythema nodosum
Definition: "An erythematous eruption commonly associated with drug reactions or infection and characterized by inflammatory nodules that are usually tender, multiple, and bilateral." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Non-caseating epithelioid cell granulomatosis
Definition: "The presence of multiple epithelioid cell granulomas consist of highly differentiated mononuclear phagocytes (epithelioid cells and giant cells) and lymphocytes, not exhibiting caseation (a form of necrosis in which the tissue changes into a dry, amorphous mass said to resemble cheese)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pretibial blistering
Definition: "A type of blistering that affects the skin of the tibial region." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:15265795]

Name: Arachnoid hemangiomatosis
Definition: "The presence of multiple hemangiomas in the arachnoid." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Splenic rupture
Definition: "A breach of the capsule of the spleen." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Circulating immune complexes
Definition: "Persistence of immune complexes in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Oligodontia of primary teeth
Definition: "Reduced number of primary teeth." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ovarian teratoma
Definition: "The presence of a teratoma in the ovary." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Urethral stricture
Definition: "Narrowing of the urethra associated with inflammation or scar tissue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Tension-type headache
Definition: "A type of headache that last hours with continuous pain of mild or moderate intensity, bilateral location, a pressing/tightening (non-pulsating) quality and that is not aggravated by routine physical activity such as walking or climbing stairs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: CSF pleocytosis
Definition: "An increased white blood cell count in the cerebrospinal fluid." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Rhegmatogenous retinal detachment
Definition: "A type of retinal detachment associated with a retinal tear, that is, with a break in the retina that allows fluid to pass from the vitreous space into the subretinal space between the sensory retina and the retinal pigment epithelium." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Exudative retinal detachment
Definition: "A type of retinal detachment arising from damage to the outer blood-retinal barrier that allows fluid to access the subretinal space and separate the neurosensory retina from the retinal pigment epithelium." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0986-4123]

Name: Shortened QT interval
Definition: "Decreased time between the start of the Q wave and the end of the T wave as measured by the electrocardiogram (EKG)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Intramuscular hematoma
Definition: "Blood clot formed within muscle tissue following leakage of blood into the tissue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Agranulocytosis
Definition: "Marked decrease in the number of granulocytes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Drug-induced agranulocytosis
Definition: "A type of agranulocytosis related to ingestion of a specific medication." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated sweat chloride
Definition: "An increased concentration of chloride in the sweat." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Urocanic aciduria
Definition: "An increased concentration of urocanic acid in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased circulating chylomicron concentration
Definition: "Increased plasma concentrations of chylomicrons, the large lipid droplet (up to 100 mm in diameter) of reprocessed lipid synthesized in epithelial cells of the small intestine and containing triacylglycerols, cholesterol esters, and several apolipoproteins." Name: Atransferrinemia
Definition: "Absence of transferrin, a protein that transports iron, in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased intramyocellular lipid droplets
Definition: "An abnormal increase in intracellular lipid droplets In a muscle. The number and size of these drops can increase with somd disorders of lipid metabolism affecting muscle. See PMID 20691590 for histological images." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20691590]

Name: Levator palpebrae superioris atrophy
Definition: "Atrophy of the levator palpebrae superioris, the extraocular muscle that elevates the superior eyelid." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Superior rectus atrophy
Definition: "Atrophy of the superior rectus, the extraocular muscle whose primary function is to elevate the globe." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal reproductive system morphology
Definition: "A structural or developmental anomaly of any of the tissues involved in the genital system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, MP:0002160]

Name: Abnormal sex determination
Definition: "Anomaly of primary or secondary sexual development or characteristics." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, MP:0002210]

Name: Sex reversal
Definition: "Development of the reproductive system is inconsistent with the chromosomal sex." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, MP:0005652]

Name: Oculomotor nerve palsy

Name: Specific anosmia
Definition: "Anosmia for one particular odor." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Prolonged PR interval
Definition: "Increased time for the PR interval (beginning of the P wave to the beginning of the QRS complex)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:23677846]

Name: Abnormal ST segment
Definition: "An electrocardiographic anomaly of the ST segment, which is the segment that connects the QRS complex and the T wave. The ST segment normally has a duration of 80 to 120 ms, is flat and at the same level (isoelectric) as the PR and TP segment." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: ST segment depression
Definition: "An electrocardiographic anomaly in which the ST segment is observed to be located inferior to the isoelectric line." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: ST segment elevation
Definition: "An electrocardiographic anomaly in which the ST segment is observed to be located superior to the isoelectric line." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal respiratory system morphology
Definition: "A structural anomaly of the respiratory system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal respiratory epithelium morphology
Definition: "Any structural anomaly of the pseudostratified ciliated epithelium that lines much of the conducting portion of the airway, including part of the nasal cavity and larynx, the trachea, and bronchi." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, MP:0010942]

Name: Ewing sarcoma
Definition: "A malignant tumor of the bone which always arises in the medullary tissue, occurring more often in cylindrical bones." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:17272319]

Name: Dynein arm defect of respiratory motile cilia
Definition: "An anomaly of the dynein arms of motile cilia. This feature is usually appreciated by electron microscopy." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19606528]

Name: Absent outer dynein arms
Definition: "Absence of the outer dynein arms of respiratory motile cilia, which normally are situated outside of the peripheral microtubules of motile cilia. This feature is usually appreciated by electron microscopy." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19606528]

Name: Absent inner dynein arms

Name: Abnormal axonemal organization of respiratory motile cilia

Name: Absent inner and outer dynein arms

This feature is usually appreciated by electron microscopy." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19606528]

Name: Abnormal central microtubular pair morphology of respiratory motile cilia
Definition: "A structural anomaly of the two central microtubules of motile cilia with a 9+2 microtubuluar configuration." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19200523]

Name: Abnormal respiratory motile cilium physiology
Definition: "Any functional anomaly of the respiratory motile cilia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, MP:0011055]

Name: Abnormal ciliary motility

Evaluation of ciliary beat frequency and ciliary beat pattern requires high-speed videomicroscopy of freshly obtained ciliary biopsies that are maintained in culture media under controlled conditions." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19606528, PMID:20301301]

Name: Absent central microtubular pair morphology of respiratory motile cilia
Definition: "Absence of the two central microtubules of motile cilia with a 9+2 microtubuluar configuration." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ciliary dyskinesia

Name: T-wave alternans

Name: Absent respiratory ciliary axoneme radial spokes
Definition: "Absence of the radial spokes of the axoneme of the respiratory cilium." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19606528]

Name: Myxoid liposarcoma
Definition: "A liposarcoma that contains myxomatous tissue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal muscle glycogen content
Definition: "Any anomaly in the amount of glycogen in muscle tissue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased muscle glycogen content
Definition: "A decreased amount of glycogen in muscle tissue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Episodic upper airway obstruction
Definition: "Intermittent episodes of increased resistance to the passage of air in the upper airway." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: J wave
Definition: "The J wave is a positive convex deflection that occurs at the junction of the QRS complex and ST segment, the J-point." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19561994]

Name: Increased carotid artery intimal medial thickness
Definition: "An increase in the combined thickness of the intima and media of the carotid artery." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:9878640]

Name: Autosomal dominant inheritance with paternal imprinting

Name: Autosomal dominant inheritance with maternal imprinting
Definition: "A type of autosomal dominant inheritance involving a gene that is imprinted with maternal silencing." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Digital flexor tenosynovitis

[https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16443118]

Name: Hypoglycinemia

Name: Abnormal circulating serine concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of serine in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyposerinemia
Definition: "Reduced concentration of serine in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hepatic amyloidosis
Definition: "A form of amyloidosis that affects the liver." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Chylous ascites
Definition: "Extravasation of chyle into the peritoneal cavity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Morbilliform rash
Definition: "An exanthema consisting of widespread pink-to-red macules (flat spots of 2-10 mm in diameter) or papules (red bumps) that blanch with pressure. The macules and papules may cluster and merge to form sheets over several days." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Small distal femoral epiphysis
Definition: "Reduced size of the Distal epiphysis of femur." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Small proximal tibial epiphyses
Definition: "Reduced size of the proximal epiphysis of the tibia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal hypothalamus physiology
Definition: "An abnormal functionality of the hypothalamus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal hypothalamus morphology
Definition: "Any structural anomaly of the hypothalamus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypothalamic luteinizing hormone-releasing hormone deficiency
Definition: "Decreased secretion of luteinizing hormone-releasing hormone by the hypothalamus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Neoplasm of head and neck
Definition: "A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the head and neck region with origin in the lip, oral cavity, nasal cavity, paranasal sinuses, pharynx, or larynx." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Facial neoplasm
Definition: "A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the face." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fusion of gums
Definition: "A congenital defect with an abnormal joining of the gums of the upper and lower jaw." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19858676]

Name: Abnormal genital pigmentation
Definition: "An abnormal pigmentation pattern of the external genitalia." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal occipital bone morphology
Definition: "Abnormality of the occipital bone of the skull." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Slender middle phalanx of finger
Definition: "Reduced diameter of the middle phalanx of finger." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Slender distal phalanx of finger
Definition: "Reduced diameter of the distal phalanx of finger." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Slender proximal phalanx of finger
Definition: "Reduced diameter of the proximal phalanx of finger." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Long middle phalanx of finger
Definition: "Increased length of the middle phalanx of finger." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Long distal phalanx of finger

Name: Ureteral agenesis

Name: Type II transferrin isoform profile
Definition: "Abnormal transferrin isoform profile consistent with a type II congenital disorder of glycosylation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:15105360, PMID:22516080]

Name: Herpes simplex encephalitis

Name: Abnormal aortic arch morphology
Definition: "An anomaly of the arch of aorta." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplastic aortic arch

Name: Coarctation of the descending aortic arch

Name: Abnormal rib ossification
Definition: "An anomaly of the process of rib bone formation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Spatulate ribs

Name: Decreased circulating complement C9 concentration
Definition: "Concentration of the complement component C9 in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal." [https://emedicine.medscape.com/article/135478-overview]

Name: Cutaneous amyloidosis

Name: Abnormal monocyte count

Name: Monocytosis

Name: Monocytopenia
Definition: "An decreased number of circulating monocytes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Heberden's node

Name: Bouchard's node

Name: Histiocytoma

Name: Fibrous tissue neoplasm
Definition: "Any neoplasm composed of fibrous tissue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sacroiliac arthritis
Definition: "Inflammation of the sacroiliac joint, generally accompanied by lower back pain." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Occipital neuralgia

Name: Absent pigmentation of the abdomen

Name: Absent pigmentation of the limbs
Definition: "Lack of skin pigmentation (coloring) of the arms and legs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: D-2-hydroxyglutaric aciduria

Name: Perifolliculitis

Name: Sleep myoclonus

Name: Myeloid leukemia

Name: Chronic myelomonocytic leukemia

[NCIT:C3178]

Name: Abnormal celiac artery morphology
Definition: "An anomaly of the celiac artery." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Celiac artery compression
Definition: "Compression of the celiac artery." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cementoma

Name: Pyelonephritis

Name: Abnormal autonomic nervous system morphology
Definition: "A structural abnormality of the autonomic nervous system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal autonomic nervous system physiology

Name: Abnormal sudomotor regulation

Name: Extrahepatic cholestasis
Definition: "Impairment of bile flow due to obstruction in large bile ducts outside the liver." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of folate metabolism
Definition: "An abnormality of the metabolism of folic acid, which is also known as vitamin B9." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal homeostasis
Definition: "An anomaly in the processes involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal energy expenditure

Name: Increased resting energy expenditure
Definition: "An increase in the number of calories used per unit time." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased resting energy expenditure
Definition: "A reduction in the number of calories used per unit time." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Microprolactinoma
Definition: "A pituitary prolactin cell adenoma of less than 10 mm diameter." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Macroprolactinoma
Definition: "A pituitary prolactin cell adenoma of more than 10 mm diameter." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased circulating ferritin concentration
Definition: "Abnormally reduced concentration of ferritin, a ubiquitous intracellular protein that stores iron, in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Morphea
Definition: "Isolated patches of hardened skin (scleroderma)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal glycosylation
Definition: "An anomaly of a glycosylation process, i.e., a process involved in the covalent attachment of a glycosyl residue to a substrate molecule." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal protein glycosylation
Definition: "An anomaly of a protein glycosylation process, i.e., of a protein modification process that results in the addition of a carbohydrate or carbohydrate derivative unit to a protein amino acid, e.g. the addition of glycan chains to proteins." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal protein N-linked glycosylation
Definition: "An anomaly of protein N-linked glycosylation, i.e., an abnormality of the protein glycosylation process in which a carbohydrate or carbohydrate derivative unit is added to a protein via a nitrogen atom in an amino acid residue in a protein." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:22516080]

Name: Decreased galactosylation of N-linked protein glycosylation
Definition: "A reduction in the amount of galactose residues of N-glycans." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal sialylation of N-linked protein glycosylation
Definition: "An anomaly of the addition of sialic acids to N-linked glycans." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased sialylation of N-linked protein glycosylation
Definition: "Decreased addition of sialic acids to N-linked glycans." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased sialylation of N-linked protein glycosylation
Definition: "Increased addition of sialic acids to N-linked glycans." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal fucosylation of protein N-linked glycosylation
Definition: "An anomaly of the addition of fucose sugar units to N-linked glycans." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased fucosylation of N-linked protein glycosylation
Definition: "Decreased addition of fucose sugar units to N-linked glycans." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased fucosylation of N-linked protein glycosylation
Definition: "Increased addition of fucose sugar units to N-linked glycans." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal mannosylation of N-linked protein glycosylation
Definition: "An anomaly of the addition of mannose to N-linked glycans." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased mannosylation of N-linked protein glycosylation
Definition: "Reduced addition of mannose to N-linked glycans." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased mannosylation of N-linked protein glycosylation
Definition: "Increased addition of mannose to N-linked glycans." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal protein O-linked glycosylation
Definition: "An anomaly of protein O-linked glycosylation, i.e., of the process in which a carbohydrate or carbohydrate derivative unit is added to a protein via the hydroxyl group of a serine or threonine residue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal fucosylation of O-linked protein glycosylation
Definition: "An anomaly of the addition of fucose sugar units to O-linked glycans." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased fucosylation of O-linked protein glycosylation
Definition: "A reduction of the addition of fucose sugar units to O-linked glycans." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased fucosylation of O-linked protein glycosylation
Definition: "Increased addition of fucose sugar units to O-linked glycans." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal sialylation of O-linked protein glycosylation
Definition: "An anomaly of the addition of sialic acids to O-linked glycans." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased sialylation of O-linked protein glycosylation
Definition: "An reduced addition of sialic acids to O-linked glycans." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased urinary potassium
Definition: "A decreased concentration of potassium(1+) in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypophosphaturia
Definition: "An abnormally decreased phosphate concentration in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Basilar invagination
Definition: "Projection of the tip of the dens more than 5 mm above a line joining the hard palate to the posterior lip of the foramen magnum (Chamberlain's line) or the tip of the dens is greater than 7 mm above McGregor's line (the back of the hard palate to the lowest point of the occipital squama)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:10084535]

Name: Extra fontanelles
Definition: "Bony defects situated along the cranial suture lines or at the junction of the bone plates of the skull." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Flat face
Definition: "Absence of concavity or convexity of the face when viewed in profile." [PMID:19125436]

Name: Prominence of the zygomatic bone
Definition: "Large or prominent malar surface of the zygomatic bone of the skull, which is convex and forms the prominence of the 'cheek bones'." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5889-4463, PMID:19125436]

Name: Hyperplasia of midface
Definition: "Abnormally anterior positioning of the infraorbital and perialar regions, or increased convexity of the face, or increased nasolabial angle. The midface includes the maxilla, the cheeks, the zygomas, and the infraorbital and perialar regions of the face" [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19125436]

Name: Abnormal eye morphology
Definition: "A structural anomaly of the globe of the eye, or bulbus oculi." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal eye physiology
Definition: "A functional anomaly of the eye." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Chemosis
Definition: "Edema (swelling) of the bulbar conjunctiva." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Microphakia
Definition: "Abnormal smallness of the lens." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hemianopia
Definition: "Partial or complete loss of vision in one half of the visual field of one or both eyes." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fatigue
Definition: "A subjective feeling of tiredness characterized by a lack of energy and motivation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating enzyme concentration or activity
Definition: "Concentration or activity of an enzyme is above or below the limits of normal in the blood circulation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, MP:0005584]

Name: Reduced carnitine O-palmitoyltransferase level
Definition: "Reduced carnitine O-palmitoyltransferase level, leading to a reduced activity of the reaction: palmitoyl-CoA + L-carnitine = CoA + L-palmitoylcarnitine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Delayed self-feeding during toddler years
Definition: "A delay in the development of skills required to feed oneself in the toddler period (between one and three years of age)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Left-to-right shunt
Definition: "Pattern of blood flow in the heart that deviates from the normal circuit of the circulatory system from the left side of the heart to the right." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9114-8737]

Name: Bidirectional shunt
Definition: "Pattern of blood flow in the heart that deviates from the normal circuit of the circulatory system from both right side of the heart to the left and vice versa." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9114-8737]

Name: Rhinitis
Definition: "Inflammation of the nasal mucosa with nasal congestion." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Camptodactyly
Definition: "The distal interphalangeal joint and/or the proximal interphalangeal joint of the fingers or toes cannot be extended to 180 degrees by either active or passive extension." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent hallux
Definition: "Aplasia of the hallux, that is, a development defect such that the big toe does not develop." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bronchitis
Definition: "Inflammation of the large airways in the lung including any part of the bronchi from the primary bronchi to the tertiary bronchi." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Acute bronchitis
Definition: "Inflammation of the large airways of the lung with rapid onset and short course usually associated with cough, mucus production, shortness of breath, wheezing, and chest tightness." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Appendicular hypotonia
Definition: "Muscular hypotonia of one or more limbs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anal fissure
Definition: "A small tear in the thin, moist tissue (mucosa) that lines the anus. It appears as a crack or slit in the mucous membrane of the anus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyporeflexia of upper limbs
Definition: "Reduced intensity of muscle tendon reflexes in the upper limbs. Reflexes are elicited by stretching the tendon of a muscle, e.g., by tapping." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Jaw hyporeflexia
Definition: "Reduced intensity of muscle tendon reflexes in jaw." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Allergy
Definition: "An allergy is an immune response or reaction to substances that are usually not harmful." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Iodine contrast allergy
Definition: "Allergy to iodine contrast media used in radiological studies." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Seasonal allergy
Definition: "An allergy experienced at a particular time of year when trees or grasses pollinate and elicit an allergic reaction." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Biliary dyskinesia
Definition: "A motility disorder characterized by biliary colic in the absence of gallstones with a reduced gallbladder ejection fraction." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:12095476]

Name: Aortic atherosclerotic lesion
Definition: "The presence of atheromas or atherosclerotic plaques in the aorta." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16818829]

Name: Peripheral edema
Definition: "An abnormal accumulation of interstitial fluid in the soft tissues of the limbs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pressure ulcer
Definition: "A type of ulcer that is caused when an area of skin is subject to pressure over a prolonged period of time, ranging in range in severity from patches of discolored skin to open wounds that expose the underlying bone or muscle. The most common sites are the sacrum, coccyx, heels and the hips." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circulating aldolase concentration
Definition: "An abnormal concentration of aldolase in the serum. Aldolase is an enzyme responsible for converting fructose 1,6-bisphosphate into the triose phosphates dihydroxyacetone phosphate and glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal urine alpha-ketoglutarate concentration
Definition: "A deviation from normal of the concentration of 2-oxoglutaric acid in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Increased urine alpha-ketoglutarate concentration
Definition: "A greater than normal concentration of 2-oxoglutaric acid in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased urine alpha-ketoglutarate concentration
Definition: "A lower than normal concentration of 2-oxoglutaric acid in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal urine citrate concentration
Definition: "A deviation from normal of the concentration of citrate(3-) in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypocitraturia
Definition: "A lower than normal concentration of citrate(3-) in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypercitraturia
Definition: "A greater than normal concentration of citrate(3-) in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Scissor gait
Definition: "A type of spastic paraparetic gait in which the muscle tone in the adductors is marked. It is characterized by hypertonia and flexion in the legs, hips and pelvis accompanied by extreme adduction leading to the knees and thighs hitting, or sometimes even crossing, in a scissors-like movement. The opposing muscles (abductors) become comparatively weak from lack of use." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Medullary nephrocalcinosis
Definition: "The deposition of calcium salts in the parenchyma of the renal medulla (innermost part of the kidney)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Cortical nephrocalcinosis
Definition: "The deposition of calcium salts in the parenchyma of the renal cortex (the outer portion of the kidney between the renal capsule and the renal medulla)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Pure red cell aplasia
Definition: "A type of anemia resulting from suppression of erythropoiesis with little or no abnormality of leukocyte or platelet production. Erythroblasts are virtually absent in bone marrow; however, leukocyte and platelet production show little or no reduction." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Premature pubarche
Definition: "The onset of growth of pubic hair at an earlier age than normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Premature adrenarche
Definition: "Onset of adrenarche at an earlier age than usual." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Notched primary central incisor
Definition: "The presence of a V-shaped indentation (notch) in the primary central incisor." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Duodenal atrophy
Definition: "Wasting or decrease in size of all or part of the duodenum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal blood gas level
Definition: "An abnormality of the partial pressure of oxygen or carbon dioxide in the arterial blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypercapnia
Definition: "Abnormally elevated blood carbon dioxide (CO2) level." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypocapnia
Definition: "Abnormally reduced blood carbon dioxide (CO2) level." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoxemia
Definition: "An abnormally low level of blood oxygen." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperoxemia
Definition: "An abnormally high level of blood oxygen." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Meconium stained amniotic fluid
Definition: "Amniotic fluid containing the earliest stools of a mammalian infant." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Congenital absence of foreskin
Definition: "Congenital lack of the skin of prepuce of penis, that is, of the double-layered fold of skin and mucous membrane that covers the glans penis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Villous hypertrophy of choroid plexus
Definition: "Overgrowth of the choroid plexus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16523225]

Name: Colonic inertia
Definition: "The inability of the colon to modify stool to an acceptable consistency and move the stool from the cecum to the rectosigmoid area at least once every three days." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:23449085]

Name: Chorioretinitis
Definition: "An inflammation of the choroid and retina." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432, PMID:16196117]

Name: Stercoral ulcer
Definition: "An ulcer of the colon due to pressure and irritation from retained fecal masses." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432, PMID:7065551]

Name: Optic disc drusen
Definition: "Optic disc drusen are acellular, calcified deposits within the optic nerve head. Optic disc drusen are congenital and developmental anomalies of the optic nerve head, representing hyaline-containing bodies that, over time, appear as elevated, lumpy irregularities on the anterior portion of the optic nerve." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:22787500, PMID:23658477, PMID:30524490]

Name: Increased femoral anteversion
Definition: "An increased degree of femoral version, which is defined as the angular difference between axis of femoral neck and transcondylar axis of the knee. Thus, femoral anteversion is an inward twisting of the femur that causes the knees and feet to turn inward." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:32579722]

Name: Prominent calcaneus
Definition: "Protruding heel bone, or calcaneus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the cerebral white matter
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the cerebral white matter." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cerebral white matter hypoplasia
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the cerebral white matter." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Episodic fatigue
Definition: "Intermittent and recurrent bouts of a subjective feeling of tiredness characterized by a lack of energy and motivation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Chronic fatigue
Definition: "Subjective feeling of tiredness characterized by a lack of energy and motivation that persists for six months or longer." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Abnormal social behavior
Definition: "An abnormality of actions or reactions of a person taking place during interactions with others." []

Name: Delayed social development
Definition: "A failure to meet one or more age-related milestones of social behavior." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Ventral shortening of foreskin
Definition: "Reduction in length of the ventral (lower) skin of prepuce of penis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Nonocclusive coronary artery atherosclerosis
Definition: "Coronary disease that has not progressed to the point of causing significant occlusion (blockage) of the coronary arteries." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Abnormal gallbladder morphology
Definition: "A structural anomaly of the gallbladder." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal gallbladder physiology
Definition: "A functional anomaly of the gallbladder." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal biliary tract physiology
Definition: "A functional abnormality of the biliary tree." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal biliary tract morphology
Definition: "A structural abnormality of the biliary tree." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Sphincter of Oddi dyskinesia
Definition: "Reduced motility through the sphincter of Oddi, resulting in impedance of bile and pancreatic juice flow from the common bile duct into the duodenum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Gallbladder dyskinesia
Definition: "Reduced motility of the gallbladder with reduced emptying fraction." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:12095476, PMID:17761125]

Name: Abnormality of brain morphology
Definition: "A structural abnormality of the brain, which has as its parts the forebrain, midbrain, and hindbrain." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Brain atrophy
Definition: "Partial or complete wasting (loss) of brain tissue that was once present." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased CSF 5-methyltetrahydrofolate concentration
Definition: "A reduced concentration of 5-methyltetrahydrofolate(2-) in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF). 5-methyltetrahydrofolate is the active folate metabolite." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal myelination
Definition: "Any anomaly in the process by which myelin sheaths are formed and maintained around neurons." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, MP:0000920]

Name: Delayed myelination
Definition: "Delayed myelination." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Sacroiliac joint synovitis
Definition: "Inflammation of the synovial membrane of the sacroiliac joint." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Chronic constipation
Definition: "Constipation for longer than three months with fewer than 3 bowel movements per week, straining, lumpy or hard stools, and a sensation of anorectal obstruction or incomplete defecation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Acute constipation
Definition: "Constipation of sudden onset and lasting for less than three months." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Restless legs
Definition: "A feeling of uneasiness and restlessness in the legs after going to bed (sometimes causing insomnia)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Bilateral wrist flexion contracture
Definition: "A chronic loss of wrist joint motion on the right and left sides." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Unilateral wrist flexion contracture
Definition: "A chronic loss of wrist joint motion on one side only." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Medial arterial calcification
Definition: "Calcification, that is, pathological deposition of calcium salts in the tunica media of arteries." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Medial calcification of medium-sized arteries
Definition: "Calcification, that is, pathological deposition of calcium salts in the tunica media of medium-sized (muscular or distributive) arteries." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Medial calcification of small arteries
Definition: "Calcification, that is, pathological deposition of calcium salts in the tunica media of small arteries." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypnic headache
Definition: "A headache disorder that occurs exclusively at night, waking the affected individual from sleep." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20585827, PMID:23832130]

Name: Dysmorphic inferior cerebellar vermis
Definition: "A structural anomaly of the inferior portion of the vermis of cerebellum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Bacteriuria
Definition: "The presence of bacteria in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Chin myoclonus
Definition: "Involuntary and irregular twitches of the chin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16816905]

Name: Elevated transferrin saturation
Definition: "An above normal level of saturation of serum transferrin with iron." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased transferrin saturation
Definition: "A below normal level of saturation of serum transferrin with iron." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated hepatic iron concentration
Definition: "An increased level of iron in liver tissues." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:10922422, PMID:14668426]

Name: Chronic respiratory acidosis
Definition: "Longstanding impairment in ventilation such that the partial pressure of carbon dioxide (PaCO2) is elevated above the upper limit of the reference range (more than 45 mm Hg), with a normal or near-normal pH secondary to renal compensation and an elevated serum bicarbonate levels (more than30 mEq/L)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Acute respiratory acidosis
Definition: "Sudden onset of impairment in ventilation such that the removal of carbon dioxide by the respiratory system is less than the production of carbon dioxide in the tissues, leading to an elevation of the partial pressure of carbon dioxide (PaCO2) above the normal limits (more than 45 mm Hg) with an accompanying acidemia (pH less than 7.35)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Chronic acidosis
Definition: "Longstanding abnormal acid accumulation or depletion of base." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Infantile spasms
Definition: "Infantile spasms represent a subset of \"epileptic spasms\". Infantile Spasms are epileptic spasms starting in the first year of life (infancy)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8486-0558]

Name: Setting-sun eye phenomenon
Definition: "An ophthalmologic sign in young children resulting from upward-gaze paresis. In this condition, the eyes appear driven downward, the sclera may be seen between the upper eyelid and the iris, and part of the lower pupil may be covered by the lower eyelid." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:17030938]

Name: Thick vermilion border
Definition: "Increased width of the skin of vermilion border region of upper lip." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Eclabion
Definition: "A turning outward of the lip or lips, that is, eversion of the lips." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Tongue atrophy
Definition: "Wasting of the tongue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Carotid artery occlusion
Definition: "Complete obstruction of a carotid artery." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Decreased circulating level of specific antibody
Definition: "The presence of normal overall immunoglobulin levels with deficiency of specific immunoglobulins directed against a specific antigen or microorganism." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:17100769]

Name: Decreased specific pneumococcal antibody level
Definition: "The presence of normal overall immunoglobulin levels with deficiency of specific immunoglobulins directed against pneumococci." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Vocal tremor
Definition: "A wavering, unsteady voice that reflects involuntary and approximately sinusoidal oscillation of motor unit firings of laryngeal muscles. Vocal tremor results in low frequency modulations of voice frequency or amplitude and intermittent voice instability." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:22505778]

Name: Temporomandibular joint ankylosis
Definition: "Bony fusion of the mandibular condyle to the base of the skull, resulting in limitation of jaw opening." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Temporomandibular joint crepitus
Definition: "Noises from the temporomandibular joint during mandibular movement (e.g., chewing). Temporomandibular joint crepitus is often described as a clicking, popping, grating sound." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal cerebral vein morphology
Definition: "An anomaly of cerebral veins." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cerebral venous angioma
Definition: "A congenital malformation of veins which drain normal brain characterized by a caput medusae or an umbrellalike convergence of multiple venules on a single, or occasionally multiple, enlarged parenchymal or medullary vein, like the trunk of a tree or the shank of an umbrella. This dilated terminal vein penetrates the cortex to drain either (a) superficially to cortical veins or sinuses, (b) deeply to subependymal veins of the lateral ventricle and then into the galenic system, (c) to the fourth ventricle and then to the pontomesencephalic vein, or (d) to the precentral cerebellar vein and into the galenic system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:8770251]

Name: Frontal venous angioma
Definition: "A venous angioma of the frontal lobe of the brain." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal alpha granules
Definition: "Defective structure, size or content of alpha granules, platelet organelles that contain several growth factors destined for release during platelet activation at sites of vessel wall injury." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7744-1790, PMID:8467233]

Name: Abnormal dense granules
Definition: "Defective structure, size or content of dense granules, platelet organelles that contain granules proaggregatory factors such as adenosine diphosphate (ADP), adenosine triphosphate (ATP), ionized calcium, histamine and serotonin." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7744-1790]

Name: Abnormal surface-connected open canalicular system
Definition: "An anomaly of the invaginations of the surface membrane that form the open canalicular system (OCS). The OCS serve as the pathway for transport of substances into the cells and as conduits for the discharge of alpha granule products secreted during the platelet release reaction." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:1760557]

Name: Myelitis
Definition: "Inflammation of the spinal cord." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cerebellopontine angle arachnoid cyst
Definition: "An arachnoid cyst located at the margin of the cerebellum and pons." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Intraventricular arachnoid cyst
Definition: "An arachnoid cyst located within the ventricular system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:8951893]

Name: Suprasellar arachnoid cyst
Definition: "An arachnoid cyst that progressively enlarges from an abnormality in the membrane of Liliequist or in the interpeduncular cistern, and typically, expands from the prepontine space, displacing the floor of the third ventricle upwards, the pituitary stalk and optic chiasm upwards and forwards, and the mammillary bodies upwards and backwards." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:21586175]

Name: Panniculitis
Definition: "Inflammation of adipose tissue." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal dense tubular system
Definition: "An anomaly of the intracellular membrane complexes known as the dense tubular system." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7744-1790, PMID:1322202]

Name: Cerebral artery stenosis
Definition: "Narrowing or constriction of the inner surface (lumen) of a cerebral artery." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Middle cerebral artery stenosis
Definition: "Narrowing or constriction of the inner surface (lumen) of the middle cerebral artery." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Anterior cerebral artery stenosis
Definition: "Narrowing or constriction of the inner surface (lumen) of the anterior cerebral artery." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Posterior cerebral artery stenosis
Definition: "Narrowing or constriction of the inner surface (lumen) of the posterior cerebral artery." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Reduced maximal inspiratory pressure
Definition: "A decrease in the maximum amount of negative pressure a person can generate during an inhalation." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Reduced maximal expiratory pressure
Definition: "A decrease in the maximum amount of pressure of expired air achieved by a person after a full inspiration." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Nuchal cord
Definition: "A complication of pregnancy and delivery in which the umbilical cord wraps around the fetal neck once or multiple times." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Descending aortic dissection
Definition: "A separation of the layers within the wall of the descending aorta. Tears in the intimal layer result in the propagation of dissection (proximally or distally) secondary to blood entering the intima-media space." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Verrucous papule
Definition: "A wartlike (with multiple small elevated projections) papule." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal brainstem white matter morphology
Definition: "An anomaly of the white matter of brainstem." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormality of the internal capsule
Definition: "An anomaly of the internal capsule, which is an area of white matter in the brain that separates the caudate nucleus and the thalamus from the putamen and the globus pallidus." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal pituitary gland morphology
Definition: "An anomaly of the pituitary gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal size of pituitary gland
Definition: "A deviation from the normal size of the pituitary gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Enlarged pituitary gland
Definition: "An abnormally increased size of the pituitary gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Small pituitary gland
Definition: "An abnormally decreased size of the pituitary gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Weakness of orbicularis oculi muscle
Definition: "Reduced strength of the orbicularis oculi, the circumorbital muscle in the face that closes the eyelid." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Metamorphopsia
Definition: "A visual anomaly in which images appear distorted. A grid of straight lines appears wavy and parts of the grid may appear blank." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Reduced thyroxin-binding globulin
Definition: "An abnormally decreased amount of thyroxin-binding globulin (TBG) in blood. TBG is responsible for carrying the thyroid hormones thyroxine (T4) and 3,5,3'-triiodothyronine (T3) in the bloodstream." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Extra-axial cerebrospinal fluid accumulation
Definition: "An increased amount of cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) in the subarachnoid space." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:22327705, PMID:23838695]

Name: Temporal optic disc pallor
Definition: "A pale yellow discoloration of the temporal (lateral) portion of the optic disc." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19668477]

Name: Diffuse optic disc pallor
Definition: "A pale yellow discoloration of the entire optic disc." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:19668477]

Name: Upper limb pain
Definition: "An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the arm." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Lower limb pain
Definition: "An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the leg." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Hip flexor weakness
Definition: "Reduced ability to flex the femur, that is, to pull the knee upward." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Tetralogy of Fallot with pulmonary atresia
Definition: "An extreme form of tetralogy of Fallot characterized by absence of flow from the right ventricle to the pulmonary arteries." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432, PMID:22368654]

Name: Reduced catalase level
Definition: "An abnormally decreased amount of catalase level." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal circle of Willis morphology
Definition: "An anomaly of the circle of Willis, also known as the cerebral arterial circle." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplastic posterior communicating artery
Definition: "A developmental anomnaly characterized by underdevelopment of the posterior communicating artery." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Dilation of Virchow-Robin spaces
Definition: "Increased dimensions of the Virchow-Robin spaces (also known as perivascular spaces), which surround the walls of vessels as they course from the subarachnoid space through the brain parenchyma. Perivascular spaces are commonly microscopic, and not visible on conventional neuroimaging. This term refers to an increase of size of these spaces such that they are visible on neuroimaging (usually magnetic resonance imaging). The dilatations are regular cavities that always contain a patent artery." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432, PMID:17620468, PMID:23867200, PMID:25564639]

Name: Optic nerve aplasia
Definition: "Congenital absence of the optic nerve." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Spider hemangioma
Definition: "A form of telangiectasis characterized by a central elevated red dot the size of a pinhead, representing an arteriole, with numerous small blood vessels that radiate out thereby resembling the legs of a spider. Characteristically, compression of the central arteriole causes the entire lesion to blanch, and the lesion quickly refills once the compression is released." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:22356347]

Name: Oral aversion
Definition: "Reluctance or refusal of a child to be breastfed or eat, manifested as gagging, vomiting, turning head away from food, or avoidance of sensation in or around the mouth (i.e. toothbrushing or face-washing)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Abnormal platelet shape
Definition: "A deviation from the normal discoid platelet shape." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7744-1790]

Name: Abnormal alpha granule distribution
Definition: "An anomalous location and arrangement of platelet alpha granules." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7744-1790]

Name: Absence of alpha granules
Definition: "A lack of platelet alpha granules. This typically results in the grey appearance of platelets in giemsa stained blood smears." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:3877532]

Name: Abnormal alpha granule content
Definition: "A deviation from the normal contents of the platelet alpha granules, which normally contain hemostatic proteins such as fibrinogen, von Willebrand factor, and growth factors such as platelet-derived growth factor." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal number of alpha granules
Definition: "A deviation from the normal count of alpha granules per thrombocyte." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7744-1790]

Name: Abnormal dense granule content
Definition: "A deviation from the normal contents of the platelet alpha granules, which normally contain adenosine triphosphate (ATP), adenosine diphosphate (ADP), serotonin, calcium, and pyrophosphate, which are secreted when platelets are activated." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7744-1790]

Name: Abnormal number of dense granules
Definition: "A deviation from the normal count of dense granules per thrombocyte." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7744-1790]

Name: Pain
Definition: "An unpleasant sensory and emotional experience associated with actual or potential tissue damage, or described in terms of such damage." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Chronic pain
Definition: "Persistent pain, usually defined as pain that has lasted longer than 3 to 6 months." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:1875958]

Name: Allodynia
Definition: "Pain due to a stimulus that does not normally provoke pain." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Dysesthesia
Definition: "Painful sensations elicited by a nonpainful cutaneous stimulus such as a light touch or gentle stroking over affected areas of the body. Sometimes referred to as hyperpathia or hyperalgesia. Often perceived as an intense burning, dyesthesias may outlast the stimulus by several seconds." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Abnormal synaptic transmission
Definition: "An anomaly in the communication from a neuron to a target across a synapse. This is a four step process, comprising (i) synthesis and storage of neurotransmitters; (ii) neurotransmitter release; (iii) activation of postsynaptic receptors by the neurotransmitter; and (iv) inactivation of the neurotransmitter. Thus, this term is defined as an anomaly of neurotransmitter metabolic process." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, MP:0003635]

Name: Maternal anticardiolipin antibody positive
Definition: "The presence of circulating autoantibodies to anticardiolipin in the mother." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432, PMID:1495720, PMID:9722063]

Name: Food intolerance
Definition: "A detrimental reaction to a food, beverage, food additive, or compound found in foods that produces symptoms in one or more body organs and systems that is not mediated by an immune reaction." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Gluten intolerance
Definition: "A detrimental reaction to the presence of gluten in food, which may include abdominal pain, fatigue, headaches and paresthesia, or celiac disease." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Non-Hodgkin lymphoma
Definition: "A type of lymphoma characterized microscopically by the absence of multinucleated Reed-Sternberg cells." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Axillary epidermoid cyst
Definition: "An epidermoid cyst in the armpit." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Cephalohematoma
Definition: "Hemorrhage between the skull and periosteum of a newborn resulting from rupture of blood vessels that cross the periosteum." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Onychauxis
Definition: "Thickened nails without deformity." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hemosiderinuria
Definition: "The presence of hemosiderin in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Elevated circulating aldolase concentration
Definition: "Concentration of fructose 1,6-bisphosphate aldolase in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Reduced circulating aldolase concentration
Definition: "Concentration of fructose 1,6-bisphosphate aldolase in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Skewed maternal X inactivation
Definition: "A deviation from equal (50%) inactivation of each parental X chromosome in maternal cells." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:18097476]

Name: Abnormal involuntary eye movements
Definition: "Anomalous movements of the eyes that occur without the subject wanting them to happen." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Fatty replacement of skeletal muscle
Definition: "Muscle fibers degeneration resulting in fatty replacement of skeletal muscle fibers" [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9046-3540, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Conjunctival lipoma
Definition: "A lipoma (a benign tumor composed of adipose tissue) located in the conjunctiva." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Colonic varices
Definition: "The presence of varices (enlarged and convoluted blood vessels) in the colon." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16688816]

Name: Absent neutrophil specific granules
Definition: "Lack of specific granules in neutrophils." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:6155073]

Name: Increased neutrophil nuclear projections
Definition: "Presence of an elevated number of projections from nuclei of neutrophils. These projections can have the shape of hooks, tags, or clubs." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hypoplastic thumbnail
Definition: "A thumbnail that is diminished in length and width, i.e., underdeveloped thumb nail." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent thumbnail
Definition: "Absence of thumb nail." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Absent nail of hallux
Definition: "Absent nail of big toe." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperbeta-alaninemia
Definition: "Increased concentration of beta-alanine in the blood." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: EEG with centrotemporal focal spike waves
Definition: "EEG with focal sharp transient waves in the centrotemporal region of the brain (also known as the central sulcus), i.e., focal sharp waves of a duration less than 80 msec followed by a slow wave." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal T3/T4 ratio
Definition: "A ratio of serum triiodothyronine (T3) to thyroxine (T4) in the blood that deviates from normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:16982586]

Name: Increased T3/T4 ratio
Definition: "A ratio of serum triiodothyronine (T3) to thyroxine (T4) in the blood that is higher than normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Decreased T3/T4 ratio
Definition: "A ratio of serum triiodothyronine (T3) to thyroxine (T4) in the blood that is lower than normal." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Unicuspid aortic valve
Definition: "The presence of an aortic valve with one instead of the normal three cusps (flaps)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:18480095, PMID:20329493]

Name: Premature epimetaphyseal fusion in hand
Definition: "Stop of growth at the epiphyseal plate the hyaline cartilage plate in the metaphysis at one or more long bones in the hand, at an earlier than normal age, resulting in growth arrest and shortening of the involved bone." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Premature epimetaphyseal fusion in foot
