Name: Elevated circulating alpha-aminoadipic semialdehyde concentration
Definition: "Increased concentration of alpha-aminoadipic semialdehyde in the blood circulation." [PMID:17560822]

Name: Fracture blister
Definition: "Fracture blister is a type of blister that forms following acute bone fractures, typically near the ankle, wrist elbow or foot, where skin adheres tightly to bone with little subcutaneous fat cushioning. The blister that results resembles that of a second degree burn." [PMID:21691490]

Name: Decreased beta-mannosidase activity
Definition: "Activity of the enzyme beta-mannosidase below the lower limit of normal. Beta-mannosidase is a lysosomal enzyme that catabolizes oligosaccharides." []

Name: Urolithiasis
Definition: "Renal stones are formed within the kidneys, and this is called nephrolithiasis. Urolithiasis is a condition that occurs when these stones exit the renal pelvis and move into the remainder of the urinary collecting system, which includes the ureters, bladder, and urethra." [PMID:32644527]

Name: Decreased level of coenzyme Q10 in skeletal muscle
Definition: "Reduced amount of coenzyme Q10,a naturally occurring quinone, in skeletal muscle tissue." [PMID:16400613]

Name: Reduced circulating prekallikrein concentration
Definition: "Reduced concentration of prekallikrein (PK; also known as Fletcher factor) in the blood circulation. PK is the precursor of plasma kallikrein, a serine protease that activates kinins. PK is cleaved to produce kallikrein by activated Factor XII." [PMID:15461630]

Name: External tibial torsion
Definition: "External twisting of the tibia resulting in the toes of each foot pointing outward (outtoeing) ." []

Name: Trident acetabulum
Definition: "Abnormal appearance of the acetabulum characterized by spurs at the medial and lateral acetabular margin and in the center of the acetabulum, giving rise to shape resembling a three-pronged spear sadi to resemble a trident." [PMID:28744080]

Name: Spherophakia
Definition: "Spherophakia is a rare congenital condition that presents with weak zonules around a smaller and more spherical crystalline lens with an increased anteroposterior thickness of the lens, and highly myopic eye. The lens zonules are developmentally hypoplastic and abnormally weak and due to non-attachment of the posterior zonules to the equatorial zone of the lens, the lens changes its normal shape to spherical." []

Name: Atrioventricular valve regurgitation
Definition: "Regurgitation of a heart valve that controls blood flow from a an atrium to a ventricle, including mitral, tricuspid, or, rarely, single atrioventicular valve." []

Name: Single atrioventricular valve regurgitation
Definition: "Regurgitation of the single atrioventricular valve regurgitation (AVVR) in the context of a congenital heart defect with a single ventricle. Roughly three quarters of patients following Fontan procedure display AVVR." [PMID:32419552]

Name: Urethrovesical occlusion
Definition: "Blockage of the flow of urine from the bladder into the urethra." []

Name: obsolete Vascular granular osmiophilic material deposition
Definition: "Accumulation of granular osmiophilic material in blood vessel walls. Osmiophilic material becomes black upon staining with osmium tetroxide." [PMID:17183453]

Name: Juvenile type testicular granulosa cell tumor
Definition: "Juvenile granulosa cell tumor of the testis of neonates and infants is an uncommon lesion frequently associated with abnormal sex chromosome and ambiguous genitalia." [NCIT:C4207, PMID:17652550]

Name: Central nervous system axonal spheroid
Definition: "Axonal spheroids are bubble-like biological features that form on most degenerating axons. During neurodegeneration, bubble-like swellings form along the length of the axon, a primary and early effect of dynamic axonal deformation. These varicosities, spheroids, or swellings have been described as beads on a string and branches bearing fruit, and they frequently appear on degenerating axons. The focal swellings on degenerating axons, axonal spheroids, are often filled with cellular debris such as organelles, pathological proteins, and disorganized cytoskeletal elements." [PMID:27423618, PMID:34678457]

Name: Disease remission
Definition: "A decrease in or disappearance of signs and symptoms typically associated with a disease course." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8314-2140]

Name: Elevated circulating biliverdin concentration
Definition: "Increased concentration of biliverdin, a green tetrapyrrolic bile pigment, in the blood circulation." [PMID:19580635]

Name: Elevated circulating insulin:C-peptide ratio
Definition: "Increased ratio of insulin to C-peptide in the blood circulation." [PMID:15161766]

Name: Abnormal left ventricular endsystolic diameter
Definition: "A deviation from the normal range of the left ventricular endsystolic diameter." [PMID:24451180]

Name: Reduced left ventricular endsystolic diameter
Definition: "A lower than normal left ventricular endsystolic diameter." []

Name: Bacterial encephalitis
Definition: "Encephalitis caused by bacterial infection." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6310-0434, PMID:20952256]

Name: Hilar lymph node enlargement
Definition: "Hilar lymphadenopathy is swelling or enlargement of lymph nodes localised in hila, wedge-shaped anatomical structures containing pulmonary vessels, major bronchi, nerves and lymph nodes. Hilar lymph nodes are not visible on chest X-ray if they are not enlarged. Hilar lymph node enlargement can be caused by benign and malignant conditions and can be symmetrical (bilateral) or asymmetrical (unilateral)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4095-8489]

Name: Pulmonary vein varix
Definition: "Pulmonary vein varix (PVV), refers to a localised dilatation of a pulmonary vein. PVV is a rare condition and can be congenital or acquired. PVV typically occur at the confluence of the veins adjacent to the left atrium. PVVs are sometimes classified into three morphological types: saccular, tortuous and confluent." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4095-8489]

Name: Decreased CSF glycine concentration
Definition: "Abnormally decreased levels of glycine in cerebrospinal fluid." []

Name: Elbow contracture
Definition: "A limitation in the passive range of motion of the elbow resulting from loss of elasticity in the periarticular tissues owing to structural changes of non-bony tissues, such as muscles, tendons, ligaments, joint capsules or skin." []

Name: Joint contracture
Definition: "A limitation in the passive range of motion of the elbow resulting from loss of elasticity in the periarticular tissues owing to structural changes of non-bony tissues, such as muscles, tendons, ligaments, joint capsules or skin. A contracture prevents movement of the associated body part." [PMID:22938881, PMID:26247029, PMID:30928194]

Name: Elbow extension contracture
Definition: "An elbow contracture that limits the ability of the elbow joint to flex (flexion of the the elbow joint refers to bending the elbow joint to bring the hand closer to the shoulder), meaning that the elbow is fixed in an extended (straight) position." []

Name: Forearm supination contracture
Definition: "A contracture that limits the ability of the forearm to stabilize the hand in pronation (pronation refers to a rotation of the forearm that causes the palm and forearm to face downwards), meaning that the palm is fixed in a upward orientation. Restriction of supination/pronation can occur at the elbow (radial-humeral joint), at the wrist (radial-ulnar joint), and anywhere in between." []

Name: Forearm pronation contracture
Definition: "A contracture that limits the ability of the forearm to stabilize the hand in supiation (supination refers to a rotation of the forearm that causes the palm and forearm to face upwards), meaning that the palm is fixed in a downward orientation. Restriction of supination/pronation can occur at the elbow (radial-humeral joint), at the wrist (radial-ulnar joint), and anywhere in between." []

Name: Hippocampal malrotation
Definition: "Hippocampal malrotation, also termed incomplete inversion of the hippocampus or hippocampal malformation, is an increasingly recognized neuroimaging finding of undetermined clinical significance. It is characterized by features including (i) Round or pyramidal shape instead of ovoid shape; (ii) Medial position of the hippocampus on the hippocampal sulcus; (iii) The collateral sulcus is excessively deep or verticalized; (iv) Fimbria located medial to the hippocampus; (v) Small or displaced fornix; (vi) Enlarged temporal horn and empty choroid fissure; (vii) Thickened subiculum; (viii) Reduced upper horizontal portion of the parahippocampal gyrus." [PMID:33916495]

Name: Claw toe deformity
Definition: "Claw toes are characterized by hyperextension at the metatarsal-phalangeal joints and flexion of the interphalangeal joints." [PMID:28461920]

Name: Toe deformity
Definition: "Abnormal positioning of toe phalanges. Deformities of the lesser toes often occur gradually, though they can be brought on by trauma. The main adult sagittal plane deformities consist of claw toes, hammer toes and mallet toes. Axial plane deformities include crossover toes." [PMID:28461920]

Name: Prolonged central motor conduction time
Definition: "Increased duration of the central motor conduction time (CMCT). The CMCT estimates the conduction time of corticospinal fibers between motor cortex and spinal (or bulbar) motoneurons. It includes the times for excitation of cortical cells, conduction via the corticobulbar-corticospinal tract and excitation of the motoneuron sufficient to reach its firing threshold. CMCT is calculated by subtracting the peripheral conduction time from the MEP latency recorded after cortical stimulation." [PMID:24752292]

Name: Circumferential skin creases on extremities
Definition: "Ringed creases of the skin of the extremities related to folding of excess skin." [PMID:26637975]

Name: Atypical teratoid/rhabdoid tumor
Definition: "An aggressive malignant embryonal neoplasm arising from the central nervous system. It is composed of cells with a large eccentric nucleus, prominent nucleolus, and abundant cytoplasm. Mutations of the SMARCB1 gene or very rarely SMARCA4 (BRG1) gene are present. The vast majority of cases occur in childhood. Symptoms include lethargy, vomiting, cranial nerve palsy, headache, and hemiplegia." []

Name: Rhabdoid tumor of the kidney
Definition: "A highly aggressive, extremely rare neoplasm of the kidney that is usually seen in children. The term rhabdoid is used because the tumor cells resemble rhabdomyoblasts but lack myogenic markers, and pathologic diagnosis requires familiarity with these microscopic features plus awareness that adult onset is possible. It can be associated with abnormalities of chromosome 22. It is characterized by the presence of cells with a large eccentric nucleus, prominent nucleolus, and abundant cytoplasm." [NCIT:C8715, PMID:24982576, PMID:33692948]

Name: Subcutaneous panniculitis-like T-cell lymphoma
Definition: "A form of T-cell non-Hodgkin lymphoma in which cytotoxic CD8+ T cells infiltrate adipose tissue forming subcutaneous nodules." []

Name: Fungal hyphae in sputum
Definition: "Presence of hyphae (long, branching, filamentous structures produced by fungi) in sputum." []

Name: Enlarged tectum
Definition: "Increasaed size of the tectum, which is the region of the midbrain posterior to the cerebral aqueduct of Sylvius. The midbrain is the most superior portion of the brainstem." [PMID:23518331]

Name: Reduced circulating 3-ketoacyl-CoA thiolase concentration
Definition: "Decreased concentration of 3-ketoacyl-CoA thiolase in th blood circulation." []

Name: Solitary angiokeratoma
Definition: "A dark, keratotic papule about 2-10 mm in diameter, usually occuring on the lower extremeities. Usually the lesions begin as bright, soft, and nonkeratotic paules which grow larger and change to a firm, blue to black and keratotic stage." [PMID:8993949]

Name: Fordyce angiokeratoma
Definition: "A type of angiokeratoma that most commonly occurs on the scrotum of patients who are 40 years old or older. The typical single lesion is a dark red to blue dome-shaped papule 2-4 mm in diameter with a very discrete keratotic surface. Typically, they are multiple and arranged in a line parallel to the raphe mediana of the scrotum. They also occur on the vulva and less commnly on the penis." [PMID:8993949]

Name: Angiokeratoma circumscriptum naeviforme
Definition: "A type of angiokeratoma that typically presents in childhood as a large, mostly linear and unilateral hyperkeratotic plaque which is composed of confluent keratotic papules. The size ranges from a few centimeters up to a major part of the body surface. Initially the lesions present asa multile reddish macules, clinically similar to a nevus flammeus. Within several years they develop into acanthokeratotic papules that agrregate into plaques which may have a hyperkeratotic surface." [PMID:8993949]

Name: Angiokeratoma of Mibelli
Definition: "A type of angiokeratoma that typically presents in women on the dorsa of fingers and toes and multiple dark red papules with a slightly verrucous surface, each measuring about 3-5 mm in diameter." [PMID:8993949]

Name: Laryngeal mass
Definition: "A lump in the region of the larynx. A mass is any lump in the body that can be caused by the abnormal growth of cells, a cyst, hormonal changes or an immune reaction. Typically a mass is an initial finding that will lead to additional workup. Laryngeal masses can be visualized by multiple methods include computed tomography." []

Name: Palate mass
Definition: "A lump in the region of the palate. A mass is any lump in the body that can be caused by the abnormal growth of cells, a cyst, hormonal changes or an immune reaction. Typically a mass is an initial finding that will lead to additional workup." []

Name: Thick oral frenulum
Definition: "Increased thickness of an oral frenulum, flaps of mucous membrane that extend from the midline gingiva to the upper or lower lip." []

Name: Tooth avulsion
Definition: "A type of dental trauma characterized by total dislocation of the tooth from its socket." [PMID:30969698]

Name: Torn oral frenulum
Definition: "Laceration or tear of an oral frenulum, flaps of mucous membrane that extend from the midline gingiva to the upper or lower lip." [PMID:25426684]

Name: Intraoral laceration
Definition: "A wound of the mucosa within the oral cavity covering lips, tongue, palate, gingiva, pharynx, or retropharynx." []

Name: Erythematous oral mucosa
Definition: "An erythematous lesion of the oral mucosa may result from a variety of tissue alterations, including inflammation, erythrocyte extravasation, and atrophy or reduced keratinization of the surface epithelium." [PMID:30693460]

Name: Mitral chordae tendinae rupture
Definition: "Breakage of the chordae tendinae of the mitral valve. This can lead to loss of tension of one of the mitral valve leaflets and mitral regurgitation." [PMID:30470812]

Name: History of cardiovascular procedure
Definition: "Indicates that a cardiovascular procedure such as stenting, bypass, catherization was performed on a patient." []

Name: Ejection click
Definition: "A high-pitched sound that occurs at the moment of maximal opening of the aortic or pulmonary valves. They are heard just after the first heart sound. The sounds occur in the presence of a dilated aorta or pulmonary artery or in the presence of a bicuspid or flexible stenotic aortic or pulmonary valve. Ejection clicks may also be called ejection sounds." []

Name: Cryofibrinogenemia
Definition: "Cryofibrinogen is an abnormal protein that forms precipitate only in plasma. consisting of fibrinogen, fibronectin, alpha1-antitrypsin and alpha2-macroglobulin." [PMID:27789759]

Name: triggered by allergens
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure to allergens." []

Name: Clicking tinnitus
Definition: "A type of tinnitus that presents as clicks, resembling the noise made by the snapping together of 2 fingers." [PMID:34147152]

Name: Reduced hair sulfur content
Definition: "Abnormally low amount of sulfur in hair." [PMID:11369901]

Name: Chromhidrosis
Definition: "Secretion of colored sweat." [PMID:32119282]

Name: Purulent eye discharge
Definition: "Secretion of pus-like (purulent) material from the eye, which may caused the eyelids to be matted together." []

Name: Megaloblepharon
Definition: "Disproportionately large eyelids" [PMID:4236972]

Name: Bacteria in cerebrospinal fluid
Definition: "Presence of bacteria in the cerebrospinal fluid, as manifested by visual inspection or bacterial culture results." []

Name: Joint crepitus
Definition: "A popping, clicking or crackling sound that accompaniees movement of a joint." []

Name: Intertriginous distribution
Definition: "Applies to the localization of a skin lesion involving any area of the body where two opposing skin surfaces can touch and rub or chaff." [PMID:21396557]

Name: Distributed along skin tension lines
Definition: "Applies to the localization of a skin lesion that correspond to skin tension lines, which are linear clefts in the skin that indicate the direction of orientation of the underlying collagen fibers. Skin tension lines are also known as Langer's lines or lines of cleavage." []

Name: Abnormal communication
Definition: "Presence of any form of communication (e.g., verbal or non-verbal) that does not align with cultural expectations or developmental level." []

Name: Abnormal eye contact
Definition: "Any abnormality of eye contact behavior. We define eye contact as a form of nonverbal communication between two individuals who are facing each other in which an individual directs the eyes towards the eyes or face of the other individual. Eye contact occurs frequently and voluntarily during face-to-face verbal communication. The duration and frequency of eye contact that is interpreted to be appropriate may follow social and situational norms." []

Name: Gaze avoidance
Definition: "A deliberate avoidance of eye contact." []

Name: Excessive eye contact
Definition: "Tendency to maintain sustained eye contact for an inappropriately long period of time." [PMID:29182643]

Name: Balanitis
Definition: "Inflammation of glans penis" []

Name: Instep location
Definition: "Applies to an abnormality that is situated in the arched middle portion of the foot in front of the ankle joint (i.e., instep)." []

Name: Ameliorated by ultraviolet light exposure
Definition: "Applies to a skin lesion that is improved or made more bearable by exposure to ultraviolet light (sunshine or phototherapy)." []

Name: Decreased circulating aspartic acid concentration
Definition: "An reduced concentration of aspartic acid in the blood circulation." []

Name: Abnormal circulating erythropoietin concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of erythropoietin in the blood circulation. Erythropoietin is a glycoprotein hormone produced by the peritubular cells of the kidney that stimulates red blood cell production." []

Name: Reduced circulating erythropoietin concentration
Definition: "Decreased concentration of erythropoietin in the blood circulation. Erythropoietin is a glycoprotein hormone produced by the peritubular cells of the kidney that stimulates red blood cell production." [PMID:30725682]

Name: Abnormal gamma-glutamyltransferase level
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal level of the enzyme gamma-glutamyltransferase (GGT). GGT is mainly present in kidney, liver, and pancreatic cells, but small amounts are present in other tissues." []

Name: Reduced gamma-glutamyltransferase level
Definition: "Decreased level of the enzyme gamma-glutamyltransferase (GGT). GGT is mainly present in kidney, liver, and pancreatic cells, but small amounts are present in other tissues." []

Name: Elevated circulating histamine concentration
Definition: "Increased concentration of histamine in the blood circulation." []

Name: Increased circulating interleukin 18 concentration
Definition: "An increased concentration of interleukin-18 in the blood circulation." []

Name: Abnormal phytanic acid:pristanic acid ratio
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal ratio of blood phytanic acid concentration to pristanic acid concentration." [PMID:21570468]

Name: Increased phytanic acid:pristanic acid ratio
Definition: "An elevation above the normal ratio of blood phytanic acid concentration to pristanic acid concentration." [PMID:31822849]

Name: Decreased phytanic acid:pristanic acid ratio
Definition: "A reduction below the normal ratio of blood phytanic acid concentration to pristanic acid concentration." []

Name: Rectovesical fistula
Definition: "An aberrant, pathological communication between the rectum and the bladder." []

Name: Rectoureteral fistula
Definition: "An abnormal connection (fistula) between the rectum and the ureter." []

Name: Hypoplastic umbilicus
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the umbilicus." []

Name: Arachnoid granulation
Definition: "Arachnoid granulations (AGs) are tufts of arachnoid membrane invaginated into the dural sinuses through which cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) enters the venous system. The lesions are primarily located in the parasagittal region along the superior sagittal sinus, which is occasionally seen at the transverse sinus. Normally dural venous sinus AGs typically range from 2 to 8 mm in size, but may grow enough to expand the dural sinuses, and even the inner table, diploic space and outer table of the skull." [PMID:22900137]

Name: Increased CSF taurine concentration
Definition: "Increased concentration of taurine in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF)." []

Name: Elevated circulating glutathione concentration
Definition: "An abnormally increased level of glutathione in the blood circulation." []

Name: Hawkinsinuria
Definition: "The concentration of hawkinsin in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated urinary phenylpyruvic acid level
Definition: "An abnormally increased amount of phenylpyruvic acid in the urine." []

Name: Ameliorated by lumbar puncture
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by lumbar puncture." []

Name: Increased CSF uracil concentration
Definition: "An increased level of uracil in the cerebrospinal fluid." []

Name: Elevated urine kynurenine level
Definition: "An abnormally increased amount of kynurenine in the urine." []

Name: Increased CSF L-alloisoleucine concentration
Definition: "An abnormally increased concentration of L-alloisoleucine in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF)." []

Name: Hydroxylysinemia
Definition: "An increased concentration of hydroxylysine in the blood circulation. Hydroxylysine arises from a post-translational hydroxy modification of lysine and is unique to collagen and proteins containing collagen-like sequences. Elevated concentrations of hydroxylysine may indicate increased bone turnover." [PMID:404321]

Name: Homocitrullinuria
Definition: "An increased amount of L-homocitrulline in the urine. L-homocitrulline is an L-lysine derivative that is L-lysine having a carbamoyl group at the N(6)-position. It is found in individuals with urea cycle disorders." []

Name: 2-hydroxyadipic aciduria
Definition: "An increase in the level of 2-hydroxyadipic acid in the urine." []

Name: Homoargininuria
Definition: "An increased amount of homoarginine in the urine. Homoarginine is a nonproteinogenic alpha amino acid." []

Name: Increased urinary cysteine level
Definition: "An increased concentration of cysteine in the urine." []

Name: Gastric xanthoma
Definition: "Gastric xanthomas (also known as xanthelasmas) are are plaque-like red lesions defined by the presence of histiocytic containing lipids." [PMID:32149048]

Name: Decreased stool elastase level
Definition: "Reduced amount of pancreatic elastase in the stool. This feature may be observed with pancreatic insufficiency." []

Name: Elevated stool chloride content
Definition: "Elevated amount of chloride in the stool." [PMID:2651131]

Name: Increased fecal coproporphyrin III:coproporphyrin I ratio
Definition: "Abnormal relative increase in the amount of fecal coproporphyrin III as compared to coproporphyrin I in the feces." []

Name: Increased fecal harderoporphyrin
Definition: "Abnormally high concentration of harderoporphyrin in feces." []

Name: Increased fecal heptacarboxylporphyrin
Definition: "Abnormally high concentration of heptacarboxylporphyrin in feces." []

Name: Increased fecal pentacarboxylporphyrin
Definition: "Abnormally high concentration of pentacarboxylporphyrin in feces." []

Name: Increased fecal isocoproporphyrin
Definition: "Abnormally high concentration of isocoproporphyrin in feces." []

Name: Positive fecal Clostridium botulinum test
Definition: "Identification of Clostridium botulinum toxin in the feces." [PMID:16614251]

Name: Perihepatic adhesions
Definition: "Abnormal union of the membranous surfaces of the liver capsule and the parietal peritoneum due to inflammation or injury. Adhesions may be visualized by laparoscopy and may have a violin string appearance." [PMID:11528133]

Name: Dilated vas deferens
Definition: "Abnormal increase in diameter (expansion) of the vas deferens." []

Name: Enlarged epididymis
Definition: "Abnormal increase in the size of the epididymis." []

Name: Atypical gestures
Definition: "Spontaneous production of communicative gestures that are perceived as odd or mechanical, or are poorly integrated with other means of communication. This may include inaccurate mimicry of typical gestures." []

Name: Bone marrow vacuolated lymphocytes
Definition: "The presence of lymphocytes with multilple vacuoles (a membrane-bound cell organelle) in the bone marrow." []

Name: Spinal cord calcifications
Definition: "The presence of calcium deposition in the spinal cord." [PMID:21427441]

Name: Neuroepithelial cyst
Definition: "A benign epithelial-lined cystic lesion that can occur anywhere in the neuraxis. Neuroepithelial cysts are ependymal or epithelial lined fluid collections of unknown etiology within the central nervous system parenchyma with no obvious ventricular or subarachnoid connection. Most cysts are asymptomatic, however, some present with seizures, mass effect, or rarely with movement disorders. On imaging, they present as CSF-like parenchymal cysts with smooth, rounded borders and minimal or no surrounding signal intensity abnormality." [PMID:14672275]

Name: Reduced circulating interleukin 7 concentration
Definition: "A diminished concentration of interleukin-7 in the circulation." []

Name: Increased circulating interleukin 12 concentration
Definition: "An increased concentration of interleukin-12 in the blood circulation." []

Name: Increased circulating interleukin 13 concentration
Definition: "An increased concentration of interleukin-13 in the blood circulation." []

Name: Increased circulating interleukin 2 concentration
Definition: "An increased concentration of interleukin-2 in the blood circulation." []

Name: Increased circulating interleukin 4 concentration
Definition: "An increased concentration of interleukin-4 in the blood circulation." []

Name: Increased circulating interleukin 5 concentration
Definition: "An increased concentration of interleukin-5 in the blood circulation." []

Name: Salpingitis
Definition: "An inflammation of the fallopian tube." [PMID:19017411]

Name: Tubo-ovarian abscess
Definition: "A tubo-ovarian abscess (TOA) is a complex infectious mass of the adnexa that forms as a sequela of pelvic inflammatory disease." [PMID:28846347]

Name: Opacified paranasal sinuses
Definition: "White appearance (radio-opaqueness) of a paranasal sinus on radiography." [PMID:16369155]

Name: Elevated brain glutamine level by MRS
Definition: "An increased in the level of glutamine in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS)." []

Name: Abnormal brain glutamine level by MRS
Definition: "A deviation from normal in the level of glutamine in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS)." []

Name: Increased urinary hexanoic acid level
Definition: "The concentration of hexanoic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Hepatic focal nodular hyperplasia
Definition: "Hepatic focal nodular hyperplasia (FNH) is a benign hepatic tumor. FNH develops within hepatic parenchymal tissue that is otherwise histologically normal. Macroscopically, the tumor is characterized by the presence of depressed, grayish-white scar, which is generally (but not always) located at the center of the lesion, with fibrous septa radiating outward, toward the periphery of the tumor. This stellate scar is found in only 50% of all FNH nodules, but its presence is regarded as pathognomonic. The lesion itself is usually lighter in color than the tissue that surrounds it, and it sometimes has a yellowish hue. FNH nodules are generally not capsulated; their margins are well defined, and they are sometimes lobulated." [PMID:23396642]

Name: Increased bone marrow iron
Definition: "An increased amount of iron in the bone marrow." [PMID:70541]

Name: Glenoid fracture
Definition: "A fracture of the glenoid fossa, a relatively shallow dish is located on the lateral scapula and is the socket portion of the shoulder joint that meets to articulate the humeral head." [PMID:31335046]

Name: Widened mediastinum
Definition: "Abnormal increase in the width of the mediastinum, often defined as being greater than 6 to 8 cm." [PMID:30969712]

Name: Narrow mediastinum
Definition: "Abnormal decrease in the width of the mediastinum." []

Name: Ovarian torsion
Definition: "Ovarian torsion is a twisting of the ligaments that support the adnexa, cutting off the blood flow to the ovary." [PMID:32809510]

Name: Septate gallbladder
Definition: "Septate gallbladder is characterized by the presence of a septum that divides the gallbladder in two chambers. When the septum dividing the gallbladder lies longitudinally it is called bilobed gallbladder and when there is a transverse septum separating the fundus from the rest of the gallbladder it is called an hour-glass gallbladder." [PMID:19547674]

Name: Gallbladder wall thickening
Definition: "Abnormal increased in the thickness of the wall of the gallbladder." [PMID:24370153]

Name: Gallbladder enlargement
Definition: "Abnormal increased in the thickness of the size of the gallbladder." [PMID:34496644]

Name: Gallbladder mass
Definition: "An abnormal lesion or swelling seen on gallbladder imaging." []

Name: Fingerprint bodies
Definition: "Fingerprint bodies are inclusion bodies located at the periphery of the muscle fibers underneath the sarcolemma (subsarcolemmal), consisting of non-membrane-bound packed lamellae arranged in concentric patterns resembling fingerprints." [PMID:32008911]

Name: Spheroid bodies
Definition: "An accumulation of myofilamentous material within individual muscle fibers, forming usually round but occasionally elongated bodies ranging from 2 to 15 pm in size. The so-called spheroid bodies stain green with the modified trichrome preparation and are mainly present in the periphery of type 1 muscle fibers, where they may occupy large sectors sharply demarcated from the remainder of the cross-sectioned muscle fiber." [PMID:571956]

Name: Abnormal muscle tissue enzyme activity or level
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal activity or histological staining of an enzyme in muscle tissue, usually measured in a muscle biopsy specimen." []

Name: Reduced muscle aconitase activity
Definition: "Diminished activity of the enzyne aconitase in muscle tissue." [PMID:29079705]

Name: Transitional-cell carcinoma of the ureter
Definition: "A cancer of the ureter that most often arises in the distal third of the ureter and is often diagnosed during the sixth and seventh decades of life. The most common presentation is gross hematuria or flank pain." [PMID:11394453]

Name: Increased circulating Interferon-alpha concentration
Definition: "An elevation in the concentration of interferon alpha measured in the blood circulation." []

Name: Liver hamartoma
Definition: "A benign (noncancerous) tumorlike malformation made up of an abnormal mixture of cells and tissues that originates in the liver." []

Name: Ameloblastoma
Definition: "Ameloblastoma is a benign odontogenic tumor generally present in the jaw bone. The tumor originates from the residual epithelium of the tooth germ, epithelium of odontogenic cysts stratified squamous epithelium and epithelium of the enamel organ." [PMID:26015700]

Name: Ameliorated by ketogenic diet
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by following a ketogenic diet." []

Name: Pretibial hyperpigmentation
Definition: "Darkening of the area of skin that overlies the shin." [PMID:27745832]

Name: Gingival fragility
Definition: "Gums that are easily damaged." [PMID:34741498]

Name: Muscle fiber fuchsinophilic inclusion bodies
Definition: "The presence of inclusion bodies within the cytoplasm of muscle cells that react positively with acid fuchsin." []

Name: Esophageal myenteric plexus degeneration
Definition: "Deterioration of the cells of the myenteric plexus (also known as the Auerbach plexus) located between the layers of the muscular propria of the esophagus." []

Name: Periorificial hyperkeratosis
Definition: "Scaling and overgrowth of horny tissue of the skin surrounding body orifices (including peri-auricular, peri-oral, peri-anal areas." [PMID:22405088]

Name: Eosinophilic lymph node infiltration
Definition: "Presence of an elevated number of eosinophils in a lymph node (usually as demonstrated by lymph node biopsy)." []

Name: Blood parasite
Definition: "Detection of a parasitic organism in the blood stream. Blood parasites include malaria plasmodia, microfilaria species, trypanosomes (the causative agents of African sleeping sickness and South American Changas disease) and the causative agents of schistosomiasis of the bladder and the intestine." [PMID:12731420]

Name: Bloodstream trypomastigotes
Definition: "Presence of trypomastigote parasites in the blood stream. This finding can be demonstrated by the identification of trypomastigote parasites on peripheral blood smear." []

Name: Adamantinoma
Definition: "A primary low-grade, malignant bone tumor that is predominantly located in the mid-portion of the tibia. Histologically, classic adamantinoma is a biphasic tumor characterized by epithelial and osteofibrous components that may be intermingled with each other in various proportions and differentiating patterns." [PMID:18279517]

Name: Abnormal enzyme activity in muscle tissue
Definition: "Deviation from the normal activity of an enzyme in muscle tissue." []

Name: Reduced muscle phosphoglycerate kinase activity
Definition: "Reduced activity of phosphoglycerate kinase (PGK) in muscle tissue. PGK is a glycolytic enzyme that catalyses one of the two ATP-producing reactions in the glycolytic pathway, through the conversion of 1,3-bisphosphoglycerate to 3-phosphoglycerate." [PMID:8998855]

Name: Reduced fibroblast type III procollagen synthesis
Definition: "Diminished production of type III procollagen by cultured skin fibroblasts." []

Name: Reduced muscle myoadenylate deaminase activity
Definition: "Diminished activity of the enzyme myoadenylate deaminase. Myoadenylate deaminase is the muscle isoform of adenosine monophosphate (AMP) deaminase and catalyzes the deamination of AMP to inosine monophosphate and ammonia." [PMID:10996775]

Name: Bent long bone
Definition: "A developmental defect of a long bone, such as the femur or the humerus, characterized by a sharply curve deviation located in the metaphysis (shaft) of the bone." [PMID:25250905]

Name: Tracheal rupture
Definition: "A break or tear in the trachea." [PMID:20693885]

Name: Increased myocardial glycogen content
Definition: "Elevated amount of glycogen in the myocardium." []

Name: Triggered by monoamine oxidase inhibitor
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure to a monoamine oxidase inhibitor." [PMID:30969670]

Name: Triggered by serotonin reuptake inhibitor
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure to a serotonin reuptake inhibitor." [PMID:32119293]

Name: Ameliorated by acetazolamide
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by treatment with acetazolamide." []

Name: Ameliorated by exposure to medication
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by treatment with a medication. Terms in this subhierarchy are intended to be used for cases in which the fact that a manifestation of a disease responds to a specific treatment can be used in the differential diagnosis." []

Name: Ameliorated by vitamin B12
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by treatment with vitamin B12." []

Name: Ameliorated by thiamine
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by treatment with thiamine." []

Name: Ameliorated by dantrolene
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by treatment with dantrolene." []

Name: Ameliorated by biotin
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by treatment with biotin." []

Name: Reduced bone-marrow megakaryocyte size
Definition: "Decreased in average size (diameter) of megakaryocytes in the bone marrow. Megakaryocyte diameter can be assessed as using automated cellular imaging systems." [PMID:17515875]

Name: Hairshafts with longitudinal grooves
Definition: "Long narrow depressions running lengthwise in hairshafts. This feature can be appreciated by scanning electron microsopy." [PMID:11234560]

Name: Mycobacterium bacteremia
Definition: "Presence of viable mycobacteria in the blood." [PMID:2498390]

Name: Decreased delta-aminolevulinate dehydratase activity
Definition: "Reduced activity of the enzyme delta-aminolevulinate dehydratase. The enzyme is active in erythrocytes." []

Name: Elevated circulating pancreatic secretory trypsin inhibitor activity
Definition: "Increased activity of the enzyme pancreatic secretory trypsin inhibitor in the blood circulation." [PMID:21607145]

Name: Presence of uterus in 46,XY individual
Definition: "A developmental anomaly in which an individual with an X chromosome and a Y chromosome (usually 46,XY) has a uterus. The uterus and Fallopian tubes are derived from the Müllerian duct and thus this phenotype is generally also associated with the presence of Fallopian tubes." [PMID:25905393]

Name: Intraluminal meconium calcification
Definition: "Deposition of calcium in meconium present in the internal cavity of the fetal bowel. This manifestation may be the result of any distal intestinal obstruction." []

Name: Portal vein hypoplasia
Definition: "A developmental defect characterized by underdevelopment of hte portal vein." []

Name: Adrenal leiomyoma
Definition: "Adrenal leiomyoma is a rare, benign solid tumor that develops from the smooth muscle of the adrenal vein and its tributaries" [PMID:34340048]

Name: Small intestinal lymphoplasmacytic infiltrate
Definition: "Infiltration of the wall of the small intestine by lymphocytes and mature plasma cells." [PMID:8343045]

Name: Triggered by neuroleptic medication
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure to neuroleptic (also known as antipsychotic) medication." [PMID:29083668]

Name: Abnormal peroxisomal morphology
Definition: "Structural anomaly of peroxisomes, which are small, membrane-enclosed metabolic organelles with roles in the metabolism of complex lipids and reactive ionic species." [PMID:35788297]

Name: Absence of peroxisomes
Definition: "Lack of observable peroxisomes. This feature can be observed by immunohistochemical staining of cultured cells (such as fibroblasts) or by electronmicroscopy." [PMID:8940266]

Name: Paucity of peroxisomes
Definition: "Reduced number of observable peroxisomes per cell. This feature can be observed by immunohistochemical staining of cultured cells (such as fibroblasts) or by electronmicroscopy." []

Name: Reduced sulfide:quinone oxidoreductase activity
Definition: "Reduced activity of the enzyme sulfide:quinone oxidoreductase, which typically is measured in a biopsy specimen from liver or muscle." []

Name: Deficit at segmental level
Definition: "Refers to distribution of neurological deficits that corresponds to a deficit of a specific spinal segment and all segments below it." []

Name: Rhabdoid tumor
Definition: "Rhabdoid tumors are rare aggressive malignancies in infants and young children with a poor prognosis. The most common anatomic localizations are the central nervous system, the kidneys, and other soft tissues." [PMID:33692948]

Name: Rhabdoid tumor of the ovary
Definition: "A highly aggressive, extremely rare neoplasm of the ovary that is usually seen in children. The term rhabdoid is used because the tumor cells resemble rhabdomyoblasts but lack myogenic markers." [PMID:26076162, PMID:26349416]

Name: Cardiac rhabdoid tumor
Definition: "A rare and aggressive neoplasms developing mainly in the kidney but also in cerebral and extra-cerebral tissues and rarely in the heart. Histologically, rhabdoid renal and extrarenal tumors share common characteristics. The cells are polygonal, with eccentric, vesicular nuclei and prominent nucleoli, eosinophilic cytoplasmic inclusions. The tumors have an infiltrative growth pattern, necrosis, and high proliferative index. The immunohistochemistry tools of investigation facilitate differential diagnosis by showing loss of INI-1 expression, usually accompanied by germline mutations of the SMARCB1 gene. When INI-1 is still expressed in the affected tissues, a rhabdoid tumor with SMARCA4 mutations should be considered." [PMID:35883926]

Name: Malignant rhabdoid tumor of the bladder
Definition: "A rhabdoid tumor (a rare aggressive malignancies in infants and young children with a poor prognosis) originating in the urinary bladder." [PMID:31733273]

Name: Malignant rhabdoid tumor of liver
Definition: "A malginant rhabdoid tumor (MRT) originating in the liver. MRT are best characterized by the presence of round or polygonal cells with abundant eosinophilic cytoplasm, typical eosinophilic perinuclear inclusions, vesicular nuclei and prominent nucleoli. Immunohistochemical expression of vimentin and epithelial markers and lack of staining for S-100, myoglobin and desmin are commonly found, but are non-specific." []

Name: Malignant rhabdoid tumor of muscle
Definition: "A malginant rhabdoid tumor (MRT) originating in muscle tissue." [PMID:33658498]

Name: Neck teratoma
Definition: "A teratoma located in the neck." []

Name: Kidney teratoma
Definition: "A teratoma located in a kidney." []

Name: Elevated urinary 5-amino-4-imidazolecarboxamide-riboside level
Definition: "Increased amount of 5-amino-4-imidazolecarboxamide(AICA)-riboside in the urine. AICA-riboside is the dephosphorylated counterpart of AICAR, an intermediate of de novo purine biosynthesis." [PMID:15114530]

Name: Aplasia of posterior communicating artery
Definition: "A developmental anomnaly characterized by the lack of development of the posterior communicating artery." []

Name: Optic pit
Definition: "A developmental anomaloy characterized by congenital excavation of the optic nerve head." [PMID:27847606]

Name: Ameliorated by naloxone
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by treatment with naloxone, an opioid antagonist." []

Name: Ameliorated by pyridoxal phosphate
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by ingestion of pyridoxal phosphate (activated vitamin B6)." []

Name: Thickened intrahepatic portal venules
Definition: "Increased width of the vascular wall of portal venules within the liver." [PMID:30900187]

Name: Ovarian fibrosis
Definition: "Excessive proliferation of fibroblasts and deposition of extracellular matrix within the ovary." [PMID:28139522]

Name: Pigment incontinence
Definition: "A process in which melanosomes (melanin granules) are deposited in the dermis. The dermal melanosomes are observed to be mainly in macrophages. This phenomenon of pigmentary incontinence usually follows an inflammatory process with the basic feature of basal cell damage, such as in lichen planus, lupus erythematosus, Riehl's melanosis, incontinentia pigmenti (Bloch-Sulzberger), and fixed drug eruption. Incontinence of pigment, or dropping off of epidermal melanin into the dermis, frequently produces a clinically recognizable and characteristic slate-gray pigmentation." [PMID:16045670, PMID:6222085]

Name: Reduced epidermal keratin 10 protein expression
Definition: "Amount of keratin 10 in the epidermis below the lower limit of normal. The findiong is typically ascertained by immunofluorescent microscopy." [PMID:21176769]

Name: Reduced epidermal collagen IV protein expression
Reduced epidermal bullous pemphigoid antigen 1 protein expression
Definition: "Lower than normal amount of bullous pemphigoid antigen 1 (BP230) in the epidermis." []

Name: Reduced epidermal collagen VII protein expression
Reduced epidermal collagen XVII protein expression
Reduced epidermal integrin alpha6beta4 protein expression
Bloodstream Trypanosoma cruzi
Definition: "Presence of Trypanosoma cruzi in the blood stream. Trypanosoma cruzii is the etiological agent of Chagas disease." [PMID:26162928]

Name: Abnormal lymph node cell composition
Definition: "A deviation from the normal distribution of cell types or their relative proprotions in a lymph node." []

Name: Lipid-laden lymph node macrophages
Definition: "Lymph node with increased numbers of macrophages heavily laden with lipids." [PMID:22488251]

Name: Abnormal pancreatic acinus morphology
Definition: "Structural anomal of pancreatic acinus." [PMID:16423553]

Name: Cochlear nerve hypoplasia
Definition: "A developmental defect characterized by underdevelopment of the cochlear nerve." [PMID:25986071]

Name: Glutathionuria
Definition: "Level of glutathione in the urine above the upper limit of normal." [PMID:29483667]

Name: Nevus psiloliparus
Definition: "Nevus psiloliparus is a rare fatty tissue nevus that is a marker for encephalocraniocutaneous lipomatosis, a neurocutaneous syndrome with ocular and central nervous system anomalies. Clinically, nevus psiloliparus is often described as a congenital alopecia and appears as an irregularly shaped, circumscribed area of alopecia on the scalp. Histopathology demonstrates a near-complete absence of mature hair follicles with preservation of arrector pili muscles and mature adipocytes within the dermis." [PMID:32034785]

Name: Crypt hyperplasia
Definition: "Crypt hyperplasia denotes elongation of the length of the crypts of Lieberkuhn, a process that initially precedes villous atrophy. Elongation may be caused by expansion of the lamina propria as a result of the proliferation of stromal cells, an influx of inflammatory cells and tissue remodelling." [PMID:17021129]

Name: Increased circulating dehydroepiandrosterone-sulfate concentration
Definition: "Concentration of dehydroepiandrosterone-sulfate in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal." [PMID:18252794]

Name: Abnormal circulating thyroxine-binding globulin concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of thyroxine-binding globulin (TBG) in the blood circulation." []

Name: Decreased circulating thyroxine-binding globulin concentration
Definition: "A reduction from the normal concentration of thyroxine-binding globulin (TBG) in the blood circulation." []

Name: Elevated circulating beta-aminoisobutyric acid concentration
Definition: "An increased concentration of beta-aminoisobutyric acid in the blood circulation." []

Name: Elevated circulating dihydrouracil concentration
Definition: "An increased concentration of dihydrouracil in the blood circulation. Dihydrouracil is an intermediate in the catabolism of uracil that is also known as 5,6-dihydrouracil." []

Name: Elevated circulating dihydrothymine concentration
Definition: "An increased concentration of dihydrothymine in the blood circulation. Dihydrouracil is an intermediate in the catabolism of thymine." []

Name: Elevated circulating N-carbamyl-beta-alanine concentration
Definition: "An increased concentrationof N-carbamyl-beta-alanine in the blood circulation." []

Name: Elevated ciculating 5-hydroxymethyluracil concentration
Definition: "An increased concentration of 5-hydroxymethyluracil in the blood circulation." []

Name: Decreased CSF creatinine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of creatinine in the cerebrrospinal fluid below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated urinary creatine level
Definition: "An increased amount of creatine in the urine." []

Name: Decreased circulating biotin concentration
Definition: "Concentration of biotin in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated circulating thrombopoietin concentration
Definition: "Concentration of thrombopoietin in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. Thrombopoietin is a glycoprotein hormone produced by the liver and kidney that stimulates the production and differentiation of megakaryocytes." []

Name: Decreased circulating C1q concentration
Definition: "Concentration or activity of the C1q protein in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal. C1q is the first component of the classical pathway and is composed of the C1qA chain, C1qB chain, and C1qC chain, which are encoded by C1qA, C1qB, and C1qC genes." [PMID:24160257]

Name: Decreased circulating apolipoprotein A-II concentration
Definition: "Concentration of apolipoprotein A-II below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated circulating CA19-9 concentration
Definition: "Concentration of CA19-9 above the upper limit of normal." [PMID:26530370]

Name: Elevated circulating DOPA concentration
Definition: "Concentration of DOPA (3,4-dihydroxyphenylalanine) in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated CSF DOPA concentration
Definition: "Concentration of DOPA (3,4-dihydroxyphenylalanine) in the cerebrospinal fluid above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated circulating porphyrin concentration
Definition: "Concentration of porphyrins or of a specific porphryin above the upper limit of normal. The most commonly tested circulating porphyrins are coproporphyrin, protoporphyrin, and uroporphyrin. Normally protoporphyrin is present in the highest concentration." []

Name: Decreased circulating 17-hydroxyprogesterone concentration
Definition: "Concentration of 17-hydroxyprogesterone in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Decreased circulating transcobalamin II concentration
Definition: "Concentration of transcobalamin II in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Polychromasia
Definition: "Increased variation in the color of the erythrocytes (red blood cells), including pale red, normal or dark colors, indicating a highly variable hemoglobin concentration. Typically this indicates the release of immature erythrocytes in states of anemia." [PMID:83524]

Name: Decreased circulating myo-inositol concentration
Definition: "Concentration of myo-inositol in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated circulating arabitol concentration
Definition: "Concentration of arabitol in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated urine arabitol level
Definition: "Amount of arabitol in the urine above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated urine erythritol level
Definition: "Amount of erythritol in the urine above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated circulating erythritol concentration
Definition: "Concentration of erythritol in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Reduced circulating matrix metalloproteinase 2 concentration
Definition: "Concentration of matrix metalloproteinase 2 in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal." [PMID:11062721]

Name: Abnormal circulating coenzyme concentration
Definition: "Concentration of a coenzyme (an organic molecule that binds to the active sites of an enzyme to promote the catalysis of a reaction) is above or below the limits of normal." []

Name: Elevated circulating S-adenosyl methionine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of S-adenosyl methionine (SAM) in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. SAM is a cosubstrate involved in methyl group transfers, transsulfuration, and aminopropylation." []

Name: Abnormal circulating membrane cofactor protein concentration
Definition: "Concentration of membrane cofactor protein in the blood circulation outside the limits of normal. Membrane cofactor protein (MCP, CD46) is a cell surface complement regulatory protein which acts as a cofactor for the factor I-mediated cleavage of the activated complement components C3b/C4b." []

Name: Decreased circulating membrane cofactor protein concentration
Definition: "Concentration of membrane cofactor protein in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated circulating membrane cofactor protein concentration
Definition: "Concentration of membrane cofactor protein in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Hepatic xanthomatosis
Definition: "Lipid deposits localized within the liver. Xanthomas are benign but are often an important visible sign of systemic conditions such as familial hypercholesterolemia." [PMID:32965912]

Name: Adrenal xanthomatosis
Definition: "Lipid deposits localized within the adrenal gland. Xanthomas are benign but are often an important visible sign of systemic conditions such as familial hypercholesterolemia." [PMID:32965912]

Name: Splenic xanthomatosis
Definition: "Lipid deposits localized within the spleen. Xanthomas are benign but are often an important visible sign of systemic conditions such as familial hypercholesterolemia." [PMID:32965912]

Name: Spinal cord xanthomatosis
Definition: "Lipid deposits localized within the spinal cord. Xanthomas are benign but are often an important visible sign of systemic conditions such as familial hypercholesterolemia." [PMID:32965912]

Name: Brain xanthomatosis
Definition: "Lipid deposits localized within the brain. Xanthomas are benign but are often an important visible sign of systemic conditions such as familial hypercholesterolemia." [PMID:32965912]

Name: Pulmonary xanthomatosis
Definition: "Lipid deposits localized within the lung. Xanthomas are benign but are often an important visible sign of systemic conditions such as familial hypercholesterolemia." [PMID:32965912]

Name: Bone marrow xanthomatosis
Definition: "Lipid deposits localized within the bone marrow. Xanthomas are benign but are often an important visible sign of systemic conditions such as familial hypercholesterolemia." [PMID:32965912]

Name: Lymph node xanthomatosis
Definition: "Lipid deposits localized within one or more lymph nodes. Xanthomas are benign but are often an important visible sign of systemic conditions such as familial hypercholesterolemia." [PMID:32965912]

Name: Xanthoma of bone
Definition: "Xanthoma of bone is an exceedingly rare benign primary bone tumor histologically characterized by mononuclear macrophage-like cells, abundant foam cells, and multinucleated giant cells." [PMID:19223950]

Name: Ameliorated by folinic acid
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by treatment with folinic acid." []

Name: Triggered by succinylcholine anesthetic
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure to a succinylcholine anesthetic such as suxamethonium." []

Name: Exogenous androgen exposure
Definition: "History of having been treated with an exogenous androgen medication." []

Name: Reduced muscle enolase activity
Definition: "Diminished activity of the enzyme enolase in muscle tissue. The enzyme enolase catalyzes the interconversion of 2-phosphoglycerate and phosphoenolpyruvate. In adult human muscle, over 90% of enolase activity is accounted for by the beta-enolase subunit, the protein product of the ENO3 gene." [PMID:11506403]

Name: Dopamine antagonist exposure
Definition: "History of having been treated with a dopamine antagonist including metaclopramide, phenothiazine; haloperidol, chlorpromazine, promethazine, prochlorperazine, ziprasidone, and quetiapine." []

Name: Muscle fiber granulofilamentous inclusion bodies
Definition: "The presence of inclusion bodies within the cytoplasm of muscle cells that contain a mxiture of granules and filaments." [PMID:19181099]

Name: Bone marrow myeloid vacuolization
Definition: "Formation of vacuoles (a space within a cell that is empty of cytoplasm, lined with a membrane, and filled with fluid) in the cytoplasm of myeloid precursors in the bone marrow." [PMID:33690844]

Name: Pulmonary cylindroma
Definition: "A cylindroma located in the lung. Cylindromas are well-circumscribed, smooth, pale pink nodular tumors, often with arborizing vessels visible. The tumors are slow growing and vary in size from a few millimeters to over 5 mm." [PMID:29569226, PMID:32298062]

Name: Colonic fibrinopurulent exudate
Definition: "Fluid visible on the colonic surface containing fibrin, inflammatory cells, and cellular debris." []

Name: Bloodstream microfilaria
Definition: "Presence of filaria in the blood stream. Filariasis is a common cause of elephantiasis in Coastal Districts of India. The initial manifestations are repeated episodes of fever with chills and rigor, lymphadenopathy which gradually progress to elephantiasis. In India filarial infestation is commonly caused by W. bancrofti and Brugia malayi, the former responsible for almost 98 percent of all cases." [PMID:32313484]

Name: Skin infectious agent
Definition: "The presence of an infectious agent in the skin." []

Name: Dermal microfilaria
Definition: "Presence of filariae in the skin." [PMID:31340993]

Name: Dermal papillary IgA deposition
Definition: "Accumulation of immunoglobulin A (IgA) surrounding dermal papillae, which are specialized cells that support the hair follicle." [PMID:33426564]

Name: Dermal immune complex deposition
Definition: "Accumulation of antigen-bound antibody in the skin." []

Name: Abnormal liver metabolite concentration
Definition: "The concentration of a metabolite in the liver is above or below the limits of normal." []

Name: Hepatic polyglucosan accumulation
Definition: "Intracellular accumulation of polyglucosan bodies-containing amylopectinlike polysaccharide-in the liver." []

Name: Urinary bladder neurofibroma
Definition: "A neurofibroma (benign peripheral nerve sheath tumor) located in the urinary bladder." []

Name: Synovial granuloma
Definition: "An aggregation of macrophages (forming in response to chronic inflammation) localized in the lining of a joint (synovium)." []

Name: Elevated urine fumaric acid level
Definition: "The concentration of fumaric acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated urine N-acetylaspartic acid level
Definition: "Amoutn of N-acetylaspartate high in the urine above upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated urine suberylglycine level
Definition: "Level of suberylglycine in urine above upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated urine phenylpropionylglycine level
Definition: "Level of phenylpropionylglycine in urine above upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated urine octenedioic acid level
Definition: "The concentration of octenedioic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Monocarboxylic aciduria
Definition: "Level of a monocarboxylic acid in the urine above the upper limit of normal. A monocarboxylic acid is an oxoacid containing one carboxy group." []

Name: Elevated urine octanoic acid level
Definition: "Amount of octanoic acid in the urine above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated urine glutaconic acid level
Definition: "The concentration of glutaconic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated urine 3-hydroxyglutaric level
Definition: "The concentration of 3-hydroxyglutaric acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated urine malonic acid level
Definition: "The concentration of malonic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated urine propionylglycine level
Definition: "Amount of propionylglycine in the urine above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated urine tiglylglycine level
Definition: "Amount of tiglylglycine in the urine above upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated urine 2-methylacetoacetic acid level
Definition: "Amount of 2-methylacetoacetic acid in the urine above upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated urine 3-hydroxypropionic acid level
Definition: "Amount of 3-hydroxypropionic acid in the urine above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated urine 2-methylcitric acid level
Definition: "Amount of 2-methylcitric acid in the urine above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated urine 4-hydroxyisovaleric acid level
Definition: "Amount of 4-hydroxyisovaleric acid in urine above upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated urine 2-hydroxy-3-methylvaleric acid level
Definition: "Amount of 2-hydroxy-3-methylvaleric acid in the urine above the upper limit of normal. 2-Hydroxy-3-methylpentanoic acid or 2-hydroxy-3-methylvaleric acid (HMVA) is an organic acid generated by L-isoleucine metabolism." []

Name: Shoulder contracture
Definition: "Lack of full passive range of motion (restrictions in flexion, extension, or other movements) of the shoulder joint resulting from structural changes of non-bony tissues, such as muscles, tendons, ligaments, joint capsules and/or skin." [PMID:16214063, PMID:24975760, PMID:31282072]

Name: Shoulder extension contracture
Definition: "Lack of the full expected passive range of flexion of the shoulder joint (Shoulder flexion puts the arms from a resting position at one's sides to straight above the head; thus, with shoulder extension contracture it is not possible to raise the arms above the head fully)." [PMID:31282072]

Name: Thumb extension contracture
Definition: "Movement in the sagittal plane that increases the angle of the thumb joint (straightens the joint); motion involving posterior bending of the vertebral column or returning to the upright position from a flexed position." []

Name: Tongue myxoma
Definition: "A myxoma (benign soft tissue neoplasm characterized by the presence of spindle and stellate cells, lobulated growth pattern, and myxoid stroma formation) localized in the tongue." [PMID:36276237]

Name: Abnormal knee morphology
Definition: "A structural abnormality of the knee joint or surrounding structures." []

Name: Abnormal knee physiology
Definition: "A functional anomaly of the knee joint." []

Name: Knee contracture
Definition: "Lack of full passive range of motion (restrictions in flexion, extension, or other movements) of the knee joint resulting from structural changes of non-bony tissues, such as muscles, tendons, ligaments, joint capsules and/or skin." [PMID:16214063, PMID:24975760, PMID:31282072]

Name: Knee extension contracture
Definition: "A type of knee joint contracture in which the knee lacks full expected flexion, such that the upper and lower leg cannot be brought together." [PMID:31282072]

Name: Abnormal ankle morphology
Definition: "A structural anomaly of the ankle." []

Name: Abnormal ankle physiology
Definition: "A functional anomaly of the ankle." []

Name: Toe joint contracture
Definition: "Lack of full passive range of motion (restrictions in flexion, extension, or other movements) of a toe joint resulting from structural changes of non-bony tissues, such as muscles, tendons, ligaments, joint capsules and/or skin." [PMID:16214063, PMID:24975760, PMID:31282072]

Name: Extension contracture of toe
Definition: "A type of toe joint contracture in which the joint lacks full expected flexion, so that the two bony segments on either side of their connecting joint cannot be brought together." [PMID:31282072]

Name: Finger joint contracture
Definition: "Lack of full passive range of motion (restrictions in flexion, extension, or other movements) of a finger joint resulting from structural changes of non-bony tissues, such as muscles, tendons, ligaments, joint capsules and/or skin." [PMID:16214063, PMID:24975760, PMID:31282072]

Name: Extension contracture of finger
Definition: "A type of finger joint contracture in which the joint lacks full expected flexion, so that the two bony segments on either side of their connecting joint cannot be brought together." [PMID:31282072]

Name: Reduced muscle telethonin level
Definition: "Amount of telethonin protein expression in muscle tissue below lower limit of normal. Telethonin is a 19-kDa sarcomeric protein, localized to the Z-disc of skeletal and cardiac muscles." []

Name: Abnormal enzyme concentration or activity
Definition: "Concentration or activity of an enzyme is above or below the limits of normal." []

Name: Abnormal liver enzyme activity or concentration
Definition: "Concentration or activity of an enzyme is above or below the limits of normal in liver tissue." []

Name: Reduced hepatic urocanase activity
Definition: "Activity of urocanase in the liver below the lower limit of normal." [PMID:19304569]

Name: Impaired cerebroside sulfate hydrolysis
Definition: "Reduced hydrolysis (splitting of a bond and the addition of the hydrogen anion of water) of the sulfuric ester linkage in the molecule of cerebroside sulfate, possibly leading to accumuation of cerebroside sulfate." [PMID:6137805]

Name: Reduced peroxisomal glutaryl-CoA oxidase activity
Definition: "Diminished enzyme activity of peroxisomal glutaryl-CoA oxidase, an enzyme that metabolizes glutaryl-CoA (a metabolite of L-lysine, L-hydroxy-lysine and L-tryptophan) by dehydrogenation to glutaconyl-CoA directly followed by decarboxylation of this to crotonyl-CoA." [PMID:6547838]

Name: Reduced sterol 27-hydroxylase activity
Definition: "Diminished activity of the enzyme sterol 27-hydroxylase, which participates in the degradation of cholesterol to bile acid. Sterol 27-hydroxylase catalyzes the first step in the normal oxidation of the steroid side chain, converting cholesterol, as well as different 7a-hydroxylated cholesterol metabolites, to 27-oxygenated steroids." [PMID:10856919]

Name: Reduced short-chain acyl-CoA dehydrogenase activity
Definition: "Diminished activbity of the enzyme Short-chain acyl-CoA dehydrogenase (SCAD), a key enzyme of fatty acid beta-oxidation that catalyses the first step in mitochondrial beta-oxidation of fatty acids." [PMID:26989860]

Name: Reduced 3-phosphoglycerate dehydrogenase activity
Definition: "Diminished activity of the enzyme 3-phosphoglycerate dehydrogenase (PGDH), which catalyzes the first step in the pathway by converting D-3-phosphoglycerate (PGA), an intermediate in glycolysis, to phosphohydroxypyruvate concomitant with the reduction of NAD+." [PMID:30619878]

Name: Elongated mitochondria
Definition: "Increase in length of mitochondria." [PMID:33262702]

Name: Reduced hepatic methionine adenosyltransferase activity
Definition: "Activity of methionine adenosyltransferase in the liver below the lower limit of normal. Note that there are multiple methionine adenosyltransferase isoezymes." [PMID:20675163]

Name: Substantia nigra dopaminergic neuron loss
Definition: "Degeneration and loss of neruons in the substantia nigra of the brain." [PMID:30028088]

Name: Intramuscular lipoma
Definition: "A lipoma that is located within a muscle." []

Name: Cutaneous telangiectasia
Definition: "Dilated blood vessels on the skin." []

Name: Abnormal aromatase activity
Definition: "Aromatase activity outside of the normal range." []

Name: Elevated aromatase activity
Definition: "Enzyme activity of aromatase above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Reduced aromatase activity
Definition: "Enzyme activity of aromatase below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Corneal amyloidosis
Definition: "A form of amyloidosis that is located in the cornea." []

Name: Abnormal keratinocyte morphology
Definition: "Any structural anomaly of the keratinocyte. The keratinocyte is the major cell type of the epidermis and is responsible for generating the protective barrier." [PMID:9114819]

Name: Keratinocyte vacuolization
Definition: "Increased number of vacuoles (membrane-bound organelles that areempty of cytoplasm, lined with a membrane, and filled with fluid) in keratinocytes." []

Name: Parotid gland adenocarcinoma
Definition: "An adenocarcinoma that arises from the parotid gland." []

Name: Pulmonary vasculitis
Definition: "Cellular inflammation, vessel destruction, and tissue necrosis of the blood vessels of the lung." [PMID:16493151]

Name: Reduced hepatic D-glycerate kinase activity
Definition: "Activity of D-glycerate kinase in the liver below the lower limit of normal." [PMID:2537226]

Name: Lymph-node hemophagocytosis
Definition: "Phagocytosis of erythrocytes, lymphocytes or other hematopoietic precursors by histiocytes or macrophages in a lymph node." [PMID:16859547]

Name: Superior pubic ramus hypoplasia
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the upper branch of the pubis bone (inferior pubic ramus)." [PMID:19104687]

Name: Uterine adenofibroma
Definition: "A rare benign mullerian mixed tumor of the uterus composed of benign epithelial and mesenchymal components." []

Name: Pulmonary hamartoma
Definition: "A benign malformation of the lung that includes an abnormal mixture of tissue components such as cartilage, epithelium, fat, or muscle which are common to the lung but without preservation of the organ architecture." [PMID:30969628]

Name: Peripheral axonal distension
Definition: "An abnormal histological finding characterized by an increase in the cross-section area of peripheral nerve axons (up to 20-25 micrometers in diameter)." [PMID:15897506]

Name: Decreased alpha-mannosidase activity
Definition: "Activity of the enzyme alpha-mannosidase below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Abnormal hepatocyte morphology
Definition: "A structural anomaly of the hepatocyte, which is the main cell type that makes up the liver perncyhma. Hepatocytes are usually binucleated and appear as sheets in the liver tissue." []

Name: Hepatic melanin-like lysosomal pigmentation
Definition: "Accumulation of dark, coarsely granular pigment localized in lysosomes of centrilobular hepatocytes." []

Name: Reduced uroporphyrinogen decarboxylase activity
Definition: "Activity of the enzyme uroporphyrinogen decarboxylase (UROD; EC 4.1.1.37) below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Reduced heme oxygenase activity
Definition: "Activity of the enzyme heme oxygenase below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Swollen achromatic neurons in the cerebral cortex
Definition: "The presence of enlarged and swollen neurons that lack Nissl bodies (the rough endoplasmic reticulum-achromasia refers to neurons that lack Nissl bodies) in the cortex of the brain." [PMID:8171960]

Name: Vacuolated hepatocytes
Definition: "Presence of vacuoles (membrane-bound organelles that areempty of cytoplasm, lined with a membrane, and filled with fluid) in hepatocytes, which normally rarely contain vacuoles." []

Name: Lack of oocyte pronucleus formation
Definition: "An abnormality of oocyte maturation characterized by the inability of oocytes to form pronuclei after in vitro fertilization procedures. Oocytes normally show two pronuclei 17 to 20 hours after in vitro insemination." [PMID:34552114]

Name: Self-healing squamous epithelioma
Definition: "A type of skin tumor that initially presents as a reddish macule and subsequently becomes papular, enlarged, ulcerated and ultimately heals leaving pitted scars." [PMID:33256177]

Name: Elevated circulating pristanic acid concentration
Definition: "Concentration of pristanic acid in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal." [PMID:16685654]

Name: Sarcoplasmic bodies
Definition: "Rounded or oval structures that appeared brown on hematoxylin and eosin and red on the modified Gomori trichrome stain." []

Name: Reduced CSF cystine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of cystine in the cerebrospinal fluid below the lower limit of normal. Cystine is sulfur-containing amino acid obtained by the oxidation of two cysteine molecules which are then linked via a disulfide bond." []

Name: Abnormal beta-mannosidase activity
Definition: "Activity of the enzyme beta-mannosidase outside normal limits. Beta-mannosidase is a lysosomal enzyme that catabolizes oligosaccharides." []

Name: Elevated beta-mannosidase activity
Definition: "Activity of the enzyme beta-mannosidase above the upper limit of normal. Beta-mannosidase is a lysosomal enzyme that catabolizes oligosaccharides." []

Name: Reduced alpha-L-fucosidase activity
Definition: "Activity of the enzyme alpha-L-fucosidase below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Abnormal alpha-L-fucosidase activity
Definition: "Activity of the enzyme alpha-L-fucosidase outside the limits of normal." []

Name: Elevated alpha-L-fucosidase activity
Definition: "Activity of the enzyme alpha-L-fucosidase above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated circulating S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine concentration
Definition: "Increased concentration of S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine in the blood circulation." [PMID:21963049]

Name: Elevated circulating S-adenosyl-L-methionine concentration
Definition: "Concentration S-adenosyl-L-methionine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Exercise-triggered malignant hyperthermia
Definition: "Malignant hyperthermia that is characterized by exercise-induced life-threatening hyperthermia with a body temperature over 40 degrees C and signs of encephalopathy ranging from confusion to convulsions or coma. Incidence increases with rising ambient temperature and relative humidity. Manifestations may include rhabdomyolysis (presenting with myalgia, muscle weakness, and myoglobinuria), tachycardia, and in severe cases multiorgan failure." []

Name: Anesthesic-triggered malignant hyperthermia
Definition: "Malignant hyperthermia that is characterized by a rapid increase in temperature to 39-42 degrees C in response to inhalational anesthetics such as halothane or to muscle relaxants such as succinylcholine." []

Name: Elevated CSF argininosuccinic acid concentration
Definition: "Concentration of argininosuccinic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated CSF aspartylglucosamine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of aspartylglucosamine in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated circulating alpha-oxoadipic acid concentration
Definition: "Concentration of alpha-oxoadipic acid in the blood above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Abnormal erythrocyte metabolite concentration
Definition: "A deviation from the normal range of a metabolite in red blood cells." []

Name: Reduced erythrocyte glutathione concentration
Definition: "Concentration of glutathione in red blood cells below the lower limit of normal. Glutathione (GSH) is an important redox active biomolecule critical in the maintenance and regulation of cellular and organismal health." [PMID:23938402]

Name: Elevated CSF sarcosine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of sarcosine in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Reduced CSF methionine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of methionine in the cerebrospinal fluid below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated circulating homoarginine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of homoarginine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated urinary formiminoglutamic acid level
Definition: "The concentration of formiminoglutamic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated CSF proline concentration
Definition: "Concentration of proline in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated urinary S-sulfocysteine level
Definition: "Level of S-sulfocysteine high in urine above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated circulating S-sulfocysteine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of S-sulfocysteine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Sertoli cell hyperplasia
Definition: "Abnormal increase in the number of Sertoli cells in the testis." [PMID:32809466]

Name: CSF infectious agent
Definition: "The presence of an infectious agent in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF)." []

Name: CSF mycobacteria
Definition: "Mycobacterium present in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF). This feature can be ascertained by CSF microscopy." []

Name: Fungal bloodstream infection
Definition: "Detection of a fungal organism (such as candida or coccidioides) in the blood stream." []

Name: Supraclavicular lymphadenopathy
Definition: "Enlarged lymph node located just above the clavicle (collarbone)." []

Name: Inguinal lymphadenopathy
Definition: "Enlarged lymph node located in the inguinal region (groin)." []

Name: Axillary lymphadenopathy
Definition: "Enlarged lymph node located in the axillary region (armpit)." []

Name: Positive Murphy sign
Definition: "Murphy's sign is elicited in patients with acute cholecystitis by asking the patient to take in and hold a deep breath while palpating the subcostal region. In practice, Murphy's sign is performed by palpating the subcostal region during inspiration. If pain is elicited and the patient suddenly stops their inspiratory effort, a positive Murphy's sign has been elicited." []

Name: Bilious emesis
Definition: "Vomiting whereby the vomit has the color of bile, yellowish-green." []

Name: Ameliorated by NSAID
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by treatment with a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID)." []

Name: Fetal exposure history
Definition: "A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to a medication or other substance." []

Name: Fetal barbiturate exposure
Definition: "A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to barbiturate medications such as phenobarbital. Barbiturates are used medically as anxiolytics, hypnotics, and anticonvulsants." []

Name: Fetal narcotic exposure
Definition: "A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to narcotic medications such as morphine or codeine. Narcotics are used medically to treat moderate or severe pain." []

Name: Ameliorated by ethosuximide
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by administration of ethosuximide. Ethosuximide is most often used to treat absence seizures." []

Name: Reduced epidermal extracellular matrix protein 1 protein expression
Definition: "Lower than normal amount of extracellular matrix protein 1 (ECM1) in the epidermis." []

Name: Neurofibroma by anatomical location
Definition: "Neurofibroma categorized according to the anatomical site of origin." []

Name: Tongue neurofibroma
