Definition: "A neurofibroma (benign peripheral nerve sheath tumor) localized in the tongue." []

Name: Cardiac neurofibroma
Definition: "A neurofibroma (benign peripheral nerve sheath tumor) localized in the heart." []

Name: Gastric neurofibroma
Definition: "A neurofibroma (benign peripheral nerve sheath tumor) localized in the stomach." []

Name: Renal neurofibroma
Definition: "A neurofibroma (benign peripheral nerve sheath tumor) localized in the kidney." []

Name: Muscle fiber polyglucosan inclusion bodies
Definition: "Accumulation of a poorly branched and poorly spherical amylopectin-like glycogen (polyglucosan) in muscle fibers." [PMID:26652229]

Name: Abnormal rete ridge morphology
Definition: "Abnormal structure of the rete ridges (also known as rete pegs), which are downward projections of epithelium surrounding the connective tissue papillae in between the dermal papillae." []

Name: Rete ridge elongation
Definition: "Increased length of the rete rdiges of the epidermis." []

Name: Pulmonary Langerhans cell histiocytosis
Definition: "Accumulation of monoclonal CD1a-positive Langerhans cells in the bronchioles and alveolar interstitium that can cause damage to the lungs." []

Name: Lumbar hypolordosis
Definition: "Flattening of a curve in the spine in the lumbar (lower back) region." []

Name: Battle sign
Definition: "Battle sign is bruising over the mastoid process that is typically the result of head trauma. It is retroauricular or mastoid ecchymosis that is typically the result of head trauma. Battle sign typically requires significant head trauma and may indicate significant internal injury to the brain and not just the posterior cranial vault or mastoid." []

Name: Decreased skull base length
Definition: "Reduced anterioposterior dimension of the skull base." [PMID:8989469]

Name: Oscillopsia
Definition: "A visual disturbance in which objects in the visual field appear to oscillate (jump, jiggle, vibrate)." [PMID:21102332]

Name: Decreased blink rate
Definition: "The frequency with which the eye is blinked is below the lower limit of normal." [PMID:2265915]

Name: Abnormal blink rate
Definition: "A deviation from the normal frequency of blinking the eye." [PMID:2265915]

Name: Elevated blink rate
Definition: "The frequecy with which the eye is blinked is above the upper limit of normal." [PMID:2265915]

Name: Purulent sputum
Definition: "Sputum contains pus." []

Name: Maternal hyperthyroidism
Definition: "The mother of a fetus or index patient has a history of hyperthyroidism during the corresponding pregnancy." []

Name: Perineal
Definition: "Applies to an abnormality that affects the perineum (the region of skin between the genitals and the anus)." []

Name: Gadolinium exposure
Definition: "History of exposure to gadolinium, a contrast medium often used for magnetic resonance imaging." []

Name: Purulent parotid gland drainage
Definition: "Excretion of pus (purulent discharge) from the opening of the parotid duct." [PMID:34952006]

Name: Obstipation
Definition: "Obstipation is the inability to pass either stool or flatus (gas)." []

Name: Posttussive emesis
Definition: "Vomiting following a coughing spell." []

Name: Vasculitis by anatomical site
Definition: "Vasculitis categorized according to the anatomical site where the finding is localized." []

Name: Vasculitis by histology
Definition: "Vasculitis categorized according to type of histological abnormality." []

Name: Leukocytoclastic vasculitis
Definition: "A type of vasculitis characterized by the presence of debris of neutrophils within the blood vessel walls." []

Name: Accumulation of lipid droplets in small-bowel enterocytes
Pericardial friction rub
Definition: "A pericardial friction rub is a grating, to-and-fro sound that occurs in phase with the heart sounds." [PMID:31194424]

Name: Abnormal muscle succinate dehydrogenase staining
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal amount of staining of succinate dehydrogenase in skeletal muscle tissue." [PMID:27556822]

Name: Small intestinal hamartoma
Definition: "A benign (noncancerous) tumorlike malformation made up of an abnormal mixture of cells and tissues that originates in the small intestine." []

Name: Pyriform sperm head
Definition: "Pyriform spermatozoa consist of a normally shaped acrosomal structure which can be normal in size or enlarged, while the post-acrosomal region shows severe elongation and an acute narrowing to the posterior end, ending in about the same thickness as the connecting mid-piece." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7651-2403, PMID:21076438]

Name: Excess residual spermatozoal cytoplasm
Definition: "Excess residual cytoplasm is associated with abnormal spermatozoa produced from a defective spermiation process. This abnormal excess cytoplasm should not be confused with more physiological cytoplasmic residues that can be observed in direct microscopy of the ejaculate but not in dried, fixed and stained morphology smears." [ISBN:9789240030787]

Name: Cardiomyocyte hyaline bodies
Definition: "Subsarcolemmal, eosinophilic glass-like regions within the cytoplasm of cardiomyocytes." []

Name: Hepatic hemophagocytosis
Definition: "Phagocytosis of erythrocytes, lymphocytes or other hematopoietic precursors by histiocytes or macrophages observed in the liver." []

Name: CSF hemophagocytosis
Definition: "Phagocytosis of erythrocytes, lymphocytes or other hematopoietic precursors by histiocytes or macrophages observed in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF)." []

Name: Splenic hemophagocytosis
Definition: "Phagocytosis of erythrocytes, lymphocytes or other hematopoietic precursors by histiocytes or macrophages observed in the spleen." []

Name: Urinary bladder granulomatosis
Definition: "The presence of multiple granulomas in the urinary bladder as based on pathological examination. Granulomas are small 0.5 to 2 mm collections of modified macrophages called epithelioid cells usually surrounded by lymphocytes." []

Name: Epidermal necrosis
Definition: "Death of keratinocytes in the epidermis layer of the skin, which generally manifests as extensive exfoliation (separation of the epidermis from the underlying dermis)." []

Name: Exacerbated by flexion
Definition: "Applied to a sign or symptom that is aggravated by (or made more painful by) bending of a limb or joint." []

Name: Hemolacria
Definition: "The presence of blood in tears." [PMID:30969596]

Name: Corneal foreign body sensation
Definition: "A perception that an object is in contact with the eye." []

Name: Buttock pain
Definition: "An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the buttock (round fleshy area at the lower rear area of a human trunk)." []

Name: Vaginal foreign body sensation
Definition: "A perception that an object located in the vagina." [PMID:17828787]

Name: Paroxysmal nocturnal dyspnea
Definition: "Attacks of breathlessness that occur at night and may awaken the sleeping patient." [PMID:26933707]

Name: Eyelid pain
Definition: "An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the eyelid." []

Name: Abnormal sperm physiology
Definition: "Abnormality of a sperm function including protection of paternal DNA, traversing the female reproductive tract, oocyte localisation, penetration of the zona pellucida, oocyte activation and centriole deposition." []

Name: Small acrosomal area
Definition: "Reduction in size of the acrosome below the lower limit of normal. The acrosome is a unique membranous organelle located over the anterior part of the sperm nucleus. According to the World Health Organization criteria, the acrosome must be clearly visible, comprising approximately 40-70 percent of the sperm head." [PMID:31939391]

Name: Bent sperm flagella
Definition: "The proportion of sperm cells whose flagella is sharply curved or has a sharp angle is above normal limits." [PMID:20111080]

Name: Spermiation failure
Definition: "Spermiation failure is indicated by apparently normal spermiogenesis, but the presence of retained Sd2 spermatids in stages III-V of human spermatogenesis, whereas maturation arrest is indicated by a lack of late Sd1 and Sd2 spermatids in the epithelium." [PMID:21866274]

Name: Hypospermatogenesis
Definition: "A morphological abnormality visible upon biopsy of the germinal epithelium of the testis in which the cellularity of the germinal epithelium is reduced in general, so that all stages of germ cells (spermatogonia, spermatocytes, and spermatids) are present but reduced in number. This term applies to biopsies with some tubules showing diminished amounts of qualitatively complete spermatogenesis in combination with a vast majority of tubules that lack germ cells." [PMID:21346828]

Name: Conjunctival membrane
Definition: "Formation of a sheet of tissue by coagulum of exudate over the conjunctiva of the eye that if removed leaves behind a denuded bleeding surface." []

Name: Extreme oligozoospermia
Definition: "A type of oligozoospermia characterized by a total number of more than zero but less than 2 million sperm in the ejaculate or a concentration of more than zero but less than one million sperm per milliliter." []

Name: Mild oligozoospermia
Definition: "A type of oligozoospermia characterized by a total number of more than 30 but less than 39 million sperm in the ejaculate or a concentration of more than 10 but less than 15 million sperm per milliliter." []

Name: Moderate oligozoospermia
Definition: "A type of oligozoospermia characterized by a total number of more than 10 but less than 29 million sperm in the ejaculate or a concentration of more than 5 but less than 10 million sperm per milliliter." []

Name: Severe oligozoospermia
Definition: "A type of oligozoospermia characterized by a total number of more than 2 but less than 10 million sperm in the ejaculate or a concentration of more than 1 but less than 5 million sperm per milliliter." []

Name: Iris nodule
Definition: "The presence of a nodule (small rounded lump of tissue) in the iris." [PMID:12185117]

Name: Koeppe nodules
Definition: "A type of iris nodule consisting of inflammatory cell precipitates which lie at the pupillary margin." [PMID:8441952]

Name: Bussaca nodules
Definition: "A type of iris nodule consisting of inflammatory cell precipitates which lie on the iris surface." [PMID:8441952]

Name: Decreased CSF copper concentration
Definition: "Concentration of copper in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Diffuse pulmonary lymphoid hyperplasia
Definition: "Diffuse lymphoid hyperplasia (DLH) describes the pathological entity that lies between follicular bronchiolitis and lymphocytic interstitial pneumonia (LIP). It is pathologically characterized by a diffuse peribronchiolar proliferation of hyperplastic lymphoid follicles (BALT), extended along the lymphatics to involve the interlobular septa and pleura. Unlike LIP, DHL does not show uniform involvement of the alveolar septa." [PMID:9714385]

Name: Ameliorated by steroid medication
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by treatment with a steroid medication such as prednisone." []

Name: Triggered by medication exposure
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by administration of a medication." []

Name: Triggered by levothyroxin exposure
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by administration of levothyroxin (thyroid hormone)." []

Name: Reduced muscle laminin alpha-2 chain staining
Definition: "A decreased amount of laminin alpha-2 chain in muscle tissue. This feature can be shown by immunohistochemistry or Western blotting of muscle tissue." []

Name: Adrenal cortical sclerosis
Definition: "Abnormal thickening of of the outer layer (cortex) of the adrenal gland due to fibrosis." []

Name: Reduced hepatic fructose-1,6-phosphate aldolase activity
Definition: "Concentration or activity of fructose 1,6-bisphosphate aldolase in liver tissue below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Pancreatic hamartoma
Definition: "A benign (noncancerous) tumorlike malformation made up of an abnormal mixture of cells and tissues that originates in the pancreas." []

Name: Liver angiomyolipoma
Definition: "A benign liver neoplasm composed of fat, vascular, and smooth muscle elements." []

Name: Cardiac lipoma
Definition: "A lipoma that is located within a the heart." []

Name: Peripheral nerve polyglucosan inclusion bodies
Definition: "Accumulation of a poorly branched and poorly spherical amylopectin-like glycogen (polyglucosan) in peripheral nerve fibers." [PMID:23034915]

Name: Cardiac polyglucosan accumulation
Definition: "Accumulation of a poorly branched and poorly spherical amylopectin-like glycogen (polyglucosan) in myocardial tissue." []

Name: Cystic nephroma
Definition: "A benign cystic neoplasm of the kidney." [PMID:23662002]

Name: Absent dermal elastic fibers
Definition: "Elastic fibers not demonstrable in skin biopsy." [PMID:27293393]

Name: Cleavage at junction of stratum corneum and stratum granulosum
Definition: "Splitting of the skin (cell-cell adhesion of keratinocytes) localized to the interface betweem the stratum corneum and stratum granulosum layers of the epidermis." []

Name: Lymphoid hyperplasia
Definition: "An abnormal bone marrow finding characterized by many poorly circumscribed and occasionally confluent lymphoid nodules. The nodules contain small and uniform lymphocytes with rounded nuclei, clumped chromatin, and without prominent nucleoli." [PMID:1246987]

Name: Absence of epidermal lamellar bodies
Definition: "Lack of lamellar bodies (LBs) inthe epidermis. LBs are specialized organelles that contain pro-barrier lipids imparting a fully lamellar internal structure, but also other cargoes such as enzymes (lipid metabolizing and proteolytic), enzyme inhibitors, and antimicrobial peptides." [PMID:22797297]

Name: Gastrointestinal granulomatosis
Definition: "The presence of multiple granulomas in the gastrointestinal tract (Pylorus, esophagus, jejunum, ileum, cecum, rectum, perirectal area, esophagus) as based on pathological examination. Granulomas are small 0.5 to 2 mm collections of modified macrophages called epithelioid cells usually surrounded by lymphocytes." []

Name: Enlarged sperm head vacuole
Definition: "Increased size of sperm vacuoles, which are surface concavities typically located at the the tip or middle area of sperm heads. According to the WHO Laboratory Manual for the Examination and Processing of Human Semen, sperm head vacuoles are considered abnormal when exceeding 20% of the cross-sectional area of the head. Vacuoles are found in almost all samples with normal sperm morphology; this term applies if the proportion of sperm with abnormally large vacuoles is above the upper limit of normal." [PMID:22559046, PMID:24818161]

Name: Ureteral hamartoma
Definition: "A benign (noncancerous) tumorlike malformation made up of an abnormal mixture of cells and tissues that originates in the ureter." []

Name: Fetal methimazole exposure
Definition: "A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to methimazole." []

Name: Fetal procarbazine exposure
Definition: "A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to procarbazine." []

Name: Fetal fluorouracil exposure
Definition: "A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to fluorouracil." []

Name: Fetal cytarabine exposure
Definition: "A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to cytarabine." []

Name: Fetal tetracycline exposure
Definition: "A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to tetracycline." []

Name: Fetal quinine exposure
Definition: "A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to quinine." []

Name: Fetal cyclophosphamide exposure
Definition: "A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to cyclophosphamide." []

Name: Fetal metronidazole exposure
Definition: "A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to metronidazole." []

Name: Fetal phenobarbital exposure
Definition: "A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to phenobarbital." []

Name: Fetal phenytoin exposure
Definition: "A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to phenytoin." []

Name: Periumbilical
Definition: "Applies to an abnormality whose distribution and appearance are located at or near the umbilicus (belly button)." []

Name: Maternal obesity during pregnancy
Definition: "A history of obesity, which can be defined as a body mass index of 30 or greater, in the mother of a fetus or index patient." [PMID:34283479]

Name: Maternal amniocentesis
Definition: "A history of amniocentesis having been performed in the mother of a fetus or index patient." [PMID:32644673]

Name: Typified by highly variable age of onset
Definition: "Description of conditions in which age of onset is highly variable even in family members who share the same disease-associated variant or variants." []

Name: Abnormal leukocyte enzyme concentration or activity
Definition: "Concentration or activity of an enzyme as measured in leukocytes is above or below the limits of normal in the blood circulation." []

Name: Reduced leukocyte beta-glucuronidase activity
Definition: "Concentration or activity of an beta-glucuronidase as measured in leukocytes is below the limits of normal in the blood circulation." []

Name: Reduced leukocyte alpha-L-fucosidase activity
Definition: "Concentration or activity of an alpha-L-fucosidase as measured in leukocytes is below the limits of normal in the blood circulation." []

Name: Reduced leukocyte arylsulfatase B activity
Definition: "Concentration or activity of an arylsulfatase B as measured in leukocytes is below the limits of normal in the blood circulation." []

Name: Reduced leukocyte steroid sulfatase activity
Definition: "Concentration or activity of an arylsulfatase C as measured in leukocytes is below the limits of normal in the blood circulation." []

Name: Reduced leukocyte arylsulfatase A activity
Definition: "Concentration or activity of an arylsulfatase A as measured in leukocytes is below the limits of normal in the blood circulation." []

Name: Decreased alpha-galactosidase A activity
Definition: "Activity of the enzyme alpha-galactosidase outsidebelow the lower limit of normal." [PMID:25106696]

Name: Positive fecal parasite test
Definition: "Demonstration of parasite in stool specimen, e.g., Parasites present on wet mount of stool.e" []

Name: Positive stool infectious agent test
Definition: "Any kind of test for an infectious agent in stool positive." []

Name: Positive stool giardia antigen
Definition: "Test for giardia antigen in stool such as immune assay or DFA positive." []

Name: Entamoeba histolytica antibody positive in stool
Definition: "Demonstration of antibody directed against Entamoeba histolytica in stool." []

Name: Reduced erythrocyte free porphyrin concentration
Definition: "Concentration of porphyrin in erythrocytes below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Reduced circulating urocanic acid concentration
Definition: "The concentration of urocanic acid in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Decreased urinary epinephrine level
Definition: "The concentration of epinephrine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Decreased CSF epinephrine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of epinephrine in the cerebrospinal fluid below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Decreased circulating epinephrine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of epinephrin in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Decreased circulating norepinephrine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of norepinephrin in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Decreased urinary norepinephrine level
Definition: "The concentration of norepinephrine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Decreased urinary metaepinephrine level
Definition: "The concentration of metanephrine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Decreased CSF metanephrine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of metanephrine in the cerebrospinal fluid below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Decreased circulating metanephrine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of metanephrin in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Ovarian mass
Definition: "A swelling or enlargment localized to the ovary. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined." []

Name: Adrenal mass
Definition: "A swelling or enlargment localized to the adrenal gland. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined." []

Name: Uterine mass
Definition: "A swelling or enlargment localized to the uterus. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined." []

Name: Prostatic calculus
Definition: "Calcium deposits in the prostate gland." []

Name: Decreased portal vein velocity
Definition: "A reduction in the velocity of portal venous flow, generally measured by Doppler ultrasound. Portal venous flow is normally towards the liver with peak systolic velocities in the range of 20-40 cm/s." [PMID:28632958]

Name: Uterine cervix mass
Definition: "A swelling or enlargment localized to the cervis of the uterus. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined." []

Name: Abnormal urinary uromodulin level
Definition: "The concentration of uromodulin (also known as Tamm Horsfall protein) in the urine, normalized for usine concentration, is outside the limits of normal." []

Name: Decreased urinary uromodulin level
Definition: "The concentration of uromodulin (also known as Tamm Horsfall protein) in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Increased urine phenylacetylglutamine level
Definition: "The concentration of phenylacetylglutamine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Decreased urine guanidinoacetic acid level
Definition: "The concentration of guanidinoacetic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Positive urine infectious agent nucleid acid test
Definition: "Detection of DNA and RNA originating from an infectious agent (bacteria, viruses, parasites and fungi) in the urine." []

Name: Positive CMV urine nucleic acid test
Definition: "Detection of Cytomegalovirus (CMV) nucleic acid in the urine by a method such as polymerase chain reaction." []

Name: Positive Neisseria gonorrhoeae urine nucleic acid test
Definition: "Detection of Neisseria gonorrhoeae nucleic acid in the urine by a method such as polymerase chain reaction." []

Name: Positive enterovirus urine nucleic acid test
Definition: "Detection of enterovirus nucleic acid in the urine by a method such as polymerase chain reaction." []

Name: Elevated brain glycine level by MRS
Definition: "An increase in the level of glycine in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS)." []

Name: Elevated brain polyol compounds by MRS
Definition: "An increase in the level of polyol compounds in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS)." []

Name: Elevated brain gamma-aminobutyric acid by MRS
Definition: "An increase in the level of gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA) in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS)." []

Name: History of recent anticoagulant ingestion
Definition: "Medical history of ingestion of anticoagulants prior to presentation." []

Name: Decreased circulating antidiuretic hormone concentration
Definition: "Concentration of antidiuretic hormone, also known as vasopressin, is below the lower limit of normal in the blood circulation." []

Name: Elevated circulating growth hormone-releasing hormone concentration
Definition: "Concentration of growth hormone-releasing hormone above the upper limit of normal in the blood circulation." []

Name: Abnormal amniotic fluid protein concentration
Definition: "Any deviation of the concentration of a protein in the amniotic fluid from normal limits" []

Name: Decreased amniotic fluid alpha-fetoprotein concentration
Definition: "Concentration of alpha-fetoprotein in the amniotic fluid below lower limit of normal." []

Name: Increased circulating vitamin E concentration
Definition: "Concentration of vitamin E in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Abnormal circulating calcitonin concentration
Definition: "Concentration of calcitonin, a 32-amino acid polypeptide hormone that is produced primarily by the parafollicular cells of the thyroid, in the blood circulation outside of normal limits." []

Name: Decreased circulating calcitonin concentration
Definition: "Concentration of calcitonin, a 32-amino acid polypeptide hormone that is produced primarily by the parafollicular cells of the thyroid, in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Decreased circulating thyrotropin releasing hormone concentration
Definition: "Concentration of thyrotropin releasing hormone below the lower limit of normal in the blood circulation." []

Name: Elevated circulating uroporphyrin concentration
Definition: "Concentration of uroporphyrin in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Increased urine pentacarboxylporphyrin level
Definition: "Concentration of pentacarboxylporphyrin in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Increased urine hexacarboxylporphyrin level
Definition: "Concentration of hexacarboxylporphyrin in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Increased circulating dehydroepiandrosterone concentration
Definition: "Concentration of dehydroepiandrosterone in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Increased erythrocyte coproporphyrin concentration
Definition: "Concentration of coproporphyrin in erythrocytes above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Increased erythrocyte uroproporphyrin concentration
Definition: "Concentration of uroproporphyrin in erythrocytes above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Decreased circulating apolipoprotein E concentration
Definition: "Concentration of apolipoprotein E below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated circulating apolipoprotein E concentration
Definition: "Concentration of apolipoprotein E above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Acrosomal hypoplasia
Definition: "Reduction in the size of the acrosome of the head of spermatozoa." [PMID:3311822]

Name: Oocyte maturation arrest
Definition: "Oocyte maturation arrest (OMA) can manifest as failed in vitro fetilization/intracytoplasmic sperm injection (IVF/ICSI) attempts using affected oocytes." [PMID:28965849, PMID:37073822]

Name: Abnormal anus morphology
Definition: "A structural anomaly of the anus." []

Name: Abnormal anus physiology
Definition: "A functional anomaly of the anus." []

Name: Weak anal sphincter tone
Definition: "Reduced muscle tone of the sphincter of the anus." [PMID:20011334]

Name: Reduced muscle 2,4-dienoyl-CoA reductase activity
Definition: "Diminished activity of the enzyme 2,4-dienoyl-CoA reductase in muscle tissue." []

Name: Reduced liver 2,4-dienoyl-CoA reductase activity
Definition: "Diminished activity of the enzyme 2,4-dienoyl-CoA reductase in liver tissue." []

Name: Nasal mucosa vasculitis
Definition: "Inflammation of blood vessels in the mucosa of the nasal cavity." [PMID:2001873]

Name: Pituitary blastoma
Definition: "Pituitary blastoma is a distinctive anterior hypophyseal tumor of infants" []

Name: Peripheral axon spheroid formation
Definition: "Axonal spheroids are bubble-like biological features that form on most degenerating axons." []

Name: Reduced liver carboxylesterase 1 activity
Definition: "Activity of the enzyme carboxylesterase 1 in liver tissue below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Abnormal dermis morphology
Definition: "A structural anomaly of the dermis, the layer of skin that lies beneath the epidermis and above the subcutaneous layer." []

Name: Perivascular dermis hyaline deposition
Definition: "Deposition of a largely amorphous hyaline (transparent and homogeneous) substance around blood vessels in the dermis layer of the skin." [PMID:11298373]

Name: Perivascular small intestinal hyaline deposition
Definition: "Deposition of a largely amorphous hyaline (transparent and homogeneous) substance around blood vessels in the wall of the small intestine." []

Name: Large keratohyaline granules
Definition: "Abnormally large keratohyalin granules (KHG). KHG are typically present in the stratum granulosum of the epidermal layer of the skin (and epithelium of the mucosae). KHG are protein structures found in the keratinocytes of the stratum granulosum." [PMID:20226437, PMID:30725734]

Name: Decreased muscle lipoic acid content
Definition: "Reduced amount of lipoic acid in muscle tissue." []

Name: Reduced hepatic cystathionine gamma-lyase activity
Definition: "Activity of cystathionine gamma-lyase in the liver below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Digestive system neoplasm
Definition: "A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the digestive system." []

Name: Lumbar spondylosis
Definition: "Arthrosis, i.e., of degenerative joint disease, affecting the lumbar vertebral column." []

Name: Decreased circulating acid maltase activity
Definition: "Activity of the enzyme acid maltase (also known as alpha-1,4-glucosidase) below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Increased circulating ribitol concentration
Definition: "The concentration of ribitol in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Abnormal circulating 7-dehydrocholesterol concentration
Definition: "Concentration of 7-dehydrocholesterol in the blood circulation outside the limits of normal." []

Name: Decreased circulating 7-dehydrocholesterol concentration
Definition: "Concentration of 7-dehydrocholesterol in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated circulating lathosterol concentration
Definition: "Concentration of lathosterol in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal." [PMID:12189593]

Name: Elevated circulating desmosterol concentration
Definition: "Concentration of desmosterol in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Decreased circulating sialic acid concentration
Definition: "Concentration of sialic acid in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Purulent synovial fluid
Definition: "The synovial fluid (also known as synovia, i.e., the fluid found in the cavities of synovial joints) contains increased quantities of white blood cells." []

Name: Muscle fiber calsequestrin 1-containing inclusion bodies
Definition: "The presence of inclusion bodies within the cytoplasm of muscle cells that demonstrate immunoreactivity for calsequestrin 1." []

Name: Palatine myxoma
Definition: "A myxoma (A benign tumor composed of myxomatous tissue composed of loosely-arranged spindle, polygonal, and stellate cells) localized to the palate. Clinically, such tumors may present as a sessile nodule on the hard palate." [PMID:33089457]

Name: Vaginal myxoma
Definition: "A myxoma (tumor of primitive connective tissue) localized in the vagina." []

Name: Decreased dermal collagen
Definition: "Abnormally reduced amount of collagen fibers in the dermis." [PMID:29606302]

Name: Irregularly shaped keratohyaline granules
Definition: "Abnormal shape of keratohyaline granules in dermal keratinocytes." [PMID:29758285]

Name: Tubular shadows
Definition: "Tubular shadows are characterised by a complete absence of cells in the testicular tubules, meaning that germ cells as well as somatic Sertoli cells are absent. The cells have been replaced by hyalinization." []

Name: Multiple eyelid margin cysts
Definition: "Presence of many apocrine hidrocystoma (cysts) on the margins of the eyelids." [PMID:19559398]

Name: Altered location of the longitudinal column in the fibrous sheath
Definition: "The fibrous sheath is a structure in the midpiece of the sperm flagellum surrounding the outer dense fibers. It comprises two longitudinal columns and tranverse ribs. In case of altered location of the longitudinal column in the fibrous sheath the symmetrical structure is lost, most commonly with the columns not being opposite to each other, which can be visualised by electron microscopy." []

Name: Uterine myxoma
Definition: "A myxoma (tumor of primitive connective tissue) localized to the uterus." []

Name: Uterine cervix myxoma
Definition: "A myxoma (tumor of primitive connective tissue) localized to the the cervix of the uterus." []

Name: Typified by complete penetrance
Definition: "Penetrance describes the proportion of genotype positive individuals that develop disease given a lifespan of 80 years. For example, penetrance of Neurofibromatosis type 1 is close to 100%." []

Name: Osteochondromyxoma
Definition: "A rare benign chondroid and osteoid matrix-producing neoplasm of bone characterized by extensive myxoid changes. OMX originate from bony cortices and have been observed in the nasal region, as well as the tibia and radius." [PMID:28008382]

Name: Gangliocytoma
Definition: "A low-grade central nervous system tumor composed of dysplastic ganglion cells, usually presenting in children or young adults and located in the cerebral hemispheres." [PMID:35239806]

Name: Duodenal gastrinoma
Definition: "A gastrinoma, a neuroendocrine tumors characterized by the secretion of gastrin with resultant excessive gastric acid production, that is localized to the duodenum." [PMID:28722872]

Name: Thymic carcinoid tumor
Definition: "A primary thymic neuroendocrine tumor." [PMID:29201451]

Name: Bone marrow eosinophilia
Definition: "Count of eosinophils in the bone marrow above the upper limit of normal." [PMID:27684977]

Name: Exacerbated by lithium exposure
Definition: "Applied to a sign or symptom that is worsened by treatment with lithium." []

Name: Reduced hepatic glycogen debrancher enzyme activity
Definition: "Activity of glycogen debrancher enzyme (also known as amylo-1,6-glucosydase, 4-alpha-glucantransferase) in liver tissue below the lower limit of normal." [PMID:20301788]

Name: Asymmetrical insertion of the midpiece into the head
Definition: "Insertion of the neck and midpiece into the head of a spermatozoon on an axis that diverges from the midline axis of the spermatozoon head. This term applies if the proportion of spermatozoa with this defect is above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Bent sperm neck
Definition: "Sharply angled insertion of the neck and midpiece into the head of a spermatozoon. This term applies if the proportion of spermatozoa with this feature is above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated urine 3,6-epoxydicarboxylic acid level
Definition: "The concentration of 3,6-epoxydicarboxylic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal." [PMID:7511488]

Name: Gallbladder biliary sludging
Definition: "Presence of biliary sludge (a mixture of particulate solids that have precipitated from bile) in the gallbladder. Such sediment consists of cholesterol crystals, calcium bilirubinate pigment, and other calcium salts. Sludge is usually detected on transabdominal ultrasonography." [PMID:11276386]

Name: Exacerbated by amiodarone exposure
Definition: "Applied to a sign or symptom that is worsened by treatment with amiodarone." []

Name: Ureteral mass
Definition: "A swelling or enlargment localized to the ureter. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined." []

Name: Wide cavum septum pellucidum
Definition: "Width of the cavum septum pellucidum above the upper limit of normal, which is defined as a separation of greater than one cm of the leaves of the cavum septum pellucidum." [PMID:1705800]

Name: Hypoplastic trochlear nerve
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the trochlear nerve, which is the fourth cranial nerve and one of the ocular motor nerves that controls eye movement." [PMID:30725929]

Name: Thymic cyst
Definition: "A closed sac of tissue (cyst) located in the thymus. Thymic cysts are a rare, benign anomaly, are usually asymptomatic, and mostly occur in the anterior mediastinum ." [PMID:29312727]

Name: Uterine cyst
Definition: "A closed sack of tissue (cyst) located in the uterus." [PMID:23091995]

Name: Urinary bladder mass
Definition: "A swelling or enlargment localized to the urinary bladder. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined." []

Name: Endosteal scalloping
Definition: "A series of indentations or erosions on a normally smooth margin of the inner layer of the cortex (i.e. the endosteum) of bones." []

Name: Urinary bladder hamartoma
Definition: "A benign (noncancerous) tumorlike malformation made up of an abnormal mixture of cells and tissues that originates in the urinary bladder." []

Name: Peritoneal mass
Definition: "A swelling or enlargment localized to the peritoneal cavity. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined." []

Name: Fallopian tube mass
Definition: "A swelling or enlargment localized to the Fallopian tube. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined." []

Name: Aplasia of the pyramids of the medulla oblongata
Definition: "Congenital absence of the pyramids, that is, of the paired structures located at the medial aspect of the ventral medulla that flank the anterior median fissure." [PMID:3976367]

Name: Bathrocephaly
Definition: "A deformity of the posterior skull with bulging of the midportion of the occipital bone that is often associated with a benign variant of the mendosal suture." [PMID:21970727]

Name: Occipital horn
Definition: "Downward pointing exostoses of the occipital bone situated in the tendinous insertions of the sternocleidomastoid and trapezius muscles." [PMID:31336972]

Name: Absent pituitary stalk
Definition: "A developmental defect characterized by failure to develop of the pituitary stalk. The pituitary stalk, also known as the infundibulum or infundibular stalk, is the connection between the hypothalamus and the pituitary gland." [PMID:25250085]

Name: Abnormal pituitary stalk morphology
Definition: "A structural anomaly of the pituitary stalk, also known as the infundibulum or infundibular stalk, is the connection between the hypothalamus and the pituitary gland." [PMID:25654066]

Name: Interrupted pituitary stalk
Definition: "A developmental defect characterized by a discontinuity of the pituitary stalk. The pituitary stalk, also known as the infundibulum or infundibular stalk, is the connection between the hypothalamus and the pituitary gland." [PMID:25250085]

Name: Facial synkinesis
Definition: "Unintentional movement in one area of the face produced during intentional movement of another area of the face." [PMID:18470836]

Name: Synkinesis
Definition: "Unintentional movement in one area of the body produced during intentional movement of another area of the body." []

Name: Exposure to birds
Definition: "History of exposure to birds." []

Name: Perianal anethesia
Definition: "Loss of sensation to the area of buttocks, perianal space and thighs." []

Name: Phenylephrine does not induce blanching of eye redness
Definition: "Instillation of 2.5% phenylephrine drops into the eye does not induce blanching of eye redness. Failure to blanch suggests redness caused by scleral vessel engorgement (e.g., scleritis) or extravascular cause (e.g., hemorrhage), not episcleritis or conjunctivitis." []

Name: Fetal alcohol exposure
Definition: "A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to ethanol (alcohol)." [PMID:28846263]

Name: Reduced cellular cobalamin uptake
Definition: "Diminished ability of cells to transport cobalamine from the extracellular space to the cytoplasm." []

Name: Focal necrotic brainstem lesion
Definition: "A localized area of cell death, often accompanied by infiltration of inflammatory cells, in the brainstem." []

Name: Focal necrotic optic nerve lesion
Definition: "A localized area of cell death, often accompanied by infiltration of inflammatory cells, in the optic nerve." []

Name: Focal necrotic thalamus lesion
Definition: "A localized area of cell death, often accompanied by infiltration of inflammatory cells, in the thalamus." []

Name: Interstitial dermal edema
Definition: "Accumulation of fluid in the interstitial spaces of the skin. This finding can be appreciated my microscopic examination of a skin biopsy." []

Name: Shoulder external rotation contracture
Definition: "A type of shoulder contracture characterized by decreased internal rotation of shoulder, that is, by a chronic reduction in active and passive ability to internally rotate the humerus at the shoulder joint (if the arm is flexed at the elbow, Internal rotation of the shoulder rotates the forearm towards the center of the body)." []

Name: Thumb adduction contracture
Definition: "A type of thumb contracture characterized by a chronic reduction in active and passive ability of the metacarpal-phalangeal and/or interphalangeal joints of the thumb to bring from medial side to neutral position, where the neutral position for the thumb is when the distal and proximal segments of the thumb joint are in linear alignment." []

Name: Reduced hepatic fructose-1,6-bisphosphatase activity
Definition: "Activity of fructose-1,6-bisphosphatase (EC 3.1.3.11) in the liver below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Reduced hepatic carbamoylphosphate synthetase activity
Definition: "Activity of carbamoylphosphate synthetase in the liver below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Reduced intraepidermal small nerve fiber density
Definition: "Reduced number of small nerve fibers in the skin." [PMID:35881752]

Name: Femoral artery duplication
Definition: "A developmental defect characterized by the presence of a supernumerary femoral artery." [PMID:27504194]

Name: Intracellular accumulation of collagen VII
Definition: "Collagen VII is the major molecular constituent of anchoring fibrils in the skin. Collagen VII is synthesized as three identical pro-alpha1(VII) polypeptide chains, which are hydroxylated and glycosylated in a coordinated manner and then fold into triple-helical procollagen VII in the endoplasmic reticulum (ER). Mature collagen VII undergoes a multistep fibril polymerization process to form the anchoring fibrils. Mutant pro-alpha1(VII) polypeptide chains or procollagen VII molecules do not pass the ER quality control and are retained in the ER or designated for ubiquitin-proteasome degradation resulting in reduced amounts of collagen VII in the skin." [PMID:19726672, PMID:8288900]

Name: Reduced reticular lamina anchoring fibril density
Definition: "Diminished amount of the anchoring fibrils in the basement membrane zone that normally attach the epithelium to the basement membrane." []

Name: Reduced lamina lucida anchoring filament density
Definition: "Diminished amount of the anchoring filaments that normally bridge the lamina lucida and insert into the lamina densa in the cutaneous basement membrane zone." []

Name: Reduced epidermal keratin 5 protein expression
Definition: "Amount of keratin 5 in the epidermis below the lower limit of normal. The findiong is typically ascertained by immunofluorescent microscopy." []

Name: Reduced epidermal keratin 14 protein expression
Definition: "Amount of keratin 14 in the epidermis below the lower limit of normal. The findiong is typically ascertained by immunofluorescent microscopy." []

Name: Reduced epidermal keratin protein expression
Definition: "Amount of one or more keratins in the epidermis below the lower limit of normal. The findiong is typically ascertained by immunofluorescent microscopy." []

Name: Reduced hepatic alanine-glyoxylate aminotransferase activity
Definition: "Activity of alanine-glyoxylate aminotransferase in the liver below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Hepatic sinusoidal dilatation
Definition: "Presence of an increased amount of blood in the hepatic capillaries." []

Name: Thin spermatozoon midpiece
Definition: "The cross-sectional size (diameter) of the midpiece of the spermatozoon is below the lower limit of normal. This term applies if the proportion of spermatozoa with this defect is above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Thick spermatozoon midpiece insertion
Definition: "Increased width of the midpiece of the spermatozoon. The midpiece is the structure that is located between the head and the flagella (tail) of the spermatozoon. This term applies if the width of the midpiece increases progressively from the flagella to the head and if the proportion of individual spermatozoa with this anomaly is above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Shoulder adduction contracture
Definition: "A type of shoulder contracture characterized by a chronic reduction in the active and passive ability to abduct the shoulder. This results in the shoulders being closer to midline. The affected individual is not able to position the shoulders away from the body." []

Name: Occupational exposure history
Definition: "Exposure to a substance that results from the performance of an employee's duties." []

Name: Occupational silver exposure
Definition: "A history of exposure to silver that has occured in relation to performance of job duties." []

Name: Abnormal femoral artery morphology
Definition: "Any structural abnormality of the femoral artey, a large blood vessel that provides oxygenated blood to lower extremity structures and in part to the lower anterior abdominal wall." [PMID:30855850]

Name: Extrahepatic bile duct fibrosis
Definition: "Accumulation of fibrous connective tissue (collagen) in the extrahepatic bile ducts." []

Name: Elevated circulating short-chain acylcarnitine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of short-chain acylcarnitine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. Acylcarnitines are classified according to the number of carbon atoms in the acyl-chain. Short chain acylcarnitines have between two and five carbon atoms in the acyl-chain (C2-C5)," []

Name: Elevated circulating C4 acylcarnitine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of C4 acylcarnitines in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. C4 acylcarnitines have a four-carbon acyl chain." [PMID:12736383]

Name: Elevated circulating medium-chain acylcarnitine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of medium-chain acylcarnitine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. Acylcarnitines are classified according to the number of carbon atoms in the acyl-chain. Medium-chain acylcarnitines have between six and twelve carbon atoms in the acyl-chain (C6-C12)," []

Name: Elevated circulating long-chain acylcarnitine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of long-chain acylcarnitine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. Acylcarnitines are classified according to the number of carbon atoms in the acyl-chain. Long-chain acylcarnitines have between thirteen and twenty carbon atoms in the acyl-chain (C13-C20)," []

Name: Elevated circulating C5 acylcarnitine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of C5 acylcarnitines in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. C5 acylcarnitines have a five-carbon acyl chain." []

Name: Elevated circulating C18 acylcarnitine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of C18 acylcarnitines in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. C18 acylcarnitines have a eighteen-carbon acyl chain." []

Name: Elevated circulating C16 acylcarnitine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of C16 acylcarnitines in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. C16 acylcarnitines have a sixteen-carbon acyl chain." []

Name: Elevated circulating very long-chain acylcarnitine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of very long-chain acylcarnitine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. Acylcarnitines are classified according to the number of carbon atoms in the acyl-chain. Very long-chain acylcarnitines have twentyone or more carbon atoms in the acyl-chain (C21 and higher)," []

Name: Elevated circulating acetylcarnitine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of acetylcarnitine (C2 acylcarnitine) in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. Acetylcarnitine has a two-carbon acyl chain." []

Name: Elevated circulating methylmalonylcarnitine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of methylmalonylcarnitine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated circulating 3-hydroxyhexadecanoylcarnitine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of 3-hydroxyhexadecanoylcarnitine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated circulating C6 acylcarnitine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of C6 acylcarnitines in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. C6 acylcarnitines have a six-carbon acyl chain." []

Name: Elevated circulating methylglutarylcarnitine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of methylglutarylcarnitine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated circulating 3-hydroxyisovalerylcarnitine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of 3-hydroxyisovalerylcarnitine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated circulating 3-hydroxyhexanoylcarnitine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of 3-hydroxyhexanoylcarnitine (C6-OH) in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated circulating carnitine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of carnitine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated circulating tiglylcarnitine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of tiglylcarnitine (C5:1) in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Reduced circulating acetylcarnitine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of acetylcarnitine (C2 acylcarnitine) in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal. Acetylcarnitine has a two-carbon acyl chain." []

Name: Reduced circulating octadecenoylcarnitine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of octadecenoylcarnitine (C18:1 acylcarnitine) in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Absent pigmentation of chest
Definition: "Lack of skin pigmentation (coloring) of the chest." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5316-1399]

Name: Hyperparakeratosis
Definition: "Abnormal keratinization of the epidermal stratum coreum (horny layer) with increased keratin formation, preservation of the nuclei in the superficial cells, and absence of the stratum granulosum." []

Name: Chromosome breakage
Definition: "Elevated rate of chromosomal breakage or interchanges occurring either spontaneously or following exposure to various DNA-damaging agents. This feature may be assayed by treatment of cultured lymphocytes with agents such as chemical mutagens, irradiation, and alkylating agents." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:12407692]

Name: Increased activity of mitochondrial respiratory chain
obsolete Radial deviation of the thumb
Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the fifth metatarsal bone
Abnormality of the second metatarsal bone
Abnormality of the fourth metatarsal bone
Onychogryposis of fingernail
Definition: "Thickened fingernails." []

Name: Toenail onycholysis
Definition: "Painless and spontaneous separation of a toenail from the nail bed." []

Name: Aplasia of the eccrine sweat glands
Hypoplasia of the eccrine sweat glands
obsolete Aplasia of the left hemidiaphragm
Macular edema
Definition: "Thickening of the retina that takes place due to accumulation of fluid in the macula as a nonspecific response to blood-retinal barrier breakdown. Macular edema is a common pathological response to a wide variety of ocular insults, most commonly after intraocular (e.g. cataract) surgery or in association with retinal vascular (e.g. diabetic eye disease, retinal vein occlusion) or inflammatory (e.g. uveitis) disease." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0986-4123]

Name: obsolete Abnormal morphology of bones of the upper limbs
obsolete Abnormal morphology of bones of the lower limbs
Abnormal morphology of ulna
Definition: "Any structural anomaly of the ulna, a bone of the forearm the extends from the elbow to the little finger." []

Name: obsolete Abnormal concentration of calcium in blood
Abnormal circulating creatine kinase concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal circulating creatine kinase concentration." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7941-2961]

Name: Happy demeanor
Definition: "A conspicuously happy disposition with frequent smiling and laughing that may be context-inappropriate or unrelated to context." [PMID:18830393]

Name: obsolete Toe walking
Definition: "Toe walking is a pattern of walking in which a person walks on balls of his or her feet, with no contact between the heels and ground. Toe-walking is common in children who are learning to walk, but most children outgrow it around the age of two years. This term refers to the persistance of toe-walking beyond the usual age." [PMID:26709689]

Name: Abnormal circulating renin
Definition: "A deviation from the normal concentration of renin in the blood, a central hormone in the control of blood pressure and various other physiological functions." [PMID:12949225]

Name: Abnormal blood folate concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of folate in the blood circulation." []

Name: Abnormal lymphocyte count
Definition: "Any abnormality in the total number of lymphocytes in the blood." []

Name: Abnormal natural killer cell count
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal overall count of natural killer (NK) cells in the circulation or a deviation from the normal distribution of NK cell subtypes." [PMID:19278419]

Name: Abnormality of the tympanic membrane
Definition: "An abnormality of the tympanic membrane" []

Name: Asymmetry of the size of ears
Asymmetry of the shape of the ears
Asymmetry of the position of the ears
Neoplasm of the outer ear
Definition: "A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the outer ear." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Neoplasm of the inner ear
Definition: "A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the inner ear." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Neoplasm of the ceruminal gland
Definition: "A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the ceruminal gland." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Cutaneous atresia of the external auditory canal
Osseous atresia of the external auditory canal
Cutaneous stenosis of the external auditory canal
Osseous stenosis of the external auditory canal
Morphological abnormality of the lateral semicircular canal
Morphological abnormality of the posterior semicircular canal
Morphological abnormality of the anterior semicircular canal
Absence of the reflex of the tensor tympani muscle
Abnormal Eustachian tube morphology
Definition: "A structural anomaly of the Eustachian tube (ET). The ET is a biomechanical valve between the nasopharynx and the middle ear. Physiologically, it controls the passive adaptation of the middle ear air pressure to the ambient air pressure primarily via direct muscular actions of the soft palate. In the closed state it protects the middle ear. Inadequate function of the ET causes middle ear ventilation disorders." [PMID:34383758]

Name: Abnormality of the reflex of the tensor tympani muscle
Abnormality of the acoustic reflex
Definition: "An abnormality in the reflexive contraction of the middle-ear muscles in response to sound stimulation." []

Name: Impairment of the the acoustic reflex
Impairment of the reflex of the tensor tympani muscle
Abnormal vitamin B12 level
Definition: "A deviation from the normal concentration of cobalamin (vitamin B12) in the blood. Vitamin B12 is one of the eight B vitamins." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal sweat homeostasis
Definition: "An abnormality of the composition of sweat or the levels of its components." []

Name: Abnormal circulating ferritin concentration
Definition: "A deviation from the normal circulating concentration of ferritin. Ferritin concentration can be measured in serum or plasma." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:29723227]

Name: Abnormal transferrin saturation
Definition: "Any abnormality in the serum transferrin saturation, which is calculated by dividing the serum iron level by total iron-binding capacity." [PMID:15083853]

Name: Comedonal acne
Definition: "A type of acne in which open and closed comedones comprise the majority of the lesions, with substantially fewer papules and pustules." [PMID:18177407]

Name: Mucinous histiocytosis
Definition: "Multiple subcutaneous non-fragile and skin-coloured papules characterized by interstitial infiltrate of spindle and epithelioid histiocytes, and mucin. There are well circumscribed aggregates of epithelioid histiocytes and mucin in the upper and middle dermis,with the histiocytes arranged between collagen bundles and separated from the epidermis by a Grenz zone." [PMID:10606860]

Name: Lipogranulomatosis
Definition: "Yellow nodules of lipoid material are deposited in the skin and mucosae. This gives rise to granulomatous reactions." []

Name: Reduced 5-oxoprolinase level
Definition: "Decreased level of the reaction 5-oxo-L-proline + ATP + 2 H(2)O = L-glutamate + ADP + 2 H(+) + phosphate." [PMID:6790862]

Name: Dystopic os odontoideum
Definition: "Os odontoideum is classified into two anatomic types (orthotopic and dystopic). Os odontoideum is defined as an ossicle that consists of smooth and separate caudal portions of the odontoid process. With orthotopic os odontoideum, the ossicle moves with the anterior arch of the atlas, while the dystopic type consists of an ossicle near the basion, or one that is fused with the clivus" []

Name: L-2-hydroxyglutaric aciduria
Definition: "An increase in the level of L-2-hydroxyglutaric acid in the urine." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Cortical myoclonus
Definition: "Cortical myoclonus mainly affects the distal upper limbs and face, which reflects the largest cortical representations of these body areas. It is often focal, but may be multifocal, bilateral or generalized, as a consequence of intracortical and transcallosal spreading of abnormal activity. It typically occurs on voluntary action and may affect speech and gait. Cortical myoclonic jerks are stimulus sensitive, typically to touch, but sensitivity to visual stimuli is also described. Most patients with cortical myoclonus have both positive myoclonus and NM, occurring either independently or together as a complex of the two kinds of myoclonus. If cortical myoclonus is prolonged and lasts for hours, days or weeks, it is called epilepsia partials continua and is considered to be a rare form of focal epileptic status. Focal cortical myoclonus almost always points to an underlining lesion of the sensori-motor cortex, which produces hyperexcitability (e.g. vascular, inflammatory or neoplastic)." [PMID:21339907]

Name: Woolly scalp hair
Definition: "The presence of woolly hair on the scalp. The term woolly hair refers to an abnormal variant of hair that is fine, with tightly coiled curls, and often hypopigmented. Optical microscopy may reveal the presence of tight spirals and a clear diameter reduction as compared with normal hair. Electron microscopy may show flat, oval hair shafts with reduced transversal diameter." [PMID:20464096]

Name: Acne inversa
Definition: "A chronic skin condition involving the inflammation of the apocrine sweat glands, forming pimple-like bumps known as abscesses." [https://www.news-medical.net/health/What-is-Hidradenitis-suppurativa-(acne-inversa).aspx]

Name: Elevated urinary 3-hydroxybutyric acid
Definition: "An increased amount of 3-hydroxybutyric acid in the urine." []

Name: Elevated urinary carboxylic acid
Definition: "An increased amount of carboxylic acid in the urine." []

Name: Orthokeratosis
Definition: "Formation of an anuclear keratin layer" []

Name: Lipomas of eyelids
Definition: "Fatty tumors on the eyelids." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0986-4123]

Name: Periostitis
Definition: "Inflammation of the periosteum" []

Name: Abnormality of extrinsic muscle of tongue
Platelet-activating factor acetylhydrolase deficiency
Definition: "Reduced level of platelet-activating factor acetylhydrolase." []

Name: Abnormal circulating phospholipid concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of a phospholipid in the blood circulation." []

Name: Chapped lip
Definition: "Cracking, fissuring, and peeling of the skin of the lips." []

Name: Inappropriate sinus tachycardia
Definition: "Inappropriate sinus tachycardia is a nonparoxysmal tachyarrhythmia characterized by an increased resting heart rate (HR) and/or an exaggerated HR response to minimal exertion or a change in body posture. HR is constantly above the physiological range with no appropriate relation to metabolic or physiological demands." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:15763524]

Name: Maculopapular exanthema
Definition: "A skin rash that is characterized by diffuse cutaneous erythema with areas of skin elevation. It may evolve to vesicles or papules as part of a more severe clinical entity. Different degrees of angioedema with involvement of subcutaneous tissue may also appear." [PMID:19398898]

Name: Neonatal sepsis
Definition: "Systemic inflammatory response to infection in newborn babies." [PMID:4067741]

Name: Osteochondrosis
Definition: "Abnormal growth ossification centers in children. Initially a degeneration/ necrosis followed by regeneration or recalcification." []

Name: Scaling skin
Definition: "Refers to the loss of the outer layer of the epidermis in large, scale-like flakes." []

Name: APUdoma
Definition: "An endocrine tumor arising from an APUD cell." []

Name: Increased head circumference
Definition: "An abnormally increased head circumference in a growing child. Head circumference is measured with a nonelastic tape and comprises the distance from above the eyebrows and ears and around the back of the head. The measured HC is then plotted on an appropriate growth chart." []

Name: Decreased head circumference
Definition: "An abnormally reduced head circumference in a growing child. Head circumference is measured with a nonelastic tape and comprises the distance from above the eyebrows and ears and around the back of the head. The measured HC is then plotted on an appropriate growth chart. Microcephaly is defined as a head circumference (HC) that is great than two standard deviations below the mean of age- and gender-matched population based samples. Severe microcephaly is defined with an HC that is three standard deviations below the mean." [PMID:26505062]

Name: Mild microcephaly
Definition: "Decreased occipito-frontal (head) circumference (OFC). For the microcephaly OFC must be between -3 SD and -2 SD compared to appropriate, age matched, normal standards (i.e. -3 SD <= OFC < -2 SD)." []

Name: Encephalomalacia
Definition: "Encephalomalacia is the softening or loss of brain tissue after cerebral infarction, cerebral ischemia, infection, craniocerebral trauma, or other injury." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0003-6754]

Name: Motor impersistence
Definition: "The inability to maintain postures or positions (such as keeping eyes closed, protruding the tongue, maintaining conjugate gaze steadily in a fixed direction, or making a prolonged 'ah' sound) without repeated prompts." [DOI:10.1007/978-0-387-79948-3_2046, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0003-6754]

Name: Simultanapraxia
Definition: "A subset of motor impersistence, defined as the inability to perform more than two of the simple voluntary acts simultaneously, such as closing the eyes and protruding the tongue." [DOI:10.1007/978-0-387-79948-3_2046, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0003-6754]

Name: Abnormal consumption behavior
Definition: "Abnormal and compulsive consumption of food, liquid, or objects that could have negative consequences for the individual." []

Name: Abnormal CSF neopterin concentration
Definition: "Abnormal concentration of neopterin in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF)." []

Name: Elevated CSF neopterin level
Definition: "Increased concentration of neopterin in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF)." []

Name: Decreased CSF neopterin level
Definition: "Decreased concentration of neopterin in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF)." []

Name: Abnormal circulating neopterin concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of neopterin in the blood circulation." []

Name: Abnormal CSF biopterin concentration
Definition: "Abnormal concentration of biopterin in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF)." []

Name: Elevated CSF biopterin level
Definition: "Concentration of biopterin in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Decreased CSF biopterin level
Definition: "Concentration of biopterin in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Abnormal circulating biopterin concentration
Definition: "A deviation from the normal concentration of biopterin in the blood circulation." []

Name: Abnormal skin morphology of the palm
Definition: "An abnormality of the skin of the palm, that is, the skin of the front of the hand." []

Name: Risus sardonicus
Definition: "Fixed sarcastic grimace and anxious expression. Caused by spasms of the masseter and other facial muscles." []

Name: Hypopnea
Definition: "Hypopnea is referring to breathing that is abnormally shallow." []

Name: Abnormal circulating insulin concentration
Definition: "An abnormal concentration of insulin in the body." []

Name: Hypoinsulinemia
Definition: "A decreased concentration of insulin in the blood." []

Name: Elevated hemoglobin A1c
Definition: "An increased concentration of hemoglobin A1c (HbA1c), which is the product of nonenzymatic attachment of a hexose molecule to the N-terminal amino acid of the hemoglobin molecule. This reaction is dependent on blood glucose concentration, and therefore reflects the mean glucose concentration over the previous 8 to 12 weeks. The HbA1c level provides a better indication of long-term glycemic control than one-time blood or urinary glucose measurements." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:20042774]

Name: Reduced natural killer cell count
Definition: "Less than normal number of natural killer cells, a type of lymphocyte in the innate immune system with an ability to mediate cytotoxicity and produce cytokines after the ligation of a germline-encoded activation receptor." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:23993353]

Name: Absent natural killer cells
Definition: "Lack of natural killer cells, a type of lymphocyte in the innate immune system that contains cytoplasmic granzymes, i.e., small granules with perforin and proteases that allow natural killer cells to form pores in the cell membrane of the target cell through which the granzymes and associated molecules can enter, inducing apoptosis." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Abnormal size of the dental root
Maternal thrombophilia
Definition: "An increased tendency towards thrombosis in the mother during a pregnancy." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:25401392]

Name: Pulmonary hemorrhage
Definition: "Pulmonary hemorrhage is a bleeding within the lungs. Older children and adults may spit blood or bloody sputum. Neonates, infants and young children usually do not spit up blood. Anemia, pulmonary infiltrates, increasingling bloody return on BAL and the presence of hemosiderin-laden macrophages in broncho-alveolar lavage (BAL) fluid or lung biopsy can diagnose lung bleeding. Alveolar macrophages contain phagocytosed red blood cells and stain positive for hemosiderin, a product of hemoglobin degradation, after about 48-72 hours following pulmonary hemorraghe. Previous or recurrent bleeding can thus be distinguished from fresh events. A differentiation into local or diffuse is of importance. Also differentiate if pulmonary hemorrhage is due to a primary lung disorder or a manifestation of a systemic disease." [PMID:16473816]

Name: Abnormality of fibrinolysis
Definition: "Clincial phenotype characterized by delayed bleeding accelerated break down of blood clot (fibrinolysis)" []

Name: Decrease in high molecular weight von Willebrand factor Multimers
Definition: "A decrease in high molecular weight von Willebrand factor multimers." []

Name: Decreased level of heparin co-factor II
Definition: "An abnormality of coagulation related to a decreased concentration of heparin co-factor II" []

Name: Decreased level of histidine-rich glycoprotein
Definition: "Decrease of these levels result in increased inhibition of fibrinolysis and reduced inhibition of coagulation" []

Name: Decreased level of plasminogen
Definition: "A decreased level of Plasminogen" []

Name: Decreased level of thrombomodulin
Definition: "Thrombomodulin is a cofactor in the thrombin induced activation of Protein C. In the case of deficiency there will be less Protein C and tendency to clot" []

Name: Decreased level of tissue plasminogen activator
Definition: "The tPA protein catalyzes the conversion of plasiminogen to plasmin, and thus break down of clots. When there is a deficiency there will be an increase of thrombosis" []

Name: Delayed onset bleeding
Definition: "Abnormal bleeding related to a procedure or trauma which does not start at the time of the initial insult, but after delay by at least 24 hours." []

Name: Factor XIII subunit A deficiency
Definition: "Deficiency of factor XIII subunit A, leading to a reduced factor XIII activity. Activated Factor XIII cross-links fibrin polymers solidifying the clot." []

Name: Factor XIII subunit B deficiency
Definition: "Deficiency of factor XIII subunit B, leading to a reduced factor XIII activity. Activated Factor XIII cross-links fibrin polymers solidifying the clot." []

Name: Leukocyte inclusion bodies
Definition: "The presence of intraceullar inclusion bodies (aggregates of stainable substances, usually proteins) in leukocytes." []

Name: Hyperfibrinolysis
Definition: "Increased degradation of fibrin, associated with clot instability and bleeding" []

Name: Impaired binding of factor VIII to VWF
Definition: "Impaired binding of factor VIII to von Willebrand Factor. This is determined using a modified ELISA assay." []

Name: Impaired neutrophil chemotaxis
Definition: "An impairment of the migration of neutrophils towards chemoattractants as part of the innate immune response" []

Name: Increased plasma vitamin K epoxide after vitamin K supplementation
Definition: "Increased plasma vitamin K epoxide after vitamin K supplementation is present in VKCFD (vitamin K-dependent clotting factor deficiency) type 2, but not in VKCFD type 1." []

Name: Increased ratio of VWF propeptide to VWF antigen
Definition: "An increased VWF propeptide to VWF antigen indicates that deficiency of VWF is not due to impaired synthesis but due to rapid clearance. The VWF propeptide is measured by ELISA." []

Name: Increased RIPA
Definition: "Increased platelet agglutination in response to low-dose ristocetin" []

Name: Muscle hemorrhage
Definition: "Bleeding occuring within a muscle" [PMID:27231694]

Name: Prolonged euglobulin clot lysis time
Definition: "Abnormally increased length of time required for an in vitro clot to dissolve in the absence of the normal plasmin inhibitors. This test is a clinical assay used to measure fibrinolysis. The euglobulin fraction of plasma is precipitated and used to form clot by addition of thrombin; after clot forms the rate of clot breakdown (fibrinolysis) can be monitored." []

Name: Prolonged Russell's viper venom time
Definition: "Increased time to coagulation in the Russell's viper venom assay" []

Name: Reduced alpha-2-antiplasmin activity
Definition: "Reduced activity of alpha-2-antiplasmin. This protein inactivates the protease plasmin that drives fibrinolysis." []

Name: Reduced antithrombin antigen
Definition: "Reduced antithrombin antigen. A reduced level of antithrombin may lead to an increased risk of thrombus formation." []

Name: Reduced euglobulin clot lysis time
Definition: "Abnormally decreased length of time required for an in vitro clot to dissolve in the absence of the normal plasmin inhibitors. This test is a clinical assay used to measure fibrinolysis. The euglobulin fraction of plasma is precipitated and used to form clot by addition of thrombin; after clot forms the rate of clot breakdown (fibrinolysis) can be monitored." []

Name: Reduced plasminogen activator inhibitor 1 activity
Definition: "Reduced activity of plasminogen activator inhibitor 1. This protein down-regulates fibrinolysis in the circulation by inhibiting the two major plasminogen activators: tissue-plasminogen activator and urokinase-plasminogen activator." []

Name: Reduced plasminogen activator inhibitor 1 antigen
Definition: "Reduced level of plasminogen activator inhibitor 1 antigen." []

Name: Reduced prothrombin antigen
Definition: "Reduced prothrombin antigen as measured by ELISA assay. Prothrombin is a vitamin K-dependent coagulation factor that is proteolytically cleaved to form thrombin." []

Name: Hand dimple
Definition: "A cutaneous indentation resulting from tethering of the skin to underlying structures (bone) of the hand." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5316-1399]

Name: Aplastic/Hypoplastic nasopharyngeal adenoids
Definition: "Absence or underdevelopment of the nasopharyngeal adenoids." []

Name: Abnormal size of nasopharyngeal adenoids
Definition: "A deviation in the size of nasopharyngeal adenoids." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7941-2961]

Name: Hypoplastic nasopharyngeal adenoids
Definition: "Underdevelopment of the nasopharyngeal adenoids." []

Name: Aplastic nasopharyngeal adenoids
Definition: "Absence of the nasopharyngeal adenoids as a developmental defect." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5208-3432]

Name: Decreased size of nasopharyngeal adenoids
Definition: "An abnormal decrease in the size of nasopharyngeal adenoids." [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7941-2961]

Name: Increased size of nasopharyngeal adenoids
Definition: "An abnormal increase in the size of nasopharyngeal adenoids." []

Name: Glue ear
Definition: "Middle ear is filled with glue-like fluid instead of air." []

Name: Jaw pain
Definition: "An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the jaw." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Upper limb muscle hypertrophy
Definition: "Abnormal increase in muscle size and mass of one or both arms not due to training." []

Name: Recurrent infections of the middle ear
Definition: "Increased susceptibility to middle ear infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of middle ear infections" [https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7941-2961]

Name: Impaired glucose tolerance
Definition: "An abnormal resistance to glucose, i.e., a reduction in the ability to maintain glucose levels in the blood stream within normal limits following oral or intravenous administration of glucose." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Hyperintensity of MRI T2 signal of the spinal cord
Definition: "A region of high intensity (brightness) observed upon magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) scans of the spinal cord." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]

Name: Adenocarcinoma of the intestines
Definition: "A malignant epithelial tumor with a glandular organization that originates in the intestines." []

Name: Adenocarcinoma of the small intestine
Definition: "A malignant epithelial tumor with a glandular organization that originates in the small intestine." []

Name: Adenocarcinoma of the large intestine
Definition: "A malignant epithelial tumor with a glandular organization that originates in the large intestine." []

Name: Prolactinoma
Definition: "A benign tumor (adenoma) of the pituitary gland" []

Name: Frequency
Definition: "Class to represent frequency of phenotypic abnormalities within a patient cohort." []

Name: Obligate
Definition: "Always present, i.e. in 100% of the cases." []

Name: Very frequent
Definition: "Present in 80% to 99% of the cases." []

Name: Frequent
Definition: "Present in 30% to 79% of the cases." []

Name: Occasional
Definition: "Present in 5% to 29% of the cases." []

Name: Very rare
Definition: "Present in 1% to 4% of the cases." []

Name: Excluded
Definition: "Present in 0% of the cases." []

Name: Abnormal axial muscle morphology
Definition: "A structural anomaly of the muscles of the trunk and head." []

Name: Nasogastric tube feeding
Definition: "The condition of inability to eat normally treated by placement of a thin tube through the nose into the stomach that is then used to carry food." [PMID:25874832]

Name: Cyclic neutropenia
Definition: "Recurrent episodes of abnormally low levels of neutrophils in the body (neutropenia)." [https://rarediseases.info.nih.gov/diseases/6229/cyclic-neutropenia]

Name: Abnormal location of the eyebrow
Definition: "Anomalous anatomical placement of the eyebrow." []

Name: Preauricular cyst
Definition: "Preauricular sinus is an occasional finding and most frequently appears as a small pit close to the anterior margin of the ascending portion of the helix. The opening has also been reported along the postero superior margin of the helix, the tragus or the lobule. Preauricular sinus may lead to the formation of a subcutaneous cyst that is intimately related to the tragal cartilage and the anterior crus of the helix." [PMID:24427573]

Name: Decreased circulating free fatty acid level
Abnormal circulating free fatty acid concentration
Definition: "Any deviation from the normal concentration of a free fatty acid in the blood circulation." []

Name: Increased urinary glycerol
Definition: "An increased concentration of glycerol in the urine." []

Name: Hyperglycerolemia
Definition: "Increased concentration of glycerol in the blood." [PMID:23415440]

Name: Increased male libido
Definition: "Increased desire for sexual activity on the part of a male." []

Name: Decreased male libido
Definition: "Reduced desire for sexual activity on the part of a male." []

Name: Male sexual dysfunction
Definition: "A problem occurring during any phase of the male sexual response cycle that prevents the individual from experiencing satisfaction from the sexual activity" [PMID:29532805]

Name: Male anorgasmia
Definition: "Inability of a male to reach orgasm." []

Name: Sterile arthritis
Definition: "An inflammatory arthritis characterized by purulent synovial fluid with neutrophil accumulation, but with negative cultures." []

Name: Symmetric polyarthritis
