Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against laminin-6." []

Name: Anti-laminin gamma1 antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against laminin gamma-1." [PMID:24154702]

Name: Anti-laminin antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against a laminin. Laminins are major components of the basement membrane." []

Name: Anti-integrin antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against an integrin. Integrins are a family of cell adhesion molecules with 24 known integrin heterodimers. Integrins transduce mechanical and biochemical signals from fibrotic extracellular matrix into the cell, activate latent TGFbeta, and subsequently modulate fibroblast adhesion, migration, and growth." [PMID:33483531]

Name: Anti-transglutaminase 6 antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against transglutaminase 6." []

Name: anti-LAD-1 antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against LAD-1, which is the soluble 120 kDa ectodomain of BP180." []

Name: Anti-LABD97 antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against LABD97, which is structurally identical to a portion of the extracellular domain of BPAg2. BPAg2, a 180 kDa bullous pemphigoid antigen, is a transmembrane protein important for basement membrane cohesion." [PMID:11180014]

Name: Antigliadin antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against gliadin." [PMID:24052912]

Name: Anti-reticulin antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against reticulin." [PMID:23365209]

Name: Anti-type VII collagen antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against collagen type VII." [PMID:29619029]

Name: False perception of self-motion
Definition: "A perception that one's body is moving or swaying despite lack of motion of the body." [PMID:29443215]

Name: Non-spinning vertigo
Definition: "A perception of unsteadiness of dizziness that is not characterized bythe spinning sensation of classic vertigo, but rather by an oscillatory perception (rocking, bobbing, or swaying despite the fact that the subject is not moving)." [PMID:27083889, PMID:32986636]

Name: Infection-associated lymphopenia
Definition: "Decreased lymphocyte count during infections." [PMID:32569607]

Name: Primary obstructive megaureter
Definition: "Megaurater associated with obstruction or an adynamic ureteral segment in the ureterovesical junction." [PMID:23533926]

Name: Encysted hydrocele of the cord
Definition: "A type of hydrocele testis in which both the proximal and distal portions of processus vaginalis get obliterated while the central portion remains patent and fluid accumulates within it." [PMID:32644551]

Name: Congenital hydrocele
Definition: "Congenital hydrocele occurs when processus vaginalis is patent and communicates with the peritoneal cavity. This communication allows the movement of peritoneal fluid but is too small to allow the intra-abdominal contents to herniate through." [PMID:32644551]

Name: Infantile hydrocele
Definition: "Infantile Hydrocele is a type pf hydrocele in which the processus vaginalis gets obliterated at the level of the deep inguinal ring. However, the portion distal to it remains patent and allows fluid accumulation." [PMID:32644551]

Name: Reduced proportion of mucosal-associated invariant T cells
Definition: "A decreased proportion of circulating mucosal-associated invariant T (MAIT) cells relative to total T cell count." [PMID:32161190]

Name: Puerpural onset
Definition: "Onset of a phenotypic abnormality or a disease during childbirth or in the period immediately following." []

Name: AA amyloidosis
Definition: "Extracellular tissue deposition of fibrils that are composed of fragments of and/or intact serum amyloid A protein, a hepatic acute phase reactant." [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3411-9598, PMID:29261990]

Name: Fracture type
Definition: "Category of fracture. Terms from this subontology can be used together with terms in the subontology that descends from Bone fracture (HP:0020110)." []

Name: Greenstick fracture
Definition: "A type of fracture in which the broken bone is not completely separated." []

Name: Transverse fracture
Definition: "A type of fracture in which the break is in a straight line across the bone." []

Name: Spiral fracture
Definition: "A type of fracture in which the break spirals around the bone." []

Name: Oblique fracture
Definition: "A type of fracture in which there is a diagonal break across the bone." []

Name: Compression fracture
Definition: "A type of fracture in which the bone is crushed, causing the broken bone to be wider or flatter in appearance." []

Name: Comminuted fracture
Definition: "A type of fracture in which the break is in three or more pieces and fragments are present at the fracture site." []

Name: Segmental fracture
Definition: "A type of fracture in which the same bone is fractured in two places, so there is a floating segment of bone." []

Name: Open fracture
Definition: "A type of fracture in which there is an open wound or break in the skin near the site of the broken bone." []

Name: Closed fracture
Definition: "A type of fracture in which the broken bone that does not penetrate the skin." []

Name: Avulsion fracture
Definition: "A type of fracture that is localied near to a a tendon or ligament and a small fragment of bone is separated from the main mass of bone as a result of physical trauma." []

Name: Displaced fracture
Definition: "A type of fracture in which the ends of the fractured bone are no longer aligned." []

Name: Exanthem
Definition: "A widespread rash." []

Name: Intestinal inflammation
Definition: "A reaction characterizeds by capillary dilatation, leukocytic infiltration, redness, heat, pain, swelling localized to the in the intestinal tract." [PMID:9897960]

Name: Abnormal apoptosis
Definition: "Any abnormality of programmed cell death (apoptosis), which is defined as the orchestrated collapse of a cell characterised by membrane blebbing, cell shrinkage, condensation of chromatin, and fragmentation of DNA followed by rapid engulfment of the corpse by neighbouring cells. Apoptosis is distinguished from death by necrosis by the absence of an associated inflammatory response." [PMID:11420279]

Name: Decreased FasL-mediated apoptosis
Definition: "A reduced amount of programmed cell death upon stimulation of the FAS receptor, which normally induces caspase-8 dependent apoptosis." [PMID:29617412]

Name: Glomerular proteinuria
Definition: "A type of proteinuria characterized by increased permeability of the glomerular capillary wall to macromolecules (particularly albumin), whereby protein excretion can reach 20 g/24 h and consists mainly of albumin." [PMID:19634399]

Name: Abnormal lung development
Definition: "A structural defect associated with abnormal development of the lung." []

Name: Pancreatic alpha-cell hyperplasia
Definition: "A diffuse and specific increase in the number of alpha-cells." [PMID:24285676]

Name: 3-4 metacarpal synostosis
Definition: "A congenital hand malformation characterized by the coalescence of the coalescence of third and fourth metacarpals (i.e., those corresponding to the middle and ring fingers)." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199, PMID:27698627]

Name: Abnormal iliac artery morphology
Definition: "Any structural anomaly of the iliac artery." []

Name: Iliac artery aneurysm
Definition: "Abnormal outpouching or sac-like dilatation in the iliac artery." [PMID:9685125]

Name: Abnormal interest
Definition: "Any deviation from normal intensity or subject of a person's interests, which can be defined as a state of giving selective attention to something." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4422-1708]

Name: Persistent preoccupation with parts of objects
Definition: "A type of abnormal interest characterized by a persistent and intense focus on parts of a toy/object. For example, affected individuals may spin the wheels on a toy car rather than drive the toy car." []

Name: Fixated interests
Definition: "Highly restricted, fixated interests that are abnormal in intensity or focus (e.g., strong attachment to or preoccupation with unusual objects, excessively circumscribed or perseverative interests)." []

Name: Abnormal language feature
Definition: "The presence of any atypical form of expressive language." []

Name: Pronoun reversal
Definition: "Atypical language features characterized by first vs. second or third person pronoun errors such as using 'you' or 'he/she' in place of 'I'." []

Name: Idiosyncratic language
Definition: "Consistent use of an unusual way of referring to something that is idiosyncratic to the individual." []

Name: Reduced frequency of facial expressions
Definition: "The number of times facial expressions are produced in a given period is lower than expected given the social and cultural context." [PMID:26803417]

Name: Use of another person's body to communicate
Definition: "Moving another person's hand, body part, or body to communicate a desire, e.g. pushing or pulling someone toward a desired object or placing someone's hand on something." [PMID:25388062]

Name: Fixated interest with abnormal focus
Definition: "A fixated interest in a specific topic that is atypical for the social context of the individual, such as topics of a non-social nature like fossils or vacuum cleaners." []

Name: Fixated interest with abnormal intensity
Definition: "An abnormally intense interest in a topic or object that is not atypical for the social context of the affected person." [PMID:23880382]

Name: Sensory seeking
Definition: "Unusual interest in sensory aspects of the environment." [PMID:29112858]

Name: Reduced production of gestures
Definition: "Diminished use of typical non-verbal conversational gestures such as shaking the head to indicate no or nodding the head to indicate yes." [PMID:21182208]

Name: Reduced collaborative play
Definition: "Impairment in a child's ability to be able to play in a way that involves peer collaboration. Collaborative play involves things such as verbal and non-verbal communication (e.g., self-initiated interactions), turn-taking, sharing, reciprocity, and collaborative problem-solving. It is often contrasted to parallel play, which involves a form of social play in which two children do similar activities near each other and often mimic each other. Typically developing children develop collaborative play between the ages of 4 and 5." []

Name: Ignores peers
Definition: "Lack of interest of an individual in peers of comparable age and social groups. For example, a child who is only interested in social interactions with adults rather than children their age." []

Name: Reduced sharing of interests
Definition: "Decreased sharing of interests with others appropriate to culture and developmental level." []

Name: Reduced object sharing
Definition: "An absence or reduction in object sharing. Object sharing is an early emerging social skill in which a child will share objects with parents or peers during object play. Object sharing typically develops within the first two years of life." []

Name: Abnormal communicative facial expressions
Definition: "Abnormal expressions (movements or position of muscles of the face that convey the emotional state of an individual to observers during social interactions) comprising abnormalities of quantity, range, context-appropriateness, and quality." []

Name: Facial expressions that do not match the context
Definition: "Production of facial expressions that are misaligned with the social context." []

Name: Abnormal quality of facial expression
Definition: "Spontaneous production of communicative facial expressions that have poor quality or are exaggerated or muted." []

Name: Abnormal gesture use
Definition: "Abnormality in the use of gestures defined as hand, shoulder, and head movements that convey a shared meaning within a culture that replace or supplement verbal communication." []

Name: Poor conversational reciprocity
Definition: "Reduced ability to conduct a reciprocal (back and forth) conversation, as expected for language level. May be characterized by deficits in the ability to make comments about discussion topics of others, failure to ask questions, and not building a conversation on comments of others. Affected persons may not know what to say next in a conversation, may not notice if others are bored with a given topic, may conduct a one-sided conversation (talking but not listening), or may veer off topic more than is socially acceptable." []

Name: Ectopic tooth eruption
Definition: "A condition in which the permanent teeth, because of deficiency of growth in the jaw or segment of jaw, assume a path of eruption that intercepts a primary tooth, causes its premature loss and produces a consequent malposition of the permanent tooth." [PMID:22114445]

Name: Corpus cavernosum hypoplasia
Definition: "A developmental anomaly characterized by undergrowth of the corpus cavernosum." [PMID:21220346]

Name: Elevated circulating thymine concentration
Definition: "Concentration of the nucleobase thymine in the blood circulation above the normal range." [PMID:33916495]

Name: Positive lactose hydrogen breath test
Definition: "Elevated hydrogen gas level in exhaled breath following oral administration of lactose. In individuals with lactose intolerance, undigested lactose in the colon will be metabolized by colonic bacteria, releasing hydrogen gas." [PMID:18985811]

Name: Triggered by exposure to medication
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure to a medication." []

Name: Triggered by allopurinol
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure to allopurinol." []

Name: Ameliorated by oral zinc supplementation
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by oral zinc supplementation." []

Name: Curved dental root
Definition: "A root of a tooth that is more rounded than normal." []

Name: Abnormal four chamber view of the fetal heart
Definition: "The four-chamber (4Ch) view of the fetal heart is the most widely used screening examination for the detection of structural cardiac abnormalities during routine fetal ultrasonography. In the healthy normal fetus, the apical 4Ch view demonstrates four well-developed chambers, a concordant atrioventricular (AV) connection, unobstructed AV valves (mitral and tricuspid valves), the foramen ovale flap opening into left atrium (LA), and an intact interventricular septum. Additionally, the pulmonary venous opening can be visualized at the LA wall. Any structural deviations from normal anatomy may lead to congenital heart disease that can be determined by the 4Ch view of the fetal heart's ultrasound imaging." [PMID:7932993]

Name: Spleen hamartoma
Definition: "A hamartomatous lesion (benign focal lesions composed of disorganized tissue elements) localized in the spleen." []

Name: Positive lupus band test
Definition: "Deposits of immunoglobulins and complement components along the dermoepidermal junction." [PMID:21339940]

Name: Bone marrow erythroid vacuolization
Definition: "Formation of vacuoles (a space within a cell that is empty of cytoplasm, lined with a membrane, and filled with fluid) in the cytoplasm of erythroid precursors in the bone marrow." [PMID:29716882]

Name: Triggered by electromagnetic field
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure to an electromagnetic field." []

Name: Exposure history
Definition: "Information about current and past exposure to metals, dust, fibers, fumes, chemicals, biologic hazards, radiation, noise, and/or vibration at work or home." []

Name: Asbestos exposure
Definition: "History of exposure to asbestos, a fibrous mineral with physical and chemical properties that make it resistant to heat and degradation." [PMID:28706902]

Name: Medication history
Definition: "Information about current or past medications taken by an individual." [PMID:16129874]

Name: Aminoglycoside exposure
Definition: "History of having taken aminoglycoside antibiotics." []

Name: Statin exposure
Definition: "History of having taken statins, also known as HMG-CoA reductase inhibitors." []

Name: Potassium-sparing diuretic exposure
Definition: "History of having taken a potassium-sparing diuretic exposure such as amiloride, eplerenone, spironolactone, and triamterene." []

Name: Carbamazepine exposure
Definition: "History of having taken carbamazepine." []

Name: Valproate exposure
Definition: "History of having taken valproate (valproic acid)." []

Name: Hydralazine exposure
Definition: "History of having taken hydralazine." []

Name: Calcium channel blocker exposure
Definition: "History of having taken a calcium channel blocker such as amlodipine, nicardipine, nifedipine, verapamil, or diltiazem." []

Name: Triggered by poison ivy, poson oak, or sumac
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure (cutaneous contact) to poison ivy, poison oak, and poison sumac. These three plants each contain urushiol. Contact with these plants is the most common causes of clinically diagnosed allergic contact dermatitis." []

Name: History of exclusive breast feeding
Definition: "A past medical history of having been fed exclusively by breast feeding." []

Name: Nutrition history
Definition: "A part of the past medical history consisting of information about the typical food intake of an individual." [PMID:10193594]

Name: High dietary oxalate intake
Definition: "A history of ingestion of a relatively high amount of foods containing high levels of oxalate, such as green-leaf vegetables, tea, nuts, chocolate and rhubarb." [PMID:32887293]

Name: Recent honey ingestion
Definition: "A history of ingestion of honey in recent weeks." []

Name: Raw egg-white ingestion
Definition: "A history of eating raw egg whites." []

Name: Exacerbated by sodium channel blocking agent exposure
Definition: "Applied to a sign or symptom that is worsened by administration of sodium channel blocking agents such as phenytoin, carbamazepine, oxcarbazepine, lamotrigine, topiramate, and zonisamide." []

Name: Nitric oxide addiction
Definition: "Addiction to inhaled nitrous oxide gas (N2O)." [PMID:26912510]

Name: Recent blood transfusion
Definition: "A past medical history of a recent blood transfusion." []

Name: Ameliorated by colchicine
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by administration of colchizine." []

Name: Ameliorated by vitamin D
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by administration of vitamin D." []

Name: Exacerbated by phenytoin exposure
Definition: "Applied to a sign or symptom that is worsened by administration of phenytoin." []

Name: Triggered by angiotensin-converting enzyme inhibitor
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure to anngiotensin-converting enzyme inhibitor such as benazepril, captopril, enalapril, fosinopril, and lisinopril." []

Name: Prostaglandin E1 exposure
Definition: "History of having been treateed with prostaglandin E1." [PMID:31536236]

Name: 5-fluorouracil exposure
Definition: "History of having been treated with 5-fluorouracil." []

Name: 6-mercaptopurine exposure
Definition: "History of having been treateed with 6-mercaptopurine." []

Name: Isoniazid exposure
Definition: "History of having been treateed with isoniazid." []

Name: Absent cavum septum pellucidum
Definition: "The cavum septum pellucidum (CSP) is an important fetal midline forebrain landmark that is normally visible by prenatal sonography. This term refers to the lack of visiblity of the CSP on prenatal sonography. The CSP normally can be visualized between 18 and 37 weeks of gestation. Lack of visualization of the CSP in this time period generally requires follow up and may indicate the presence of underlying malformations such as malformations of the corpus callosum. The lack of CSP before 18 weeks or after 37 weeks of gestation (or postnatally) is considered a normal finding." [PMID:26123886]

Name: Fetal abdominal cyst
Definition: "Fetal abdominal cysts are usually detected during the second trimester anomaly scan or discovered incidentally at later gestations. However, a definitive diagnosis is often not made until postnatal life. The most common etiologies of fetal abdominal cysts are: ovarian, gastrointestinal cystic duplication, liver and choledochal, meconium pseudocysts, mesenteric and adrenal. Following identification of a cyst, careful morphological assessment allows the prediction of their natural history and importantly, the likelihood of surgical intervention being required postnatally." [PMID:12780436, PMID:30763268, PMID:34189111]

Name: Fetal bowel dilatation
Definition: "Fetal bowel dilatation is characterized by fluid-filled intestinal loops which measure at least fifteen millimeters long or seven millimeters in diameter. Ultrasonographic image of dilated fetal bowel is a sign of intestinal mechanical or functional obstruction and its prevalence will depend on the underlying condition: bowel atresia or stenosis, malrotation with volvulus, meconium ileus, total colonic aganglionosis, and meconium plug syndrome. The etiology of fetal bowel dilatation is a difficult prenatal diagnosis since ultrasound has limited accuracy for bowel evaluation." []

Name: Left ventricular dilatation
Definition: "Enlargement of the chamber of the left heart ventricle." []

Name: Fetal trigonocephaly
Definition: "A fetal ultrasound finding defined by flattening of the occiput with pointing of the frontal bones and brachycephaly with an increased cephalic index. It is characterized by keel shaped deformity of forehead with midline ridge, bilateral fronto temporal constriction with compensatory biparietal expansion, supra orbital and lateral orbital retrusion and hypotelorism. This finding is said to resemble a strawberry." [PMID:25250065, PMID:26498670, PMID:30363185]

Name: Abnormal fetal heart outflow tract
Definition: "A prenatal anomaly of the outflow tract. Fetal ultrasound may not always be able to easily and accurately describe the outflow anomaly, but can detect abnormal anatomy. Often, follow up with a fetal echo is recommended, but fetal ultrasound is limited." []

Name: Recent past medical history
Definition: "History of events that precede the current presenting condition and are thought to be of potential relevance, having occured in the hours, days, or weeks before the current condition." []

Name: History of recent viral illness
Definition: "Medical history of a viral illness in recent weeks." []

Name: History of recent dental procedure
Definition: "Medical history of a dental procedure in recent weeks." []

Name: Abnormal hepatic artery morphology
Definition: "Any structural anomaly of the hepatic artery or its branches." []

Name: Hepatic artery hyperplasia
Definition: "Abnormal increase in size of the hepatic arteries." []

Name: Lymph node necrosis
Definition: "Areas of necrotic tissue within a lymph node." [PMID:3317224]

Name: Multinucleated neuron
Definition: "Neurons that contain more than one nucleus." []

Name: History of recent contralateral injury
Definition: "A history of an injury that occurred several hours, days, or weeks before the current presenting complaint and is located on the other side of the body relative to the current presenting complaint." []

Name: Alternating laterality
Definition: "Occuring on the left and right in succession. This term can refer to alternating sides of the body (e.g., Alternating hemiplegia) or alternative sides of the visual field (e.g., some migraine auras)." []

Name: Cervical squamous cell papilloma
Definition: "A benign tumor arising from the epithelial surface of the cervix and usually caused by Human Papillomavirus infection." [PMID:32809572]

Name: Liver leiomyoma
Definition: "A benign smooth muscle neoplasm that arises in the liver." [PMID:33139985]

Name: Typified by high penetrance
Definition: "Description of conditions in which only an incomplete but relatively high proportion of individuals with a given genotype exhibit the disease regardless of age assuming a full lifespan of 80 years. There is no commonly accepted definition for incomplete, but high penetrance, but we suggest that this term be applied if at least 80 percent but less than 100 percent of individuals with the given genotype would manifest the disease with a full lifespan." []

Name: Typified by moderate penetrance
Definition: "Description of conditions in which only a moderate proportion of individuals with a given genotype exhibit the disease regardless of age assuming a full lifespan of 80 years. There is no commonly accepted definition for moderate penetrance, but we suggest that this term be applied if at least 20 percent but less than 80 percent of individuals with the given genotype would manifest the disease with a full lifespan." []

Name: Typified by low penetrance
Definition: "Description of conditions in which only a low proportion of individuals with a given genotype exhibit the disease regardless of age assuming a full lifespan of 80 years. There is no commonly accepted definition for low penetrance, but we suggest that this term be applied if at least some but less than 20 percent of carriers would manifest the disease with a full lifespan." []

Name: Decreased Succinyl-CoA 3-ketoacid CoA transferase activity
Definition: "Decreased activity of the enzyme succinyl-CoA 3-ketoacid CoA transferase." [PMID:21296660]

Name: Decreased phytanoyl-CoA hydroxylase activity
Definition: "Reduced activity of the enzyme phytanoyl-CoA hydroxylase, which plays a role in the catabolism of phytanic acid, a branched-chain fatty acid that is a normal constituent of the human diet." [PMID:10767344]

Name: Reduced bifunctional protein activity
Definition: "Diminished activity of hydroxysteroid 17-beta dehydrogenase 4 (HSD17B4), also known as D-bifunctional protein (DBP), a peroxisomal enzyme that catalyzes multiple steps of beta-oxidation of very long chain fatty acids." [PMID:32904102]

Name: Decreased circulating plasmalogen concentration
Definition: "Reduced plasmalogen concentration in the blood circulation." [PMID:30974122]

Name: Post-vaccination varicella zoster virus infection
Definition: "Infection with live, attenuated varicella-zoster virus following vaccination. This is an extreemely rare event that may indicate immunocompromise." [PMID:31527188]

Name: Recent steroid exposure
Definition: "History of having been treated with corticosteroid medications in recent weeks." []

Name: Shark teeth
Definition: "Eruption of permanent teeth behind deciduous (baby) teeth before they have fallen out, resulting in a double row of teeth. This phenomen is typically observed between the ages of 5 to 7 years." []

Name: Pontine T2 hypointensity
Definition: "A darker than expected T2 signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the pons." [PMID:23497566]

Name: Anti-platelet antigen antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against antigens present on the surface of thrombocytes such as the glycoproteins GPIIb/IIIa, GPIb/IX, and GPIa/IIa." []

Name: Anti-voltage-gated potassium channel antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against a voltage-gated potassium channel." [PMID:20816272]

Name: Vegan diet
Definition: "A history of following a vegan diet characterized by avoidance of food sourced from animals including meet, fish, and dairy products." []

Name: History of previous pregnancy with hydrops fetalis
Definition: "One or more previous pregnancies in which the fetus developed hydrops fetalis." []

Name: Ameliorated by potassium supplements
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by ingesting a potassium supplement." []

Name: Ameliorated by niacin
Definition: "Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by ingesting niacin (vitamin B3)." []

Name: Aggravated by exposure to medication
Definition: "Applied to a sign or symptom that is worsened by treatment with a medication." []

Name: Bleeding ameliorated by vitamin K
Definition: "Applies to bleeding that is significantly reduced by treatment with vitamin K." []

Name: Anti-retroviral therapy exposure
Definition: "History of having been treated with an antiretroviral agent." [PMID:36454551]

Name: Potassium-wasting diuretic exposure
Definition: "History of having been treated with a potassium-wasting diuretic such as thiazide (chlorothiazide, chlorthalidone, hydrochlorothiazide, indapamide, metolazone) and loop (bumetanide, ethacrynic acid, furosemide, torsemide) diuretics." []

Name: Tricyclic antidepressant exposure
Definition: "History of having been treated with a tricyclic antidepressant medication." []

Name: Excessive dental attrition
Definition: "A higher than expected amount of attrition of teeth, as menifested by loss of tooth characteristics including rounding or sharpening of incisal edges, loss of cusps, and fracturing of teeth, to an extent that is deemed more than would be expected at a given age." []

Name: Positionally dependent pain
Definition: "Pain improves or worsens with changes in body position." []

Name: Abnormal erythrocyte adenosine triphosphate concentration
Definition: "Concentration of adenosine triphosphate (ATP) in red blood cells (erythrocytes) outside of the normal range." []

Name: Reduced erythrocyte adenosine triphosphate concentration
Definition: "Concentration of adenosine triphosphate (ATP) in red blood cells (erythrocytes) below the lower limit of normal." []

Name: Elevated erythrocyte adenosine triphosphate concentration
Definition: "Concentration of adenosine triphosphate (ATP) in red blood cells (erythrocytes) above the upper limit of normal." []

Name: Spermatogonial maturation arrest
Definition: "A type of spermatogenesis maturation arrest in which the block of developmental occurs in the spermatogonial stage. Testicular histology shows seminiferous tubules with Sertoli cells and spermatogonial cells but no further differentiated cells like spermatocytes or round spermatids." []

Name: Anti-AK5 antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against anti-adenylate kinase 5 (AK5)." [PMID:28062719, PMID:33843981]

Name: Anti-AMPAR antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against anti-alpha-amino-3-hydroxy-5-methyl-4-isoxazolepropionic acid receptor (AMPAR)." [PMID:25979696, PMID:29225271]

Name: Anti-Amphiphysin antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Amphiphysin." [PMID:20420178, PMID:27773907, PMID:31624089, PMID:32087460, PMID:33173498]

Name: Anti-ARHGAP26 antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Rho GTPase-activating protein 26 (ARHGAP26)." [PMID:26298328, PMID:28601293, PMID:30158896]

Name: Anti-CARP VIII antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Carbonic anhydrase-related protein VIII (CARPVIII)." [PMID:23568983, PMID:26377085]

Name: Anti-CASPR2
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against contactin-associated protein-like 2 (CASPR2)." [PMID:29561731, PMID:32651251, PMID:32783406]

Name: Anti-CV2/CRMP5 antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against CV2/CRMP5. Anti-CV2/CRMP5 autoantibody is the most commonly detected anti-neuronal autoantibody. Patients with typical paraneoplastic chorea show fully developed chorea in the course of weeks to months with acute inflammation in the striatum." [PMID:18931014, PMID:31656691, PMID:32110228]

Name: Anti-DPPX antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against dipeptidyl-peptidase-like protein 6 (DPPX)." [PMID:27299786, PMID:28258082, PMID:32087460]

Name: Anti-FGFR3 antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against FGFR3." [PMID:33563795, PMID:33588772]

Name: Anti-GABA(A)R antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against gamma-aminobutyric acid A receptor, i.e., GABA(A)R." [PMID:28202703, PMID:30347219]

Name: Anti-GABA(B)R antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against gamma-aminobutyric acid B receptor, i.e., GABA(B)R." [PMID:32103919, PMID:32710704, PMID:32783406]

Name: Anti-GAD65 antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against glutamic acid decarboxylase 65 (GAD65)." [PMID:30343467, PMID:32087461, PMID:32123047]

Name: Anti-Gephyrin antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Gephyrin." [PMID:20420178, PMID:22270318, PMID:29561731]

Name: Anti-GFAP antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against glial fibrillary acidic protein (GFAP)." [PMID:28120349, PMID:30663514, PMID:32019875, PMID:32827972]

Name: Anti-GlyR antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Glycine receptor (GlyR)." [PMID:21242500, PMID:22215239, PMID:32087460, PMID:32585946]

Name: Anti-Homer-3 antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Homer-3." [PMID:26377085]

Name: Anti-Hu antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Hu." [PMID:11344832, PMID:18931014, PMID:19015226, PMID:25764259, PMID:32851899]

Name: Anti-Iglon5 antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against immunoglobulin-like cell adhesion molecule 5 (IgLON5)." [PMID:27299786, PMID:28381508, PMID:30694925]

Name: Anti-ITPR1 antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against inositol 1,4,5-trisphosphate receptor 1 (ITPR1)." [PMID:28203616]

Name: Anti-Kelch like protein 11 antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against kelch-like protein 11 (KLHL11)." [PMID:31269365]

Name: Anti-LGI1 antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against leucine-rich glioma-inactivated 1 (LGI1)." [PMID:32710704, PMID:32783406]

Name: Anti-Ma antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Ma." [PMID:27460184, PMID:33070888]

Name: Anti-Ma2 antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Ma2." [PMID:15179063, PMID:15215214, PMID:18223018, PMID:26664526, PMID:27460184, PMID:31044049, PMID:31454760]

Name: Anti-Ma1 antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Ma1." [PMID:15179063, PMID:27460184]

Name: Anti-mGluR1 antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against metabotropic glutamate receptor 1 (mGluR1)." [PMID:26377085]

Name: Anti-mGluR5 antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against metabotropic glutamate receptor 5 (mGluR5)." [PMID:29703767]

Name: Anti-neurexin-3alpha antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against neurexin-3alpha." [PMID:27170572, PMID:27170573, PMID:28840178]

Name: Anti-P/Q-type VGCC antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against P/Q-type voltage-gated calcium channels (VGCCs)." [PMID:18295972, PMID:18653248, PMID:21115345]

Name: Anti-MAP1B antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against microtubule-associated protein 1B (MAP1B)." [PMID:28074593, PMID:31801846]

Name: Anti-PKCgamma antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against protein kinase Cgamma." [PMID:16801349]

Name: Anti-Ri antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Ri, an antineuronal antibody." [PMID:15179063, PMID:29332416, PMID:32170042]

Name: Anti-Septin-5 antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Septin-5." [PMID:29998156]

Name: Anti-SEZ6L2 antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against seizure-related 6 homolog like 2 (SEZ6L2)." [PMID:33144342]

Name: Anti-SOX1 antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against SOX1. Anti-SOX1 antibodies, also known as antiglial nuclear antibody (AGNA), are specifically found in paraneoplastic neurological disorders. Since SOX1 is expressed in neuronal precursor cells in the developing central nervous system, it has been used as an early marker of neural stem cells." [PMID:19667272, PMID:32103919]

Name: Anti-Tr/DNER antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Tr/DNER. Anti-Tr antibodies are directed against cerebellar Purkinje cells (termed anti-Tr or PCA-Tr). Anti-Tr autoantibodies are frequently associated with Hodgkin lymphoma (HL). Anti-Tr antibodies are defined by a specific staining pattern in cerebellar tissue that is characterized by punctate immunoreactivity in both the dendritic tree and soma of Purkinje cells but not in their axons. This characteristic pattern is indicative of the presence of anti-Tr antibodies. The Delta/Notch-like epidermal growth factor-related receptor (DNER) was identified as the target antigen of anti-Tr." [PMID:15179063, PMID:25745634, PMID:26377319]

Name: Anti-TRIM46 antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against the axon initial segment protein tripartite motif 46 (TRIM46)." [PMID:28904989]

Name: Anti-TRIM9/TRIM67 antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against TRIM9/TRIM67." [PMID:30350014]

Name: Anti-Yo antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Yo." [PMID:10980743, PMID:27606347]

Name: Anti-titin antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against titin." [PMID:27235344, PMID:30918333, PMID:32830177]

Name: Anti-Zic4 antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Zic family member 4 (ZIC4)." [PMID:29249374, PMID:29525731, PMID:31533147, PMID:32087460]

Name: Anti-Sj/ITPR1 antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Sj/inositol 1,4,5-trisphosphate receptor." [PMID:23568983, PMID:26377085]

Name: Anti-D2 R antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against dopamine-2 receptor." [PMID:27299786, PMID:32612568]

Name: Anti-GluK2 antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against glutamate kainate receptor subunit 2 (GluK2)." [PMID:33949707]

Name: Anti-Lrp4 antibody positivity
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against low-density lipoprotein receptor (Lrp4)." [PMID:32830177]

Name: Anti-ryanodine receptor antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against ryanodine receptor." [PMID:30918333]

Name: Anti-Kv1.4 antibody
Definition: "The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against the voltage-gated potassium channel Kv1.4." [PMID:22167224, PMID:30918333]

Name: Selective mutism
Definition: "Voluntary failure to use spoken language (at whatever level attained) in selective social contexts over a period of time." []

Name: Limited repertoire of facial expression
Definition: "An abnormally limited range of facial expressions demonstrated by a lack of nuance of facial expression to match specific social situations or an inability to demonstrate a normal range of emotions with one's face." []

Name: Excessive interest in others
Definition: "An unusually strong interest in others in general or tendency to develop a strong interest in certain individuals." []

Name: Reduced response to another's attempt to get direct attention
Definition: "A reduced interest in all people including both peers and non-peers." []

Name: Abnormal pitch
Definition: "Abnormally high or low-pitched vocalization or speech." []

Name: Loose association
Definition: "Speech characterized by weak (e.g. tangential/circumstantial) or absent (e.g. word salad) connections between ideas." []

Name: Neologism
Definition: "Consistent use of an invented word that is unique to an individual." []

Name: Overly formal/pedantic language
Definition: "Use of language that is overly formal, precise, detailed, or pedantic for the social context." []

Name: Midline hand movements
Definition: "Hand stereotypies within the medial plane of the body." [PMID:28838622]

Name: Abnormal Intonation
Definition: "Abnormal rise and fall of the voice in speech and vocalization." []

Name: Abnormal speech rate
Definition: "Speech that is abnormally fast or slow" []

Name: Abnormal speech rhythm
Definition: "Speech with abnormal rhythm or pattern" []

Name: Ambiguous facial expression
Definition: "Spontaneous production of communicative facial expressions that have poor quality or are perceived as odd or mechanical. This may include inaccurate mimicry of typical facial expressions. These expressions may be difficult to interpret for someone who is not familiar with the individual making the expression." []

Name: Exaggerated facial expression
Definition: "A tendency to make facial expressions that are exaggerated and a failure to make subtle facial expressions in a social context when a subtle expression is more appropriate." []

Name: Muted facial expression
Definition: "A tendency to produce facial expressions with decreased intensity or expressivity which appear muted or flat." []

Name: Abnormal peer relationships
Definition: "The state of having abnormal relationships with others. This does not describe specific aspects of one's social aptitudes but rather a state which may come about from these aptitudes, such as lacking peer relationships or lacking close friends." []

Name: Abnormal movements of face and head
Definition: "Abnormal movements of face and head." []

Name: Abnormal movements of the upper extremities
Definition: "Abnormal movements of the upper extremities." []

Name: Abnormal movements of the whole body
Definition: "Abnormal movements of the whole body." []

Name: Abnormal interest in others
Definition: "A social interest in others that is abnormal given the social context. This can include an increased interest with another person or an abnormal lack of interest in other people." []

Name: Reduced social insight
Definition: "A lack of awareness or failure to apply social rules in multiple social settings which are simple or intuitive to others in the same social setting." []

Name: Reduced awareness of convention
Definition: "Reduced awareness of expected conventions which are normal and expected for particular social settings or interactions." []

Name: Abnormal relationship
Definition: "The state of having abnormal relationships with others. This does not describe specific aspects of one's social aptitudes but rather a state which may come about from these aptitudes, such as lacking peer relationships, lacking close friends, or having a relational network that is abnormal given one's cultural context." []

Name: Abnormal social imitation
Definition: "A reduced ability to imitate a task or the movements of others." [PMID:18221343]

Name: Reduced attempt to get or direct another's attention
Definition: "An abnormality in one's tendency to initiate social interactions." []

Name: Reduced response to social cues
Definition: "Abnormality in the way one responds to social cues such as a verbal cue (which should cause one to shift attention) or someone sharing their emotions (which should elicit a sympathetic response)." []

Name: Diminished integration of verbal and non-verbal communicative behavior
Definition: "A communicative abnormality where one's nonverbal and verbal communication are poorly integrated. This may occur when verbal and nonverbal communication are intact alone but are abnormal when used together, or an abnormality in the use of typically integrated communication such as the use of beat gestures during speech." []

Name: obsolete Reduced immediate imitation of others
Reduced collaborative imaginative play
Definition: "Failure of a child to integrate with peers in imaginative play." []

Name: Lack of response to verbal cues
Definition: "A consistent failure to make any response to verbal cues." []

Name: Reduced sympathetic expression
Definition: "A reduction in showing sympathy to others, such as providing comfort when someone is sad or crying." []

Name: Bradylalia
Definition: "Slow speech." []

Name: Excessively loud speech
Definition: "Speech which is abnormally loud that is not due to a structural or muscular abnormality." []

Name: Excessively quiet voice
Definition: "Speech which is abnormally quiet or inappropriate whispering that is not due to a structural or muscular abnormality." []

Name: Abnormal speech volume
Definition: "Speech that is abnormally loud or quiet for the social context in which it is spoken." []

Name: Reduced attention regulation
Definition: "Abnormality in one's ability to control their attention toward a specific subject or task. This could include the inability to change attention or hold attention." [PMID:26386541]

Name: Reduced impulse control
Definition: "Reduced ability to control, or a failure to resist a temptation, urge, or impulse." [PMID:16263865]

Name: Sensory behavioral abnormality
Definition: "Abnormal sensory behavior, including avoiding or seeking sensory input or difficulty modulating sensory stimuli." []

Name: Idiosyncratic gesture
Definition: "When one uses gestures that are unique to them and have no apparent meaning to others." [PMID:22954367]

Name: Atypical sorting
Definition: "Atypical focus on arranging, balancing, or positioning objects; may be atypical in focus or intensity." [PMID:31016439]

Name: Excessive checking
Definition: "Checking behavior that is excessive for the situational context." [PMID:31016439]

Name: Excessive hand washing
Definition: "Hand washing behavior that is excessive for the situational context." []

Name: Resistance to trivial environmental changes
Definition: "Distress in response to minor changes in one's environmental expectations." []

Name: Lack of nonverbal response to verbal cues
Definition: "A consistent failure to nonverbally respond to verbal cues such as a failure to shift attention or look at the source of the cue." []

Name: Lack of verbal response to verbal cues
Definition: "A consistent failure to verbally respond to verbal cues which are intended to elicit a verbal response." []

Name: Reduced co-speech gestures
Definition: "Reduced use of speech-integrated gestures such as the use of beat gestures." []

Name: Limited head nodding or shaking
Definition: "Absence or reduction in the use of head nodding to indicate \"yes\" or head shaking to indicate \"no\"." []

Name: Limited pointing
Definition: "Absence or reduction in the use of pointing to request or direct another's attention." []

Name: Sensory hypersensitivity
Definition: "A decreased tolerance to sensory stimuli that triggers emotional and/or physical distress." [PMID:29112858]

Name: Sensory hyposensitivity unexplained by sensory deficit
Definition: "Increased tolerance to sensory stimuli due to diminished sensory ability." [PMID:29112858]

Name: Auditory hypersensitivity
Definition: "Hyperresponsive to sound that is abnormal in intensity and/or frequency." [PMID:29112858]

Name: Tactile hypersensitivity
Definition: "A decreased tolerance to physical touch." [PMID:29112858]

Name: Auditory sensory seeking
Definition: "Pursuit of specific sounds or noises that is abnormal in intensity and/or frequency." [PMID:29112858]

Name: Gustatory sensory seeking
Definition: "Pursuit of a particular taste that is abnormal in intensity and/or frequency." [PMID:29112858]

Name: Olfactory sensory seeking
Definition: "Pursuit of specific scents, smells, or fragrances that is abnormal in intensity and/or frequency." [PMID:29112858]

Name: Tactile sensory seeking
Definition: "Pursuit of a specific texture that is abnormal in intensity and/or frequency." [PMID:29112858]

Name: Vestibular sensory seeking
Definition: "Pursuit of vestibular stimulation that is abnormal in intensity and/or frequency." [PMID:29112858]

Name: Visual sensory seeking
Definition: "Pursuit visual stimulation by looking at specific sights, images, and/or colors that is abnormal in intensity and/or frequency." [PMID:29112858]

Name: Socially innappropriate questioning
Definition: "A tendency to ask questions that are overly personal or otherwise inappropriate in the social situation in which they are asked." []

Name: Spinning
Definition: "An excessive frequency of spinning one's body." []

Name: Delayed Echolalia
Definition: "Repetition of borrowed words or phrases outside of the context in which they were originally heard. E.g., scripting from TV shows or movies." []

Name: Immediate Echolalia
Definition: "Immediate repetition of another person's speech." []

Name: Excessive cleaning
Definition: "Excessive cleaning of surfaces, living space, or environment that is excessive for the situational context." []

Name: Facial expressions not directed to others
Abnormal play
Definition: "An abnormality in a child's ability play." []

Name: Reduced imaginative play skills
Definition: "Reduced or lack of pretending in play (does not assign abstract properties to objects, use invisible objects, or use objects in nonliteral ways other than their intended purpose in play)." [PMID:26263228]

Name: Nonfunctional or atypical use of objects in play
Definition: "Use of objects in atypical, unimaginitive ways other than for which they are intended (banging, throwing, shaking, sorting, lining up, spinning)." []

Name: Difficulty understanding nonliteral meaning of conversation
Deficit applying language skills across context
Abnormal rituals
Definition: "Insistence on rituals which are self-imposed on a person's environment including directing the behavior of those around them." []

Name: Reduced use of language for social purposes
Jumping
Definition: "An excessive frequency of jumping in place." []

Name: Delay in the acquisition of play skills
Reduced attempt to get or direct attention of peers
Incomplete unilateral cleft lip
Definition: "Unilateral cleft lip cleft that starts from the bottom of the upper lip but does not reach the nasal cavity." [PMID:21331089, PMID:26171570]

Name: Complete unilateral cleft lip
Definition: "Unilateral cleft lip cleft that starts from the bottom of the upper lip and reaches the nasal cavity." [PMID:21331089, PMID:26171570]

Name: Microform unilateral cleft lip
Definition: "Notch, groove, or scar of the upper lip without noticeable rupture of the lip. Microforms are sometimes associated with disruption of the continuity of the orbicularis oris muscle." [PMID:21331089, PMID:26171570, PMID:33729631]

Name: Complete cleft hard palate
Definition: "Cleft hard palate in which the cleft goes through the entire length of the hard palate." [PMID:21331089, PMID:26171570]

Name: Incomplete cleft hard palate
Definition: "Cleft hard palate in which the cleft doe not goes through the entire length of the hard palate." [PMID:21331089, PMID:26171570]

Name: Complete cleft soft palate
Definition: "Cleft soft palate in which the cleft goes through the entire length of the soft palate." [PMID:21331089, PMID:26171570]

Name: Incomplete cleft soft palate
Definition: "Cleft soft palate in which the cleft doe not goes through the entire length of the soft palate." [PMID:21331089, PMID:26171570]

Name: Incomplete cleft maxillary alveolar ridge
Definition: "Cleft maxillary alveolar ridge in which the cleft does not go through the entire length of the maxillary alveolar ridge." [PMID:21331089, PMID:26171570]

Name: Complete cleft maxillary alveolar ridge
Definition: "Cleft maxillary alveolar ridge in which the cleft goes through the entire length of the maxillary alveolar ridge." [PMID:21331089, PMID:26171570]

Name: Complete cleft of the upper lip
Definition: "Cleft of the upper lip that starts from the bottom of the upper lip and reaches the nasal cavity." [PMID:21331089, PMID:26171570, PMID:33729631]

Name: Microform cleft of the upper lip
Definition: "Notch, groove, or scar of the upper lip without noticeable rupture of the lip." [PMID:21331089, PMID:26171570, PMID:33729631]

Name: Complete bilateral cleft lip
Definition: "Bilateral cleft lip in which the cleft lip on both sides is complete, i.e. start from the bottom of the upper lip and reach the nasal cavity." [PMID:19884685]

Name: Incomplete bilateral cleft lip
Definition: "Bilateral cleft lip in which the cleft lip on both sides are incomplete (i.e. start from the bottom of the upper lip but do not reach the nasal cavity), or the cleft lip on one is incomplete and a microform on the other side." [PMID:19884685]

Name: Microform bilateral cleft lip
Definition: "Bilateral cleft lip in which the cleft lip on both sides are microform, i.e. a notch, groove, or scar without noticeable rupture of the lip." [PMID:19884685]

Name: Asymmetric bilateral cleft lip
Definition: "Bilateral cleft lip in which the cleft lip on one side is complete (i.e. starts from the bottom of the upper lip and reaches the nasal cavity), and the one on the other side is incomplete (i.e. starts from the bottom of the upper lip but does not reach the nasal cavity) or microform (i.e. a notch, groove, or scar without noticeable rupture of the lip)." [PMID:19884685]
